#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:681
msgid "Death of Kyara"
msgstr "Muerte de Kyara"

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:385
msgid ""
"I don’t like this place. It feels as if something is waiting to ambush us in "
"the darkness."
msgstr ""
"No me gusta este lugar. Siento como si algo estuviera esperando para "
"emboscarnos en la oscuridad."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:390
msgid ""
"Heh, darkness. These elves aren’t very smart after all. Why would they think "
"that sending one of their sun-loving youths would be of any help to us?"
msgstr ""
"Je, oscuridad. Estos elfos no son muy listos después de todo. ¿Por qué "
"pensarían que enviar a uno de sus jóvenes amantes del sol nos sería de ayuda?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:395
msgid ""
"Keep your mouth shut, decrepit lich! We are being <i>far</i> more lenient "
"than anyone would be with those who deal with your unnatural minions and "
"these filthy apes."
msgstr ""
"¡Cierra la boca, liche decrépito! Estamos siendo <i>mucho</i> más "
"indulgentes de lo que cualquiera sería con quienes tratan con tus esbirros "
"antinaturales y con estos simios inmundos."

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:400
msgid "Who are you calling “filthy apes”, you..."
msgstr "¿A quién llamas “simios inmundos”, tú...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:405
msgid ""
"Calm down, everyone! If we are to explore these caverns, we’ll need to stay "
"together."
msgstr ""
"¡Cálmense todos! Si queremos explorar estas cavernas, necesitaremos "
"mantenernos unidos."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:410
msgid "What are you looking for? Some kind of artifact? Rocks? Spiders?"
msgstr "¿Qué buscan? ¿Algún tipo de artefacto? ¿Rocas? ¿Arañas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:415
msgid ""
"We believe these caves beneath the dark citadel may have once been used by "
"our enemies. If that is the case, they may have left behind scrolls, "
"artifacts, or anything else that could provide us with hints."
msgstr ""
"Creemos que estas cuevas bajo la ciudadela oscura pudieron haber sido usadas "
"por nuestros enemigos. Si es así, puede que hayan dejado pergaminos, "
"artefactos o cualquier otra cosa que nos dé pistas."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:420
msgid ""
"This is no time to fight amongst ourselves. Just stay alert and let us see "
"what we can find."
msgstr ""
"No es momento de pelearnos entre nosotros. Manténganse alerta y veamos qué "
"podemos encontrar."

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:425
msgid "We will help you as best we can, elf."
msgstr "Te ayudaremos en lo que podamos, elfo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:498
msgid ""
"Hmmm, at first glance this seems like a dead end, but those rocks over there "
"seem like they might be concealing something. Galas, I believe we should "
"have some explosives to spare still?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:503
msgid ""
"What’s left should be more than enough to clear the rubble out of the way, "
"but are you sure this isn’t horribly unsafe?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:508
msgid ""
"These tunnels seem very well built and have withstood the passage of time "
"for centuries. I reckon it will take more than a few explosions to bring the "
"ceiling down on us."
msgstr ""

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_mining_charge_help
#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_siege_charge_help
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:513
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1317
msgid "Help: Using Charges"
msgstr "Ayuda: Uso de Cargas"

#. [event]: id=wme_mining_charge_help
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:535
msgid ""
"In this scenario, you will come across special marked locations where "
"explosives can be set off in order to clear obstructions. Move <b>Galas</b>, "
"<b>Elynia</b>, <b>Mal Keshar</b>, <b>Horo</b>, or <b>Kyara</b> to these "
"locations in order to prime a barrel of explosives which will detonate at "
"the start of next turn.\n"
"\n"
"Beware that the ensuing explosion will <b>kill</b> any units within a one-"
"hex radius, so you must ensure your unit has enough movement points left to "
"move to a safe spot before deploying."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:578
msgid "All set. Clear the area!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$random
#. [message]: race=human,orc,wolf,goblin,faerie,elf
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:598
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1682
msgid "Fire in the hole!"
msgstr "¡Fuego en el agujero!"

#. [unit]: type=Death Knight, id=Firden
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:710
msgid "Firden"
msgstr "Firden"

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:732
msgid "<i>Hissssssss</i>"
msgstr "<i>Ssssssssss</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:737
msgid "A giant spider. Just a bothersome giant spider."
msgstr "Una araña gigante. Solo una molesta araña gigante."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:756
msgid "Look out, there are undead sentinels standing in our way!"
msgstr "¡Cuidado, hay centinelas no-muertos bloqueando nuestro camino!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:761
msgid ""
"This is impossible! Our druids purged any evil creatures left on this island "
"after Kalehssar’s victory!"
msgstr ""
"¡Esto es imposible! Nuestros druidas purgaron a todas las criaturas malignas "
"que quedaban en esta isla tras la victoria de Kalehssar."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:766
msgid ""
"Above the surface, they might have been unable to detect these slumbering "
"minions. Yes, it appears our presence is what has awakened them after so "
"long."
msgstr ""
"En la superficie puede que no lograran detectar a estos esbirros dormidos. "
"Sí, parece que nuestra presencia es lo que los ha despertado después de "
"tanto tiempo."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:782
msgid ""
"There was very little strength left in this guardian. I wonder who was the "
"master of these minions before the place was abandoned?"
msgstr ""
"Quedaba muy poca fuerza en este guardián. Me pregunto quién fue el amo de "
"estos esbirros antes de que este lugar fuera abandonado."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:787
msgid "Argan, of course. There’s no doubt about it."
msgstr "Argan, por supuesto. No hay ninguna duda."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:809
msgid "Not bad for a sun-loving little girl."
msgstr "No está mal para una niñita amante del sol."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:814
msgid "Shut up, necromancer."
msgstr "Cállate, nigromante."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:856
msgid "Another dead end. Now what?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:861
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If our past experiences with this sort of construction are anything to go "
"by, this is most likely not the dead end it appears to be. Let us check the "
"small cave to the east."
msgstr ""
"Si nos basamos en nuestras experiencias pasadas con este tipo de fortalezas, "
"lo más probable es que esto no sea el callejón sin salida que parece. Vamos "
"a revisar la cueva al este."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:897
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3657
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1127
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1236
msgid "Touchplate triggered. A wall moves."
msgstr "Placa de presión activada. Una pared se mueve."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:917
msgid ""
"ER█OR: Object connec█ion failed██status code: 0xC000023C█\n"
"\n"
"Acce█s denied."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:934
msgid ""
"What is this?? Why isn’t this damned contraption working? Oh well, I suppose "
"this place has been left unattended for a <b>very</b> long time. No matter, "
"we should be able to blast that brick wall open."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:939
msgid ""
"Actually, no... we don’t know exactly how thick it is, and we barely have "
"any explosives left. We would have to head back to the surface to restock."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:944
msgid "Wait! Look at that wall to the west!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:971
msgid "The water at its feet is moving. That can only mean..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:976
msgid ""
"... that there is a stream on the other side. Well spotted! It should be "
"worth a shot."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1006
msgid "These accursed bats are everywhere!"
msgstr "¡Estos malditos murciélagos están por todas partes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1011
msgid "It’s a cave, what did you expect? Rabbits?"
msgstr "Es una cueva, ¿qué esperabas? ¿Conejos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1027
msgid "Those water creatures don’t look friendly at all."
msgstr "Esas criaturas acuáticas no parecen nada amistosas."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1038
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"What in Uria’s name?? These abominations look much like Yechnagoth’s true "
"form did according to our druids. But how? Our ancestors purged them all!"
msgstr ""
"Estas abominaciones se parecen mucho a la verdadera forma de Yechnagoth, "
"según nuestros druidas..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1043
msgid ""
"These tunnels had been completely inaccessible until now, so it stands to "
"reason there could have been stragglers left trapped in here. But from what "
"we learned back in Wesmere, these creatures should not be able to prosper if "
"left to their own devices for so long..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1079
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It seems there was a cave-in here long ago. The blocked passage might have "
"led to the citadel back in day. Let’s see what lies down the other way."
msgstr ""
"Parece que aquí hubo un derrumbe hace mucho tiempo. Este pasaje bloqueado "
"podría haber llevado a la ciudadela; veamos qué hay más adelante."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1142
msgid ""
"So this must be Argan’s old base of operations. We should see what we can "
"find, but beware of its current residents — we may need to evict a few in "
"order to progress."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1147
msgid "Gather all information you can from Argan’s lair"
msgstr "Reúne toda la información que puedas de la guarida de Argan"

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1171
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The bones of a human, it seems. Who knows how this poor bastard ended up "
"thrown into this chamber."
msgstr ""
"Parece el esqueleto de un humano. Quién sabe cómo terminó este pobre "
"desgraciado arrojado a esta cámara."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1188
msgid ""
"This gate doesn’t budge, and we don’t have more explosives left. There’s got "
"to be a way to open it — we should look around."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. "Access granted."
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1225
msgid "Acc██s gr█nte██ ¢ 0█ B"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1237
msgid "Good thing this glyph <i>mostly</i> works still."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1266
msgid ""
"It looks like this section is completely flooded; some parts have even "
"collapsed seemingly from erosion. Whatever lies down there, I doubt it’s "
"going to be of much use at this point."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1287
msgid ""
"S: Research Labs\n"
"SE: Manufacturing\n"
"SW: Catacombs"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1450
msgid "Crystal Glyph"
msgstr "Glifo de cristal"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1482
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1504
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This glyph may only be used by a true descendant of She who wields the "
"Arcane Flame that protects Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Este glifo solo puede ser usado por los verdaderos descendientes de Aquella "
"que porta la Llama Arcana que protege Irdya."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1486
msgid "Elynia, you should check this crystal; it may have information we need."
msgstr ""
"Elynia, deberías revisar este cristal; puede contener información que "
"necesitamos."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1506
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Within this glyph lies encoded a <b>Teleport</b> spell which will allow you "
"to cross great distances if you let your soul travel unimpeded by your body. "
"Gaze beyond with your eyes closed, and touch the existence outside your "
"reach. Given sufficient focus, you shall be able to transport your being to "
"any place from your memories and find any soul within your heart’s sight.\n"
"\n"
"Yet cautiously you must tread, for not all the possibilities are written, "
"and those who stray from their reality might not find anything on the other "
"side of the mirror."
msgstr ""
"Dentro de este glifo está codificado un hechizo de <b>Teletransportación</b> "
"que te permitirá atravesar grandes distancias si dejas que tu alma viaje sin "
"el impedimento de tu cuerpo. Mira más allá con los ojos cerrados y toca la "
"existencia fuera de tu alcance. Con la concentración suficiente, podrás "
"transportar tu ser a cualquier lugar de tus recuerdos y encontrar cualquier "
"alma dentro de la vista de tu corazón.\n"
"\n"
"Pero debes proceder con cautela, pues no todas las posibilidades están "
"escritas, y aquellos que se desvían de su realidad podrían no encontrar nada "
"al otro lado del espejo."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1512
msgid ""
"That’s strange. Why would Argan keep something he obviously couldn’t use in "
"his lair?"
msgstr ""
"Qué extraño. ¿Por qué Argan guardaría algo que evidentemente no podía usar "
"en su guarida?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1517
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Certainly this must be a trap intended to get rid of us or anyone else who "
"would somehow manage to find this place."
msgstr ""
"Es más probable que quisiera tendernos una trampa a nosotros o a cualquiera "
"que lograra encontrar este lugar."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1522
msgid ""
"(<i>wistfully</i>) Or maybe... he foresaw me coming to this place and wanted "
"to lend me a hand, even if he couldn’t break free from Uria’s control "
"himself. He didn’t seem fully in control of his mental faculties in the end, "
"but I don’t believe he ever intended to cause me any permanent harm."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1527
msgid "Elynia, what do you mean? He came horribly close to murdering you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1532
msgid ""
"He could’ve killed me with ease if he truly wanted, especially when I fought "
"him up close while you were reduced to an inert pile of bones. Think about "
"it: his biomechanical body granted him enough strength to pulverize stone "
"and tear living creatures in half. Even as my staff violently clashed "
"against his arms, he chose to continue attempting to subdue rather than "
"eliminate me. Even when... Uria took control of his body... he resisted her "
"enough to keep himself from squashing me like a bug."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1537
msgid "I’m taking the spell."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1542
#, fuzzy
msgid "Wait! Elynia, don’t—"
msgstr "Elynia, no—"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1556
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"As Elynia grazed the crystal’s surface with her hand, the glyph instantly "
"disintegrated into fine glistering golden dust, and furiously swirled all "
"around her for a few seconds. The onlookers could only stare in horror as it "
"suddenly covered her entire body..."
msgstr ""
"Cuando Elynia acercó su mano a la superficie del cristal, el glifo se "
"desintegró en un fino polvo dorado, cubriéndola durante unos instantes..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1587
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"... and then swiftly vanished into thin air, revealing no visible harm on "
"the faerie."
msgstr "... Y luego se desvaneció en el aire."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1596
msgid ""
"I don’t feel any different, but... I guess I need to figure out exactly how "
"this power works, now."
msgstr ""
"No me siento diferente, pero... Supongo que ahora debo averiguar exactamente "
"cómo funciona este poder."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1601
#, fuzzy
msgid "Elynia! Thank the Lords of Light you are all right..."
msgstr "... Que los Señores de la Luz tengan misericordia..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1606
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Hmph. In <b>my</b> times, you didn’t acquire magic abilities from shiny "
"rocks. Be careful if you ever attempt to use that spell; knowing who most "
"likely put it there, I really don’t think it’s safe. And more generally, "
"while it is well known that powerful mages learned to travel across great "
"distances like that, it also true that many of them randomly vanished "
"leaving no trace behind."
msgstr ""
"Hmph. En mis tiempos, no adquirías habilidades mágicas de una roca. Bueno, "
"ten cuidado si alguna vez intentas usar ese hechizo; sabiendo quién podría "
"haberlo puesto ahí, no creo que sea seguro. Y en general, aunque se sabe que "
"los magos poderosos pueden aprender a recorrer grandes distancias así, "
"muchos también desaparecen en ocasiones y nunca se vuelve a saber de ellos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1611
msgid ""
"While I appreciate your newfound concern for my safety, Malin, I am very "
"well aware of all this — so spare me the lecture."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1717
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There doesn’t seem to be much more to see here due to the lower levels being "
"completely flooded. It’s really unfortunate."
msgstr "No parece haber mucho más que ver aquí. Es una lástima."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#. "Our priestesses won’t accept this truth." or something similarly terrifying.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1723
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"What we have found here though, is... frightening, to say the least. We "
"always thought that there was only Irdya, not this... nonsense. Our "
"priestesses won’t... What— what do we do with this?!"
msgstr ""
"Lo que hemos encontrado aquí es... aterrador. Siempre pensamos que solo "
"existía un mundo, aquel en el que vivimos. Nuestras sacerdotisas no... ¿Qué "
"hacemos con esto?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1728
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The ‘First’ is also described in the ruins of a hidden city beneath the "
"Heart Mountains. It is said that he created ten powerful demons, the "
"Original Ten. All this would imply that all elves and other faerie creatures "
"are descended, or at least created in the image of this mysterious wielder "
"of the Arcane Flame, sister of Uria and Yechnagoth, and one of the Original "
"Ten."
msgstr ""
"Esto me recuerda que la ‘Primera’ también es mencionada en las ruinas de una "
"ciudad oculta bajo las Montañas del Corazón. Se dice que creó diez poderosos "
"demonios, los Diez Originales. Todo esto implicaría que todos los elfos y "
"otras criaturas feéricas descienden, o al menos fueron creados a imagen de "
"esta misteriosa portadora de la Llama Arcana, hermana de Uria y Yechnagoth, "
"y una de los Diez Originales."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1733
msgid ""
"Eloh. That’s her name — a name that was seldom heard in my times, for nearly "
"nothing was known for certain about her and the myths neglected explaining "
"the origin of every other race on Irdya. I suppose that Zhangor’s influence "
"upon Wesmere may have resulted in the reintroduction of that name to our "
"kin’s lore. Regardless, even though linguistics are not my specialty, I "
"suspect that’s still not her true name, much like the case of Yechnagoth."
msgstr ""
"Eloh. Ese es su nombre, un nombre que rara vez se escuchaba en mis tiempos, "
"pues casi nada se sabía con certeza sobre ella y los mitos omitían explicar "
"el origen de todas las demás razas en Irdya. Supongo que la influencia de "
"Zhangor en Wesmere pudo haber provocado la reintroducción de ese nombre en "
"la tradición de nuestro pueblo. De todos modos, aunque la lingüística no es "
"mi especialidad, sospecho que ese tampoco es su verdadero nombre, al igual "
"que en el caso de Yechnagoth."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1738
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"What you have learned here about all this... it would probably be best to "
"keep it a secret for now, especially the allusions to other worlds. In these "
"times when demons roam and spoil Irdya at will, realizing that they might be "
"closely related to us, and that there might be even more awaiting out "
"there... it could be devastating to our cultures. Perhaps after all this is "
"over..."
msgstr ""
"Lo que habéis aprendido aquí sobre todo esto... probablemente sea mejor "
"mantenerlo en secreto por ahora, especialmente las alusiones a otros mundos. "
"En estos tiempos en que los demonios deambulan y corrompen Irdya a voluntad, "
"darse cuenta de que podrían estar más estrechamente relacionados con "
"nosotros de lo que sospechábamos, y que podría haber más esperándonos allá "
"afuera... podría ser devastador para nuestras culturas, como mínimo. Quizá "
"después de que todo esto termine..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1743
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<i>(snicker)</i> You said that Argan never intended to cause you any harm? "
"All that we have found proves that he really wanted to destroy your kind "
"after all! Using the powers of an ancient demon, no less!"
msgstr ""
"<i>(risilla)</i> ¿Y dices que Argan nunca pretendió hacerte daño? ¡Todo lo "
"que hemos encontrado prueba que realmente quería destruir a los tuyos! ¡Y "
"usando los poderes de un demonio ancestral, nada menos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1748
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I don’t believe that he did any of his plotting against elvenkind out of his "
"own volition. He was... under Uria’s control."
msgstr ""
"No creo que nada de esto lo haya hecho por su propia voluntad. Él estaba... "
"bajo el control de Uria."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1753
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"So, have you forgotten what he said? “I guess I had this coming ever since "
"then.” I know, his last words were very vague, but it certainly sounded like "
"he was well aware of what he was doing the whole time. Perhaps you are right "
"and it was not his intention to cause harm to <i>you</i> in particular, but "
"the damage he caused throughout the continent, in the name of Uria, to the "
"things you protect... did it not affect you emotionally? Furthermore, it "
"seemed like Uria truly felt his loss. Would she have resented his death so "
"much if he was a mere puppet like that old elf guy?"
msgstr ""
"¿Acaso has olvidado lo que dijo? “Supongo que esto me lo tenía merecido "
"desde entonces.” Lo sé, sus últimas palabras fueron muy vagas, pero "
"ciertamente sonaba como si fuera plenamente consciente de lo que estaba "
"haciendo todo el tiempo. Quizá no fuera su intención causar daño a <i>ti</i> "
"en particular, pero el daño que causó por todo el continente, en nombre de "
"Uria, a las cosas que proteges... ¿no te afectó? Además, parecía que Uria "
"sintió su pérdida. Si él hubiera sido solo un títere suyo, ¿habría lamentado "
"tanto su muerte?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1775
msgid ""
"Elynia slowly approached Mal Keshar with a grim expression in her eyes — "
"neither the lich nor Galas had seen that much rage reflected in her before."
msgstr ""
"Elynia se acercó lentamente a Mal Keshar con una expresión sombría en sus "
"ojos — ni el lich ni Galas habían visto antes tanta rabia reflejada en ella."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1790
msgid "You know nothing."
msgstr "No sabes nada."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1795
msgid ""
"I saw enough. I heard enough.\n"
"\n"
"Whoever you loved so deeply back then is not who died at your hand."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1806
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<i>(nervously)</i> Er— I think we should return to the surface before we run "
"out of provisions."
msgstr ""
"<i>(nervioso)</i> Deberíamos regresar a la superficie antes de quedarnos sin "
"provisiones."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1811
msgid ""
"Elynia... if I’m not mistaken, we found a journal in the Heart, and you have "
"kept it all this time with you, correct?"
msgstr ""
"Elynia... si no me equivoco, encontramos un diario en el Corazón, y lo has "
"guardado todo este tiempo contigo, ¿correcto?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1820
msgid ""
"I... the elf who suggested that we take the journal, he was under Uria’s "
"control, wasn’t he? It might not truly be Argan’s."
msgstr ""
"Yo... el elfo que sugirió que tomáramos el diario, estaba bajo el control de "
"Uria, ¿no? Puede que realmente no sea de Argan."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1825
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I am sure it is. I knew Lord Lédinor well enough, and I’m sure that was him "
"speaking, not Uria. It was after we left Argan’s lair that his face and "
"demeanor changed completely. No matter what Uria said, I’m certain that "
"Lédinor was resisting her control just long enough so that he could help us, "
"even though he must have known deep down that she would overpower him in the "
"end.\n"
"\n"
"We are descendants of Eloh, and as the Quenoth elves can attest, not even "
"Yechnagoth’s mind control can work on us that easily. Like Argan before him, "
"it seemed more like his body was infected by some kind of parasite."
msgstr ""
"Estoy seguro de que sí. Conocía bien a Lédinor, y estoy seguro de que era él "
"quien hablaba, no Uria. Fue después cuando su rostro y comportamiento "
"cambiaron por completo. No importa lo que Uria dijera, estoy convencido de "
"que Lédinor luchaba por superar su control todo ese tiempo, resistiéndolo lo "
"suficiente para ayudarnos, aunque sabía que ella triunfaría al final. Si nos "
"lo hubiera contado, se habría derrumbado mucho antes."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1836
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I know you are probably hesitant about reading Argan’s journal because you "
"fear to learn more about how he became the Emperor, and about the trail of "
"destruction he left in his wake..."
msgstr ""
"Sé que probablemente dudas en leer el diario de Argan porque temes descubrir "
"cuánto se convirtió en un monstruo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1845
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2791
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/01_Beyond_her_Smile.cfg:1549
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3924
msgid "I..."
msgstr "Yo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1854
msgid ""
"If you prefer, I could read it for you, and keep any details besides what is "
"relevant to our quest from reaching anyone."
msgstr ""
"Si prefieres, podría leerlo por ti, y evitar que cualquier detalle que no "
"sea relevante para nuestra misión llegue a alguien."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1863
#, fuzzy
msgid "<i>(with a calmer expression)</i> Very well. I trust you."
msgstr "<i>(con expresión más tranquila)</i> Muy bien."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1868
msgid ""
"In the meantime, perhaps you could socialize with the locals or something. "
"Perhaps try to have fun and smile? It really helps when you’ve lived for so "
"long — I should be one to know. While you do that, I’ll be <i>killing</i> "
"myself reading a damn book; I haven’t found any good reading material since "
"the Fall, you know? It seems like everyone suddenly forgot how to read and "
"write after the Wesnothians singlehandedly ended the world!"
msgstr ""
"Mientras tanto, quizás podrías socializar con los locales o algo así. "
"¿Quizás intentar divertirte y sonreír? Realmente ayuda cuando has vivido "
"tanto tiempo — yo debería saberlo. Mientras haces eso, yo me estaré "
"<i>matando</i> leyendo un maldito libro; no he encontrado buen material para "
"leer desde la Caída, ¿sabes? ¡Parece que todos olvidaron de repente cómo "
"leer y escribir después de que los Wesnothianos acabaran con el mundo ellos "
"solos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1873
msgid "... You are already dead."
msgstr "... Ya estás muerto."

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1886
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We have spent too much time in these caverns, and many of my men are "
"starving. I’m sorry, but we’re resuming this expedition another time."
msgstr ""
"Hemos pasado demasiado tiempo en estas cavernas, y muchos de mis hombres "
"están hambrientos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1891
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<i>(furiously sighs, staring at the ceiling)</i> Why do we <b>always</b> "
"have a time limit of some sort for everything we do?"
msgstr ""
"<i>(suspira, mirando al techo)</i> ¿Por qué siempre tenemos algún límite de "
"tiempo para todo lo que hacemos?"

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:179
msgid "Resolutions"
msgstr "Resoluciones"

#. [event]: id=Galas, id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:111
msgid "Vordel"
msgstr "Vordel"

#. [event]: id=Galas, id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:115
msgid "Naron"
msgstr "Naron"

#. [event]: id=Galas, id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:119
msgid "Dela"
msgstr "Dela"

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:131
msgid ""
"It is certainly unfortunate that you couldn’t find a solution to this "
"problem. Everything seems peaceful and good from our current location, but "
"if Uria’s minions win the war and take over the continent, it will only be a "
"matter of time until they come to claim this island. And what if Yechnagoth "
"is able to control the surface creatures of the continent again?"
msgstr ""
"Ciertamente es desafortunado que no pudieras encontrar una solución a este "
"problema. Todo parece pacífico y bueno desde nuestra posición actual, pero "
"si los esbirros de Uria ganan la guerra y toman el continente, solo será "
"cuestión de tiempo hasta que reclamen esta isla. ¿Y si Yechnagoth logra "
"controlar nuevamente a las criaturas de la superficie del continente?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:136
msgid ""
"At least we know that her soul is no longer in this world. There’s a faint "
"possibility that they might be unable to use her heart for anything yet. We "
"must make haste and instruct our allies to purge the remains of Wesmere."
msgstr ""
"Al menos sabemos que su alma ya no está en este mundo. Existe una leve "
"posibilidad de que aún no puedan usar su corazón para nada. Debemos "
"apresurarnos e instruir a nuestros aliados para purgar los restos de Wesmere."

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:141
msgid ""
"A few of our people expressed interest on joining your group to help you in "
"this quest, and learn more about the state of the lands whence we came a "
"couple of centuries ago."
msgstr ""
"Algunos de los nuestros expresaron interés en unirse a tu grupo para "
"ayudarte en esta misión y aprender más sobre el estado de las tierras de "
"donde venimos hace un par de siglos."

#. [message]: speaker=Dela
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:146
msgid "Eloh would want us to help our kin in these dark times."
msgstr ""
"Eloh querría que ayudáramos a nuestros parientes en estos tiempos oscuros."

#. [message]: speaker=Vordel
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:151
msgid ""
"Our numbers are very small, and we don’t have the resources to support an "
"army, but we have the knowledge, and the faith to try to make a difference "
"on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"Nuestro número es muy pequeño y no tenemos recursos para sostener un "
"ejército, pero tenemos el conocimiento y la fe para intentar marcar la "
"diferencia en el campo de batalla."

#. [message]: speaker=Naron
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:156
msgid "It would be an honor to fight alongside you, sir."
msgstr "Sería un honor luchar a tu lado, señor."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Fight, indeed. We have spent too much time far from ‘home’ — who knows "
"what’s become of it since we left."
msgstr ""
"Luchar, sí. Hemos pasado demasiado tiempo lejos del ‘hogar’ — quién sabe qué "
"habrá sido de él desde que nos fuimos."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:166
msgid ""
"The honor is ours. We appreciate and accept your help on this day, but we "
"are even more grateful for the day on which you released Irdya from the "
"eternal nightmare of Yechnagoth’s control."
msgstr ""
"El honor es nuestro. Agradecemos y aceptamos tu ayuda hoy, pero estamos aún "
"más agradecidos por el día en que liberaste a Irdya de la pesadilla eterna "
"del control de Yechnagoth."

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:171
msgid ""
"Young Galas, what you three have done for us is no small deed either. "
"Although your journey is not quite complete yet, by defeating Uria’s "
"designated sovereign of Chaos, you proved that her forces are not "
"invincible, and rekindled that flame of hope everyone needed. You truly are "
"the heroes of the forest elves of this era."
msgstr ""
"Joven Galas, lo que ustedes tres han hecho por nosotros tampoco es una "
"hazaña menor. Aunque su viaje aún no ha terminado, al derrotar al soberano "
"designado por Uria del Caos, demostraron que sus fuerzas no son invencibles, "
"y reavivaron la llama de esperanza que todos necesitaban. Realmente son los "
"héroes de los elfos del bosque de esta era."

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:185
msgid ""
"Kyara is one of our most skilled archers, and she has expressed her desire "
"to join you in your quest. Seeing as how you will need all the help you can "
"get, we thought you might welcome her support."
msgstr ""
"Kyara es una de nuestras arqueras más habilidosas, y ha expresado su deseo "
"de unirse a tu misión. Dado que necesitarás toda la ayuda posible, pensamos "
"que podrías aceptar su apoyo."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. "I’m not sure that’s a good idea."
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:191
msgid "I’m not—"
msgstr "Yo no—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:196
msgid ""
"You can come with us if you wish, but you need to be aware of the dangers "
"that lie in our way."
msgstr ""
"Puedes venir con nosotros si quieres, pero debes estar al tanto de los "
"peligros que se encuentran en nuestro camino."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:201
msgid ""
"I <i>am</i> aware. I’ve already talked with Lord Galas about it — I just "
"want to be of help to our forest cousins in this struggle for our future."
msgstr ""
"Yo <i>lo</i> sé. Ya hablé con Lord Galas al respecto — solo quiero ayudar a "
"nuestros primos del bosque en esta lucha por nuestro futuro."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:210
msgid ""
"Well, we must now prepare for departing tomorrow in the morning. A long "
"voyage back home awaits us..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, ahora debemos prepararnos para partir mañana por la mañana. Nos "
"espera un largo viaje de regreso a casa..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:94
msgid "Explore the peninsula"
msgstr "Explora la península"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:112
msgid ""
"The fog is so thick I can barely see anything in the distance. It’s rather "
"unsettling..."
msgstr ""
"La niebla es tan densa que apenas puedo ver nada a lo lejos. Es bastante "
"inquietante..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:117
msgid ""
"Indeed. We should explore this peninsula carefully and stay together. Maybe "
"we can find an abandoned castle or village where we can rest while we plan "
"our next course of action."
msgstr ""
"Así es. Deberíamos explorar esta península con cuidado y permanecer juntos. "
"Quizás encontremos un castillo o pueblo abandonado donde podamos descansar "
"mientras planeamos nuestro próximo paso."

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:122
msgid ""
"The air is unusually dense. There’s something more about this place I don’t "
"like."
msgstr ""
"El aire está inusualmente denso. Hay algo más en este lugar que no me gusta."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:127
msgid "We may soon find out..."
msgstr "Pronto lo descubriremos..."

#. [unit]: type=Chaos Magus, id=Essornius
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:172
msgid "Essornius"
msgstr "Essornius"

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:282
msgid "What kind of infernal spawn is that thing?!"
msgstr "¿Qué clase de engendro infernal es esa cosa?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:287
msgid "Shaxthals. We are definitely not alone here."
msgstr "Shaxthals. Definitivamente no estamos solos aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:292
msgid "We’ll have to fight our way through this place then."
msgstr "Entonces tendremos que abrirnos paso a la fuerza por este lugar."

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:327
msgid "Yes, we did it!"
msgstr "¡Sí, lo logramos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:332
msgid "Let’s leave this land as quickly as possible."
msgstr "Salgamos de esta tierra lo más rápido posible."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:356
msgid "Galas?"
msgstr "¿Galas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:382
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1380
msgid "... Elynia?"
msgstr "... Elynia?"

#. [scenario]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:4
msgid "The Triad — Part 1"
msgstr "La Tríada — Parte 1"

#. [unit]: type=Chaos Razerman, id=Aethercyn
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:284
msgid "Aethercyn"
msgstr "Aethercyn"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:378
msgid "Galas... you too..."
msgstr "Galas... tú también..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:383
msgid "Well done, Kendria. Well done."
msgstr "Bien hecho, Kendria. Bien hecho."

#. [message]: speaker=Nar-hamoth
#. “master” here is feminine
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:389
msgid ""
"I see that the little vermin fell into the master’s trap as expected. And "
"they brought the Ruby of Fire with them! Ha, ha!"
msgstr ""
"Veo que la pequeña sabandija cayó en la trampa de la maestra como "
"esperábamos. ¡Y trajeron el Rubí de Fuego con ellos! ¡Ja, ja!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:394
msgid "What are you talking about..."
msgstr "¿De qué estás hablando...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Nar-hamoth
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:416
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Keep it shut, pathetic Irdyan rats! Were it up to me, we would have killed "
"you all on sight, but our master greatly wanted to see your faces one last "
"time."
msgstr ""
"Los habríamos matado al verlos, ratas, pero nuestra maestra deseaba ver sus "
"caras por última vez."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:421
msgid ""
"Temper your anger, my friend — after all, would it not be bad form to let "
"their souls depart blissfully unaware of their mistake in bringing the "
"artifact straight to us? Ha, ha!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:426
msgid "You... don’t have... a master... We killed... him..."
msgstr "Ustedes... no tienen... una maestra... La matamos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:444
msgid "We have reserves, my dear."
msgstr "Tenemos reservas, querida."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:453
msgid "You...?! We should have finished you off... when we had the chance..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:458
msgid ""
"Had you done that, someone else would have taken Argan’s position in my "
"stead — someone less generous, perhaps, like our brutish colleague over "
"here. Do you not wish to hear the story I have to tell you as proof of my "
"gratitude? I am fairly certain Elynia in particular would love to know more "
"about the significance of the little trinket she’s been carelessly parading "
"around for so many generations."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. [message]: speaker=Halbadrel
#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:463
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:487
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2203
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:777
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:815
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:829
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:839
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:947
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2104
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2279
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2284
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2289
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2294
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:1761
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2143
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2037
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3459
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4385
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1016
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2921
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:523
msgid "..."
msgstr "..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:468
msgid ""
"Irdya, like many other worlds, is littered with spatial anomalies that "
"result in unstable pathways between them and Inferno. Long ago, it was "
"decided that these breaches in our worlds should be guarded by very powerful "
"demons to prevent unwanted contact. Think of it as a quarantine of sorts, "
"established out of fear that the denizens of Inferno could interfere with "
"the healing process that followed the First Cycle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:473
msgid ""
"Alas, untold millennia ago, humans on this earth discovered that they could "
"harness the forces of nature to overcome all sorts of challenges. Eventually "
"they created a series of artifacts capable of building portals between "
"locations on Irdya with ease. How, you may ask? My research never managed to "
"uncover the specifics of the ritual, but all evidence points to them "
"subduing some kind of dark god and using its blazing flesh and blood in the "
"construction of these devices.\n"
"\n"
"But they were mere replicas of an original — without contact with it, the "
"power within them eventually faded away. Meanwhile, the original was thought "
"lost in a bloody war between the descendants of its creators and uncultured "
"barbarians."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:480
msgid ""
"I thought this sounded familiar. For the longest time I had been in search "
"of a relic of the old empire, one whose history started with a similar "
"event. Could they be one and the same? After all, few people ever came close "
"to grasping the true nature of the Ruby of Fire before somebody ordered its "
"destruction. Yet... it was never truly destroyed, was it?\n"
"\n"
"My vast experience carrying out tasks for Uria gave me some familiarity with "
"the power of the Gatekeepers, enough to identify it as its bearer "
"unwittingly brought it before my eyes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:492
msgid ""
"I could not believe my eyes — after wasting most of my original life trying "
"to find it, the Ruby of Fire found <i>me</i> instead! Whoever would have "
"thought that the staff that once belonged to the Enchantress Niryone of "
"Wesmere had become a vessel of such ancient power! If only Argan had known "
"about this — there would have been no need for us to trace the rifts created "
"by Naia and her fallen sister in order to sustain our operations."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Nar-hamoth
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:501
msgid ""
"Now that we have the artifact, we can use it to merge this pitiful world "
"with Inferno..."
msgstr ""
"Ahora que tenemos el artefacto, podemos usarlo para fusionar este patético "
"mundo con Inferno..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:506
msgid "... dispel the curse of Iluvia..."
msgstr "... disipar la maldición de Iluvia..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:511
msgid "... and reunite Uria and the other Guardians..."
msgstr "... y reunir a Uria con los otros Guardianes..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:516
msgid "... to restore the Initial Order."
msgstr "... para restaurar el Orden Inicial."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:578
msgid "Now this belongs to us."
msgstr "Ahora esto nos pertenece."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:585
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"At long last! The Ruby of Fire, in all its glory! May I borrow it for a "
"second, my lady?"
msgstr "¡Sí! ¡Nos pertenece! ¿Puedo tomarlo un segundo, mi señora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:614
msgid "This is not over yet!"
msgstr "¡Esto aún no ha terminado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:804
msgid "AAAAAAAAAAH!"
msgstr "¡AAAAAAARRGH!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:847
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/02_02_Reckoning.cfg:259
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:749
msgid "How did you—"
msgstr "¿Cómo supiste—?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:867
msgid "Kill the intruders! Kill them all! NOW!"
msgstr "¡Maten a los intrusos! ¡Mátenlos a todos! ¡AHORA!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:904
msgid ""
"By the power you have bestowed upon me, Uria, may the spells conferring life "
"to the dead be canceled now!"
msgstr ""
"Por el poder que me has otorgado, Uria, ¡que los hechizos que confieren vida "
"a los muertos sean cancelados ahora!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:907
msgid "dispel undead"
msgstr "disipar no-muertos"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:944
msgid "AGGGGGGGGGHHHHH!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡AGGGGGGGGGHHHHH!!!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:949
msgid "What is this...?!"
msgstr "¿Qué es esto...?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:956
msgid ""
"Unbind the dust from this world and smite the unworthy descendants of Xia’el!"
msgstr ""
"¡Libera el polvo de este mundo y castiga a los indignos descendientes de "
"Xia’el!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:959
msgid "dispel faerie"
msgstr "disipar hadas"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:996
msgid "This... is this the kind of powers possessed by Uria?!"
msgstr "Esto... ¿es este el tipo de poder que posee Uria?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1001
msgid "We need to get out of this place, quickly!"
msgstr "¡Debemos salir de este lugar, rápido!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1006
msgid "Kendria, call upon our new weapon."
msgstr "Kendria, invoca nuestra nueva arma."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1011
msgid "But we... we haven’t finished—"
msgstr "Pero nosotros... no hemos terminado—"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1032
msgid "Reinforcements! Don’t allow them to escape!"
msgstr "¡Refuerzos! ¡No permitan que escapen!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1114
msgid "That corridor is clear! It’s our only hope!"
msgstr "¡Ese pasillo está despejado! ¡Es nuestra única esperanza!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1123
msgid "Move Galas, Elynia or Mal Keshar to the exit location"
msgstr "Mueve a Galas, Elynia o Mal Keshar al punto de salida"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1229
msgid "More reinforcements! Strike down those heathens, now!"
msgstr "¡Más refuerzos! ¡Derribad a esos infieles, ahora!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1234
msgid ""
"We weren’t fast enough — now they are coming from that corridor as well!"
msgstr ""
"No fuimos lo suficientemente rápidos — ¡ahora vienen también por ese pasillo!"

#. [scenario]: type=Shaxthal Drone
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:4
msgid "The Triad — Part 2"
msgstr "La Tríada — Parte 2"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:172
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:208
msgid "Locate an exit"
msgstr "Localiza una salida"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:325
msgid ""
"We must make haste before their reinforcements catch up with us. Which "
"direction should we go?"
msgstr ""
"Debemos darnos prisa antes de que sus refuerzos nos alcancen. ¿Hacia qué "
"dirección deberíamos ir?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:330
msgid ""
"A slight breeze comes from the passage to our left; we should follow it."
msgstr ""
"Una ligera brisa viene del pasaje a nuestra izquierda; deberíamos seguirla."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:335
msgid ""
"These passages are eerily vacant. I feel we are being led into a trap of "
"some sort..."
msgstr ""
"Estos pasajes están inquietantemente vacíos. Siento que nos están "
"conduciendo a alguna clase de trampa..."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:400
msgid "Mal Keshar, we’ll need some reinforcements to get through!"
msgstr "¡Mal Keshar, necesitaremos refuerzos para poder avanzar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:426
msgid ""
"Things are looking rather grim... We have not fully recovered from that "
"demon’s attack, and her guards are in hot pursuit. Our backup has most "
"certainly been scattered or slaughtered by now. What do you plan to do now "
"that this has turned into a suicide mission?"
msgstr ""
"La situación se ve bastante sombría... No nos hemos recuperado del ataque de "
"esa demonio, y sus guardias nos siguen de cerca. Nuestros refuerzos "
"seguramente ya han sido dispersados o masacrados. ¿Qué planeas hacer ahora "
"que esto se ha convertido en una misión suicida?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:440
msgid "A gate! Let’s strike it down—"
msgstr "¡Una puerta! Derribémosla—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:494
msgid "It’s an ambush!"
msgstr "¡Es una emboscada!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:499
msgid ""
"Damn them all! I don’t know if I’ll be able to keep on with this for much "
"longer."
msgstr ""
"¡Malditos sean todos! No sé si podré continuar con esto por mucho más tiempo."

#. [message]: type=Shaxthal Stormblade Ivyel
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:536
#, fuzzy
msgid "... Elynia... please... don’t..."
msgstr "... Elynia... por favor..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:541
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/02_01_Return_to_Raelthyn.cfg:1092
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2181
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3540
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr "¿Eh?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:546
msgid "It’s running away!"
msgstr "¡Está huyendo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:577
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I— Hopefully it’s sufficiently damaged so that it won’t attack us from "
"behind again. We need to advance, quickly."
msgstr ""
"Espero que esté lo suficientemente dañado como para que no nos ataque por la "
"retaguardia otra vez. Debemos avanzar, rápido."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:899
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2109
msgid "What the—"
msgstr "¿Pero qué—?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:909
msgid ""
"Amidst the smoke from the explosion, a pair of red glowing eyes could be "
"seen..."
msgstr ""
"Entre el humo de la explosión, se podían ver un par de ojos rojos "
"brillantes..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:980
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You thought you could escape so easily, didn’t you? I have not forgotten "
"what you did back then. How does it feel to be the ones at a disadvantage "
"now?"
msgstr ""
"¿Acaso pensaron, insensatos, que podrían escapar <i>tan</i> fácilmente de "
"nosotros? No he olvidado lo que me hicieron. ¿Cómo se siente estar en "
"desventaja ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:985
msgid "Elynia, Mal Keshar! Go! Now!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:992
#, fuzzy
msgid "Galas, no!"
msgstr "Galas, yo—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1037
msgid "Commendable effort, elf. Alas, not enough."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1110
msgid ""
"It doesn’t have to be like this. Just give me the staff back and <b>I</b> "
"will spare your life like you did with mine."
msgstr ""
"No tiene por qué ser así. Solo devuélveme el báculo y <b>yo</b> perdonaré tu "
"vida como tú hiciste con la mía."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1129
#, fuzzy
msgid "Over there! Follow the track, quick!"
msgstr "¡Sigan este raíl, rápido!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1202
msgid "Follow the underground rail and locate an exit"
msgstr "Sigue el raíl subterráneo y localiza una salida"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1254
msgid ""
"There are more of those biomechanical creatures pursuing us now. Oh, well, "
"this entire plan was doomed to failure from the very beginning — I don’t "
"know what I was thinking!"
msgstr ""
"Ahora hay más de esas criaturas biomecánicas persiguiéndonos. En fin, todo "
"este plan estaba condenado al fracaso desde el principio… ¡No sé en qué "
"estaba pensando!"

#. [scenario]: type=Shaxthal Drone
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:4
msgid "The Triad — Part 3"
msgstr "La Tríada — Parte 3"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:229
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:163
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:537
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:334
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2836
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2847
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3115
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2622
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:239
#: After_the_Storm/macros/character-defines.cfg:41
msgid "Elyssa"
msgstr "Elyssa"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:241
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1883
msgid "What now?"
msgstr "¿Y ahora qué?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:246
msgid "Let’s keep moving. Hopefully there is an exit somewhere ahead. Elynia—"
msgstr "Sigamos avanzando. Con suerte, hay una salida más adelante. Elynia—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:251
#, fuzzy
msgid "I’m fine — don’t worry about me! What about you?!"
msgstr "E— Estoy bien. No te preocupes."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:254
msgid "You haven’t escaped, you know."
msgstr "No han escapado, ¿saben?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:258
msgid "MOVE!"
msgstr "¡MUÉVANSE!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:265
msgid "It would have been so much better for all of you to give up..."
msgstr "Habría sido mucho mejor para todos ustedes rendirse…"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:273
msgid ""
"Galas... Why did you do that? Why did you charge straight at her? She "
"could’ve easily killed you with a single blast of her fire!!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:278
msgid ""
"She is a formidable opponent for sure, but I desperately needed to buy you "
"and Mal Keshar time to find a way out. It worked, didn’t it? Even though I "
"did not count on you getting involved and doing... that. I’m not even sure "
"how you managed to hit her so hard with only your staff."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:283
msgid ""
"I heard you very well you back then — and you thought I would leave you for "
"dead just like that?? I <b>refuse</b> to let you play hero now, after "
"everything we have been through! Please, <b>please</b> don’t scare me like "
"that again!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:292
msgid ""
"... I am sorry, Elynia. I just desperately wanted to help you escape this "
"place alive."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:297
msgid ""
"Galas, I... I just don’t want you to put your life on the line like that "
"ever again. After everything we’ve been through, I need— we need to stick "
"together. We can’t lose you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:306
#, fuzzy
msgid "I understand. I’m sorry."
msgstr "Lo entiendo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:311
msgid ""
"... I’m sorry too. I didn’t mean to sound so harsh, Galas. Just promise me "
"you’ll stay by my side from here on."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:316
msgid "I will, Elynia. I promise."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:366
msgid "Uria be damned! It’s a dead end."
msgstr "¡Maldita sea Uria! Es un callejón sin salida."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:371
msgid "It’s more like a trap—"
msgstr "Es más bien una trampa—"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:374
msgid ""
"You cannot blame me. I gave you one opportunity to reconsider your actions — "
"I’m not giving you another."
msgstr ""
"No pueden culparme. Les di una oportunidad para reconsiderar sus acciones; "
"no les daré otra."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:397
msgid "You made a big mistake in leaving the safety of the Northlands..."
msgstr ""
"Cometieron un gran error al abandonar la seguridad de las Tierras del Norte…"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:416
msgid "—I knew it. We are trapped."
msgstr "—Lo sabía. Estamos atrapados."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:421
msgid "Not quite — there seems to be a passage behind that crack on the wall!"
msgstr "No del todo; ¡parece haber un pasaje detrás de esa grieta en la pared!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:444
msgid ""
"Elynia, the teleportation spell you learned back in Zocthanol! Can you use "
"it?"
msgstr ""
"¡Elynia, el hechizo de teletransportación que aprendiste en Zocthanol! "
"¿Puedes usarlo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:449
msgid ""
"I— I don’t know, it wasn’t really made to transport more than one person, "
"and I haven’t had a chance to try it myself."
msgstr ""
"Yo… no lo sé. En realidad no fue diseñado para transportar a más de una "
"persona, y no he tenido la oportunidad de probarlo."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:454
msgid ""
"This is probably not the best moment to fiddle with unpredictable kinds of "
"magic like this. As I said before, many mages have disappeared attempting to "
"master the power of teleportation."
msgstr ""
"Probablemente este no sea el mejor momento para jugar con un tipo de magia "
"tan impredecible. Como dije antes, muchos magos han desaparecido intentando "
"dominar el poder de la teletransportación."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:459
msgid "It’s an option to consider, nonetheless..."
msgstr "Aun así… es una opción a considerar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:579
msgid "This place stinks of <i>blood</i>. What’s with that water?"
msgstr "Este lugar apesta a <i>sangre</i>. ¿Qué pasa con esa agua?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:584
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I fear that it <i>is</i> blood, in fact. Something is really wrong. No "
"single creature could contain so much of it. Who knows what kinds of twisted "
"experiments these fiends perform in here?"
msgstr ""
"Me temo que en realidad <i>es</i> sangre. Algo anda muy mal. Ninguna "
"criatura podría contener tanta. ¿Quién sabe qué clase de experimentos "
"retorcidos hacen estos demonios aquí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:589
msgid "There truly appears to be no way out of this chamber. What do we do?"
msgstr "Realmente no parece haber salida de esta cámara. ¿Qué hacemos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:594
msgid ""
"I’ll tell you what: we shall create our own exit from this accursed place by "
"tearing it all down from the inside!"
msgstr ""
"Te diré qué haremos: ¡crearemos nuestra propia salida de este maldito lugar "
"derrumbándolo desde adentro!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#. The otherwise intended end of the sentence is: "try that teleportation spell now!".
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:600
msgid "Or we could take the risk and—"
msgstr "O podríamos arriesgarnos y—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:666
msgid "G—"
msgstr "¡G—!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Lady of Light
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:707
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/08_And_then_there_was_Chaos.cfg:770
msgid "NO!"
msgstr "¡NO!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:722
msgid ""
"You opted for doing this the hard way after all, didn’t you? The staff — "
"hand it over now."
msgstr ""
"Al final optaron por hacerlo de la manera difícil, ¿verdad? El bastón… "
"entréguenmelo ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:727
msgid "—I..."
msgstr "—Yo…"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:732
msgid "Elynia... we must..."
msgstr "Elynia… debemos…"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:743
msgid "—I... I damn you, Elyssa... I damn you and your kind... for this..."
msgstr "—Yo… te maldigo, Elyssa… te maldigo a ti y a los tuyos… por esto…"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:756
msgid ""
"My dear, we were damned long ago by the First Gods. Your petty words are "
"irrelevant in the grand scheme of things. Hand it over now."
msgstr ""
"Querida mía, fuimos malditos hace mucho por los Primeros Dioses. Tus "
"palabras insignificantes son irrelevantes en el gran esquema de las cosas. "
"Entrégalo ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:761
msgid "Elynia, the spell!"
msgstr "¡Elynia, el hechizo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:770
msgid ""
"Don’t you see? We aren’t that different after all. You just lost your new "
"beloved just like you lost Argan. I lost <i>much</i> more than that long "
"ago. You think he was important because you never had to endure the cruelty "
"and ruthlessness of the beasts that dare call themselves ‘humans’."
msgstr ""
"¿No lo ves? Después de todo, no somos tan diferentes. Acabas de perder a tu "
"nuevo amado igual que perdiste a Argan. Yo perdí <i>mucho</i> más que eso "
"hace tiempo. Piensas que él era importante porque nunca tuviste que soportar "
"la crueldad y la brutalidad de las bestias que se atreven a llamarse a sí "
"mismas ‘humanos’."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:775
msgid "Stop listening to her, Elynia!"
msgstr "¡Deja de escucharla, Elynia!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:796
msgid "What a waste. Don’t think you’ll find anything of value in Wesmere."
msgstr "Qué desperdicio. No creas que encontrarás nada de valor en Wesmere."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:839
msgid ""
"That’s it. We are now utterly lost in these infested passages... and the "
"worst part is that I was the one who devised this disastrous rescue plan."
msgstr ""
"Eso es todo. Ahora estamos completamente perdidos en estos pasajes "
"infestados... y lo peor es que fui yo quien ideó este desastroso plan de "
"rescate."

