#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1598
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2295
msgid ""
"You will not be able to recall or recruit any units until the end of the "
"mission"
msgstr ""
"No podrás reincorporar ni reclutar unidades más tarde hasta el final de la "
"misión"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:895
msgid "Locate Yechnagoth’s heart"
msgstr "Localiza el corazón de Yechnagoth"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:908
msgid ""
"Somehow, this place seems much larger than it was last time we set foot in "
"it. Then again, we did intentionally avoid venturing deeper into the hive as "
"we were in a rush."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:913
msgid ""
"So, from what you said we are looking for a roughly-spherical scarlet gem-"
"like artifact, about the size of a closed fist and which gives off a very "
"distinctive aura, which may or may not be embedded in some sort of shell. "
"Are we absolutely sure it’s not been relocated since Argan wrote about it? "
"Neither last time nor now can I feel anything of importance other than "
"Zhangor’s taint."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:918
msgid ""
"As I understand, these things are much like oil lamps and their intensity "
"can be adjusted at will, or even turned off entirely when not in use. "
"Argan’s lead is all we have for now, I fear."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Mal Abaddon, type=Chaos Lorekeeper
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1009
#, fuzzy
msgid "Mal Abaddon"
msgstr "Mal Arkelean"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#. The "fated one" he refers to is Elynia. As world lore will reveal in the
#. next scenario, Mal Abaddon took part in a program codenamed "Thornfire".
#. As part of the program, both he and Mal Si'ah had access to privileged
#. information about Elynia's true nature, that they were under oath to not
#. divulge to anyone else, not even the Iron Council.
#. Meanwhile, neither Elynia nor Mal Keshar are heeding his words; even though
#. Mal Keshar knows quite a lot more than he lets on at this point, he's not
#. interested in listening to Chaos preachers.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1037
msgid ""
"O fated one, led astray by the non-believers! I pray that the Mistress of "
"the Void takes pity on your soul. Come forth and hear the truth!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1042
msgid "I would roll my eyes if I had any."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1079
msgid "A prayer for your salvation!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1087
msgid ""
"Only ruination awaits those who willfully transgress into the territory of "
"the divine."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1100
msgid "O fated one... your pilgrimage continues. May peace... find... you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1112
msgid ""
"What’s the point of turning themselves into these hideous biomechanical "
"abominations if they are just as mortal as before? Oh hey, I seem to have "
"found something in his robes. Let’s see..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1121
msgid ""
"I also found what appears to be a miniature version of those crystal glyphs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1126
msgid ""
"These things must be very important if one of their high-ranking priests was "
"carrying them around. I shall keep them safe."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1168
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1266
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:309
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:793
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1254
msgid "Access granted."
msgstr "Acceso concedido."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1204
msgid "We should have access to the lower levels now. Onward!"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Dante, type=Chaos Arbalestier
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1228
msgid "Dante"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1298
msgid "So glad we did not need to fiddle with the glyph to get this gate open."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1304
msgid ""
"The area up ahead seems very different to the rest. We must be on guard."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: race=orc,goblin,faerie,human,elf, type=Shaxthal Drone
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:4
msgid "Wesmere Terminus"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:56
#, fuzzy
msgid "team_name^Wesmere Terminus"
msgstr "Defensa de Wesmere"

#. [label]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:194
msgid "Terminal Hub C1"
msgstr ""

#. [label]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:199
msgid "Genetic Repository C3"
msgstr ""

#. [label]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:204
msgid "Power Plant NW-ß"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:508
msgid "Search for clues as to the whereabouts of Yechnagoth’s heart"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:525
msgid ""
"The group proceeded into an enormous chamber, carved deep into the bowels of "
"the earth through clearly artificial means. Some of the technological "
"structures around seemed to have been long in disuse, with evident signs of "
"weathering, while others appeared to have been recently operated or even "
"rearranged."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:530
msgid ""
"Still no sign of anything out of the ordinary, as far as I can perceive. "
"(<i>sighs</i>) We’ll need to sweep this place if we hope to locate that "
"accursed artifact. How well could these self-important wretches possibly "
"conceal the remains of a god they worship so fervently, anyway?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:582
msgid ""
"Locking us in already? Do they seriously expect us to be deterred by a rusty "
"metal gate?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:587
msgid ""
"Something doesn’t seem right. Someone is clearly watching our every move and "
"doesn’t want us to leave — yet, it remains eerily vacant in here. Not to "
"mention that surely they would do anything in their power to keep us from "
"reaching Yechnagoth’s heart."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:592
msgid ""
"Well, it’s not like you could ever resist the allure of a trap like this, "
"anyway. We came in here ready for anything, so let us get working on that "
"investigation now! It might not be in here but we may be able to at least "
"find more clues."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:654
msgid "Level 5 clearance required. Access denied."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:659
msgid ""
"Hmmm, Elynia, this crystal glyph seems to want some sort of identity proof. "
"Remember that crystal we got from the custodian of this place? You should "
"try bringing it here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:678
msgid ""
"Operator credentials verified: Mal Zagarn\n"
"\n"
"Access granted."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:685
msgid "Mal Zagarn... it can’t be..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:690
msgid ""
"I remember I saw the name somewhere in the documents we pilfered from their "
"capital... The name of the founder of Uria’s cult... Argan. He was here "
"after all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:695
msgid ""
"Bear in mind someone else could have borrowed — or even ‘borrowed’ — the "
"crystal from him. It matters little to us, anyway. Shall we see what "
"information we can squeeze out of this shiny rock?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=loredump_glyph
