"\n"
"Stand-by block rescinded.\n"
"\n"
"Core unit insertion complete.\n"
"\n"
"Critical block initialization complete.\n"
"\n"
"Phase one start-up complete.\n"
"\n"
"Incubation chamber draining started."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:866
msgid "... What is that mechanical voice?"
msgstr "... ¿Qué es esa voz mecánica?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:873
msgid ""
"<i>(Male voice)</i>\n"
"\n"
"Entity induction rod detached.\n"
"\n"
"Neural phase normalization in progress.\n"
"\n"
"Estimated time for incubation chamber draining: five minutes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:959
msgid ""
"Bad news for us is what it is. Look! They are unleashing their vermin on us!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:964
#, fuzzy
msgid "Brace yourselves!"
msgstr "¡Prepárate!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:969
msgid "Survive the assault"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1046
msgid ""
"Malin, I can feel it now... I can feel its presence. But how— where have I "
"felt this before...?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1053
msgid ""
"Elynia, I found something else in the glyph. You <b>need</b> to read this, "
"now."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_note_443
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1059
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:123
msgid "Personal Note #443: Usurping the Divine"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1079
#, fuzzy
msgid "... We are too late already, aren’t we?"
msgstr "... No estamos intentando localizar a Zhangor, ¿verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1265
msgid "—Uria be damned!"
msgstr "¡—Maldita sea Uria!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1270
msgid ""
"Hey, that conspicuous glowing orb embedded in its torso seems important!"
msgstr "¡Oye, esa esfera luminosa incrustada en su torso parece importante!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1283
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Yes. It must be the very thing we have been searching for. Destroy it! "
"Destroy it at all costs!"
msgstr ""
"Sí. Debe ser exactamente lo que hemos estado buscando. No podríamos haber "
"llegado en peor momento... ¡Destrúyanla! ¡Destrúyanla a toda costa!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1287
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1593
msgid "Destroy the Queen"
msgstr "Destruye a la Reina"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1295
msgid "The Queen"
msgstr "La Reina"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1295
msgid "Last Steward of the Sylvan Dominion"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1378
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We have found those things before! They must have something to do with the "
"hive, and possibly this creature as well — perhaps some kind of power "
"source? Try destroying them!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ya hemos encontrado esas cosas antes, en la antigua capital! Deben tener "
"algo que ver con la colmena y, posiblemente, también con esta criatura... "
"¿quizá alguna clase de fuente de energía? ¡Intenten destruirlas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1517
msgid "This appears to be causing some damage to the beast!"
msgstr "¡Parece que esto está causando daño a la bestia!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1522
msgid "Very well — let’s do some more!"
msgstr "Muy bien, ¡hagamos un poco más!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1526
msgid "Destroy the energy supply units in the Queen’s chamber"
msgstr ""
"Destruye las unidades de suministro de energía en la cámara de la Reina"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1589
#, fuzzy
msgid "It’s working! Let’s strike it down now!"
msgstr "¡Está funcionando! ¡Acaben con ella ahora!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1749
msgid "*Uurgh*"
msgstr "*Uurgh*"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1754
msgid "—Malin? Are you all right?"
msgstr "—¿Malin? ¿Estás bien?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1763
msgid ""
"This... this place is not doing me any good... There is a greater force at "
"work in here, pulling our souls into it..."
msgstr ""
"E-este lugar... no me está haciendo ningún bien... Hay una fuerza mayor "
"obrando aquí, que está absorbiendo nuestras almas..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1768
msgid "I should be able to heal you, just—"
msgstr "Debería poder curarte, solo—"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1773
msgid ""
"No... Maybe if you and Argan hadn’t decided to use me as your punching bag "
"back there... Let me just... lend you a hand while I still can."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1829
msgid "My work here is not done."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1853
msgid ""
"The unsightly behemoth let out a terrifying loud screech with its dying "
"breath. As the creature collapsed, the alien core in its chest shattered, "
"and burst, releasing a great amount of energy that enveloped all in ghostly "
"red tendrils..."
msgstr ""
"El deforme coloso dejó escapar un chillido aterrador con su último aliento. "
"Cuando la criatura se desplomó, el núcleo alienígena de su pecho se hizo "
"añicos y estalló, liberando una gran cantidad de energía que envolvió todo "
"en espectrales zarcillos rojos..."

#. [message]
#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2001
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2007
#, fuzzy
msgid "The energy is flooding the entire chamber!"
msgstr "¡La energía está llenando este lugar!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2016
msgid "... an energy of a kind unknown to either Elynia or the lich."
msgstr ""
"... una energía de un tipo desconocido tanto para Elynia como para el liche."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. Condenser/capacitor.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2064
msgid ""
"plural_you^... It’s clear now that those power condensers were essential for "
"running something else here. All of you, make haste and return to the "
"surface before the hive collapses."
msgstr ""
"plural_you^... Ahora está claro que esos condensadores de energía eran "
"esenciales para hacer funcionar algo más aquí. Todos ustedes, dense prisa y "
"regresen a la superficie antes de que la colmena colapse."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2069
msgid "<i>We</i>? What about <i>you</i>?!"
msgstr "<i>¿Nosotros</i>? ¿Y qué hay de <i>ti</i>?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. Condenser/capacitor.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2076
msgid ""
"singular_you^... It’s clear now that those power condensers were essential "
"for running something else here. You must make haste and return to the "
"surface before the hive collapses."
msgstr ""
"singular_you^... Ahora está claro que esos condensadores de energía eran "
"esenciales para hacer funcionar algo más aquí. Debes darte prisa y regresar "
"a la superficie antes de que la colmena colapse."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2081
msgid "<i>I</i>? What about <i>you</i>?!"
msgstr "<i>¿Yo</i>? ¿Y qué hay de <i>ti</i>?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2096
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Surely you realize that I am well past my time to roam this earth — I am as "
"old as a fossil, and our clashes with Elyssa and Argan have truly had a long-"
"lasting effect on my power... The energy that’s engulfing all right now is "
"tearing into my very soul... Heh... It has truly been an eternity since the "
"last time I felt pain like this."
msgstr ""
"Seguramente te das cuenta de que mi tiempo deambulado por esta tierra ya ha "
"pasado... Soy tan viejo como un fósil, y nuestra pequeña lucha contra Elyssa "
"y Argan en la frontera entre el Infierno e Irdya realmente dejó un efecto "
"duradero en mis poderes... El poder que está consumiendo este lugar ahora "
"está desgarrando mi propia alma... Duele."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2101
msgid "Malin, you can’t... You have to—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2106
msgid ""
"You and I... we have many followers from diverse backgrounds. I am sure "
"that, should you need a new necromancer to help you, many will be willing to "
"take up my position. Just make sure to not get yourself killed and don’t "
"forget that you are here fighting for a greater cause, one that transcends "
"the fate of Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Tú y yo... tenemos muchos seguidores de distintos orígenes. Estoy seguro de "
"que, si necesitas un nuevo nigromante que te ayude, muchos estarán "
"dispuestos a ocupar mi lugar. Solo asegúrate de no dejarte matar y no "
"olvides que estás aquí luchando por una causa mayor, una que trasciende el "
"destino de Irdya."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2113
msgid "(<i>in tears</i>) Argan’s journal... Where is it?"
msgstr "(<i>entre lágrimas</i>) El diario de Argan... ¿Dónde está?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2121
msgid "Kyara—"
msgstr "Kyara—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2133
msgid "Malin..."
msgstr "Malin..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2145
msgid "<i>(Tears.)</i>"
msgstr "<i>(Lágrimas.)</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2154
#, fuzzy
msgid "How could I let this happen?"
msgstr "¿Cómo pude dejar que esto pasara? ¡NO!"

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2190
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"My lady, we cannot spend any more time here! We must find a way out, quick!"
msgstr "¡Mi señora, no podemos permanecer más tiempo aquí!"

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2212
msgid "Lady!"
msgstr "¡Señora!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2228
msgid ""
"<i>... Don’t forget that you are here fighting for a greater cause, one that "
"transcends the fate of Irdya.</i>"
msgstr ""
"<i>... No olvides que estás aquí luchando por una causa mayor, una que "
"trasciende el destino de Irdya.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2242
msgid "We must get out of here."
msgstr "Debemos salir de aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2248
msgid "I must get out of here."
msgstr "Debo salir de aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2270
#, fuzzy
msgid "This way..."
msgstr "Por allí..."

#. [event]: id='Elynia',
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2291
msgid "Find an alternate exit to the surface"
msgstr "Encuentra una salida alternativa a la superficie"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2434
msgid "<i>... I have always been alone...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... Siempre he estado sola...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. She's talking about a different necromancer, from much longer ago.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2477
msgid ""
"<i>... This is my fate... It is just as the necromancer said back then...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2503
#, fuzzy
msgid "<i>... Perhaps it is time to rest...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... que una vez fui...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2526
msgid ""
"<i>... No...\n"
"\n"
"Galas...\n"
"\n"
"Malin...\n"
"\n"
"Anlindë...\n"
"\n"
"They sacrificed their lives so I could see this through.\n"
"\n"
"I cannot... I will <b>not</b> fail them.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2611
#, fuzzy
msgid "... No turning back now..."
msgstr "... Ya no hay vuelta atrás..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2629
msgid "... It’s all crumbling down. There is no way out..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2742
#, fuzzy
msgid "The spell... I must use Argan’s spell... no matter where it takes me."
msgstr "El hechizo... Debo usar el hechizo..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2758
msgid "<i>... I lost </i>much<i> more than that long ago...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... Perdí </i>mucho<i> más que eso hace tiempo...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2768
msgid "<i>... We aren’t that different after all...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... Después de todo, no somos tan diferentes...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Callback to AtS E1S12 "The Queen".
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2780
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4766
msgid "<i>... a greater cause, one that transcends the fate of Irdya...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... una causa mayor, que trasciende el destino de Irdya...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [event]
#. [side]: type=Guardian of Life Uria, id=Uria
#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2809
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2832
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:795
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2278
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:37
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:57
msgid "Uria"
msgstr "Uria"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2810
msgid "<i>Do you truly think you can fight me?</i>"
msgstr "<i>¿Realmente crees que puedes enfrentarme?</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2833
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<i>You do not have the power of the Union to help you anymore. Your friends "
"are gone. My power is unlimited. You cannot win.</i>"
msgstr ""
"<i>Ya no tienes el poder de la Unión para ayudarte. Tus amigos se han ido. "
"Nuestro poder es ilimitado. No puedes ganar.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2861
msgid "... must..."
msgstr "... debo..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2946
msgid "<i>... Where am I?</i>"
msgstr "<i>... ¿Dónde estoy?</i>"

#. [scenario]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:4
msgid "Death and Rebirth"
msgstr "Muerte y Renacimiento"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [unit]: id=Mal Kendria, type=Necromancer, gender=female
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:136
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:159
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_1.cfg:2755
#: After_the_Storm/macros/character-defines.cfg:53
msgid "Mal Kendria"
msgstr "Mal Kendria"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:138
msgid "<i>My lady?</i>"
msgstr "<i>¿Mi señora?</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:161
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:165
msgid "<i>Where are you?</i>"
msgstr "<i>¿Dónde estás?</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:200
msgid ""
"My lady, we have been looking for you! We have just received excellent news—"
msgstr ""
"¡Mi señora, hemos estado buscándola! Acabamos de recibir excelentes noticias—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:205
msgid "She’s not dead."
msgstr "No está muerta."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:214
msgid ""
"B— but, the Wesmere facility was vaporized after the destruction of the core!"
msgstr ""
"P— pero, ¡la instalación de Wesmere fue vaporizada tras la destrucción del "
"núcleo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:219
msgid ""
"That’s right, but she is not dead. I can feel her. I don’t know where she "
"is, but she’s certainly not dead."
msgstr ""
"Es cierto, pero no está muerta. Puedo sentirla. No sé dónde está, pero sin "
"duda no está muerta."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:234
msgid "But not in Irdya either, or is she?"
msgstr "Pero tampoco está en Irdya, ¿o sí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:243
msgid "She’s not."
msgstr "No lo está."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#. The lackey in question is Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:249
msgid ""
"Good. Wherever she is, she can’t bother us anymore, and her lackey was "
"destroyed in the explosion. It’s a pity that we lost the experimental core "
"units along with such a very strategic location, but we can do without them "
"anyway. I feel the need to ask, however, why install the third unit on our "
"new weapon when any of us could make a better use of it?"
msgstr ""
"Bien. Donde sea que esté, ya no podrá molestarnos, y su lacayo fue destruido "
"en la explosión. Es una pena haber perdido las unidades experimentales del "
"núcleo junto con un lugar tan estratégico, pero podemos arreglárnoslas sin "
"ellos de todas formas. Sin embargo, siento la necesidad de preguntar: ¿por "
"qué instalar la tercera unidad en nuestra nueva arma cuando cualquiera de "
"nosotros podría darle un mejor uso?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:254
msgid ""
"I believe the Norsulans haven’t resolved the contamination issue yet. It’s "
"not the best moment to make risky choices like that with our limited "
"resources; we need to reclaim some land and complete the construction of the "
"other hives."
msgstr ""
"Creo que los norsulanos aún no han resuelto el problema de la contaminación. "
"No es el mejor momento para tomar decisiones arriesgadas como esa con "
"nuestros recursos limitados; necesitamos recuperar algo de territorio y "
"completar la construcción de las otras colmenas."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:259
msgid "As for the original..."
msgstr "En cuanto al original..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:264
msgid "She said we should not do anything with it yet."
msgstr "Dijo que aún no debíamos hacer nada con él."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:273
msgid "I see. Well, that’s all I wanted to know."
msgstr "Ya veo. Bien, eso era todo lo que quería saber."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:280
msgid "Don’t forget that you have a mission to carry out, too."
msgstr "No olvides que también tienes una misión que cumplir."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/13_Death_and_Rebirth.cfg:295
msgid "I am aware, <i>my lady</i>. I am well aware."
msgstr "Lo sé, <i>mi señora</i>. Lo sé muy bien."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:26
msgid ""
"“The defeat of Zhangor.\n"
"\n"
"The destruction of Yechnagoth.\n"
"\n"
"The end of the Chaos Emperor’s rule."
msgstr ""
"La derrota de Zhangor.\n"
"\n"
"La destrucción de Yechnagoth.\n"
"\n"
"El fin del reinado del Emperador del Caos."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:33
msgid ""
"I had hoped all such evil influence on Irdya would be over after all our "
"sacrifices. For a while, I had the conviction that we could somehow restore "
"our world’s past glory.\n"
"\n"
"But I was wrong."
msgstr ""
"Esperaba que toda esa influencia maligna sobre Irdya terminara tras todos "
"nuestros sacrificios. Por un tiempo, tuve la convicción de que podríamos "
"devolverle a nuestro mundo su antigua gloria.\n"
"\n"
"Pero estaba equivocada."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:39
msgid ""
"I am Elynia, former disciple of the late Enchantress Niryone of the Ka’lian "
"of Wesmere Forest. But many remember me instead as the Lady of Light, the "
"blessed elf who fought along Argan, the Master of Darkness, and prevailed "
"against the nigh invincible Demon Lord Zhangor.\n"
"\n"
"My love, Argan. Together, we wielded the legendary Union of Light and "
"Darkness against the false god who nearly exterminated the elvish "
"civilization, the people whom I vowed to protect. Our bond was unbreakable. "
"Until fate forced us apart, and Uria came along."
msgstr ""
"Soy Elynia, antigua discípula de la difunta hechicera Niryone del Ka’lian "
"del Bosque Wesmere. Pero muchos me recuerdan en cambio como la Dama de la "
"Luz, la elfa bendita que luchó junto a Argan, el Maestro de la Oscuridad, y "
"prevaleció contra el casi invencible Señor Demonio Zhangor.\n"
"\n"
"Mi amado Argan. Juntos blandimos la legendaria Unión de Luz y Oscuridad "
"contra el falso dios que casi exterminó la civilización élfica, el pueblo "
"que juré proteger. Nuestro vínculo era irrompible. Hasta que el destino nos "
"separó, y apareció Uria."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:44
msgid ""
"So strong was our bond that only the power of the Union itself could end "
"Argan’s corruption and suffering.\n"
"\n"
"After so long, I was forced to kill him with my own hands."
msgstr ""
"Tan fuerte era nuestro vínculo que solo el poder de la Unión misma pudo "
"poner fin a la corrupción y el sufrimiento de Argan.\n"
"\n"
"Después de tanto tiempo, me vi obligada a matarlo con mis propias manos."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:49
msgid ""
"There was a time when I was said to be pure of heart, that I was fit to "
"wield this staff that was once Niryone’s. But now, I fear that the evil I "
"have committed could overtake my very soul. Ever since the Union left us, I "
"feel as though I am not myself. I can no longer enjoy a gentle breeze, the "
"taste of food, or fresh water. I do not think I could love again either."
msgstr ""
"Hubo un tiempo en que se decía que mi corazón era puro, que era digna de "
"empuñar este báculo que una vez perteneció a Niryone. Pero ahora temo que el "
"mal que he cometido pueda apoderarse de mi propia alma. Desde que la Unión "
"nos abandonó, siento como si ya no fuera yo misma. Ya no puedo disfrutar de "
"una suave brisa, del sabor de la comida ni del agua fresca. Tampoco creo que "
"pueda volver a amar."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:52
msgid ""
"This staff has suddenly become a burden, somehow. Is it because I am "
"allowing myself to be overcome by regret and hesitation? The oath I broke... "
"What if by killing Argan I have taken the next step in allowing myself to be "
"corrupted by this unfathomable force? Is it my destiny to become another "
"pawn in Uria’s schemes?"
msgstr ""
"Este báculo se ha vuelto de repente una carga, de algún modo. ¿Será porque "
"estoy permitiendo que el arrepentimiento y la duda me dominen? El juramento "
"que rompí... ¿Y si al matar a Argan he dado el siguiente paso para dejarme "
"corromper por esta fuerza insondable? ¿Es mi destino convertirme en otro "
"peón de los planes de Uria?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:56
msgid ""
"The Vast Sea seems to be in perpetual unrest now. It was not like this back "
"when I was a young girl. Perhaps Irdya herself is trying to communicate "
"something to us through the changing tides.\n"
"\n"
"The war between the free peoples of Irdya and the forces of Chaos "
"established by Uria and Yechnagoth continues. Unseen enemies of the ancient "
"world, foes from a forgotten era, they threaten to end all life on Irdya "
"through different means. And both bands are relentless in their desire for "
"bloodshed. This is surely pleasing for the so-called mother of demons. But "
"who is she in truth?"
msgstr ""
"El Mar Inmenso parece estar en un perpetuo desasosiego ahora. No era así "
"cuando yo era una joven. Quizá la propia Irdya intenta comunicarnos algo a "
"través de las mareas cambiantes.\n"
"\n"
"La guerra entre los pueblos libres de Irdya y las fuerzas del Caos "
"establecidas por Uria y Yechnagoth continúa. Enemigos invisibles del mundo "
"antiguo, adversarios de una era olvidada, amenazan con acabar con toda la "
"vida en Irdya mediante otros medios. Y ambos bandos son implacables en su "
"deseo de derramamiento de sangre. Esto seguramente complace a la llamada "
"madre de los demonios. Pero, ¿quién es ella en verdad?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:67
msgid ""
"I had not seen the high, snowy peaks of the Heart Mountains in a long time. "
"When last we traveled through them, it was with one of Uria’s foul henchmen "
"in hot pursuit: Mal Hekuba, powerful undead sorcerer of the Iron Triad, one "
"of those that counted themselves the leaders of Uria’s cult on Irdya, and "
"the Chaos Empire in Argan’s absence."
msgstr ""
"Hacía mucho que no veía las altas y nevadas cumbres de las Montañas del "
"Corazón. La última vez que viajamos por ellas, uno de los inmundos secuaces "
"de Uria nos perseguía: Mal Hekuba, poderoso hechicero no-muerto de la Tríada "
"de Hierro, uno de los que se consideraban líderes del culto de Uria en Irdya "
"y del Imperio del Caos en ausencia de Argan."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:71
msgid ""
"Even then, somehow his power seemed greater than Malin Keshar’s own. It "
"would be highly unfortunate for us to come across him now, of all times, as "
"our own necromancer seems to have been debilitated by the ordeal at the "
"Empire’s capital."
msgstr ""
"Incluso entonces, de algún modo su poder parecía superior al del propio "
"Malin Keshar. Sería sumamente desafortunado encontrarnos con él ahora, "
"precisamente cuando nuestro nigromante parece haber quedado debilitado tras "
"la terrible prueba en la capital del Imperio."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:80
msgid ""
"We rested for one night, and swiftly resumed our travel back to the Far "
"North. With their most powerful overlord gone for good, the undead creatures "
"and their masters roaming about the mountains proved to be little more than "
"an occasional nuisance.\n"
"\n"
"A few cultists dared to challenge Mal Keshar on repeated occasions, but none "
"of them were an appropriate match for his power, however weakened he might "
"be after all these years."
msgstr ""
"Descansamos una noche y reanudamos rápidamente nuestro viaje de regreso al "
"Lejano Norte. Con su más poderoso señor eliminado para siempre, las "
"criaturas no-muertas y sus amos que merodeaban por las montañas resultaron "
"ser poco más que una molestia ocasional.\n"
"\n"
"Algunos cultistas se atrevieron a desafiar a Mal Keshar en repetidas "
"ocasiones, pero ninguno fue rival para su poder, por debilitado que pudiera "
"estar tras todos estos años."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:85
msgid ""
"Naturally, their lives were cut short by their futile boldness.\n"
"\n"
"Some of those who witnessed our combined force hastened to offer us shelter "
"and provisions to make it across the long pass. A handful of young acolytes "
"even went as far as to inquire about joining Mal Keshar’s own sizable cult "
"of followers. None of us particularly objected to the motion, but we all "
"agreed to keep them under careful observation."
msgstr ""
"Naturalmente, sus vidas fueron segadas por su fútil osadía.\n"
"\n"
"Algunos de los que presenciaron nuestra fuerza combinada se apresuraron a "
"ofrecernos refugio y provisiones para cruzar el largo paso. Un puñado de "
"jóvenes acólitos incluso se atrevió a preguntar por unirse al nutrido culto "
"de seguidores de Mal Keshar. Ninguno de nosotros se opuso particularmente a "
"la idea, pero acordamos vigilarlos con mucho cuidado."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:91
msgid ""
"After many days, our trip finally came to an end: we were back in the "
"northern country, safe and away from strife’s grasp. Or so it seemed at "
"first."
msgstr ""
"Tras muchos días, nuestro viaje finalmente llegó a su fin: estábamos de "
"regreso en las tierras del norte, a salvo y fuera del alcance de la "
"contienda. O eso parecía al principio."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:100
msgid ""
"We abandoned Aragwaith territory as agreed, never to return. It was a just "
"deal."
msgstr ""
"Abandonamos el territorio aragwaith como se había acordado, para no volver "
"jamás. Fue un trato justo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:103
msgid ""
"The members of the Grand Council stated that no-one witnessed any elf "
"entering or leaving Inodien’s tent. And yet, some people claimed to have "
"heard strange sounds in the forest around the time he was found dead.\n"
"\n"
"But none of this was enough to extinguish the flames surrounding the elvish "
"leaders’ exalted egos. Their brash and unrelenting demeanor disappointed me "
"deeply. It used to be that only the eldest and wisest of us could rise to "
"the highest ranks as members of the Ka’lian in Wesmere; decisions were made "
"after meticulous deliberation and careful planning, always taking into "
"account our needs, desires, and hopes as a civilization. Selfish interests, "
"personal quarrels, and such were swept aside for the purpose of our councils."
msgstr ""
"Los miembros del Gran Consejo afirmaron que nadie vio a ningún elfo entrar o "
"salir de la tienda de Inodien. Y, sin embargo, algunas personas aseguraron "
"haber oído ruidos extraños en el bosque alrededor del momento en que fue "
"hallado muerto.\n"
"\n"
"Pero nada de esto bastó para apagar las llamas que rodeaban los exaltados "
"egos de los líderes élficos. Su actitud temeraria e implacable me decepcionó "
"profundamente. Antes, solo los más ancianos y sabios de los nuestros podían "
"ascender a los rangos más altos como miembros del Ka’lian en Wesmere; las "
"decisiones se tomaban tras una meticulosa deliberación y una planificación "
"cuidadosa, siempre teniendo en cuenta nuestras necesidades, deseos y "
"esperanzas como civilización. Los intereses egoístas, las disputas "
"personales y demás eran apartados para el bien de nuestros consejos."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:108
msgid ""
"I cannot say that the current state of affairs has taken me by surprise. I "
"had already seen our culture decay towards the end of the previous age. "
"After peace on the continent was secured by the men of Wesnoth, our Ka’lian "
"was gradually plagued by inexperienced leaders with ambitious plans, leading "
"up to the greatest mistake of all: Wesmere’s alliance with Zhangor, in "
"anticipation of the Fall of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Still, what happened in the northern country was my fault to some extent. "
"Keeping our kin united under a single banner was supposed to be my mission "
"as well. How could I be so foolish as to allow Galas to delegate leadership "
"to such an unprepared handful?"
msgstr ""
"No puedo decir que el estado actual de las cosas me haya tomado por "
"sorpresa. Ya había visto nuestra cultura decaer hacia el final de la era "
"anterior. Tras asegurarse la paz en el continente gracias a los hombres de "
"Wesnoth, nuestro Ka’lian se vio gradualmente plagado de líderes inexpertos "
"con planes ambiciosos, lo que condujo al mayor error de todos: la alianza de "
"Wesmere con Zhangor, en previsión de la Caída de Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Aun así, lo sucedido en las tierras del norte fue en parte culpa mía. "
"Mantener a los nuestros unidos bajo un solo estandarte también debía ser mi "
"misión. ¿Cómo pude ser tan necia como para permitir que Galas delegara el "
"liderazgo en un grupo tan poco preparado?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:114
msgid ""
"Perhaps they would have fared better with the elf who led them to new "
"prosperous lands in the first place."
msgstr ""
"Quizás les habría ido mejor con la elfa que los condujo a nuevas tierras "
"prósperas en primer lugar."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:124
msgid "As it turned out, our arrival to Tirigaz could not be more timely."
msgstr ""
"Resultó que nuestra llegada a Tirigaz no podría haber sido más oportuna."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:133
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"True to his word, the orcish lord gave us the fastest transport ship in his "
"possession; he also provided us with an experienced crew and many select "
"warriors, and enough provisions for months of travel across the sea. "
"However, he adamantly refused to allow us to hear the news brought by the "
"messenger we saved, and evaded our inquiries about what prompted the "
"conflict between Tirigaz and the saurians. To be fair, there is usually no "
"reason why that sort of trivial quarrel should concern us, but the "
"circumstances were strikingly suspicious.\n"
"\n"
"With Mal Keshar’s help, I managed to pinpoint the approximate location of "
"Zocthanol based on a faint, dark presence towards the southwest — surely a "
"lingering remnant of Yechnagoth’s power."
msgstr ""
"Fiel a su palabra, el señor orco nos entregó la nave de transporte más "
"rápida en su poder; también nos proveyó de una tripulación experimentada y "
"numerosos guerreros selectos, así como provisiones suficientes para meses de "
"travesía por el mar. Sin embargo, se negó rotundamente a permitirnos "
"escuchar las noticias traídas por el mensajero que rescatamos, y esquivó "
"nuestras preguntas sobre el motivo del conflicto entre Tirigaz y los "
"saurios. A decir verdad, por lo general no hay razón para que ese tipo de "
"disputas triviales nos conciernan, pero las circunstancias eran notablemente "
"sospechosas.\n"
"\n"
"Con la ayuda de Mal Keshar, logré precisar la ubicación aproximada de "
"Zocthanol basándome en una tenue y oscura presencia hacia el suroeste — "
"seguramente un remanente persistente del poder de Yechnagoth."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:138
msgid ""
"By the time Naia appeared the next morning, we had already set sail.\n"
"\n"
"Never before in my entire life had I been so far from the forests of the "
"Great Continent, surrounded by an endless body of water brimming with all "
"sorts of majestic and dangerous creatures. Aside from our loud crew, the "
"occasional sight of marine beasts and small deserted isles was all there was "
"to distract us from the overwhelming immensity and solitude of the open "
"ocean. In spite of its alluring beauty, the large body felt hostile and "
"menacing to me. Does that make sense? Admittedly, words to describe the "
"incongruous feeling elude me, even now."
msgstr ""
"Cuando Naia apareció la mañana siguiente, ya habíamos zarpado.\n"
"\n"
"Nunca antes en mi vida había estado tan lejos de los bosques del Gran "
"Continente, rodeada por un cuerpo interminable de agua rebosante de toda "
"clase de criaturas majestuosas y peligrosas. Aparte de nuestra ruidosa "
"tripulación, la vista ocasional de bestias marinas y pequeñas islas "
"desiertas era todo lo que nos distraía de la inmensidad abrumadora y la "
"soledad del océano abierto. A pesar de su belleza cautivadora, el vasto "
"cuerpo de agua me parecía hostil y amenazante. ¿Tiene sentido? Admito que me "
"faltan palabras para describir esa sensación incongruente, incluso ahora."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:143
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"My fear of the ocean’s mysterious nature did not let me sleep well for any "
"single night since we left land. For much of the voyage I stayed awake late "
"during the long darkness, guarding the deck alongside Mal Keshar, "
"contemplating the ever changing mood of the waves, wondering what events "
"continued to transpire on the continent in our absence... reminiscing of the "
"past... pondering my mistakes."
msgstr ""
"El temor a la misteriosa naturaleza del océano no me permitió dormir bien ni "
"una sola noche desde que dejamos tierra.\n"
"\n"
"Gran parte del viaje permanecí despierta hasta tarde durante la larga "
"oscuridad, vigilando la cubierta junto a Mal Keshar, contemplando el siempre "
"cambiante humor de las olas, preguntándome qué acontecimientos seguían "
"ocurriendo en el continente en nuestra ausencia... recordando el pasado... "
"meditando sobre mis errores."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:147
msgid ""
"After countless days, we finally reached our destination as it was lit up by "
"the setting suns.\n"
"\n"
"We carefully planned our landing, and decided that it would be best to keep "
"the orcs and the undead waiting aboard the ship while Galas and I contacted "
"the elves and explained the situation to them. If they once had to survive "
"in the wild, perilous desert, they surely wouldn’t have fond memories of "
"such creatures."
msgstr ""
"Tras incontables días, finalmente alcanzamos nuestro destino iluminado por "
"los soles ponientes.\n"
"\n"
"Planeamos cuidadosamente nuestro desembarco y decidimos que lo mejor sería "
"mantener a los orcos y a los no-muertos esperando a bordo del barco mientras "
"Galas y yo contactábamos a los elfos y les explicábamos la situación. Si "
"alguna vez tuvieron que sobrevivir en el salvaje y peligroso desierto, "
"seguramente no guardan buenos recuerdos de tales criaturas."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:158
msgid ""
"The elves guided us through the forest toward the mountains at the island’s "
"heart, without saying a word to us. We knew it was best to not ask them any "
"questions or do anything that could seem suspicious until we met their "
"authorities.\n"
"\n"
"Their clothes, armor, and weapons seemed much more primitive compared to "
"those used by Galas’ kinsmen. Apparently, much of our craft was forgotten by "
"Quetor’el’s group and their descendants. As we approached the more populated "
"areas, I noticed that even their building designs were much unlike those of "
"their ancestors."
msgstr ""
"Los elfos nos guiaron a través del bosque hacia las montañas en el corazón "
"de la isla, sin decirnos una palabra. Sabíamos que lo mejor era no hacerles "
"preguntas ni realizar nada que pudiera parecer sospechoso hasta encontrarnos "
"con sus autoridades.\n"
"\n"
"Su ropa, armaduras y armas parecían mucho más primitivas en comparación con "
"las usadas por los parientes de Galas. Al parecer, gran parte de nuestro "
"arte se había olvidado por el grupo de Quetor’el y sus descendientes. Al "
"acercarnos a las zonas más pobladas, noté que incluso el diseño de sus "
"edificaciones era muy distinto al de sus antepasados."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:169
msgid ""
"Beyond Galas’ and Anlindë’s second-hand account of the desert elves’ "
"struggle against Yechnagoth, I had not heard the name ‘Eloh’ in a very long "
"time. It is just one of many names used in old myths to refer to the "
"Guardian of the Arcane Flame, a deity-like figure said to have given life to "
"all faerie beings, including us, elves. Nobody knows exactly when or how "
"those tales first appeared, but it is evident that the Quenoth elves have "
"forgotten, misinterpreted, and exaggerated them over time.\n"
"\n"
"These people thrive and live in peace despite having lost much of our "
"civilization’s knowledge and skills, but it was their faith that led them to "
"challenge fate and build a new future — not just for their race, but for all "
"living creatures under the suns. Our gratitude and respect will never "
"suffice to repay that debt..."
msgstr ""
"Más allá del relato de segunda mano de Galas y Anlindë sobre la lucha de los "
"elfos del desierto contra Yechnagoth, hacía mucho tiempo que no oía el "
"nombre ‘Eloh’. Es solo uno de muchos nombres usados en viejos mitos para "
"referirse al Guardián de la Llama Arcana, una figura similar a una deidad "
"que se dice dio vida a todos los seres feéricos, incluidos nosotros, los "
"elfos. Nadie sabe exactamente cuándo o cómo surgieron esos relatos, pero es "
"evidente que los elfos Quenoth los han olvidado, malinterpretado y exagerado "
"con el tiempo.\n"
"\n"
"Estas gentes prosperan y viven en paz a pesar de haber perdido gran parte "
"del conocimiento y las habilidades de nuestra civilización, pero fue su fe "
"lo que los llevó a desafiar el destino y construir un nuevo futuro — no solo "
"para su raza, sino para todas las criaturas vivientes bajo los soles. "
"Nuestra gratitud y respeto nunca serán suficientes para saldar esa deuda..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:174
msgid ""
"... which makes it all the more shameful that I couldn’t think of a better "
"justification for our presence than “Eloh’s guidance”. I never really gave "
"much credit to those ancient creation myths in the first place. And was it "
"really necessary to boast of my past deeds to earn our descendants’ trust? "
"Then again, somehow their head priestess did not seem to find a problem with "
"attributing Zhangor’s downfall to a messenger of the goddess instead of the "
"goddess herself...\n"
"\n"
"Again, I find myself reflecting upon the simple and idyllic lifestyle of our "
"kin on this island. Perhaps it’s for the best that they do not feel the need "
"to aim higher — those of us who lived to see Zhangor’s rule know well how "
"dire the consequences of ambition and revenge can be."
msgstr ""
"... lo que hace aún más lamentable que no pudiera encontrar una mejor "
"justificación para nuestra presencia que la «guía de Eloh». En realidad "
"nunca di mucho crédito a esos antiguos mitos de la creación. ¿Era realmente "
"necesario alardear de mis hazañas pasadas para ganarme la confianza de "
"nuestros descendientes? Por otro lado, de algún modo su sacerdotisa "
"principal no pareció tener problema en atribuir la caída de Zhangor a un "
"mensajero de la diosa en lugar de a la diosa misma...\n"
"\n"
"De nuevo, me encuentro reflexionando sobre el estilo de vida simple e "
"idílico de nuestros parientes en esta isla. Quizás sea mejor que no sientan "
"la necesidad de aspirar a más — quienes vivimos para ver el reinado de "
"Zhangor sabemos bien cuán terribles pueden ser las consecuencias de la "
"ambición y la venganza."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:180
msgid ""
"We were told Yechnagoth originally controlled a citadel in the heart of "
"Zocthanol, where her body resided. Although both the body and the citadel "
"were destroyed by Kalehssar’s people, we suspected that there was much more "
"to find deep under the earth.\n"
"\n"
"On the next day, we descended into the caves nearby to search for more "
"remains of the place. As I expected, we found some unusually clean walls "
"concealing an entrance to a larger underground complex forgotten by time. As "
"we proceeded further into the forbidden realm lying beneath what once was "
"Yechnagoth’s throne, it became evident that Argan, or whoever first settled "
"Zocthanol, had received some help to build it all."
msgstr ""
"Nos dijeron que Yechnagoth controlaba originalmente una ciudadela en el "
"corazón de Zocthanol, donde residía su cuerpo. Aunque tanto el cuerpo como "
"la ciudadela fueron destruidos por la gente de Kalehssar, sospechábamos que "
"había mucho más por descubrir bajo la tierra.\n"
"\n"
"Al día siguiente, descendimos a las cuevas cercanas en busca de más "
"vestigios del lugar. Como esperaba, encontramos paredes inusualmente limpias "
"que ocultaban la entrada a un complejo subterráneo mayor, olvidado por el "
"tiempo. A medida que avanzábamos en el reino prohibido bajo lo que alguna "
"vez fue el trono de Yechnagoth, se hizo evidente que Argan, o quien haya "
"sido el primer habitante de Zocthanol, había recibido ayuda para construirlo "
"todo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:191
msgid ""
"Argan’s mention of ‘Norsulan’ technology in his records worried me. What if "
"we are fighting for a doomed cause? Perhaps Uria’s influence has already "
"caused permanent, irreversible damage on other worlds besides Irdya, and "
"there’s nothing we can do to stop the enemy now?\n"
"\n"
"The information previously gathered by Galas, Anlindë and Mal Keshar seems "
"consistent with what we have just learned from Argan... which he most "
"certainly learned from Uria and her highest-ranking demon lords.\n"
"\n"
"We are not alone."
msgstr ""
"La mención de Argan sobre la tecnología ‘norsulana’ en sus registros me "
"preocupó. ¿Y si estamos luchando por una causa perdida? Quizás la influencia "
"de Uria ya ha causado daños permanentes e irreversibles en otros mundos "
"además de Irdya, y no hay nada que podamos hacer para detener al enemigo "
"ahora.\n"
"\n"
"La información recopilada previamente por Galas, Anlindë y Mal Keshar parece "
"coincidir con lo que acabamos de aprender de Argan... que seguramente obtuvo "
"de Uria y sus señores demoníacos de más alto rango.\n"
"\n"
"No estamos solos."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:198
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The sole thought that there is a world out there more technologically "
"advanced than our own is... overwhelming, to say the least. I wonder what "
"kind of people live there? Assuming they weren’t exterminated by the legions "
"of Inferno in the time that has passed since Argan encoded those records, "
"that is. Are these ‘Norsulans’ a noble people unveiling the mysteries of the "
"universe for the good of all, or wretched demons bent on destroying the "
"creations of nature with their machines like the ruler of Inferno herself? "
"If the former, might they be aware that their knowledge has been subverted "
"by this cruel demoness?\n"
"\n"
"Even though Uria’s forces no longer have a direct passageway between our "
"world and theirs, as long as there are summoners on this side and Uria’s "
"demon lords on the other, she will continue to hold our home in her grasp. "
"But perhaps there is a way to weaken the Chaos Empire further. If killing "
"the Chaos Emperor did not suffice, it might be because his direct "
"subordinates still exist: the Iron Triad."
msgstr ""
"La sola idea de que exista un mundo allá afuera más avanzado "
"tecnológicamente que el nuestro es... abrumadora, por decir lo menos. Me "
"pregunto qué clase de personas viven allí. Asumiendo que no hayan sido "
"exterminadas por las legiones del Infierno en el tiempo transcurrido desde "
"que Argan registró esos datos. ¿Son estos ‘norsulanos’ un pueblo noble que "
"desvela los misterios del universo para el bien de todos, o demonios ruines "
"empeñados en destruir las creaciones de la naturaleza con sus máquinas, como "
"la propia gobernante del Infierno? ¿Serán conscientes de que su conocimiento "
"ha sido subvertido por esta cruel demonisa?\n"
"\n"
"Aunque las fuerzas de Uria ya no tengan un paso directo entre nuestro mundo "
"y el suyo, mientras haya invocadores de este lado y señores demoníacos de "
"Uria del otro, ella continuará manteniendo nuestro hogar bajo su dominio. "
"Pero tal vez haya una forma de debilitar aún más al Imperio del Caos. Si "
"matar al Emperador del Caos no fue suficiente, podría ser porque sus "
"subordinados directos aún existen: la Tríada de Hierro."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:203
msgid ""
"But before we can even attempt to deal with them, we’ll need to deal with "
"another problem. According to Mal Keshar—by means of that accursed journal—"
"Argan abandoned Zocthanol Isle after Yechnagoth was vanquished, but not "
"before recovering the creature’s heart. Although her soul was effectively "
"destroyed along with her provisional body, her source of power—her heart—"
"wasn’t directly connected to it, and Argan apparently ordered his minions to "
"preserve it beneath the ruined plains of Wesmere. I presume that the "
"biomechanical creatures we found in the caves there might be guarding it.\n"
"\n"
"With that great source of power still intact and on Irdya, our time is "
"running out. We decided to return to the Great Continent as soon as we could "
"to contact our allies and warn them about the imminent danger lying in the "
"Shaxthal hive beneath Wesmere. We must not allow that power to be unleashed "
"on the world again. I can only hope it isn’t too late already."
msgstr ""
"Pero antes de siquiera intentar enfrentarlos, tendremos que resolver otro "
"problema. Según Mal Keshar — por medio de ese maldito diario — Argan "
"abandonó la isla Zocthanol tras la derrota de Yechnagoth, pero no sin antes "
"recuperar el corazón de la criatura. Aunque su alma fue efectivamente "
"destruida junto con su cuerpo provisional, su fuente de poder — su corazón — "
"no estaba directamente conectada a él, y Argan aparentemente ordenó a sus "
"esbirros preservarlo bajo las llanuras en ruinas de Wesmere. Presumo que las "
"criaturas biomecánicas que encontramos en las cuevas podrían estar "
"custodiándolo.\n"
"\n"
"Con esa gran fuente de poder aún intacta y en Irdya, nuestro tiempo se "
"acaba. Decidimos regresar al Gran Continente cuanto antes para contactar a "
"nuestros aliados y advertirles sobre el peligro inminente que yace en la "
"colmena Shaxthal bajo Wesmere. No debemos permitir que ese poder se desate "
"sobre el mundo nuevamente. Solo puedo esperar que no sea ya demasiado tarde."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:209
msgid ""
"I wish I had mastered the power of teleportation that I obtained from the "
"crystal so we wouldn’t have to waste so many days on the Great Ocean. "
"Unfortunately, my mind has been in perpetual unrest as of late, unable to "
"focus on any advanced spell-casting. Attempting to travel such a great "
"distance without having managed first to do as much as teleporting across a "
"room would be reckless."
msgstr ""
"Ojalá hubiera dominado el poder de la teleportación que obtuve del cristal "
"para no tener que desperdiciar tantos días en el Gran Océano. "
"Desafortunadamente, mi mente ha estado en perpetuo desasosiego últimamente, "
"incapaz de concentrarse en hechizos avanzados. Intentar viajar una distancia "
"tan grande sin antes haber logrado siquiera teletransportarme al otro lado "
"de una habitación sería una locura."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:218
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We finally bid farewell to the peaceful island.\n"
"\n"
"Once again, I was tempted by my heart to elude the call of duty and forget "
"completely about the happenings on the Great Continent. It was the first "
"time since I rejoined reality that I truly wanted to flee from it — the same "
"emotion which led Argan and me to abandon our guidance of the elves after "
"the War of Wesmere came to an end...\n"
"\n"
"We ended one armed conflict only to get involved in another, with each of us "
"on opposite sides."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente nos despedimos de la pacífica isla.\n"
"\n"
"Una vez más, mi corazón me tentó a eludir el llamado del deber y a olvidar "
"por completo lo ocurrido en el Gran Continente. Fue la primera vez desde que "
"regresé a la realidad que quise realmente huir de ella. Sin embargo, esa "
"emoción fue precisamente lo que llevó a Argan y a mí a abandonar nuestra "
"guía de los elfos tras el fin de la Guerra de Wesmere.\n"
"\n"
"Terminamos un conflicto armado solo para involucrarnos en otro, cada uno en "
"lados opuestos."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:225
msgid ""
"I wish I could go back to the old times and prevent that disaster that "
"ruined our beautiful world forever. Life was much simpler when the only "
"forces threatening the order of nature were common necromancers who could be "
"easily dispatched by anyone capable of wielding a weapon.\n"
"\n"
"At some point we thought we knew everything about our place in the universe. "
"Argan’s appearance was the first event to challenge that vain pretension. "
"Then Zhangor came. Now this. What other revelations does the future hold for "
"us? When will my mission to protect Irdya and the habitants of its forests "
"be over?”"
msgstr ""
"Ojalá pudiera volver a los viejos tiempos y evitar ese desastre que arruinó "
"nuestro hermoso mundo para siempre. La vida era mucho más simple cuando las "
"únicas fuerzas que amenazaban el orden de la naturaleza eran necromantes "
"comunes que cualquiera capaz de manejar un arma podía despachar fácilmente.\n"
"\n"
"En algún momento pensamos que lo sabíamos todo sobre nuestro lugar en el "
"universo. La aparición de Argan fue el primer acontecimiento que desafió esa "
"vana pretensión. Luego vino Zhangor. Y ahora esto. ¿Qué otras revelaciones "
"nos depara el futuro? ¿Cuándo terminará mi misión de proteger Irdya y a los "
"habitantes de sus bosques?”"

#. [part]
#. The lines consisting of a single em dash represent a long pause.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:231
msgid ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"“Not everything went according to our plans.\n"
"\n"
"A storm caught us by surprise and drove us off course. The ship barely "
"withstood long enough to take us ashore, just in time to be greeted by the "
"setting suns and a thick fog enveloping all. Stranded on an unknown land, we "
"found ourselves before a foreboding forest at dusk."
msgstr ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"“No todo salió según nuestros planes.\n"
"\n"
"Una tormenta nos sorprendió y nos desvió del rumbo. El barco apenas resistió "
"lo suficiente para llevarnos a la costa, justo a tiempo para ser recibidos "
"por los soles ponientes y una densa niebla que lo envolvía todo. Varados en "
"una tierra desconocida, nos encontramos frente a un bosque amenazante al "
"anochecer."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:249
msgid ""
"In midst of the battle, a dark mist enshrouded everything around me. I tried "
"casting a fire to help me see my surroundings, but somehow the flames did "
"not appear. It was then that a tremendous force pierced my head, a force too "
"strong to resist...\n"
"\n"
"Something was draining my life force, and there was nothing I could do to "
"stop it.\n"
"\n"
"Blinded by the pain, I attempted to strike out at whoever was standing "
"behind me, but my body did not move."
msgstr ""
"En medio de la batalla, una oscura niebla envolvió todo a mi alrededor. "
"Intenté lanzar un fuego para ayudarme a ver lo que me rodeaba, pero de algún "
"modo las llamas no aparecieron. Fue entonces cuando una fuerza tremenda "
"atravesó mi cabeza, una fuerza demasiado fuerte para resistir...\n"
"\n"
"Algo estaba drenando mi fuerza vital, y no había nada que pudiera hacer para "
"detenerlo.\n"
"\n"
"Cegado por el dolor, intenté atacar a quien estuviera detrás de mí, pero mi "
"cuerpo no se movió."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:256
msgid ""
"... A voice... I heard a crystalline and enchanting voice uttering words in "
"a language I did not know. Had I heard that voice before? For a moment I "
"felt as if I was falling into a bottomless abyss, plunging into the shadows "
"below...\n"
"\n"
"The darkness...\n"
"\n"
"The fear..."
msgstr ""
"... Una voz... Escuché una voz cristalina y encantadora pronunciando "
"palabras en un idioma que no conocía. ¿Había oído esa voz antes? Por un "
"momento sentí que caía en un abismo sin fondo, sumergiéndome en las sombras "
"abajo...\n"
"\n"
"La oscuridad...\n"
"\n"
"El temor..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:263
msgid ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"The strong pulling of Uria’s power had knocked me unconscious. I had been "
"defeated, caught off guard. I had... failed...\n"
"\n"
"When I finally opened my eyes, it was already too late."
msgstr ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"El fuerte tirón del poder de Uria me dejó inconsciente. Había sido "
"derrotado, sorprendido. Había... fracasado...\n"
"\n"
"Cuando finalmente abrí los ojos, ya era demasiado tarde."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:270
msgid ""
"My hands and feet were burning. I was chained to the floor of a pitch-black "
"cell, unable to escape, screaming and writhing in pain. They had finally "
"captured me, and subjected me to the customary torture employed on those of "
"my kind; because they knew I could pose no threat to them for as long as I "
"was bound by the cold iron.\n"
"\n"
"Such was the curse imposed at the beginning of time on faerie and elvenkind."
msgstr ""
"Mis manos y pies ardían. Estaba encadenado al suelo de una celda "
"completamente oscura, incapaz de escapar, gritando y retorciéndome de dolor. "
"Finalmente me habían capturado y me sometieron a la tortura acostumbrada a "
"los de mi clase; porque sabían que no podía representar una amenaza mientras "
"estuviera atado por el frío hierro.\n"
"\n"
"Tal era la maldición impuesta desde el comienzo de los tiempos sobre los "
"seres feéricos y elfos."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:275
msgid ""
"My staff was nowhere to be seen, and the pain would not let me pronounce a "
"single spell. Since I lacked the means to break free, all I could do was to "
"wait.\n"
"\n"
"The pain.\n"
"\n"
"I know not how much time passed in reality, for the excruciating pain kept "
"me only barely conscious until they arrived to drag me out of the dungeon. "
"Was it hours? Days, perhaps? Does it even matter?"
msgstr ""
"Mi bastón no estaba a la vista, y el dolor no me permitía pronunciar ni un "
"solo hechizo. Al no tener medios para liberarme, lo único que podía hacer "
"era esperar.\n"
"\n"
"El dolor.\n"
"\n"
"No sé cuánto tiempo pasó en realidad, pues el dolor insoportable me mantuvo "
"apenas consciente hasta que llegaron a arrastrarme fuera de la mazmorra. "
"¿Fueron horas? ¿Días, tal vez? ¿Importa siquiera?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:282
msgid "The Triad"
msgstr "La Tríada"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:283
msgid "Finally, I was taken to meet my captors, face to face."
msgstr "Finalmente, me llevaron a encontrarme con mis captores, cara a cara."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:291
msgid ""
"It is really hard to acknowledge your own mistakes, at times. It’s "
"especially hard to face reality once it turns against you by taking away "
"those whom you love the most.\n"
"\n"
"Galas was more than just a friend."
msgstr ""
"A veces es realmente difícil reconocer tus propios errores. Y es "
"especialmente duro enfrentarse a la realidad cuando esta se vuelve en tu "
"contra arrebatándote a quienes más amas.\n"
"\n"
"Galas fue más que un simple amigo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:296
msgid ""
"I could never tell him how I really felt. I could never tell him why I "
"<i>cared</i> so much.\n"
"\n"
"After Argan’s death, I swore I would not get emotionally involved with "
"anyone again. There is no point in trying if this is the inevitable end met "
"by all those around me. It has happened before, and yet... this feeling of "
"emptiness... it is as overwhelming as ever."
msgstr ""
"Nunca pude decirle cómo me sentía en realidad. Nunca pude decirle por qué me "
"<i>importaba</i> tanto.\n"
"\n"
"Tras la muerte de Argan, juré no volver a involucrarme emocionalmente con "
"nadie. No tiene sentido intentarlo si este es el final inevitable que les "
"espera a todos los que me rodean. Ha sucedido antes y, aun así... este "
"sentimiento de vacío... sigue siendo tan abrumador como siempre."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:301
msgid ""
"It’s evident that my heart had already gotten too close to him. Lord Galas "
"of the Forest Elves of the Valley of Elynia, he who renounced to his "
"rightful place amongst his people to die fighting for a hopeless cause! "
"Would that his death had been as heroic as the short life he lived. Would "
"that we could have at least retrieved his body, instead of it being left to "
"rot in that horrid lake of blood.\n"
"\n"
"Now I am on my own again, much like I was for much of my life, even after "
"Argan first found me, even after he secretly married me; for neither in "
"Wesnoth nor the domains of the elves was it considered acceptable to get "
"involved in any way with men like him. If I had given them a chance to "
"discover our secrets, we both would have been punished... with death."
msgstr ""
"Es evidente que mi corazón ya se había acercado demasiado a él. Lord Galas, "
"de los elfos del bosque del Valle de Elynia, aquel que renunció a su lugar "
"legítimo entre su pueblo para morir luchando por una causa sin esperanza. "
"¡Ojalá su muerte hubiera sido tan heroica como la corta vida que llevó! "
"Ojalá al menos hubiéramos podido recuperar su cuerpo, en vez de dejarlo "
"pudrirse en aquel horrendo lago de sangre.\n"
"\n"
"Ahora estoy sola otra vez, como lo estuve durante buena parte de mi vida, "
"incluso después de que Argan me encontrara, incluso después de que se casara "
"conmigo en secreto; pues ni en Wesnoth ni en los dominios de los elfos se "
"consideraba aceptable relacionarse de ninguna manera con hombres como él. Si "
"les hubiera dado la oportunidad de descubrir nuestros secretos, a ambos nos "
"habrían castigado... con la muerte."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:306
msgid ""
"I don’t want to risk approaching Mal Keshar. I know he had long since "
"accepted Galas as his only friend. How am I supposed to face him when we "
"both know this is all my fault? Because it was my reluctance that ultimately "
"led to the young elf’s demise at the hands of the demoness.\n"
"\n"
"I don’t know what to do anymore..."
msgstr ""
"No quiero arriesgarme a acercarme a Mal Keshar. Sé que hace mucho tiempo "
"aceptó a Galas como su único amigo. ¿Cómo se supone que voy a enfrentarlo "
"cuando ambos sabemos que todo esto es mi culpa? Porque fue mi reticencia la "
"que finalmente llevó a la caída del joven elfo a manos de la demoníaca.\n"
"\n"
"Ya no sé qué hacer..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:312
msgid ""
"But I do know that Galas would not have given up, no matter how great the "
"loss. Not even Anlindë’s sacrifice was enough to break his conviction that "
"our fate could be changed.\n"
"\n"
"I have to carry on and put a stop to the plans of Elyssa and the Iron "
"Council, somehow. I have to — even if it might require a sacrifice of my own."
msgstr ""
"Pero sí sé que Galas no se habría rendido, sin importar cuán grande fuera la "
"pérdida. Ni siquiera el sacrificio de Anlindë fue suficiente para quebrar su "
"convicción de que nuestro destino podía cambiarse.\n"
"\n"
"Debo seguir adelante y poner fin a los planes de Elyssa y del Consejo de "
"Hierro, de alguna manera. Debo hacerlo... incluso si eso requiere un "
"sacrificio propio."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:323
msgid ""
"As I was his second-in-command, I know that I am expected to replace Galas "
"at the helm of our group, but doing so is a constant and painful reminder of "
"the circumstances of his death. I have to try to put those thoughts aside "
"for now — there will be plenty of time for grieving later.\n"
"\n"
"We continued our march towards northeastern Wesmere. Along the way, I could "
"spot a few familiar landmarks, ruined as they were, eroded by the elements; "
"reminders of the past glory of the peoples of Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Como era su segunda al mando, sé que se espera que reemplace a Galas al "
"frente de nuestro grupo, pero hacerlo es un recordatorio constante y "
"doloroso de las circunstancias de su muerte. Tengo que intentar apartar esos "
"pensamientos por ahora; ya habrá tiempo de sobra para el duelo más "
"adelante.\n"
"\n"
"Continuamos nuestra marcha hacia el noreste de Wesmere. En el camino, pude "
"ver algunos lugares familiares, arruinados como estaban, erosionados por los "
"elementos; recordatorios de la antigua gloria de los pueblos de Irdya."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:328
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Even though I was actually born in Lintanir, I spent all but the first two "
"years of my childhood in Wesmere. Later, even if my duty required me to "
"travel large distances across the continent, I continued to feel at home in "
"Wesmere... for some time.\n"
"\n"
"In the late years of the Golden Age, Wesmere lost their trust in the Empire "
"of Wesnoth; the humans’ unilateral decision to create a second sun was the "
"trigger. The Ka’lian held me responsible for not finding out sooner and "
"stopping Wesnoth’s arrogance before the damage was done. My subsequent "
"resignation from my position as advisor to the human Emperor only further "
"deepened their spite towards me; no longer a useful asset for meddling with "
"foreign affairs, I became little more than a bothersome obstacle for the "
"younger leadership.\n"
"\n"
"Eventually, I simply decided to cut my ties with Wesmere and wander the "
"earth with Argan by my side."
msgstr ""
"Aunque en realidad nací en Lintanir, pasé toda mi infancia, salvo los dos "
"primeros años, en Wesmere. Más tarde, aunque mi deber requería que viajara "
"grandes distancias por el continente, seguía sintiéndome en casa en "
"Wesmere... por un tiempo.\n"
"\n"
"Al comenzar el fin de la Edad Dorada, la confianza de Wesmere en el Imperio "
"de Wesnoth se había roto; la decisión unilateral de los humanos de crear un "
"segundo sol fue el detonante. Una vez que el Ka’lian supo de mi renuncia "
"como consejera del Emperador de Wesnoth, consideraron que ya no era útil "
"para sus fines y se aseguraron de dificultarme la vida en cada oportunidad. "
"En cierto momento, simplemente decidí dejar Wesmere y vagar por la tierra "
"con Argan a mi lado."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:335
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Of course, that was before the dreams of all civilizations were shattered to "
"pieces. After the Fall, we had no choice but to settle in Lintanir, where we "
"would remain blissfully ignorant of the atrocities taking place in Wesmere. "
"But in time, Lintanir too crumbled down like most other forests did, which "
"led to us seeking refuge in Wesmere and discovering the dreadful truth. It "
"goes without saying that my most recent memories of the place are beyond "
"unpleasant."
msgstr ""
"Por supuesto, eso fue antes de que los sueños de numerosas civilizaciones se "
"hicieran añicos. Tras la Caída, no tuvimos más remedio que asentarnos en "
"Lintanir, donde permanecimos felizmente ignorantes de las atrocidades que "
"tenían lugar en Wesmere. Pero con el tiempo, como muchos otros bosques, "
"Lintanir se desmoronó y nos vimos obligados a volver a Wesmere y descubrir "
"la espantosa verdad.\n"
"\n"
"Está de más decir que mis recuerdos más recientes de ese lugar son "
"particularmente desagradables."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:339
msgid ""
"Back to present times.\n"
"\n"
"The melancholic desert landscape was dominated by an ominous stronghold in "
"the north, guarding the entrance to the infested plains.\n"
"\n"
"As our living troops were exhausted from the lengthy journey across the "
"desert, we decided to stop and rest in the ruins of an ancient elvish "
"outpost for a while, unsuspecting of our forthcoming final confrontation "
"with the forces of Uria."
msgstr ""
"De vuelta al presente.\n"
"\n"
"El melancólico paisaje desértico estaba dominado por una ominosa fortaleza "
"al norte, que custodiaba la entrada a las llanuras infestadas.\n"
"\n"
"Como nuestras tropas vivas estaban exhaustas por el largo viaje a través del "
"desierto, decidimos detenernos y descansar un rato en las ruinas de un "
"antiguo puesto avanzado élfico, sin sospechar la inminente confrontación "
"final con las fuerzas de Uria."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:352
msgid ""
"No matter how many times I set foot in this ravaged land, the sight remains "
"as appalling as ever.\n"
"\n"
"Wesmere is cursed — no green life will ever thrive in it again, as long as "
"the forces of Inferno thirst for revenge upon us."
msgstr ""
"No importa cuántas veces pise esta tierra devastada, la visión sigue siendo "
"tan espantosa como siempre.\n"
"\n"
"Wesmere está maldito; ninguna vida verde volverá a prosperar aquí mientras "
"las fuerzas del Infierno sigan sedientas de venganza contra nosotros."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:358
msgid ""
"Now that we head back into these caves, I can’t help but ponder Mal Keshar’s "
"words... Am I in denial of my own thirst for revenge now? Perhaps my quest "
"isn’t as noble as I want to believe it is.\n"
"\n"
"“We aren’t that different after all.”"
msgstr ""
"Ahora que nos adentramos nuevamente en estas cuevas, no puedo evitar "
"reflexionar sobre las palabras de Mal Keshar... ¿Estoy negando mi propia sed "
"de venganza ahora? Quizás mi misión no sea tan noble como quiero creer.\n"
"\n"
"“No somos tan diferentes después de todo.”"

#. [character_profile]: id=Durvan, race=human, gender=male
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/characters.cfg:32
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/characters.cfg:18
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:6
