msgid "team_name^Dark Hive"
msgstr "Colmena Oscura"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:265
msgid "Proceed further underground with Elynia"
msgstr "Avanzar más bajo tierra con Elynia"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:279
msgid "What is this place?"
msgstr "¿Qué es este lugar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:284
msgid ""
"According to Unarye, the valley was only slightly habitable at first; the "
"elves had to seek refuge in the caverns during the day, while they worked to "
"adapt the surface land to their needs at night. It appears that the Chaos "
"Empire saw fit to turn the place into a Shaxthal hive."
msgstr ""
"Según Unarye, el valle solo era ligeramente habitable al principio; los "
"elfos tenían que refugiarse en las cavernas durante el día, mientras "
"trabajaban por la noche para adaptar la tierra de la superficie a sus "
"necesidades. Parece que el Imperio del Caos consideró adecuado convertir el "
"lugar en una colmena Shaxthal."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:289
msgid ""
"Although Shaxthal creatures are particularly weak against our fire, it’s "
"essential that we remain together as we proceed further underground."
msgstr ""
"Aunque las criaturas Shaxthal son particularmente débiles contra nuestro "
"fuego, es esencial que permanezcamos juntos mientras avanzamos más bajo "
"tierra."

#. [unit]: type=Chaos Magus, id=Kaceldyn
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:409
msgid "Kaceldyn"
msgstr "Kaceldyn"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:482
msgid "What was that?"
msgstr "¿Qué fue eso?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:487
msgid ""
"I am not sure, but I fear we have wasted too much time in these caves. "
"Whatever happens next is surely our fault."
msgstr ""
"No estoy seguro, pero temo que hemos perdido demasiado tiempo en estas "
"cavernas. Sea lo que sea que pase a continuación, seguramente es culpa "
"nuestra."

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:239
msgid "The Betrayal"
msgstr "La Traición"

#. [side]: type=Hell Guardian, id=Stalygvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:98
msgid "Stalygvan"
msgstr "Stalygvan"

#. [side]: type=Gutwrencher Imp, id=Dorghazaquiel
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:123
msgid "Dorghazaquiel"
msgstr "Dorghazaquiel"

#. [side]: type=Demon Warrior, gender=female, id=Elathea
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:153
msgid "Elathea"
msgstr "Elathea"

#. [side]: type=Chaos Razerman, id=Alareanthalcan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:183
msgid "Alareanthalcan"
msgstr "Alareanthalcan"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:393
msgid "Defeat the false Lady of Light"
msgstr "Derrota a la falsa Dama de la Luz"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:444
msgid "Another gate..."
msgstr "Otra puerta..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:518
msgid "Look! It’s the impostor again!"
msgstr "¡Mira! ¡Es la impostora otra vez!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lady of Light
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:535
msgid "I have to destroy her... yes, I have to... I must not fail this time..."
msgstr ""
"Tengo que destruirla... sí, debo hacerlo... No puedo fallar esta vez..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:544
msgid "So here you are, traitor."
msgstr "Así que aquí estás, traidora."

#. [message]: speaker=Lady of Light
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:559
msgid "I AM NOT A TRAITOR! I’LL DESTROY YOU THIS TIME!"
msgstr "¡NO SOY UNA TRAIDORA! ¡TE DESTRUIRÉ ESTA VEZ!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:564
msgid ""
"I have had enough of this — surround her and strike her down! Do not let her "
"get away!"
msgstr "Ya basta de esto — ¡rodéenla y derríbenla! ¡No la dejen escapar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lady of Light
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:600
msgid "No... Let me go!"
msgstr "No... ¡Déjame ir!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:623
msgid ""
"You and your accursed allies have been conspiring against us and the Grand "
"Council of the Northern Peoples, sowing strife and destruction. Whoever you "
"are, your heinous deeds make you unworthy of my mercy. You no longer deserve "
"a place amongst elvenkind."
msgstr ""
"Tú y tus malditos aliados han estado conspirando contra nosotros y el Gran "
"Consejo de los Pueblos del Norte, sembrando discordia y destrucción. "
"Quienquiera que seas, tus atroces actos te hacen indigno de mi misericordia. "
"Ya no mereces un lugar entre los elfos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lady of Light
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:628
msgid "... Elynia... please..."
msgstr "... Elynia... por favor..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:633
msgid "Leave this world <b>now</b>, and never return again!"
msgstr "¡Deja este mundo <b>ahora</b> y no regreses jamás!"

#. [modify_unit]: id=Ivyel
#. [unit]: type=Shaxthal Infiltrator, id=Ivyel
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:663
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2373
msgid "Ivyel"
msgstr "Ivyel"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:685
msgid "(<i>confused</i>) What is this?"
msgstr "(<i>confundida</i>) ¿Qué es esto?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ivyel
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:694
msgid "... Please... don’t... attack me..."
msgstr "... Por favor... no... me ataques..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:699
msgid "But... how... how is this possible?"
msgstr "Pero... ¿cómo... cómo es esto posible?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:717
msgid "This doesn’t make sense!"
msgstr "¡Esto no tiene sentido!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:727
msgid "(<i>cackling</i>)"
msgstr "(<i>riendo siniestramente</i>)"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:732
msgid "Who is that?!"
msgstr "¿Quién es ese?!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:742
msgid ""
"(<i>more cackling</i>) <i>What do you think of our first complete "
"infiltrator? It took us great effort to design and build such perfection.</i>"
msgstr ""
"(<i>más risas siniestras</i>) <i>¿Qué opinas de nuestro primer infiltrador "
"completo? Nos costó mucho esfuerzo diseñar y construir tal perfección.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:751
msgid ""
"(<i>angry</i>) I know you... You are one of the members of the Iron Council, "
"Mal Hekuba!"
msgstr ""
"(<i>enojada</i>) Te conozco... ¡Eres uno de los miembros del Consejo de "
"Hierro, Mal Hekuba!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:783
msgid "Did you miss me, Elynia?"
msgstr "¿Me extrañaste, Elynia?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:798
msgid ""
"... I couldn’t possibly wish harder for you and your friends’ destruction."
msgstr "... No podría desear más la destrucción tuya y de tus amigos."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:803
msgid "Ha, ha, but that’s not going to happen in your lifetime, or is it?"
msgstr "Ja, ja, pero eso no sucederá en tu vida, ¿o sí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:871
msgid "Where are you? Stop fooling around and show yourself, you—"
msgstr "¿Dónde estás? Deja de jugar y muéstrate, tú—"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:878
msgid ""
"I understand that you must be confused and enraged after losing your friends "
"to such a pointless cause, and traveling so far only to slaughter the same "
"people whom you once vowed to protect!"
msgstr ""
"Entiendo que debas estar confundida y enfurecida después de perder a tus "
"amigos por una causa tan absurda, y viajar tan lejos solo para masacrar a "
"las mismas personas que una vez juraste proteger."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:893
msgid "It appears to be just an illusion..."
msgstr "Parece ser solo una ilusión..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:898
msgid "Destroying you is NOT a pointless cause!"
msgstr "¡Destruirte NO es una causa inútil!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:904
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1419
#: After_the_Storm/macros/character-defines.cfg:79
msgid "Mal Hekuba"
msgstr "Mal Hekuba"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:910
msgid ""
"But of course it is! You cannot destroy us! Not without the power of the "
"Union, anyway, which you left behind in Uria’s sacred domain when you "
"destroyed your beloved Argan."
msgstr ""
"¡Pero claro que sí! ¡No podéis destruirnos! Al menos no sin el poder de la "
"Unión, que dejaste atrás en el dominio sagrado de Uria cuando destruiste a "
"tu amado Argan."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:914
msgid "I still have the Ruby of Fire!"
msgstr "¡Aún tengo el Rubí de Fuego!"

#. [event]
#. "Argan’s treacherous little girl" refers to Elyssa.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:918
msgid ""
"That understandably attractive relic is not important for <b>me</b>. Argan’s "
"treacherous little girl likes to think of it as if it were unique and "
"irreplaceable, and convinced Uria of that — but in truth, it is not."
msgstr ""
"Esa reliquia, comprensiblemente atractiva, no es importante para <b>mí</b>. "
"La pequeña traicionera de Argan gusta pensar que es única e insustituible, y "
"convenció a Uria de eso — pero en realidad no es así."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:926
msgid "What are you babbling about?"
msgstr "¿De qué estás balbuceando?"

#. [event]
#. "Her finding out" refers to Elyssa.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:930
msgid ""
"The first set of replicas of Yechnagoth’s heart were lost when you and your "
"pathetic lackey destroyed our base in Wesmere, but I have had plenty of time "
"to create more here without her finding out. I am sure that together, they "
"are as good or better than the original, and they might even be a superior "
"substitute for your precious gem."
msgstr ""
"El primer conjunto de réplicas del corazón de Yechnagoth se perdió cuando tú "
"y tu patético lacayo destruyeron nuestra base en Wesmere, pero he tenido "
"tiempo suficiente para crear más aquí sin que ella lo descubriera. Estoy "
"seguro que juntos son tan buenos o mejores que el original, y quizás incluso "
"un sustituto superior para tu preciosa gema."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:938
msgid "Are you working against Uria’s will, then?"
msgstr "¿Entonces estás obrando en contra de la voluntad de Uria?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:956
msgid ""
"(<i>losing his temper</i>) We cannot speak to her directly! We can only do "
"so through that treacherous wench, who keeps the Dark Lady’s heart within "
"her for her own purposes!"
msgstr ""
"(<i>perdiendo la paciencia</i>) ¡No podemos hablar con ella directamente! "
"Solo podemos hacerlo a través de esa traicionera bruja, que guarda el "
"corazón de la Dama Oscura dentro de ella para sus propios fines."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:967
msgid ""
"... We... We destroyed Wesmere... Yechnagoth’s heart wasn’t there?! What did "
"we destroy when we..."
msgstr ""
"... Nosotros... destruimos Wesmere... ¿El corazón de Yechnagoth no estaba "
"allí?! ¿Qué fue lo que destruimos cuando nosotros..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:970
msgid ""
"The energy that should have destroyed you was released from the <b>second</"
"b> replica of her heart, and various experimental units stored in the same "
"place. The third one still exists within our infiltrator, imbuing her with "
"Yechnagoth’s grace and might — which is why your power is no match for hers."
msgstr ""
"La energía que debería haberte destruido fue liberada desde la <b>segunda</"
"b> réplica de su corazón, junto con varias unidades experimentales "
"almacenadas en el mismo lugar. La tercera aún existe dentro de nuestra "
"infiltrada, imbuyéndola con la gracia y poder de Yechnagoth — por eso tu "
"poder no es rival para el de ella."

#. [event]
#. "Argan’s pet" is Elyssa.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:973
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, I do not have time to continue talking to you. Right now, I "
"need to go to tend to some... rituals. Ivyel was created to destroy both you "
"and Argan’s pet. Take a good glance at her perfection once she returns, for "
"it will be your last opportunity."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, no tengo tiempo para seguir hablando contigo. Ahora mismo, debo "
"atender algunos... rituales. Ivyel fue creada para destruirte a ti y a la "
"mascota de Argan. Observa bien su perfección cuando regrese, pues será tu "
"última oportunidad."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:978
msgid "(<i>more cackling</i>)"
msgstr "(<i>más risas siniestras</i>)"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:996
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1393
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/01_Beyond_her_Smile.cfg:1520
msgid "What are we going to do now?"
msgstr "¿Qué vamos a hacer ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1001
msgid "Those bastards can’t get away with this! My lady, we must do something!"
msgstr "¡Esos bastardos no saldrán impunes! Mi señora, debemos hacer algo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1010
msgid ""
"I don’t think we have the power necessary to destroy the artifacts that Mal "
"Hekuba is going to use to..."
msgstr ""
"No creo que tengamos el poder necesario para destruir los artefactos que Mal "
"Hekuba va a usar para..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1015
msgid ""
"Of course we do! We didn’t come all the way from the northern lands risking "
"that blasted Ruby for nothing! Whatever that lich is going to do, it will "
"destroy us all if we don’t stop him now!"
msgstr ""
"¡Por supuesto que sí! ¡No vinimos desde las tierras del norte arriesgando "
"ese maldito Rubí para nada! Lo que sea que ese lich vaya a hacer, nos "
"destruirá a todos si no lo detenemos ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1020
msgid ""
"The last time we fought against that power, I lost a friend, and the vast "
"plains of Wesmere vanished with his remains..."
msgstr ""
"La última vez que luchamos contra ese poder, perdí a un amigo, y las vastas "
"llanuras de Wesmere desaparecieron con sus restos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1025
msgid ""
"Any course of action at this point will inevitably lead to someone’s "
"destruction, but I’m sure we can do it this time! If the lich is going to "
"create a... path to Inferno, as Elorran said, perhaps we can cause it to "
"collapse at the other side!"
msgstr ""
"Cualquier acción en este punto inevitablemente llevará a la destrucción de "
"alguien, ¡pero estoy segura de que esta vez podemos lograrlo! Si el lich va "
"a crear un... camino hacia el Infierno, como dijo Elorran, tal vez podamos "
"hacer que colapse al otro lado."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1030
msgid ""
"I don’t truly understand most of this nonsense about hearts and Yechnagoth, "
"but I reckon we need to destroy the lich and the impostor — and we can’t do "
"that without your help, Elynia."
msgstr ""
"No entiendo bien la mayoría de estas tonterías sobre corazones y Yechnagoth, "
"pero creo que debemos destruir al lich y al impostor — y no podemos hacerlo "
"sin tu ayuda, Elynia."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1035
msgid ""
"We don’t have much time! That thing we just fought could be back at any "
"moment!"
msgstr ""
"¡No tenemos mucho tiempo! ¡Esa cosa con la que acabamos de luchar podría "
"regresar en cualquier momento!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1044
msgid ""
"I appreciate your support... I don’t think I could have come this far alone. "
"And I don’t want to force you to follow me..."
msgstr ""
"Agradezco vuestro apoyo... No creo que hubiera llegado tan lejos sola. Y no "
"quiero obligaros a que me sigáis..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1049
msgid "Of course not! We are your friends!"
msgstr "¡Por supuesto que no! ¡Somos tus amigos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1054
msgid "Let’s find that foul fiend and destroy him once and for all."
msgstr "Vamos a encontrar a ese vil enemigo y destruirlo de una vez por todas."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1059
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1441
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:423
msgid "Proceed further underground with Elynia to find Mal Hekuba"
msgstr "Avanza más profundo bajo tierra con Elynia para encontrar a Mal Hekuba"

#. [message]: speaker=Alareanthalcan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1216
msgid "They are getting closer to the control chamber! Get them, quickly!"
msgstr "¡Se están acercando a la cámara de control! ¡Detenedlos, rápido!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1221
msgid "I don’t like the sound of that..."
msgstr "No me gusta cómo suena eso..."

#. [message]: speaker=Stalygvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1275
msgid "You! You can’t stop our master! You can’t—"
msgstr "¡Tú! ¡No puedes detener a nuestro maestro! ¡No puedes—"

#. [event]: id=Kardas
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1292
msgid "Kardas"
msgstr "Kardas"

#. [message]: speaker=Kardas
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1306
msgid "My lady! At last, I found you! I know where the lich is!"
msgstr "¡Mi señora! ¡Por fin te encontré! ¡Sé dónde está el lich!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1311
msgid "Speak."
msgstr "Habla."

#. [message]: speaker=Kardas
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1335
msgid ""
"The catacombs below guard an artifact of some sort. Nobody knows exactly "
"what it is, but we know the entrance is protected by a gate controlled by "
"three crystals found near this guard post."
msgstr ""
"Las catacumbas debajo guardan algún tipo de artefacto. Nadie sabe "
"exactamente qué es, pero sabemos que la entrada está protegida por una "
"puerta controlada por tres cristales encontrados cerca de este puesto de "
"guardia."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1346
msgid "Let’s find those crystals, then."
msgstr "Entonces, busquemos esos cristales."

#. [event]: id=Kardas
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1355
msgid ""
"Locate and activate the three control crystals to open the central gates"
msgstr ""
"Localiza y activa los tres cristales de control para abrir las puertas "
"centrales"

#. [message]: speaker=Elathea
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1373
msgid "May Uria punish you all for this—"
msgstr "Que Uria os castigue a todos por esto—"

#. [message]: speaker=Dorghazaquiel
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1385
msgid "Nooooaaagh... it hurts!!!"
msgstr "Nooooaaagh... ¡duele!!!"

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1402
msgid "The beast’s body is dissolving into slime!"
msgstr "¡El cuerpo de la bestia se está disolviendo en baba!"

#. [message]: speaker=Alareanthalcan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1459
msgid "Even though I have fallen, you are no match for my master’s power!"
msgstr "¡Aunque haya caído, no sois rival para el poder de mi maestro!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1464
msgid "We’ll see about that very soon."
msgstr "Ya veremos eso muy pronto."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1490
msgid "What in blazes is that creature?!"
msgstr "¡¿Qué demonios es esa criatura?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1495
msgid "Don’t meet its gaze! It will drain your life force!"
msgstr "¡No la mires fijamente! ¡Te drenará la fuerza vital!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1520
msgid ""
"The whirlpool is overflowing with an unusual energy.\n"
"\n"
"A dark energy."
msgstr ""
"El remolino está rebosando con una energía inusual.\n"
"\n"
"Una energía oscura."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1539
msgid "Hm, what is this? There seems to be something at the bottom..."
msgstr "Hm, ¿qué es esto? Parece que hay algo en el fondo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1544
msgid ""
"I wouldn’t get too close if I were you. It could be another one of those "
"biomechanical abominations."
msgstr ""
"Yo no me acercaría demasiado si fuera tú. Podría ser otra de esas "
"abominaciones biomecánicas."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1549
msgid ""
"I mean, it doesn’t look like there are any creatures in the water anyway. "
"(<i>touches the water</i>)"
msgstr ""
"Quiero decir, no parece que haya criaturas en el agua de todos modos. "
"(<i>toca el agua</i>)"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1558
msgid "Anya, what are you doing?"
msgstr "Anya, ¿qué estás haciendo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1563
msgid "Er, ummm... nothing! I just— <b>AAAAAAAAAAAHHHH!!!</b>"
msgstr "Eh, ummm... nada! Solo— <b>¡¡¡¡AAAAAAAHHH!!!</b>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1584
msgid "Elynia and Durvan"
msgstr "Elynia y Durvan"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1586
msgid "ANYA!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡ANYA!!!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1605
msgid "No... please don’t do this to me—"
msgstr "No... por favor, no me hagas esto—"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1611
msgid "I am all right!"
msgstr "¡Estoy bien!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1617
msgid "... Anya? Where are you???"
msgstr "... ¿Anya? ¿Dónde estás???"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1639
msgid ""
"I don’t really know? The current dragged me into a small chamber that seems "
"to be right below where you are. I think I may be able to get back to you? "
"Good thing I can swim."
msgstr ""
"¿Realmente no lo sé? La corriente me arrastró a una pequeña cámara que "
"parece estar justo debajo de donde están ustedes. Creo que puedo volver con "
"ustedes. Menos mal que sé nadar."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1649
msgid ""
"Yes, you can swim... but I cannot. You should return to us before anything "
"happens to you down there."
msgstr ""
"Sí, tú puedes nadar... pero yo no. Deberías regresar con nosotros antes de "
"que algo te pase ahí abajo."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1659
msgid ""
"Nah, it will be fine. Don’t worry about me. I am just going to do a little "
"exploring down here and come back."
msgstr ""
"Nah, estaré bien. No se preocupen por mí. Solo voy a explorar un poco aquí "
"abajo y regreso."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1666
msgid ""
"Anya can return to the main area by going back through the whirlpool, in a "
"similar fashion to how units can teleport between villages they already "
"control."
msgstr ""
"Anya puede volver al área principal regresando por el remolino, de forma "
"similar a como las unidades pueden teletransportarse entre aldeas que ya "
"controlan."

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1697
msgid "Mermaid’s Pendant"
msgstr "Colgante de Sirena"

#. [transient_message]
#. The sudden shift to second person narration is quite
#. intentional. You will see more of this throughout Episode 3.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1701
msgid ""
"This beautiful pendant made from an iridescent conch shines all the colors "
"of the rainbow under the light cast on the altar. The spectacle is "
"absolutely mesmerizing, but you figure you need to find out what uses this "
"marvelous item has.\n"
"\n"
"Unfortunately, there is absolutely nothing engraved on it or the altar that "
"could possibly be of help to you. How disappointing, you think. Maybe this "
"little adventure was an absolute waste of time. But something in your mind "
"tells you that perhaps you are supposed to wait for the right person and the "
"right opportunity to make use of the artifact. When is that going to be, you "
"wonder? The answer eludes you.\n"
"\n"
"You should probably go back to Elynia for the time being."
msgstr ""
"Este hermoso colgante hecho de una concha iridiscente brilla con todos los "
"colores del arcoíris bajo la luz que ilumina el altar. El espectáculo es "
"absolutamente hipnotizante, pero consideras que necesitas descubrir para qué "
"sirve este maravilloso objeto.\n"
"\n"
"Por desgracia, no hay absolutamente nada grabado en él ni en el altar que "
"pueda ayudarte. Qué decepción, piensas. Tal vez esta pequeña aventura fue "
"una completa pérdida de tiempo. Pero algo en tu mente te dice que quizá "
"debas esperar a la persona adecuada y el momento adecuado para usar el "
"artefacto. ¿Cuándo será eso?, te preguntas. La respuesta se te escapa.\n"
"\n"
"Probablemente deberías volver con Elynia por el momento."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1731
msgid "So, how was your little adventure?"
msgstr "Entonces, ¿cómo fue tu pequeña aventura?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1736
msgid "Well, I found this on an altar! It’s so shiny!"
msgstr "¡Bueno, encontré esto en un altar! ¡Es tan brillante!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1741
msgid ""
"... A seashell pendant? How did it find its way here, so far from the ocean?"
msgstr ""
"... ¿Un colgante de concha marina? ¿Cómo llegó hasta aquí, tan lejos del "
"océano?"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1746
msgid ""
"It could be some kind of keepsake the elves brought here when they first "
"arrived?"
msgstr ""
"¿Podría ser algún tipo de recuerdo que los elfos trajeron aquí cuando "
"llegaron por primera vez?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1751
msgid "That is the most likely answer, yes."
msgstr "Esa es la respuesta más probable, sí."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1756
msgid ""
"Do you think it has magical properties? Maybe I can summon water creatures! "
"Or water... projectiles of some kind? Perhaps I can shoot bubbles!"
msgstr ""
"¿Crees que tiene propiedades mágicas? ¡Quizá pueda invocar criaturas de "
"agua! ¿O proyectiles de agua de algún tipo? ¡Quizás pueda disparar burbujas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1765
msgid "No... I am afraid there is no magic in this pendant at all."
msgstr "No... me temo que este colgante no tiene ninguna magia."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1770
msgid "Wh... what."
msgstr "¿Qu... qué?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1779
msgid ""
"Did I actually just risk my life fighting that... giant... spider... to "
"obtain a completely mundane pendant?"
msgstr ""
"¿Realmente arriesgué mi vida luchando contra esa... araña... gigante... para "
"obtener un colgante completamente mundano?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1784
msgid "So it would seem."
msgstr "Eso parece."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1793
msgid ""
"... Oh well... At least it’s pretty! I’m going to keep it if you don’t mind."
msgstr "... Bueno... Al menos es bonito. Me lo voy a quedar si no te importa."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1798
msgid ""
"Sure. Just... don’t do that again, please? You had us really worried for a "
"moment there."
msgstr ""
"Claro. Solo... no vuelvas a hacer eso, ¿sí? Nos tuviste realmente "
"preocupados por un momento."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1803
msgid "I know, I’m sorry..."
msgstr "Lo sé, lo siento..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1828
msgid "It is probably too late to stop that lich by now..."
msgstr "Probablemente ya sea demasiado tarde para detener a ese lich..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/10_The_Betrayal.cfg:1839
msgid "Make haste!"
msgstr "¡Daos prisa!"

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:248
msgid "A Final Confrontation"
msgstr "Una confrontación final"

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:47
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:100
msgid "team_name^Mal Hekuba"
msgstr "Mal Hekuba"

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:117
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:182
msgid "team_name^Chamber Guards"
msgstr "Guardianes de la cámara"

#. [unit]: type=Demon Zephyr, gender=female, id=Azalia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:137
msgid "Azalia"
msgstr "Azalia"

#. [unit]: type=Demon Zephyr, gender=male, id=Rhadiarch
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:151
msgid "Rhadiarch"
msgstr "Rhadiarch"

#. [unit]: type=Demon Zephyr, gender=female, id=Galaviel
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:166
msgid "Galaviel"
msgstr "Galaviel"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:437
msgid "This goes deeper and deeper—"
msgstr "Esto se adentra cada vez más—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:446
msgid ""
"... I fear we don’t have much more time. Just where in this accursed place "
"are you, Hekuba?"
msgstr ""
"... Temo que no tenemos mucho más tiempo. ¿Dónde estás en este maldito "
"lugar, Hekuba?"

#. [unit]: type=Chaos Lorekeeper, id=Jarlean
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:591
msgid "Jarlean"
msgstr "Jarlean"

#. [unit]: type=Chaos Arbalestier, id=Terryl
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:615
msgid "Terryl"
msgstr "Terryl"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:722
msgid "The earth shakes."
msgstr "La tierra tiembla."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:766
msgid "Move Elynia to the central chamber"
msgstr "Mueve a Elynia a la cámara central"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:871
msgid "Be careful. I’m sure he is in this chamber, somewhere..."
msgstr ""
"Ten cuidado. Estoy segura de que está en esta cámara, en algún lugar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:902
msgid ""
"Most likely on that tall platform at the center. We need to get up there "
"somehow."
msgstr ""
"Lo más probable es que esté en esa plataforma alta del centro. Tenemos que "
"subir allí de algún modo."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:911
msgid "What’s that noise?"
msgstr "¿Qué es ese ruido?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:968
msgid "... That energy... It’s the same..."
msgstr "... Esa energía... Es la misma..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:973
msgid "Elynia? What’s happening?"
msgstr "¿Elynia? ¿Qué está pasando?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:982
msgid ""
"... A dark energy emanates from those spires... It’s the same energy that "
"was released in Wesmere when we destroyed the creature within the hive. "
msgstr ""
"... Una energía oscura emana de esas agujas... Es la misma energía que se "
"liberó en Wesmere cuando destruimos a la criatura dentro de la colmena."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:987
msgid "How should we destroy them?"
msgstr "¿Cómo deberíamos destruirlas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:992
msgid "Search the chamber — there must be some mechanism controlling them."
msgstr "Busquen en la cámara; debe haber algún mecanismo que las controle."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1003
msgid "Explore the central chamber"
msgstr "Explora la cámara central"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1219
msgid "Welcome to your end, heathens!"
msgstr "¡Bienvenidos a su final, infieles!"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1307
msgid "What kind of evil magic is this?"
msgstr "¿Qué clase de magia maligna es esta?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1312
msgid "Is he... fused with one of the spires?"
msgstr "¿Está... fusionado con una de las agujas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. "Your leader" refers to Elyssa.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1318
msgid ""
"What do you expect to achieve by creating a new portal to Inferno with your "
"new-found powers? Your troops are falling one by one under the might of the "
"northern peoples’ alliance, while you decided to rebel against your leader "
"in this dead land?"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué esperas lograr creando un nuevo portal al Infierno con tus nuevos "
"poderes? Tus tropas están cayendo una a una bajo la fuerza de la alianza de "
"los pueblos del norte, mientras tú decidiste rebelarte contra tu líder en "
"estas tierras muertas."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#. "her" refers to Elyssa, again.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1324
msgid ""
"Ha, ha, ha, ha! Don’t forget that your shortsightedness is the chief cause "
"of your friends’ demise, foolish creature. The power I control now is too "
"great, even for her."
msgstr ""
"¡Ja, ja, ja, ja! No olvides que tu miopía es la causa principal de la caída "
"de tus amigos, criatura necia. El poder que ahora controlo es demasiado "
"grande, incluso para ella."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1329
msgid ""
"What if you don’t truly control it? You said you cannot speak to Uria "
"directly — what if her will is <i>your</i> destruction?"
msgstr ""
"¿Y si en realidad no lo controlas? Dijiste que no puedes hablar directamente "
"con Uria; ¿y si su voluntad es <i>tu</i> destrucción?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1334
msgid "Insolent girl! You shall all die!"
msgstr "¡Muchacha insolente! ¡Todos morirán!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1342
msgid "YOU SHALL ALL DIE NOW!"
msgstr "¡AHORA TODOS MORIRÁN!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1398
msgid ""
"Everyone, stay away from the spires and the portal! I must think of "
"something..."
msgstr "¡Todos, aléjense de las agujas y del portal! Debo pensar en algo..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1402
msgid ""
"The portal grows in size every turn, taking adjacent ground hexes with it"
msgstr ""
"El portal crece de tamaño cada turno, llevándose las casillas de suelo "
"adyacentes."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1403
msgid "Unless adjacent to a spire, road hexes cannot disappear"
msgstr ""
"A menos que estén junto a una aguja, las casillas de camino no pueden "
"desaparecer."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1404
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Units incapable of flight will die should the ground below them disappear"
msgstr ""
"Las unidades incapaces de volar sobre abismos morirán si el suelo bajo ellas "
"desaparece."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1405
msgid ""
"While the portal is active, faeries and shydes <b>cannot</b> fly over "
"unwalkable terrain"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1410
msgid "Survive until the end of turns"
msgstr "Sobrevive hasta el final de los turnos"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1419
msgid "Undying Elder of Yechnagoth’s Iron Council"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1614
msgid ""
"There’s no use in attacking those structures — the energy they release in "
"retaliation could kill us all!"
msgstr ""
"No sirve de nada atacar esas estructuras: ¡la energía que liberan en "
"represalia podría matarnos a todos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1786
msgid "Attacking me is futile!"
msgstr "¡Atacarme es inútil!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1808
msgid ""
"The more time passes, the more energy fills the place and binds our worlds "
"together. I must go and try to destroy that lich by myself."
msgstr ""
"Cuanto más tiempo pasa, más energía llena este lugar y une nuestros mundos. "
"Debo ir e intentar destruir a ese liche yo sola."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1815
msgid "Elynia? No! If you go he will—"
msgstr "¿Elynia? ¡No! Si vas, él—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1820
msgid ""
"I am well aware, but I’m also the only one who can wield this staff and not "
"become corrupted by the power of the Ruby. Using it to vanquish this evil... "
"if my own sacrifice is necessary, I will gladly accept my fate. There’s "
"nothing left in Irdya for me now, and there will certainly be nothing for "
"you all if this fiend succeeds."
msgstr ""
"Lo sé bien, pero también soy la única que puede empuñar este báculo sin "
"corromperse por el poder del Rubí. Usarlo para derrotar este mal... si mi "
"propio sacrificio es necesario, aceptaré mi destino con gusto. Ya no queda "
"nada en Irdya para mí, y ciertamente no quedará nada para ustedes si este "
"demonio triunfa."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1829
msgid "I— I—"
msgstr "Yo... yo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1844
msgid ""
"You cannot go with me, for someone must survive the ordeal to pass the news "
"on to our allies. You are a very smart girl, and I’m sure you all will be "
"able to escape together with your power."
msgstr ""
"No puedes venir conmigo, alguien debe sobrevivir a esta prueba para "
"transmitir la noticia a nuestros aliados. Eres una chica muy lista, y estoy "
"segura de que podrán escapar juntos con tu poder."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1855
msgid "I must go now."
msgstr "Debo irme ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1862
msgid "Elynia, my lady... Good luck!"
msgstr "Elynia, mi señora... ¡Buena suerte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1867
msgid "(<i>tearful</i>) Elynia! Don’t die up there! Please!"
msgstr "(<i>llorando</i>) ¡Elynia! ¡No mueras allí arriba! ¡Por favor!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1876
msgid "(<i>muttering to herself</i>) I can only try."
msgstr "(<i>murmurando para sí misma</i>) Solo puedo intentarlo."

#. [object]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1885
msgid "Darkness Flight"
msgstr "Vuelo de la Oscuridad"

#. [object]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1886
#, fuzzy
msgid "Elynia is now able to fly unimpeded over the portal."
msgstr "Elynia ahora puede volar sobre abismos."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1953
msgid "Attack Mal Hekuba with Elynia"
msgstr "Ataca a Mal Hekuba con Elynia"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1983
msgid "And just what are you doing now?"
msgstr "¿Y qué se supone que haces ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:1988
msgid "I’m going to destroy you!"
msgstr "¡Voy a destruirte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2056
msgid "How pathetic."
msgstr "Qué patético."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2077
msgid ""
"Have you not learned anything after your friends’ vain sacrifices, Elynia? "
"Have you not learned to GIVE UP?"
msgstr ""
"¿No has aprendido nada tras los vanos sacrificios de tus amigos, Elynia? ¿No "
"has aprendido a RENDIRTE?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2150
msgid "ELYNIA!"
msgstr "¡ELYNIA!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2155
msgid "Why won’t you just accept your fate and <b>DIE</b>?!"
msgstr "¿Por qué no aceptas tu destino y <b>MUERES</b>?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2167
msgid "We must do something!"
msgstr "¡Debemos hacer algo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2172
msgid ""
"If Elynia herself doesn’t have the power to destroy that lich, I don’t think "
"there’s anything we can do about it..."
msgstr ""
"Si ni siquiera Elynia tiene el poder para destruir a ese liche, no creo que "
"haya nada que podamos hacer..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2177
msgid "Survive until the opportunity to destroy Mal Hekuba presents itself"
msgstr "Sobrevive hasta que surja la oportunidad de destruir a Mal Hekuba"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2196
msgid "It’s too late to stop me!"
msgstr "¡Es demasiado tarde para detenerme!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2206
msgid "There’s absolutely <i>nothing</i> you can do!"
msgstr "¡No hay absolutamente <i>nada</i> que puedan hacer!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2321
msgid "Have you had enough already?"
msgstr "¿Ya has tenido suficiente?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2326
msgid "No?"
msgstr "¿No?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2334
msgid ""
"<i>... Don’t forget that you are here fighting for a greater cause...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... No olvides que estás aquí luchando por una causa mayor...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2339
msgid "... I..."
msgstr "... Yo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2348
msgid "Stupid little vermin..."
msgstr "Estúpida alimaña..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2416
msgid ""
"Ah, Ivyel, at long last! It’s good to see you again... This pitiful creature "
"is hindering me. Could you sweep her away for me?"
msgstr ""
"Ah, Ivyel, ¡por fin! Me alegra verte de nuevo... Esta criatura miserable me "
"estorba. ¿Podrías barrerla por mí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2457
msgid "... What’s this?"
msgstr "... ¿Qué es esto?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2468
msgid "... I cannot be defeated by the likes of you..."
msgstr "... No puedo ser derrotada por alguien como tú..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2499
#, fuzzy
msgid "... I am the Lady of Light, Protector of the Elves of Irdya..."
msgstr ""
"Dedicado a Elynia-Thanadria de Wesmere, Dama de la Luz y Protectora de los "
"Elfos de Irdya."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2508
msgid "... even without my former power, I shall destroy you..."
msgstr "... incluso sin mi antiguo poder, te destruiré..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2513
msgid "Of course not. TAKE HER DOWN!"
msgstr "Por supuesto que no. ¡DERRÓTALA!"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2522
msgid "What’s she going to do? Does she have a plan?"
msgstr "¿Qué va a hacer? ¿Tiene algún plan?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2527
msgid ""
"I am not sure. It appears she wants to attack the infiltrator creature..."
msgstr "No estoy segura. Parece que quiere atacar a la criatura infiltrada..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2531
msgid "Destroy Ivyel"
msgstr "Destruye a Ivyel"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2542
#, fuzzy
msgid "“Ivyel”"
msgstr "Ivyel"

#. [event]
#. Rev.: Revision
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2544
msgid ""
"Biomechanical Infiltrator Unit 01 (Equipment Type C, Core MTAL-03 Rev. 2)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2562
msgid "This is <i>your</i> end, Mal Hekuba..."
msgstr "Este es <i>tu</i> fin, Mal Hekuba..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2611
msgid "... Irdya is not yours to destroy!"
msgstr "... ¡Irdya no es tuya para destruir!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2629
msgid "AAAAAAAARRGH!"
msgstr "¡AAAAAAARRGH!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:2676
msgid "WHAT HAVE YOU DONE?"
msgstr "¿QUÉ HAS HECHO?"

#. [side]
#. [side]: type=Boss Guardian of Darkness Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:42
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:57
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:57
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:35
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:125
msgid "team_name^Elyssa"
msgstr "Elyssa"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:194
msgid ""
"Severely injured, Elynia manages to escape from the underground base as the "
"energy destroys Mal Hekuba and his minions."
msgstr ""
"Gravemente herida, Elynia logra escapar de la base subterránea mientras la "
"energía destruye a Mal Hekuba y sus esbirros."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:235
msgid "Ungh..."
msgstr "Ungh..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:245
msgid ""
"Just as she tries, to no avail, to stand up, Elynia senses the presence of "
"creatures of some sort amidst the dense night fog."
msgstr ""
"Justo cuando intenta, sin éxito, ponerse de pie, Elynia percibe la presencia "
"de criaturas de algún tipo entre la densa niebla nocturna."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:271
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:445
msgid "And then..."
msgstr "Y entonces..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:309
msgid "... darkness."
msgstr "... oscuridad."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:319
msgid "<i>I cannot bring myself to kill someone so much weaker than I.</i>"
msgstr "<i>No puedo obligarme a matar a alguien mucho más débil que yo.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. The implication is not only that Elynia is hearing words she
#. herself uttered once (near the end of IftU), but also that
#. she is hearing them in her voice, possibly as a result of a
#. head trauma-induced hallucination.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:334
msgid "<i>Are those my words?</i>"
msgstr "<i>¿Son esas mis palabras?</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:344
msgid "(<i>in a seductive tone</i>) <i>It would be unfair... and cruel...</i>"
msgstr "(<i>con tono seductor</i>) <i>Sería injusto... y cruel...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. See the previous implication. This is why the line is "who
#. are you?" and not "who is there?".
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:357
msgid "<i>Who are you?</i>"
msgstr "<i>¿Quién eres?</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Take note of the description. She continues to do this for
#. the remainder of the scene.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:383
msgid ""
"The demoness stared directly into her eyes, with a deeply unsettling, "
"emotionless expression."
msgstr ""
"La demonio la miró directamente a los ojos, con una expresión profundamente "
"inquietante y sin emociones."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:393
msgid "Elynia was still unable to stand up and defend herself."
msgstr "Elynia aún no podía ponerse de pie ni defenderse."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:399
msgid ""
"As Elyssa bent down to reach her head, Elynia prepared for the inevitable."
msgstr ""
"Mientras Elyssa se inclinaba para alcanzar su cabeza, Elynia se preparaba "
"para lo inevitable."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:409
msgid ""
"But instead of dealing the killing blow, Elyssa stroked the elf’s hair — the "
"expression on her face unchanged — and continued to speak in a soft tone of "
"voice."
msgstr ""
"Pero en lugar de asestar el golpe mortal, Elyssa acarició el cabello de la "
"elfa — la expresión en su rostro sin cambios — y siguió hablando con voz "
"suave."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:418
msgid "I don’t want to kill you."
msgstr "No quiero matarte."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. "He" refers to Argan.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:428
msgid "You spared my life, just like he did."
msgstr "Me perdonaste la vida, tal como él lo hizo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. No, she isn't sorry. Unfortunately there's pretty much no
#. way to convey this in direct written speech, so we only have
#. the previous description of an emotionless expression. You
#. could say she is being sardonic about it all; after all, she
#. also knows for a fact that Elynia won't actually step aside.
#. Finally, the person who "didn't give [her] a choice" is
#. Uria.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:444
msgid ""
"I’m truly sorry about your friends. She didn’t give me a choice. Now, just "
"let me take what I need, and die in peace if you need to — otherwise, don’t "
"inconvenience us anymore and I’ll never cause you any harm again."
msgstr ""
"Lamento mucho lo de tus amigos. Ella no me dio opción. Ahora, déjame tomar "
"lo que necesito, y muere en paz si es necesario — de lo contrario, no nos "
"molestes más y nunca te haré daño."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:458
msgid ""
"Elynia felt the exchange could have taken place at a better time, and not "
"during such a terrible display of weakness."
msgstr ""
"Elynia sintió que ese intercambio podría haber ocurrido en un mejor momento, "
"y no durante una terrible muestra de debilidad."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:473
msgid "<i>... Why... why do you do this...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... ¿Por qué... por qué haces esto...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:482
msgid "... Because it’s all I have left, my dear."
msgstr "... Porque es todo lo que me queda, querida."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. Still sardonic.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:527
msgid "... And thank you for getting rid of that bothersome upstart for me."
msgstr "... Y gracias por deshacerte de ese molesto novato por mí."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/12_Fate.cfg:553
msgid "<i>... Elynia?</i>"
msgstr "<i>... ¿Elynia?</i>"

#. [page]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:8
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:8
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<b>If you have not completed Episode I of <i>After the Storm</i>, you should "
"not play this episode yet.</b>"
msgstr ""
"<b>Si no has completado el Episodio I de <i>Tras la Tormenta</i>, "
"definitivamente no deberías jugar este episodio todavía.</b>"

#. [part]
#. The lines consisting of a single em dash represent a long pause.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:23
msgid ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"—\n"
"\n"
"—"
msgstr ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"—\n"
"\n"
"—"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:30
msgid ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"—\n"
"\n"
"“The light..."
msgstr ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"—\n"
"\n"
"“La luz..."

#. [part]
#. Warm as in warm colors.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:39
msgid ""
"A familiar light...\n"
"\n"
"It was the warm light of the second sunset."
msgstr ""
"Una luz familiar...\n"
"\n"
"Era la cálida luz del segundo ocaso."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:44
msgid ""
"Where was I?\n"
"\n"
"I found myself in the middle of a glade, lying on the ground. My entire body "
"was in pain and my clothes were considerably scorched, but somehow... I had "
"survived."
msgstr ""
"¿Dónde estaba?\n"
"\n"
"Me encontraba en medio de un claro, tendida en el suelo. Todo mi cuerpo "
"estaba adolorido y mi ropa bastante chamuscada, pero de algún modo... había "
"sobrevivido."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:49
msgid ""
"It took me some time to recover from the initial stupor and remember what "
"had happened moments before. The terrifying feeling of my soul fading away, "
"the crumbling underground hive, my despair as I struggled to find a way back "
"to the surface... and my only remaining friend..."
msgstr ""
"Me tomó un tiempo recuperarme del estupor inicial y recordar lo que había "
"ocurrido instantes antes. La aterradora sensación de mi alma "
"desvaneciéndose, la colmena subterránea derrumbándose, mi desesperación por "
"encontrar una salida hacia la superficie... y mi único amigo restante..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:52
msgid ""
"Malin Keshar.\n"
"\n"
"His dark existence full of resentment and spite, an eternity spent as a "
"harbinger of death and destruction... an eternity at long last come to an "
"end, but not without first proving his worth against the Chaos Emperor and "
"the creature in possession of Yechnagoth’s heart.\n"
"\n"
"Oh, who would have ever thought that I would grieve for he whom I was once "
"destined to eliminate, or that his final death would be one befitting a hero?"
msgstr ""
"Malin Keshar.\n"
"\n"
"Su oscura existencia llena de rencor y odio, una eternidad como heraldo de "
"la muerte y la destrucción... una eternidad que al fin llegó a su fin, pero "
"no sin antes demostrar su valía contra el Emperador del Caos y la criatura "
"que poseía el corazón de Yechnagoth.\n"
"\n"
"Oh, ¿quién habría pensado que lloraría por aquel a quien una vez estuve "
"destinada a eliminar, o que su muerte final sería digna de un héroe?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:60
msgid ""
"As my memory became clearer, I realized I had cast the teleport spell at the "
"last moment, as if by instinct, in a desperate attempt to escape to the "
"surface. However, a quick glance at my surroundings revealed that it didn’t "
"work quite as I had intended; instead, it had taken me far away from the "
"cursed plains of Wesmere.\n"
"\n"
"But how far, exactly?"
msgstr ""
"A medida que mi memoria se aclaraba, me di cuenta de que había lanzado el "
"hechizo de teletransporte en el último momento, casi por instinto, en un "
"desesperado intento por escapar a la superficie. Sin embargo, un rápido "
"vistazo a mi alrededor reveló que no había funcionado tal como esperaba; en "
"su lugar, me había llevado lejos de las malditas llanuras de Wesmere.\n"
"\n"
"Pero, ¿qué tan lejos exactamente?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:72
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There were very few friendly faces amongst the villagers. From what I heard "
"during my stay, they feel forsaken by the Grand Council, which has been too "
"preoccupied with the war against the Chaos Empire to heed civilian demands. "
"The unforgiving weather and the growing scarcity of resources to sustain "
"their settlement has made these men and women increasingly bitter about the "
"state of affairs.\n"
"\n"
"I can’t help but wonder how the Alliance has fared in battle ever since we "
"left their lands."
msgstr ""
"Había muy pocos rostros amables entre los aldeanos. Por lo que escuché "
"durante mi estancia, se sienten abandonados por el Gran Consejo, que ha "
"estado demasiado ocupado en la guerra contra el Imperio del Caos como para "
"atender las demandas de los civiles. El clima implacable y la creciente "
"escasez de recursos para sostener su asentamiento han vuelto a estos hombres "
"y mujeres cada vez más amargados por el estado de las cosas.\n"
"\n"
"No puedo evitar preguntarme cómo le habrá ido a la Alianza en la batalla "
"desde que dejamos sus tierras."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:83
msgid ""
"This Allyna girl seems oddly over-enthusiastic about everything in spite of "
"the difficulties she encountered before we found her. To say that it has "
"been a long time since I last had the opportunity to talk to someone like "
"that would be a great understatement.\n"
"\n"
"Sadly, her cheerful demeanor is not enough to dispel the shadows that have "
"followed me wherever I go since Galas’ death; nor does it do anything to "
"keep me from remembering Malin and his habit of trying to make the most fun "
"of any situation."
msgstr ""
"Esta chica, Allyna, parece extrañamente entusiasta con todo a pesar de las "
"dificultades que encontró antes de que la halláramos.\n"
"\n"
"Decir que hace mucho que no tenía la oportunidad de hablar con alguien así "
"sería quedarse muy corto. Lamentablemente, su actitud alegre no es "
"suficiente para disipar las sombras que me han seguido a donde sea que voy "
"desde la muerte de Galas; ni tampoco logra evitar que recuerde a Malin y su "
"costumbre de intentar sacar el máximo provecho de cualquier situación."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:88
msgid ""
"For somebody who has lived for so long, it’s hard to see the world in the "
"same light as young people do. Nowadays I can barely remember those times of "
"blithe disregard for responsibility, my romantic escapades, and the "
"misguided notion that we had all the time of the world for ourselves.\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes, I wish I could get rid of this burden."
msgstr ""
"Para alguien que ha vivido tanto tiempo, es difícil ver el mundo con la "
"misma luz que los jóvenes. Hoy en día apenas puedo recordar aquellos tiempos "
"de alegre despreocupación por las responsabilidades, mis aventuras "
"románticas y la equivocada noción de que teníamos todo el tiempo del mundo "
"para nosotros.\n"
"\n"
"A veces desearía poder librarme de esta carga."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:94
msgid ""
"Before dying, my master told me that the true power of the Ruby of Fire "
"would become crucial for the fate of our world, and that I must make sure "
"it’s never misused by anyone again. It never occurred to me that her words "
"could turn out to be more than a pain-induced delusion."
msgstr ""
"Antes de morir, mi maestra me dijo que el verdadero poder del Rubí de Fuego "
"sería crucial para el destino de nuestro mundo y que debía asegurarme de que "
"nadie volviera a usarlo mal. Nunca se me ocurrió que sus palabras pudieran "
"resultar ser algo más que un delirio inducido por el dolor."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:103
msgid ""
"And so we left for the eastern marches, with a renewed and clear purpose.\n"
"\n"
"Surprisingly enough, Durvan and some of the other hunters from the Heart "
"Forest agreed to participate in our expedition. Allyna offered her help as "
"well, providing us with a safe route to follow, incidentally crossing "
"through her village."
msgstr ""
"Y así partimos hacia las marcas orientales, con un propósito renovado y "
"claro.\n"
"\n"
"Sorprendentemente, Durvan y algunos de los otros cazadores del Bosque "
"Corazón aceptaron participar en nuestra expedición. Allyna también ofreció "
"su ayuda, proporcionándonos una ruta segura que, casualmente, pasaba por su "
"aldea."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:109
msgid ""
"We proceeded as swiftly as we could, hoping for an uneventful journey — "
"given the nature of our mission, expending our energy before reaching the "
"elves could prove disastrous later on."
msgstr ""
"Procedimos tan rápido como pudimos, esperando un viaje sin contratiempos — "
"dada la naturaleza de nuestra misión, gastar energías antes de llegar a los "
"elfos podría resultar desastroso más adelante."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:118
msgid ""
"Had the circumstances been only slightly different, I would have been much "
"more reluctant to converse with the outcast demon lord; in fact, I would "
"have been more likely to attack without even giving him a chance to speak.\n"
"\n"
"That girl, Anya. It was her curious personality, and her sincerity and "
"admiration for me that led me to try my late friend’s approach to dealing "
"with a similarly unusual enemy. I thought that such a person could not "
"possibly side with the cruel creatures working for Uria — not that faeries "
"of the deep forest like her are known to side with anyone at all."
msgstr ""
"Si las circunstancias hubiesen sido solo un poco diferentes, habría estado "
"mucho más reacia a conversar con el exiliado señor demonio; de hecho, lo más "
"probable es que lo hubiese atacado sin darle siquiera la oportunidad de "
"hablar.\n"
"\n"
"Esa chica, Anya. Fue su curiosa personalidad, su sinceridad y su admiración "
"hacia mí lo que me llevó a intentar el enfoque de mi difunto amigo para "
"tratar con un enemigo igual de inusual. Pensé que una persona así no podría "
"ponerse del lado de las crueles criaturas que servían a Uria — aunque las "
"hadas del bosque profundo como ella no son precisamente conocidas por "
"aliarse con nadie."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:123
msgid ""
"But, did I make that choice for her or for me? Perhaps I merely wanted "
"someone by my side to whom I could relate, someone who personified the "
"bright and hopeful part of me that died with Argan.\n"
"\n"
"Perhaps... I didn’t want to face the possibility of having to kill that part "
"of me a second time."
msgstr ""
"Pero, ¿hice esa elección por ella o por mí? Quizás solo quería a alguien a "
"mi lado con quien pudiera identificarme, alguien que personificara la parte "
"brillante y esperanzada de mí que murió con Argan.\n"
"\n"
"Quizás... no quería enfrentar la posibilidad de tener que matar esa parte de "
"mí una segunda vez."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:128
msgid ""
"All this seems so absurd as I write it. Sometimes I wonder why I let Galas "
"convince me to write another journal."
msgstr ""
"Todo esto me parece tan absurdo mientras lo escribo. A veces me pregunto por "
"qué dejé que Galas me convenciera de escribir otro diario."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:132
msgid ""
"After a couple of days, we finally arrived at the frontier. Unfortunately, "
"we’d soon learn that the Council’s fears had become more than mere "
"speculations."
msgstr ""
"Tras un par de días, finalmente llegamos a la frontera. Desafortunadamente, "
"pronto descubriríamos que los temores del Consejo se habían convertido en "
"algo más que meras especulaciones."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:141
msgid ""
"Unarye told us to follow her guards into a nearby forest where some of the "
"allied elves had just set up camp. I could tell by her grave expression that "
"she bore bad news. It took her almost the entire afternoon to make time for "
"speaking to us."
msgstr ""
"Unarye nos dijo que siguiéramos a sus guardias hasta un bosque cercano donde "
"algunos de los elfos aliados acababan de montar un campamento. Su expresión "
"grave me hizo saber que traía malas noticias. Le tomó casi toda la tarde "
"hacerse un tiempo para hablar con nosotros."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:150
msgid ""
"I continued to feel uneasy about the decision for some time. Leaving both "
"the Grand Council and Elorran awaiting our return for so long...\n"
"\n"
"According to Valen, the Council understood the urgency of the situation and "
"the importance of our mission for the elves. Unfortunately, the same "
"couldn’t be said for the demon lord; it took Anya her best effort to "
"persuade him to let us take the Ruby of Fire to enemy territory."
msgstr ""
"Continué sintiéndome inquieta por la decisión durante un tiempo. Dejar tanto "
"al Gran Consejo como a Elorran esperando nuestro regreso por tanto "
"tiempo...\n"
"\n"
"Según Valen, el Consejo comprendió la urgencia de la situación y la "
"importancia de nuestra misión para los elfos. Lamentablemente, no se podía "
"decir lo mismo del señor demonio; Anya tuvo que esforzarse al máximo para "
"convencerlo de dejarnos llevar el Rubí de Fuego a territorio enemigo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:155
msgid ""
"It is decidedly not easy to deal with both the Council and my people without "
"telling them of our pact with Elorran. What concerns me the most is the "
"possibility that one of our men might accidentally or deliberately divulge "
"information pertaining to the subject. This is not like every other time I "
"have had to keep a secret for a greater good — alone.\n"
"\n"
"It does raise the question of whether I have chosen my allies prudently or "
"am making a big mistake."
msgstr ""
"Definitivamente no es fácil tratar tanto con el Consejo como con mi gente "
"sin contarles sobre nuestro pacto con Elorran. Lo que más me preocupa es la "
"posibilidad de que alguno de nuestros hombres divulgue accidental o "
"deliberadamente información al respecto. No es como las otras veces que he "
"tenido que guardar un secreto por un bien mayor — sola.\n"
"\n"
"Esto plantea la pregunta de si he elegido a mis aliados con prudencia o si "
"estoy cometiendo un gran error."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Then again, Malin would insist that the existence of that accursed artifact "
"is a big mistake by itself."
msgstr ""
"Por otro lado, Malin insistiría en que la existencia de ese maldito "
"artefacto ya es un gran error en sí misma."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:170
msgid ""
"After the events in Gralseth, the journey across the desert turned into a "
"nightmare. We had to be wary of every single thing we saw, no matter how "
"small or innocuous it seemed. Our enemies could be anywhere, everywhere. We "
"were walking into a trap by our own choice... No, it was <i>my</i> choice.\n"
"\n"
"Even without taking our enemies into account, traversing the vast dry plains "
"was a highly dangerous thing to do. While it wasn’t possible for us to lose "
"track of our destination for long with our maps and Valen’s indications, the "
"stifling heat during the day, frequent sandstorms, and lack of water sources "
"could have resulted in catastrophic losses."
msgstr ""
"Tras los acontecimientos en Gralseth, el viaje a través del desierto se "
"convirtió en una pesadilla. Tuvimos que ser cautelosos con cada cosa que "
"veíamos, por pequeña o inocua que pareciera. Nuestros enemigos podían estar "
"en cualquier parte, en todas partes. Caminábamos hacia una trampa por "
"elección propia... No, fue <i>mi</i> elección.\n"
"\n"
"Incluso sin tener en cuenta a nuestros enemigos, atravesar las vastas "
"llanuras áridas era una empresa sumamente peligrosa. Aunque no podíamos "
"perder de vista nuestro destino por mucho tiempo gracias a los mapas y las "
"indicaciones de Valen, el calor sofocante durante el día, las frecuentes "
"tormentas de arena y la falta de fuentes de agua podrían haber provocado "
"pérdidas catastróficas."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:175
msgid ""
"Eventually, it became evident that our enemies didn’t want to take risks in "
"the hostile sands either. Aside from a few armed encounters with the "
"natives, we found very little opposition on our way.\n"
"\n"
"At the end, we reached a small oasis near some ruins."
msgstr ""
"Con el tiempo, se hizo evidente que nuestros enemigos tampoco querían correr "
"riesgos en las arenas hostiles. Aparte de unos pocos enfrentamientos armados "
"con los nativos, encontramos muy poca oposición en nuestro camino.\n"
"\n"
"Al final, llegamos a un pequeño oasis cerca de unas ruinas."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:181
msgid ""
"We had reached the northern defense line of the valley Telchior named after "
"me."
msgstr ""
"Habíamos alcanzado la línea defensiva norte del valle que Telchior nombró en "
"mi honor."

#. [part]
#. Condenser/capacitor.
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:191
msgid ""
"The Ruby of Fire. A great energy condenser of uncertain origin, used by "
"humans throughout Irdya’s history as both a symbol of power and a catalyst "
"to exert control over all within their reach, and beyond. Through abuse of "
"this artifact, our world was made susceptible to corrupting influences from "
"other realms.\n"
"\n"
"Now that we are without a necromancer, using its dangerous power to command "
"the undead minions left behind by Zynara is the only option we have left if "
"we want to have a chance to vanquish the impostor despite our small numbers. "
"But, who is she in truth?"
msgstr ""
"El Rubí de Fuego. Un gran condensador de energía de origen incierto, usado "
"por los humanos a lo largo de la historia de Irdya tanto como símbolo de "
"poder como catalizador para ejercer control sobre todo lo que estaba a su "
"alcance, y más allá. Por el abuso de este artefacto, nuestro mundo quedó "
"expuesto a influencias corruptoras de otros reinos.\n"
"\n"
"Ahora que no tenemos un nigromante, usar su peligroso poder para comandar a "
"los esbirros no-muertos que dejó Zynara es la única opción que nos queda si "
"queremos tener una oportunidad de derrotar a la impostora pese a nuestro "
"reducido número. Pero, ¿quién es ella en realidad?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:196
msgid ""
"Up to this point I have broken more rules than is acceptable for any elf, or "
"human.\n"
"\n"
"First, the Ruby. Then I chose Argan, of all people, to be my ally and lover, "
"and asked him to help me learn to use the artifact’s power more effectively. "
"I asked him to teach me the basics of this forbidden magic, and only my fear "
"deterred me from delving deeper — had it not, I probably wouldn’t be here "
"writing these words."
msgstr ""
"Hasta este punto he roto más reglas de las que serían aceptables para "
"cualquier elfo, o humano.\n"
"\n"
"Primero, el Rubí. Luego elegí a Argan, de entre todas las personas, para que "
"fuera mi aliado y amante, y le pedí que me ayudara a aprender a usar el "
"poder del artefacto con mayor eficacia. Le pedí que me enseñara los "
"fundamentos de esta magia prohibida, y solo mi miedo me impidió profundizar "
"más — de no ser así, probablemente no estaría aquí escribiendo estas "
"palabras."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:201
msgid ""
"Then, I joined the Empire of Wesnoth as an advisor, against the wishes of "
"the Ka’lian, who only realized the benefits much later. But eventually, I "
"was betrayed by the humans; I turned my back on the world and unknowingly "
"left my kinsmen in Wesmere to be caught in Zhangor’s trap at the onset of "
"the end.\n"
"\n"
"Perhaps if I hadn’t broken so many rules before, none of that would have "
"ever come to pass."
msgstr ""
"Después, me uní al Imperio de Wesnoth como consejera, en contra de los "
"deseos del Ka’lian, que solo reconoció los beneficios mucho más tarde. Pero "
"al final, fui traicionada por los humanos; le di la espalda al mundo y dejé "
"sin saberlo a mis parientes en Wesmere para que cayeran en la trampa de "
"Zhangor al inicio del fin.\n"
"\n"
"Quizás, si no hubiese roto tantas reglas antes, nada de eso habría llegado a "
"ocurrir."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:206
msgid ""
"Our alliance with Mal Keshar in this era was not my choice, however. Galas "
"and Anlindë knew well what it entailed, and opted for a desperate solution "
"to a desperate situation. But now... I appear to be following the same "
"logic, commanding the dead with a power that was meant to be purged from "
"this world long ago. It seems selfish, and others could misinterpret my "
"actions."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, nuestra alianza con Mal Keshar en esta era no fue mi decisión. "
"Galas y Anlindë sabían bien lo que implicaba y optaron por una solución "
"desesperada para una situación desesperada. Pero ahora... parece que estoy "
"siguiendo la misma lógica, comandando a los muertos con un poder que debía "
"haber sido purgado de este mundo hace mucho tiempo. Parece egoísta, y otros "
"podrían malinterpretar mis acciones."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:209
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I no longer command the Union, and now I am about to confront our enemy "
"while leading my own army of darkness.\n"
"\n"
"It would be no exaggeration to say that I am, in fact, another impostor."
msgstr ""
"Ya no comando a la Unión, y ahora estoy a punto de enfrentar a nuestro "
"enemigo mientras lidero mi propio ejército de oscuridad.\n"
"\n"
"No sería una exageración decir que la verdadera Dama de la Luz es, en "
"realidad, otra impostora."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/storytxt.cfg:215
msgid ""
"Some day all this will be over, and I will be able to distance myself from "
"civilization again.\n"
"\n"
"But for now, I must fight. And afterwards, I must recover that journal."
msgstr ""
"Algún día todo esto habrá terminado, y podré alejarme de la civilización "
"otra vez.\n"
"\n"
"Pero por ahora, debo luchar. Y después, debo recuperar ese diario."

#: After_the_Storm/episode3/characters.cfg:47
msgid "Irylean"
msgstr "Irylean"

#: After_the_Storm/episode3/characters.cfg:76
msgid "General Bardyl"
msgstr "General Bardyl"

#: After_the_Storm/episode3/characters.cfg:119
msgid "Cron"
msgstr "Cron"

#: After_the_Storm/episode3/characters.cfg:134
msgid "Ergea"
msgstr "Ergea"

#: After_the_Storm/episode3/characters.cfg:148
msgid "Naiad"
msgstr "Náyade"

#: After_the_Storm/episode3/characters.cfg:260
msgid ""
"Certain high-level units in this campaign under your control — such as "
"Elynia and Anya — have special <b>After Maximum Level Advancements (AMLAs)</"
"b>. You can learn more about those by right-clicking applicable units and "
"choosing the <b>Unit Advancements</b> option."
msgstr ""
"Algunas unidades de alto nivel bajo tu control en esta campaña —como Elynia "
"y Anya— tienen <b>Mejoras tras el nivel máximo (AMLAs)</b> especiales. "
"Puedes obtener más información sobre ellas haciendo clic derecho en las "
"unidades correspondientes y seleccionando la opción <b>Mejoras de unidad</b>."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:72
msgid "No! Elynia, please!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡Elynia, por favor!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:84
msgid "No... Elynia... save me..."
msgstr "No... Elynia... sálvame..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:89
msgid "No... NO!"
msgstr "¡No... NO!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:100
msgid "I guess... I will never see my home again..."
msgstr "Supongo que... nunca volveré a ver mi hogar..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:111
msgid "It is over for me..."
msgstr "Se acabó para mí..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. He's referring to Galas and Mal Keshar.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:123
msgid "I couldn’t... I couldn’t avenge the elf friend and the scary lich..."
msgstr "No pude... no pude vengar al amigo elfo y al terrible lich..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:129
msgid ""
"I should have seen this coming... I’m sorry we failed to protect you, "
"friend. I’m sorry..."
msgstr ""
"Debí haberlo previsto... Siento que no pudimos protegerte, amigo. Lo "
"siento..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:140
msgid "I don’t think I— ARGH!"
msgstr "No creo que— ¡ARGH!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:151
msgid "This couldn’t be more untimely... ugh..."
msgstr "Esto no podría ser más inoportuno... ugh..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:162
msgid "Alas, I thought I’d... recover Aran-Balgur... before... this..."
msgstr ""
"Lamentablemente, pensé que podría... recuperar Aran-Balgur... antes... de "
"esto..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:174
msgid "Oh, Elynia... I wish... you could be... with me now..."
msgstr "Oh, Elynia... desearía... que pudieras estar... conmigo ahora..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:185
msgid "... I knew this was... a terrible idea... heh...."
msgstr "... Sabía que esto era... una idea terrible... je..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:190
msgid "No! It didn’t have to end like this!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡No tenía que terminar así!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:201
msgid "Alas... nobody will mourn my passing..."
msgstr "Lamentablemente... nadie llorará mi partida..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:212
msgid "No... we were so close to the end..."
msgstr "No... estuvimos tan cerca del final..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:218
msgid ""
"I cannot believe it... I’m sorry, Elynia. I could’ve done better, I could’ve "
"saved him..."
msgstr ""
"No puedo creerlo... Lo siento, Elynia. Podría haberlo hecho mejor, podría "
"haberlo salvado..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:223
msgid ""
"It’s not your fault, Anya. At least he died a hero — better than can be said "
"for most goblins who just end up as cannon fodder for— Irylean what are you "
"doing??"
msgstr ""
"No es tu culpa, Anya. Al menos murió como un héroe — mejor que la mayoría de "
"los goblins que sólo terminan como carne de cañón para— ¡Irylean, ¿qué "
"haces?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:228
msgid ""
"Master Mal Keshar once told me that the goblin’s life-long wish was to rise "
"again as a fearsome undead champion."
msgstr ""
"El maestro Mal Keshar me dijo una vez que el deseo de toda la vida de un "
"goblin era resurgir como un temible campeón no-muerto."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:233
msgid ""
"No!!! I am <b>not</b> allowing you to do this! I never had the chance to "
"meet the guy but I have a feeling he wasn’t being serious when he said that."
msgstr ""
"¡No!!! ¡No te permitiré hacer esto! Nunca tuve la oportunidad de conocer al "
"tipo, pero tengo la sensación de que no hablaba en serio cuando dijo eso."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:238
msgid ""
"Very well, if you say so... I’ve got to admit I am not very good at raising "
"the recently deceased anyway."
msgstr ""
"Muy bien, si lo dices... debo admitir que no soy muy bueno levantando a los "
"recién fallecidos de todos modos."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:249
msgid "I failed you all..."
msgstr "Los he fallado a todos..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:263
msgid "This battle is not mine to fight. Farewell, Anya."
msgstr "Esta batalla no es mía para pelear. Adiós, Anya."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:274
msgid "Cron falls... and bids the storm lady... farewell..."
msgstr "Cron cae... y se despide de la dama de la tormenta..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:279
msgid "No! This... this was not supposed to happen! Cron!"
msgstr "¡No! Esto... esto no se suponía que pasara! ¡Cron!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:288
msgid ""
"Such an incompetent fool. I should have known she would be useless in the "
"end."
msgstr "Una tonta tan incompetente. Debí saber que sería inútil al final."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:297
msgid "Even with her greater experience... This is hopeless..."
msgstr "Incluso con su mayor experiencia... Esto es desesperanzador..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/deaths.cfg:306
msgid "I should have known this would fail so horribly in the end..."
msgstr "Debí saber que esto fallaría tan horriblemente al final."

#. [campaign]: id=After_the_Storm_III
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/menu.cfg:15
msgid "AtS-3"
msgstr "AtS-3"

#. [campaign]: id=After_the_Storm_III
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/menu.cfg:17
msgid "Final"
msgstr "Final"

#. [campaign]: id=After_the_Storm_III
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/menu.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Though at the end of the day darkness may claim our homes and lives and trap "
"the world beneath its impenetrable veil, the night is not eternal, and even "
"amidst chaos, hope shines forth as a beacon which can help us vanquish our "
"worst fears and reunite us with our destiny."
msgstr ""
"Aunque al final del día la oscuridad pueda reclamar nuestros hogares y vidas "
"y atrapar el mundo bajo su velo impenetrable, la noche no es eterna, y aun "
"en medio del caos, la esperanza brilla como un faro que puede ayudarnos a "
"vencer nuestros peores temores y reunirmos con nuestro destino."

#. [campaign]: id=After_the_Storm_III
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/menu.cfg:28
msgid "difficulty_menu^Dancer"
msgstr "Bailarina"

#. [campaign]: id=After_the_Storm_III
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/menu.cfg:29
msgid "difficulty_menu^Dryad"
msgstr "Dríada"

#. [campaign]: id=After_the_Storm_III
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/menu.cfg:30
msgid "difficulty_menu^Warden"
msgstr "Guardián"

#. [scenario]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:4
msgid "Opening"
msgstr "Apertura"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:124
msgid ""
"My lady, you have finally returned! I was concerned for you, since you left "
"without notice! What do you have there?"
msgstr ""
"¡Mi señora, finalmente has regresado! Me preocupé por ti, ¡ya que te fuiste "
"sin avisar! ¿Qué tienes ahí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:133
msgid ""
"The Ruby of Fire! You retrieved it, my lady! Was the faerie elf already "
"dead, or did you kill her yourself?"
msgstr ""
"¡El Rubí de Fuego! ¡Lo recuperaste, mi señora! ¿La elfa hada ya estaba "
"muerta o la mataste tú misma?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:162
msgid ""
"She destroyed Hekuba for us first in the elves’ valley. Naturally, she paid "
"the price."
msgstr ""
"Ella destruyó a Hekuba por nosotros primero en el valle de los elfos. "
"Naturalmente, pagó el precio."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:167
msgid "So they destroyed each other? Excellent news!"
msgstr "¿Así que se destruyeron entre ellos? ¡Excelente noticia!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:178
msgid "So, what are we going to do now?"
msgstr "Entonces, ¿qué vamos a hacer ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:183
msgid "Where is Nar-hamoth?"
msgstr "¿Dónde está Nar-hamoth?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:188
msgid ""
"I believe he’s busy battling the allied forces remaining near the Bay of "
"Glamdrol. Should you require his immediate presence here with us, I can "
"summon him—"
msgstr ""
"Creo que está ocupado luchando contra las fuerzas aliadas que quedan cerca "
"de la Bahía de Glamdrol. Si necesitas su presencia inmediata aquí con "
"nosotros, puedo convocarlo—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:193
msgid "That shall not be necessary. Not anymore."
msgstr "No será necesario. Ya no."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:203
msgid ""
"As Elyssa whispers an incantation never heard by Mal Kendria before, the "
"staff she holds changes its shape into a four-bladed weapon with the "
"glowing, unshielded Ruby at its very end. The necromancer stares in awe..."
msgstr ""
"Mientras Elyssa susurra una invocación nunca antes escuchada por Mal "
"Kendria, el bastón que sostiene cambia su forma en un arma de cuatro hojas "
"con el Rubí brillante y sin protección en su extremo. El nigromante mira "
"asombrado..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:239
msgid "That’s amazing!"
msgstr "¡Eso es asombroso!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:255
msgid ""
"But the feeling promptly vanishes as Elyssa’s eyes turn blood red. An eerie "
"aura engulfs both former allies as the demoness advances towards the "
"necromancer, now petrified with dread."
msgstr ""
"Pero la sensación desaparece rápidamente cuando los ojos de Elyssa se "
"vuelven rojo sangre. Un aura inquietante envuelve a ambos antiguos aliados "
"mientras la demonio avanza hacia el nigromante, ahora petrificado por el "
"miedo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:282
msgid ""
"(<i>whispering</i>) Bind the soul to stone, turn the memories to dust..."
msgstr ""
"(<i>susurrando</i>) Ata el alma a la piedra, convierte los recuerdos en "
"polvo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:299
msgid "M-m-my lady..."
msgstr "M-m-mi señora..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:308
msgid "(<i>whispering</i>) ... erase the spirit and shed the hollow shell."
msgstr ""
"(<i>susurrando</i>) ... borra el espíritu y desprende la cáscara vacía."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:317
msgid "... Elyssa... <small>I feel... <small>unwell...</small></small>"
msgstr "... Elyssa... <small>Me siento... <small>mal...</small></small>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:322
msgid "Goodbye, Kendyare."
msgstr "Adiós, Kendyare."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:336
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2094
