msgstr "($beams_remaining estructuras restantes)"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:619
msgid "(One structure remaining)"
msgstr "(Una estructura restante)"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:630
msgid "Running out of barrels of explosives"
msgstr "Quedarse sin barriles explosivos"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:659
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:676
msgid "Secure the portal located within the central keep"
msgstr "Asegura el portal situado dentro de la fortaleza central"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:710
msgid "Aran-Balgur is really impressive. How could it fall to Uria’s forces?"
msgstr ""
"Aran-Balgur es realmente impresionante. ¿Cómo pudo caer ante las fuerzas de "
"Uria?"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:715
msgid ""
"Some people say the lord of the stronghold was brutally killed by the Chaos "
"thugs on the battlefield some time after their Emperor fell. The man left in "
"charge in his place wasn’t very bright, and couldn’t stand a chance when the "
"angry enemy troops arrived. Others say they found the descendant of the "
"architect who helped build its walls a century ago, and forced him to reveal "
"the plans with all the secret passages and weak points."
msgstr ""
"Algunos dicen que el señor de la fortaleza fue brutalmente asesinado por los "
"matones del Caos en el campo de batalla poco después de que cayera su "
"Emperador. El hombre que quedó a cargo en su lugar no era muy brillante y no "
"tuvo ninguna oportunidad cuando llegaron las tropas enemigas enfurecidas. "
"Otros dicen que encontraron al descendiente del arquitecto que ayudó a "
"construir sus muros un siglo atrás, y lo obligaron a revelar los planos con "
"todos los pasajes secretos y puntos débiles."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:720
msgid ""
"Regardless of the rumors, the fact is that they killed everyone. See the "
"stains on the exterior walls? Everyone says it’s the blood of the former "
"occupants. Some believe that the General’s family was amongst them."
msgstr ""
"Independientemente de los rumores, el hecho es que mataron a todos. ¿Ves las "
"manchas en las paredes exteriores? Todos dicen que es la sangre de los "
"antiguos ocupantes. Algunos creen que la familia del General estaba entre "
"ellos."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:725
msgid "I guess... that explains why he’s such an unpleasant person."
msgstr "Supongo... eso explica por qué es una persona tan desagradable."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:744
msgid "I hope everyone is ready for the battle ahead of us."
msgstr "Espero que todos estén listos para la batalla que nos espera."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:749
msgid "We are, my lady. What are your orders?"
msgstr "Lo estamos, mi señora. ¿Cuáles son sus órdenes?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:754
msgid ""
"Just assist our allies with the siege and deal with whatever creatures guard "
"the keep and the rumored portal. We ought to make this quick, for the "
"demoness that awaits us at the other end might not be too patient, and this "
"mission has delayed us too much already."
msgstr ""
"Solo ayuden a nuestros aliados con el asedio y enfréntense a las criaturas "
"que custodian la fortaleza y el supuesto portal. Debemos hacerlo rápido, "
"pues la demonio que nos espera al otro lado podría no ser muy paciente, y "
"esta misión ya nos ha retrasado demasiado."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:759
msgid "You haven’t changed your mind..."
msgstr "No has cambiado de opinión..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:764
msgid "Indeed, I have not."
msgstr "En efecto, no lo he hecho."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:790
msgid "I don’t like that sound..."
msgstr "No me gusta ese sonido..."

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:809
msgid "It is time. At last... I’ll have my revenge..."
msgstr "Ha llegado la hora. Por fin... Tendré mi venganza..."

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:814
msgid "And what about us?"
msgstr "¿Y qué hay de nosotros?"

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:819
msgid ""
"You two shall be allowed to leave once the battle is over — that is, "
"assuming you survive."
msgstr ""
"A ustedes dos se les permitirá marcharse una vez termine la batalla... eso, "
"claro, si sobreviven."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:824
msgid "What if we lose?"
msgstr "¿Y si perdemos?"

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:829
msgid ""
"Should it come to that, you’d best hope those fiends will be swift to end "
"your pitiful lives."
msgstr ""
"Si llegara a suceder, más vale que recen para que esos demonios terminen "
"rápido con sus miserables vidas."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:834
msgid "That’s truly motivating..."
msgstr "Eso es realmente motivador..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:843
msgid ""
"Durvan, what are you going to do after this is over? You said earlier you "
"had some doubts about Elynia’s plan, and you..."
msgstr ""
"Durvan, ¿qué vas a hacer cuando esto termine? Antes dijiste que tenías "
"algunas dudas sobre el plan de Elynia y tú..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:848
msgid ""
"Yes, I won’t be going with you. Her plan just seems too risky... What the "
"hell is she thinking? Didn’t you say Elorran himself knew his kinsmen "
"couldn’t be trusted? Besides, I won’t be very useful once you arrive there. "
"From what I’ve heard, the natives hate us, and motivating and talking to "
"people is really all I have done ever since I joined Elynia."
msgstr ""
"No, no iré con ustedes. Su plan simplemente parece demasiado arriesgado... "
"¿Qué demonios está pensando? ¿No dijiste que el propio Elorran sabía que no "
"se podía confiar en los suyos? Además, no seré de mucha utilidad una vez que "
"lleguen allí. Por lo que he oído, los nativos nos odian, y motivar y hablar "
"con la gente es prácticamente todo lo que he hecho desde que me uní a Elynia."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:853
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2912
msgid "But..."
msgstr "Pero..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#. The other human is Erathan from IftU.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:859
msgid ""
"You two and the necromancer woman have all those magic abilities and powers "
"I will never have. I’m tired of risking my life fighting alongside you "
"against powerful demons and psychotic cultists. I just... I just want to "
"live a longer life than the other human Elynia got killed in enemy "
"territory, the poor bastard."
msgstr ""
"Ustedes dos y la mujer nigromante tienen todas esas habilidades y poderes "
"mágicos que yo nunca tendré. Estoy cansado de arriesgar mi vida luchando "
"junto a ustedes contra demonios poderosos y cultistas psicópatas. Yo solo... "
"solo quiero vivir una vida más larga que la del otro humano que Elynia llevó "
"a morir en territorio enemigo, el pobre desgraciado."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:864
msgid "Heh, yes... But you were really brave in the valley..."
msgstr "Je, sí... Pero fuiste realmente valiente en el valle..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:869
msgid ""
"I was really <i>stupid</i>! I hadn’t heard of that guy and his fate yet!"
msgstr ""
"¡Fui realmente <i>estúpido</i>! ¡Todavía no había oído hablar de ese tipo y "
"su destino!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:879
msgid ""
"I still think I will miss you... even if you only rarely start a "
"conversation! And I’m sure Elynia will miss you as well."
msgstr ""
"Sigo pensando que te extrañaré... ¡aunque rara vez empieces una "
"conversación! Y estoy segura de que Elynia también te extrañará."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:885
msgid "Sure..."
msgstr "Claro..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:894
msgid "I wish you two all the luck in the world. You’ll surely need it."
msgstr "Les deseo toda la suerte del mundo. Seguramente la necesitarán."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:909
msgid ""
"I want this to be over as soon as possible so I can bid farewell to the "
"giant wolves."
msgstr ""
"Quiero que esto termine lo antes posible para poder despedirme de los lobos "
"gigantes."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:914
msgid "Why? They are so cute!"
msgstr "¿Por qué? ¡Son tan adorables!"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:919
msgid "Nope, they’re terrifying. And they smell."
msgstr "No, son terroríficos. Y apestan."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:929
msgid "What about Willow? She’s so fluffy and cuddly and..."
msgstr "¿Y qué hay de Willow? ¡Es tan esponjosa y adorable y..."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:934
msgid ""
"I <i>really</i> don’t like her. She follows me around as though she knows I "
"am terrified of her."
msgstr ""
"<i>Realmente</i> no me gusta. Me sigue a todos lados como si supiera que le "
"tengo terror."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:939
msgid ""
"Awwww, but she just wants to be your friend! You should give her a chance!"
msgstr ""
"Awwww, ¡pero solo quiere ser tu amiga! ¡Deberías darle una oportunidad!"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:944
msgid ""
"<i>(sighs)</i> I don’t think this is the right time and place to practice "
"shock therapy, Anya. Maybe when things have calmed down a little."
msgstr ""
"<i>(suspira)</i> No creo que este sea el momento ni el lugar para practicar "
"terapia de choque, Anya. Tal vez cuando las cosas se hayan calmado un poco."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1193
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In this scenario, most units under your control can carry barrels of "
"explosives, which can be used to destroy structures and other units.\n"
"\n"
"To retrieve a barrel, move a unit over it. You will be given the choice to "
"grab the barrel or leave it for another unit. Once a unit gets the barrel, "
"it will gain the <b>Demolition</b> ability, allowing it to destroy "
"everything within a one-hex radius upon death. The unit will also be able to "
"<b>drop</b> the barrel for another unit to pick it up, or <b>deploy</b> an "
"activated charge. Once a barrel is deployed, it will <b>destroy</b> "
"everything within a one-hex radius at the start of the next first-player "
"turn, so you want to make sure your unit has enough movement points left to "
"get away before deploying.\n"
"\n"
"Units lose the Demolition ability after dropping or deploying barrels.\n"
"\n"
"Use these barrels wisely! You start with a limited number, and you need at "
"least <b>six</b> to complete the main objective!"
msgstr ""
"En este escenario, la mayoría de las unidades bajo tu control pueden llevar "
"barriles de explosivos, los cuales pueden usarse para destruir estructuras y "
"otras unidades.\n"
"\n"
"Para obtener un barril, mueve una unidad sobre él. Se te dará la opción de "
"tomar el barril o dejarlo para otra unidad. Una vez que una unidad toma el "
"barril, ganará la habilidad <b>Demolición</b>, lo que le permite destruir "
"todo en un radio de una casilla al morir. La unidad también podrá <b>soltar</"
"b> el barril para que otra unidad lo recoja o <b>activar</b> una carga en el "
"lugar. Una vez que un barril se despliega, <b>destruirá</b> todo en un radio "
"de una casilla al inicio del próximo turno del primer jugador, por lo que "
"debes asegurarte de que tu unidad tenga suficientes puntos de movimiento "
"para alejarse antes de desplegarlo.\n"
"\n"
"Las unidades pierden la habilidad Demolición al soltar o desplegar los "
"barriles.\n"
"\n"
"¡Usa estos barriles con sabiduría! Empiezas con un número limitado y "
"necesitas al menos <b>seis</b> para completar el objetivo principal."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1226
msgid ""
"Deploying these explosives so close to your encampment would be an "
"incredibly ill-advised idea!"
msgstr ""
"¡Desplegar estos explosivos tan cerca de tu campamento sería una idea "
"increíblemente imprudente!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1249
msgid ""
"That is not an appropriate location for deploying these explosives. Try "
"elsewhere."
msgstr ""
"Ese no es un lugar adecuado para desplegar estos explosivos. Intenta en otro "
"sitio."

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_siege_charge_deploy
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1331
msgid "Deploy Charge"
msgstr "Desplegar carga"

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_siege_charge_drop
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1356
msgid "Drop Charge"
msgstr "Soltar carga"

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Elynia.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1471
msgid ""
"elynia^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield "
"carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether "
"your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"The thought of leaving this world with yet another explosion is inviting at "
"this point, but you have been through that in three different occasions "
"already, and survived to get this far. What would the point be? Perhaps Anya "
"is right, and there is still much more left to do before your time comes. "
"You want to find that demoness in the Pass of Sorrows first, after all."
msgstr ""
"elynia^Consideras en silencio la posibilidad de lanzarte al campo de batalla "
"cargando tú sola este pesado barril de explosivos. Te preguntas si tus "
"compañeros verían tu acción como heroica o insensata.\n"
"\n"
"La idea de abandonar este mundo en medio de otra explosión resulta tentadora "
"a estas alturas, pero ya has pasado por eso en tres ocasiones distintas y "
"has sobrevivido para llegar hasta aquí. ¿Cuál sería el sentido? Quizás Anya "
"tenga razón y aún quede mucho por hacer antes de que llegue tu hora. Después "
"de todo, quieres encontrar a esa demonio en el Paso de las Penas primero."

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Anya.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1479
msgid ""
"anya^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield "
"carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether "
"your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"That sure was a silly thought to entertain! But your hope has not waned just "
"yet, and Elynia needs your help. You are determined to stay at her side "
"until it is all over. She is all you have left, and perhaps more than you "
"will ever have."
msgstr ""
"anya^Consideras en silencio la posibilidad de lanzarte al campo de batalla "
"cargando tú sola este pesado barril de explosivos. Te preguntas si tus "
"compañeros verían tu acción como heroica o insensata.\n"
"\n"
"¡Vaya pensamiento tan tonto! Pero tu esperanza aún no se ha apagado, y "
"Elynia necesita tu ayuda. Estás decidida a permanecer a su lado hasta que "
"todo termine. Ella es todo lo que te queda, y quizá más de lo que alguna vez "
"tendrás."

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Kyara.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1487
msgid ""
"kyara^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield "
"carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether "
"your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"That pointless exercise of thought promptly leaves way for recalling the "
"stories of your people’s arrival to Quenoth Isle. Many say they were "
"assisted in their journey by dwarves, underground dwellers with an "
"inclination to devise this kind of evil artifact. You decide it may be for "
"the best that a civilization with such destructive potential confined itself "
"to the caverns beneath the surface."
msgstr ""
"kyara^Consideras en silencio la posibilidad de lanzarte al campo de batalla "
"cargando tú sola este pesado barril de explosivos. Te preguntas si tus "
"compañeros verían tu acción como heroica o insensata.\n"
"\n"
"Este ejercicio mental inútil pronto da paso a los recuerdos de las historias "
"sobre la llegada de tu pueblo a la Isla Quenoth. Muchos dicen que fueron "
"asistidos en su travesía por enanos, habitantes del subsuelo con una "
"inclinación por idear este tipo de artefactos malignos. Decides que quizá es "
"lo mejor que una civilización con tal potencial destructivo se haya "
"confinado en las cavernas bajo la superficie."

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Durvan.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1495
msgid ""
"durvan^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield "
"carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether "
"your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"But you would not be caught dead carrying such dangerous materials. As "
"everyone knows, your craft is hunting prey; you ain’t anybody’s transport "
"man."
msgstr ""
"durvan^Consideras en silencio la posibilidad de lanzarte al campo de batalla "
"cargando tú solo este pesado barril de explosivos. Te preguntas si tus "
"compañeros verían tu acción como heroica o insensata.\n"
"\n"
"Pero ni muerto te verían cargando un material tan peligroso. Como todos "
"saben, lo tuyo es cazar presas; no eres el transportista de nadie."

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Igor.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1503
msgid ""
"igor^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield "
"carrying this heavy barrel of “boom” artifacts all by yourself. You wonder "
"whether Elynia and her new friends would regard your action as heroic or "
"foolish.\n"
"\n"
"Upon further thought, however, you realize that giving up on the peaceful "
"street perform life to become fireworks goblin is probably not quite what "
"people mean when they talk about “going out with a bang”. Not to mention you "
"could not possibly bring yourself to leaving poor Willow alone in this "
"nasty, cruel world. Perhaps you will look into procuring a safer source of "
"“boom” at a later time, you think to yourself — something like one of those "
"fire sticks that high-ranked Chaos officers carry around these days. Your "
"mighty steed gives you an approving nod."
msgstr ""
"igor^Consideras en silencio la posibilidad de lanzarte al campo de batalla "
"cargando tú solo este pesado barril de artefactos \"¡bum!\". Te preguntas si "
"Elynia y sus nuevos amigos verían tu acción como heroica o insensata.\n"
"\n"
"Tras pensarlo mejor, te das cuenta de que abandonar la vida pacífica de "
"artista callejero para convertirte en un goblin pirotécnico probablemente no "
"es lo que la gente quiere decir con \"salir con un estallido\". Sin "
"mencionar que no podrías dejar a la pobre Willow sola en este mundo tan "
"cruel y desagradable. Quizá deberías buscar una fuente más segura de \"¡bum!"
"\" en otro momento, piensas — algo como esos palos de fuego que llevan los "
"oficiales de alto rango del Caos. Tu poderoso corcel te asiente con "
"aprobación."

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is the General Bardyl.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1511
msgid ""
"bardyl^You contemplate one of the barrels of explosives your superiors sent "
"from Fort Rylgur before the Far North fell to those infernal bastards. You "
"feel glad that you are not one of the poor nameless soldiers who were "
"charged with the task of carrying these to Aran-Balgur’s main keep!"
msgstr ""
"bardyl^Contemplas uno de los barriles de explosivos que tus superiores "
"enviaron desde el Fuerte Rylgur antes de que el Lejano Norte cayera ante "
"esos bastardos infernales. ¡Te alegra no ser uno de los pobres soldados sin "
"nombre encargados de llevarlos hasta la fortaleza principal de Aran-Balgur!"

#. [then]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up a barrel
#. is one of the other female heroines.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1519
msgid ""
"female^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield "
"carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether "
"your comrades would regard your actions as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, you are not so stupid as to attempt such a pointless move now."
msgstr ""
"Consideras en silencio la posibilidad de lanzarte al campo de batalla "
"cargando tú sola este pesado barril de explosivos. Te preguntas si tus "
"compañeros verían tu acción como heroica o insensata.\n"
"\n"
"En cualquier caso, no eres tan estúpida como para intentar un movimiento tan "
"inútil ahora."

#. [else]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up a barrel
#. is one of the other male heroes.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1526
msgid ""
"You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield "
"carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether "
"your comrades would regard your actions as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, you are not so stupid as to attempt such a pointless move now."
msgstr ""
"Consideras en silencio la posibilidad de lanzarte al campo de batalla "
"cargando tú solo este pesado barril de explosivos. Te preguntas si tus "
"compañeros verían tu acción como heroica o insensata.\n"
"\n"
"En cualquier caso, no eres tan estúpido como para intentar un movimiento tan "
"inútil ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1574
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The unit you have chosen for this task is not able to lift the weight! Try "
"another unit."
msgstr ""
"¡La unidad que has elegido para esta tarea no puede levantar el peso! "
"Intenta con otra unidad."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1589
msgid "Should this unit carry the barrel of explosives?"
msgstr "¿Debería esta unidad cargar el barril de explosivos?"

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1591
msgid "Yes, pick up the barrel."
msgstr "Sí, tomar el barril."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1601
msgid ""
"To drop or deploy the charge, right-click on the unit and choose the desired "
"option from the context menu."
msgstr ""
"Para soltar o desplegar la carga, haz clic derecho sobre la unidad y elige "
"la opción deseada en el menú contextual."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1608
msgid "No, let someone else do it."
msgstr "No, que lo haga otra unidad."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1641
msgid "You cannot carry more than one barrel at once!"
msgstr "¡No puedes cargar más de un barril a la vez!"

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1848
msgid ""
"Blast it, we have wasted our explosives on the battlefield instead of saving "
"them for the main keep! We can’t continue like this — retreat!"
msgstr ""
"¡Maldición, hemos desperdiciado nuestros explosivos en el campo de batalla "
"en vez de guardarlos para la fortaleza principal! ¡No podemos continuar así, "
"retirada!"

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2030
msgid ""
"Destroy that enormous monster before it gets a chance to rain its fire upon "
"our troops!"
msgstr ""
"¡Destruyan a ese enorme monstruo antes de que tenga la oportunidad de llover "
"fuego sobre nuestras tropas!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2058
#, fuzzy
msgid "Custodian of Aran-Balgur"
msgstr "Aran-Balgur"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2058
msgid "Protector of the Chaos Stronghold"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2282
msgid "But... how?"
msgstr "Pero... ¿cómo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2287
msgid ""
"Shapeshifters. They are somewhat different to other demons in that the more "
"mature individuals are much harder to kill without arcane magic than the "
"rest. (<i>disgusted</i>) It’s said they are basically extinct, but some "
"demon lords still keep them as slaves."
msgstr ""
"Cambiaformas. Son algo diferentes de otros demonios, ya que los individuos "
"más maduros son mucho más difíciles de matar sin magia arcana que el resto. "
"(<i>disgustada</i>) Se dice que están básicamente extintos, pero algunos "
"señores demoníacos todavía los mantienen como esclavos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2292
msgid "How do you know that?"
msgstr "¿Cómo sabes eso?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2297
msgid "Well, Elorran did tell me a lot of things about them..."
msgstr "Bueno, Elorran me contó muchas cosas sobre ellos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2306
msgid ""
"(<i>muttering to herself, aside</i>) ... mainly because I am one of them."
msgstr ""
"(<i>murmurando para sí misma, aparte</i>) ... principalmente porque soy una "
"de ellos."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2319
msgid "Battle goblin strikes again, yes! Take that, wretched scum!!!"
msgstr ""
"¡El goblin de batalla ataca de nuevo, sí! ¡Tomen eso, escoria miserable!"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2324
msgid ""
"He’s got an endearing quality to him most of the time, but I’m still not "
"quite sure whether I <i>should</i> be concerned about his more bloodthirsty "
"side...?"
msgstr ""
"Tiene un lado entrañable la mayor parte del tiempo, pero todavía no estoy "
"del todo seguro de si <i>debería</i> preocuparme por su faceta más sedienta "
"de sangre..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2329
msgid ""
"Nah, I think he’s all right. You too have your moments despite being cute "
"most of the time, after all."
msgstr ""
"Nah, creo que está bien. Tú también tienes tus momentos a pesar de ser "
"adorable casi siempre."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2334
msgid "<i>(blushing)</i> Well... thanks, I guess."
msgstr "<i>(sonrojándose)</i> Bueno... gracias, supongo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2356
msgid "Finally, that thing was a real nuisance."
msgstr "Por fin, esa cosa fue una verdadera molestia."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2369
msgid "Are you leaving now, Elynia?"
msgstr "¿Te vas ahora, Elynia?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2374
msgid "Well..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2376
msgid "Yes, I think it is the right time."
msgstr "Sí, creo que es el momento adecuado."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2380
msgid "All right, then."
msgstr "Está bien, entonces."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2387
msgid "No. Our allies still need our help."
msgstr "No. Nuestros aliados aún necesitan nuestra ayuda."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2391
msgid ""
"As much as I dislike General Bardyl and his people, we wouldn’t have "
"achieved this victory without them. I think it’s best to assist them until "
"the battle is over. But I’ll keep the portal in mind if things don’t go as "
"planned later."
msgstr ""
"Por mucho que me desagrade el general Bardyl y su gente, no habríamos "
"logrado esta victoria sin ellos. Creo que es mejor ayudarlos hasta que la "
"batalla termine. Pero tendré en cuenta el portal si las cosas no salen como "
"planeamos más adelante."

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_leave_battle
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2396
msgid "Leave Battle"
msgstr "Abandonar la batalla"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2436
msgid ""
"If you change your mind later, you can choose the <b>Leave Battle</b> option "
"in the context menu by right-clicking on any unit or vacant hex."
msgstr ""
"Si cambias de opinión más tarde, puedes elegir la opción <b>Abandonar "
"Batalla</b> en el menú contextual haciendo clic derecho sobre cualquier "
"unidad o hexágono vacío."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2447
msgid "Do you really wish to leave the battle?"
msgstr "¿Realmente deseas abandonar la batalla?"

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2450
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3580
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3635
msgid "Yes."
msgstr "Sí."

#. [option]
#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2456
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3197
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3608
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3719
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:361
msgid "No."
msgstr "No."

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2519
msgid ""
"Call more reinforcements! We can’t afford to lose control of this region to "
"these wretches!"
msgstr ""
"¡Llama a más refuerzos! ¡No podemos permitir perder el control de esta "
"región ante estos desgraciados!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2540
msgid "Let us find that portal."
msgstr "Vamos a encontrar ese portal."

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:186
msgid "Gateway"
msgstr "Portal"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:168
msgid "I guess I have to admit I am hesitant to continue..."
msgstr "Supongo que debo admitir que dudo en continuar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:177
msgid ""
"He said it was a greater cause, after all. I fear that once we step into "
"this portal... We might never come back to these lands alive."
msgstr ""
"Dijo que era una causa mayor, después de todo. Temo que una vez que crucemos "
"este portal... quizá nunca volvamos a estas tierras con vida."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:182
msgid ""
"Why do you want to come, anyway? Haven’t all my decisions led to awful "
"disasters since we began? All our victories have been small in the grand "
"scheme of things, and many have died because of my desire for answers... and "
"revenge."
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué quieres venir, de todos modos? ¿No han llevado todas mis decisiones "
"a desastres terribles desde que empezamos? Todas nuestras victorias han sido "
"pequeñas en el gran esquema, y muchos han muerto por mi deseo de "
"respuestas... y venganza."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:209
msgid ""
"Elynia... While all that is true, you can’t deny you have helped us all do "
"more good than any of us alone could otherwise. No-one is perfect..."
msgstr ""
"Elynia... aunque todo eso sea cierto, no puedes negar que nos has ayudado a "
"hacer más bien del que cualquiera podría hacer solo. Nadie es perfecto..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:214
msgid "... not even gods, as it turns out."
msgstr "... ni siquiera los dioses, al parecer."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:223
msgid ""
"... But most importantly, we work as a team! I for one promise I won’t give "
"up in the face of danger."
msgstr ""
"... Pero lo más importante es que trabajamos en equipo. Yo, por mi parte, "
"prometo no rendirme ante el peligro."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:228
msgid "Neither will I, my lady!"
msgstr "¡Yo tampoco, mi señora!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:233
msgid "Yes, I know. Galas never gave up either..."
msgstr "Sí, lo sé. Galas tampoco se rindió jamás..."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:238
msgid "Nor did Mal Keshar."
msgstr "Ni Mal Keshar."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:243
msgid "... That is true... too true."
msgstr "... Eso es cierto... demasiado cierto."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:252
msgid ""
"I understand that you won’t be joining us in this suicidal mission, Durvan, "
"so... What will you do?"
msgstr ""
"Entiendo que no te unirás a nosotros en esta misión suicida, Durvan, así "
"que... ¿Qué harás?"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:257
msgid ""
"Eh, I will just stay safe and sound here and help defend the castle until I "
"find a way to return home. Maybe try to convince that general or Lord "
"Torancyn—"
msgstr ""
"Eh, me quedaré aquí a salvo y ayudaré a defender el castillo hasta encontrar "
"la manera de volver a casa. Quizá trate de convencer a ese general o al Lord "
"Torancyn—"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:262
msgid "<i>Supreme</i> Lord Torancyn. (<i>snickers</i>)"
msgstr "<i>Supremo</i> Lord Torancyn. (<i>se ríe)</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:267
msgid ""
"... They might be willing to send someone to check the situation in Kalari "
"if you can secure the portal from the other side."
msgstr ""
"... Podrían estar dispuestos a enviar a alguien a revisar la situación en "
"Kalari si puedes asegurar el portal desde el otro lado."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:275
msgid ""
"I hope that is the case, yes. Bardyl seemed rather grateful for our "
"assistance at the end of the day."
msgstr ""
"Espero que sea así, sí. Bardyl pareció bastante agradecido por nuestra ayuda "
"al final del día."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:281
msgid ""
"I doubt Bardyl will understand that I simply could not tarry here for longer "
"than strictly necessary, especially since ‘my’ little band failed to live up "
"to his expectations. And Torancyn... I wouldn’t bet on his support at this "
"point."
msgstr ""
"Dudo que Bardyl entienda que simplemente no podía quedarme aquí más tiempo "
"del estrictamente necesario, especialmente porque ‘mi’ pequeño grupo no "
"cumplió con sus expectativas. Y Torancyn... no apostaría por su apoyo en "
"este momento."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:288
msgid ""
"Many of our men seem willing to follow you. I just don’t know what their "
"motivation is — money, bloodshed, adventure? It’s rather strange, really. "
"But I’m sure you could use their help."
msgstr ""
"Muchos de nuestros hombres parecen dispuestos a seguirte. No sé cuál es su "
"motivación: ¿dinero, derramamiento de sangre, aventura? Es bastante extraño, "
"en verdad. Pero estoy seguro de que podrías usar su ayuda."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:293
msgid "What will you do, Horo, Kyara?"
msgstr "¿Qué harán ustedes, Horo, Kyara?"

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:298
msgid ""
"Well, returning home is out of the question for me with Tirigaz gone. Those "
"vermin will surely head back here as soon as they hear of our victory, "
"presumably led by that hideous demon midget... Right now, there’d be nothing "
"more satisfying for me than breaking his stumpy neck and wearing his hollow "
"skull as a helmet."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, regresar a casa está fuera de cuestión para mí con Tirigaz "
"desaparecido. Esos alimañas seguramente volverán aquí tan pronto sepan de "
"nuestra victoria, presumiblemente liderados por ese horrible enano "
"demonio... Ahora mismo, nada me satisfaría más que romperle el cuello a ese "
"chaparro y usar su cráneo hueco como casco."

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:303
msgid ""
"As soon as I may, I’m returning to Quenoth Isle to spread the word about all "
"these events... Perhaps, if the war comes to an end first, we could even "
"send some people back here, to trade with the humans and orcs... I know "
"that’s all very unlikely with the current state of things, but... "
"(<i>shrugs</i>) dreaming never hurt anybody."
msgstr ""
"Tan pronto pueda, regresaré a la Isla Quenoth para difundir lo sucedido... "
"Quizá, si la guerra termina antes, podríamos incluso enviar gente de vuelta "
"aquí para comerciar con humanos y orcos... Sé que es muy improbable con el "
"estado actual de las cosas, pero... (<i>se encoge de hombros</i>) soñar "
"nunca le hizo daño a nadie."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:312
msgid "I guess so..."
msgstr "Supongo que sí..."

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:321
msgid "Pass of Sorrows"
msgstr "Paso de las Penas"

#. [side]: type=Ancient Lich, id=Vissalen
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:110
msgid "Vissalen"
msgstr "Vissalen"

#. [side]: type=Ancient Lich, id=Algessel
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:147
msgid "Algessel"
msgstr "Algessel"

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:221
msgid "team_name^Unknown"
msgstr "Desconocidos"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:279
msgid "Explore around"
msgstr "Explorar alrededor"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:295
msgid ""
"There’s absolutely <i>nothing</i> hinting at this place having served as a "
"Chaos base of any sort in recent times. It’s completely deserted and ruined. "
"I fear we have been misled. We might not even be in Kalari for all I know."
msgstr ""
"No hay absolutamente <i>nada</i> que indique que este lugar haya servido "
"como base del Caos en tiempos recientes. Está completamente desierto y en "
"ruinas. Temo que nos hayan engañado. Quizás ni siquiera estemos en Kalari, "
"por lo que sé."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:300
msgid ""
"No. I recognize that mountain range to the south. We... we never saw what "
"lay north of it. We are a little farther from Kalari than I expected, but "
"it’s not like any of us—or our allies—knew exactly where the Pass of Sorrows "
"is. Let us proceed south, carefully."
msgstr ""
"No. Reconozco esa cadena montañosa al sur. Nosotros... nunca vimos lo que "
"había al norte de ella. Estamos un poco más lejos de Kalari de lo que "
"esperaba, pero ninguno de nosotros —ni nuestros aliados— sabía exactamente "
"dónde está el Paso de las Penas. Avancemos al sur, con cuidado."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:314
msgid ""
"Igor, do you think you could help watch our backline for any potential "
"attacks from the north?"
msgstr ""
"Igor, ¿crees que podrías ayudar a vigilar nuestra retaguardia por si hay "
"ataques desde el norte?"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:319
msgid "Awww, but I wanted to help..."
msgstr "Awww, pero quería ayudar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:324
msgid ""
"I have seen that you prefer a more frontal approach to battle these days, "
"but right now my main concern is that we don’t get ambushed. You will still "
"be able to help by alerting us of any possible threats."
msgstr ""
"He visto que prefieres un enfoque más frontal en batalla últimamente, pero "
"ahora mismo me preocupa que no nos embosquen. Aún podrás ayudar alertándonos "
"de cualquier posible amenaza."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:329
msgid ""
"If you think that’s the best way I can help then I’ll do it, my lady. Let’s "
"go, Willow!"
msgstr ""
"Si crees que esa es la mejor forma en que puedo ayudar, entonces lo haré, mi "
"señora. ¡Vamos, Willow!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:347
msgid "The solitude of this place is unsettling."
msgstr "La soledad de este lugar es inquietante."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:368
msgid "Ugh. The fog is getting thicker..."
msgstr "Uf. La niebla se está espesando..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:430
msgid "Elynia, Irylean... you should see this."
msgstr "Elynia, Irylean... deberían ver esto."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:453
msgid ""
"These ruins appear to be centuries old — probably older than the Chaos "
"Empire itself. I imagine they have remained untouched by our enemies because "
"of their inconvenient location. What may have become of their former "
"denizens?"
msgstr ""
"Estas ruinas parecen tener siglos de antigüedad — probablemente más viejas "
"que el propio Imperio del Caos. Imagino que han permanecido intactas por "
"nuestros enemigos debido a su ubicación inconveniente. ¿Qué habrá sido de "
"sus antiguos habitantes?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:458
msgid "There’s a large monolith over there."
msgstr "Allí hay un gran monolito."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:493
msgid "Elynia should be the one to investigate this monolith."
msgstr "Elynia debería ser quien investigue este monolito."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:518
msgid ""
"I don’t understand this inscription — some glyphs vaguely resemble the "
"ancient ceremonial Elvish script, but I don’t recognize the rest."
msgstr ""
"No entiendo esta inscripción — algunos glifos se parecen vagamente a la "
"antigua escritura ceremonial élfica, pero no reconozco el resto."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:525
msgid "The wind blows."
msgstr "El viento sopla."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:530
msgid "Wait..."
msgstr "Espera..."

#. [message]: speaker=ruins ghost 4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:601
msgid "... Mal-Zagarn..."
msgstr "... Mal-Zagarn..."

#. [message]: speaker=ruins ghost 3
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:607
msgid "... come..."
msgstr "... ven..."

#. [message]: speaker=ruins ghost 2
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:613
msgid "... she..."
msgstr "... ella..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:622
msgid "Wh— What’s going on?"
msgstr "¿Q-Qué está pasando?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:627
msgid "This pass is inhabited by restless spirits of the past! My lady!"
msgstr ""
"¡Este paso está habitado por espíritus inquietos del pasado! ¡Mi señora!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:706
msgid ""
"There seem to be more undead creatures crawling out of the caverns to the "
"south. Perhaps if we can clear them out we’ll find a way out of this valley."
msgstr ""
"Parece que más criaturas no muertas salen arrastrándose de las cavernas al "
"sur. Quizás si las despejamos encontremos una salida de este valle."

#. [message]: speaker=Algessel
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:718
msgid "Thank... you..."
msgstr "Gra... cias..."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:740
msgid "The lich’s staff is glowing! What could it possibly mean?"
msgstr "¡El bastón del lich está brillando! ¿Qué podría significar eso?"

#. [message]: speaker=Vissalen
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:762
msgid "Free..."
msgstr "Libre..."

#. [message]: speaker=Vissalen
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:771
msgid "... at last..."
msgstr "... al fin..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. [message]: speaker=Ethealim
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:776
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:1486
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:1492
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:64
msgid "Who are you?"
msgstr "¿Quién eres?"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:808
msgid ""
"Many centuries ago, our ancestors came from the Great Southern Desert "
"seeking fertile lands to settle. They gave up much to get to this valley: "
"their lives, their families... Most of them died along the way. The few "
"survivors found a ruined temple amidst the mountains, probably built by an "
"extinct civilization. From that temple they learned the ways of fire magic, "
"and the song of Shardia, She who forged knowledge from the fire of our "
"hearts.\n"
"\n"
"They thrived with their newfound skills and the protection granted by the "
"precipitous mountain range. They continued to learn from Her, and longed for "
"the day when She would come to this earth and bless it with Her song. And in "
"time, so did we.\n"
"\n"
"Until..."
msgstr ""
"Hace muchos siglos, nuestros antepasados vinieron desde el Gran Desierto del "
"Sur buscando tierras fértiles para asentarse. Renunciaron a mucho para "
"llegar a este valle: sus vidas, sus familias... La mayoría murió en el "
"camino. Los pocos sobrevivientes encontraron un templo en ruinas entre las "
"montañas, probablemente construido por una civilización extinta. De ese "
"templo aprendieron las artes de la magia de fuego y la canción de Shardia, "
"Ella que forjó el conocimiento desde el fuego de nuestros corazones.\n"
"\n"
"Prosperaron con sus nuevas habilidades y la protección otorgada por la "
"escarpada cadena montañosa. Continuaron aprendiendo de Ella, y anhelaron el "
"día en que Ella viniera a esta tierra y la bendijera con Su canción. Y con "
"el tiempo, nosotros también.\n"
"\n"
"Hasta que..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:816
msgid ""
"One day, a man shrouded in darkness came. His eyes were bright like Naia’s "
"never-ending shine; his mouth, concealed by twisted metal and decayed flesh. "
"His companions called him Mal-Zagarn.\n"
"\n"
"He spoke a message from the so-called Goddess of Life from beyond the Void, "
"Uria, who had tasked him with the mission of spreading her voice to all non-"
"believers in this land. But other than the Goddess who gave us our fire "
"magic, we would worship no-one, especially not someone who only communicated "
"through an embodiment of the unnatural like that dark prophet. And so we "
"dismissed his words as the blasphemous ramblings of a barbarian.\n"
"\n"
"In time, we would be proven wrong."
msgstr ""
"Un día, llegó un hombre envuelto en oscuridad. Sus ojos brillaban como el "
"resplandor interminable de Naia; su boca, oculta tras metal retorcido y "
"carne putrefacta. Sus compañeros lo llamaban Mal-Zagarn.\n"
"\n"
"Él transmitía un mensaje de la llamada Diosa de la Vida desde más allá del "
"Vacío, Uria, que le había encomendado la misión de difundir su voz a todos "
"los incrédulos en esta tierra. Pero excepto la Diosa que nos dio nuestra "
"magia de fuego, no adoraríamos a nadie, especialmente a alguien que sólo se "
"comunicaba a través de una encarnación de lo antinatural como aquel oscuro "
"profeta. Por eso desestimamos sus palabras como los blasfemos delirios de un "
"bárbaro.\n"
"\n"
"Con el tiempo, nos demostrarían que estábamos equivocados."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:822
msgid ""
"Years later, the man returned, but not with a handful of trusted followers. "
"Instead, he brought with him innumerable horrors from the Abyss to rain acid "
"and smoke upon our homes. He gave our leader a last chance to convert to his "
"unholy sect.\n"
"\n"
"That is to say, <b>I</b> was offered that last chance.\n"
"\n"
"Everyone was slaughtered. Everyone except me, my brother, and a child with "
"beautiful hair, whom we believed was the heiress of Her fire; for never "
"before we saw one of our own be born with the same hair color as our "
"Goddess. But just like the scrolls and books we hoarded, we eventually lost "
"her to the walking vultures of the desert, who took her as their own. They "
"spared her life, seeing as she was but a child, but our own fate was vastly "
"different."
msgstr ""
"Años después, el hombre regresó, pero no con un puñado de seguidores fieles. "
"En cambio, trajo innumerables horrores del Abismo para llover ácido y humo "
"sobre nuestros hogares. Dio a nuestro líder una última oportunidad para "
"convertirse a su secta impía.\n"
"\n"
"Es decir, a <b>mí</b> se me ofreció esa última oportunidad.\n"
"\n"
"Todos fueron masacrados. Todos excepto yo, mi hermano y una niña de hermoso "
"cabello, a quien creíamos heredera de Su fuego; pues nunca antes habíamos "
"visto a uno de los nuestros nacer con el mismo color de cabello que nuestra "
"Diosa. Pero al igual que los pergaminos y libros que acumulamos, finalmente "
"la perdimos ante los buitres ambulantes del desierto, que la tomaron como "
"propia. Le perdonaron la vida, al ser apenas una niña, pero nuestro destino "
"fue muy distinto."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:828
msgid ""
"The Goddess of Life had cursed us to linger in this form, and dwell in the "
"caves beneath the earth in shame. The light of the suns we once revered "
"became a scorching enemy by day. Our fire magic was quickly displaced by "
"shadow magic as we could no longer even withstand the heat of our flames. We "
"had too become embodiments of corruption, a mockery of the beings we once "
"were.\n"
"\n"
"We vowed to take revenge upon the dark courier who brought disgrace upon our "
"kind, and anyone who was ever close to him or his followers. Either we would "
"be destroyed and released from our prison, or our curse would be extended to "
"the creatures we abhorred.\n"
"\n"
"But it is all over now."
msgstr ""
"La Diosa de la Vida nos maldijo para permanecer en esta forma y habitar las "
"cuevas bajo la tierra con vergüenza. La luz de los soles que una vez "
"reverenciamos se convirtió en un enemigo abrasador durante el día. Nuestra "
"magia de fuego fue rápidamente desplazada por la magia de las sombras, pues "
"ya no podíamos soportar ni el calor de nuestras propias llamas. También nos "
"habíamos convertido en encarnaciones de la corrupción, una burla de los "
"seres que fuimos.\n"
"\n"
"Juramos vengarnos del oscuro mensajero que trajo la desgracia a nuestra "
"raza, y de cualquiera que estuviera cerca de él o sus seguidores. O seríamos "
"destruidos y liberados de nuestra prisión, o nuestra maldición se extendería "
"a las criaturas que aborrecíamos.\n"
"\n"
"Pero todo terminó ya."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:834
msgid ""
"We may still be able to find Her on the other side of the Veil, and bask in "
"the glory of Her song..."
msgstr ""
"Quizás todavía podamos encontrarla al otro lado del Velo y deleitarnos con "
"la gloria de Su canción..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:864
msgid "Argan..."
msgstr "Argan..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:873
msgid "Elynia..."
msgstr "Elynia..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:878
msgid "I— I am fine. Don’t worry about it."
msgstr "E— Estoy bien. No te preocupes."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:947
msgid "Proceed to the southern cavern exit with Elynia"
msgstr "Lleva a Elynia hasta la salida sur de la caverna"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:973
msgid ""
"We don’t know what lies outside. Are you sure you want to proceed, my lady?"
msgstr ""
"No sabemos lo que hay fuera. ¿Está segura de que quiere continuar, mi señora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:978
msgid "Allow me to ponder this for a moment..."
msgstr "Permítanme reflexionar un momento..."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:980
msgid "Yes, I think it’s time to go."
msgstr "Sí, creo que es hora de irnos."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:986
msgid ""
"No, let us see whether there might be something else of value in these caves "
"first."
msgstr "No, veamos primero si hay algo más de valor en estas cavernas."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:990
msgid "Very well."
msgstr "Muy bien."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1091
msgid "A lone troll?"
msgstr "¿Un troll solitario?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1098
msgid "He bears an unusual sigil on his armor for a troll..."
msgstr "Lleva un sigilo inusual en su armadura para un troll..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1109
msgid "Hail there, whoever you are. Are you our enemy?"
msgstr "Saludos, sea quien seas. ¿Eres nuestro enemigo?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1119
msgid ""
"The old battle-hardened troll stared at the sky for a minute before "
"answering, while Anya and Irylean eyed each other nervously."
msgstr ""
"El viejo troll, curtido en batalla, miró al cielo durante un minuto antes de "
"responder, mientras Anya e Irylean se miraban con nerviosismo."

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1124
msgid "Cron works for no-one but the storm lady."
msgstr "Cron no trabaja para nadie salvo la dama de la tormenta."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1129
msgid "(<i>whispering</i>) Elynia, would that be..."
msgstr "(<i>susurrando</i>) Elynia, ¿sería ella...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1134
msgid "(<i>whispering</i>) Yes, I think so."
msgstr "(<i>susurrando</i>) Sí, eso creo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1139
msgid ""
"Cron, if you allow me to ask, where is this person? We... may or may not "
"have arranged a meeting with her, here. This is a quite urgent matter, "
"and... Are you even listening to me?"
msgstr ""
"Cron, si me permite preguntar, ¿dónde está esta persona? Nosotros... puede "
"que hayamos concertado o no una reunión con ella, aquí. Es un asunto "
"bastante urgente y... ¿me estás escuchando siquiera?"

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1144
msgid "(<i>pointing at the sky</i>) There."
msgstr "(<i>señalando al cielo</i>) Ahí."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1178
msgid ""
"The demoness descended from the sky in an impressive whirl of dust and "
"leaves. Anya and Irylean stared in awe, and immediately knew they would be "
"at a disadvantage if she were, in fact, their enemy. But Elynia did not have "
"an opportunity to entertain such thoughts. She could tell at first glance "
"that in spite of her young age, the Demon Lord of the Storms was not the "
"type that would take admiration and other displays of weakness very well.\n"
"\n"
"After all, she had risked it all and come only to enlist powerful allies for "
"her dwindling cause."
msgstr ""
"La demonio descendió del cielo en un impresionante torbellino de polvo y "
"hojas. Anya e Irylean la miraron con asombro y supieron de inmediato que "
"estarían en desventaja si ella, de hecho, fuera su enemiga. Pero Elynia no "
"tuvo oportunidad de entretener tales pensamientos. Supo a primera vista que, "
"a pesar de su juventud, la Señora Demoníaca de las Tormentas no era del tipo "
"que aceptara bien la admiración ni otras muestras de debilidad.\n"
"\n"
"Después de todo, lo había arriesgado todo y acudido únicamente para reclutar "
"aliados poderosos para su menguante causa."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1185
msgid ""
"(<i>whispering</i>) All right... I <i>think</i> these two look rather "
"frightening..."
msgstr ""
"(<i>susurrando</i>) Bien... <i>creo</i> que estos dos se ven bastante "
"aterradores..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1190
msgid "Ergea, Demon Lord of the Storms, I suppose?"
msgstr "Ergea, Señora Demoníaca de las Tormentas, ¿supongo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1195
msgid ""
"That is correct, Elynia, the Lady of Light. I have been eagerly awaiting "
"this moment for weeks. What took you and your party so long? I heard you "
"hired the services of the northerners to prepare an assault to the gateway "
"fortress, instead of infiltrating it on your own. That wasteful spectacle "
"could have ruined our plans."
msgstr ""
"Correcto, Elynia, Dama de la Luz. He estado esperando ansiosamente este "
"momento durante semanas. ¿Qué les tomó tanto tiempo a ti y a tu grupo? "
"Escuché que contrataste los servicios de los norteños para preparar un "
"asalto a la fortaleza de la puerta, en lugar de infiltrarte por tu cuenta. "
"Ese derroche de espectáculo pudo haber arruinado nuestros planes."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1200
msgid ""
"And your plans are intended to help us, or is this just part of a convoluted "
"scheme to catch me off-guard near your headquarters?"
msgstr ""
"¿Y tus planes están destinados a ayudarnos, o es esto solo parte de un "
"enrevesado plan para atraparme desprevenida cerca de tu cuartel?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1205
msgid ""
"My priority is putting a halt to Uria’s schemes, preferably while keeping "
"collateral damage to a minimum. There just are not a lot of people these "
"days who can truly be trusted. I had to ask the human seer to deliver my "
"message to you because sensing people’s intentions is not one of your "
"powers, and you have committed too many mistakes as of late in that vein, "
"much like Elorran."
msgstr ""
"Mi prioridad es detener los planes de Uria, preferiblemente manteniendo el "
"daño colateral al mínimo. Hoy en día no hay muchas personas en quienes se "
"pueda confiar verdaderamente. Tuve que pedirle al vidente humano que te "
"entregara mi mensaje porque percibir las intenciones de las personas no es "
"uno de tus poderes, y has cometido demasiados errores últimamente en ese "
"sentido, al igual que Elorran."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1210
msgid "Elorran...?"
msgstr "¿Elorran...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1215
msgid ""
"I tried to warn him that Zhangor sent his new pets after him, but that fool "
"never allowed my minions to approach him or his informants. I assume he "
"never told you that—"
msgstr ""
"Intenté advertirle que Zhangor envió a sus nuevas mascotas tras él, pero ese "
"necio nunca permitió que mis esbirros se acercaran a él ni a sus "
"informantes. Supongo que nunca te dijo eso—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1226
msgid "Repeat that name."
msgstr "Repite ese nombre."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1233
msgid "Zhangor?"
msgstr "¿Zhangor?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1238
msgid "How...?"
msgstr "¿Cómo...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1243
msgid ""
"He recently became the Fist of Uria. I thought Elorran and you of all people "
"on Irdya would be aware of this."
msgstr ""
"Recientemente se convirtió en el Puño de Uria. Pensé que Elorran y tú, de "
"entre todas las personas en Irdya, estarían al tanto de esto."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1252
msgid "Elynia? You don’t look good..."
msgstr "¿Elynia? No te ves bien..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1259
msgid ""
"Wh— why...? Why is he here? Why is he... on Irdya... again? I— I did "
"everything within my power to... to..."
msgstr ""
"¿P— por qué...? ¿Por qué está aquí? ¿Por qué está... en Irdya... otra vez? Y"
"— yo hice todo lo que estaba en mi poder para... para..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1264
msgid ""
"Destroying a shapeshifter of his level is nigh impossible; and frankly, you "
"never truly learned to employ the Power of the Union effectively. Argan and "
"you played around with it like children instead of working towards "
"harnessing its full potential. But I don’t blame you. There is a lot you "
"need to learn right now, and I can help you with that. However, we are "
"running out of time."
msgstr ""
"Destruir a un cambiaformas de su nivel es casi imposible; y francamente, "
"nunca aprendiste realmente a emplear el Poder de la Unión de manera "
"efectiva. Argan y tú lo usaron como niños jugando, en vez de trabajar para "
"aprovechar todo su potencial. Pero no te culpo. Hay mucho que necesitas "
"aprender ahora, y puedo ayudarte con eso. Sin embargo, se nos acaba el "
"tiempo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1269
msgid "Will you help me?"
msgstr "¿Me ayudarás?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1274
msgid ""
"I came to seek your help only because our goals converge on the ultimate "
"purpose of ending this war. I can only help you if you are willing to help "
"us — and first I need to speak to you in private."
msgstr ""
"Vine a buscar tu ayuda solo porque nuestros objetivos coinciden en el "
"propósito final de acabar con esta guerra. Solo puedo ayudarte si estás "
"dispuesta a ayudarnos — y primero necesito hablar contigo en privado."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1283
msgid "... Very well."
msgstr "... Está bien."

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:331
msgid "Divergence"
msgstr "Divergencia"

#. [scenario]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:49
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr "Objetivo:"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:107
msgid "Talk to Anya before going to sleep"
msgstr "Hablar con Anya antes de dormir"

#. [trait]: id=staff_of_akhlys_lvl1_tag
#. [effect]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:137
#: After_the_Storm/macros/items.cfg:395
msgid "staff of akhlys"
msgstr "bastón de Akhlys"

#. [trait]: id=staff_of_akhlys_lvl1_tag
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:138
msgid "Immune to poison"
msgstr "Inmune al veneno"

#. [trait]: id=staff_of_akhlys_lvl1_tag
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:139
msgid "The wielder of this staff is immune to poison."
msgstr "El portador de este bastón es inmune al veneno."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:293
msgid "Still awake? You haven’t slept well in months."
msgstr "¿Sigues despierta? No has dormido bien en meses."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:298
msgid ""
"I just can’t get to sleep knowing that we are in this land, Anya — it brings "
"back bad memories."
msgstr ""
"Simplemente no puedo dormir sabiendo que estamos en estas tierras, Anya; me "
"trae malos recuerdos."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:303
msgid "I understand."
msgstr "Lo entiendo."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:313
msgid "Discuss your plans with Anya."
msgstr "Hablar sobre tus planes con Anya."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:316
msgid "Speak to Anya about Ergea."
msgstr "Hablar con Anya sobre Ergea."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:319
msgid "Ask Anya a question."
msgstr "Hacerle una pregunta a Anya."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:329
msgid ""
"I am still worried about tomorrow. Ergea said reinforcements were coming for "
"us, but we have not gotten confirmation from Aran-Balgur and that damned "
"portal closed on its own. And regardless, it would be foolish to rely on "
"Bardyl and his people."
msgstr ""
"Sigo preocupada por lo que nos espera mañana. Ergea dijo que vendrían "
"refuerzos para nosotros, pero no hemos recibido confirmación de Aran-Balgur "
"y ese maldito portal se cerró solo. Y, aun así, sería una locura confiar en "
"Bardyl y su gente."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:334
msgid "We still have the undead, and surely Ergea wouldn’t lie to us?"
msgstr "Todavía tenemos a los no-muertos, ¿y acaso Ergea nos mentiría?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:339
msgid ""
"I suppose not, but her sources might not necessarily be the most reliable. "
"For all we know, they could have already betrayed her. They might be leading "
"us to a slaughter, and—"
msgstr ""
"Supongo que no, pero sus fuentes no necesariamente deben ser las más "
"fiables. Por lo que sabemos, ya podrían haberla traicionado. Podrían estar "
"llevándonos directo a una masacre, y—"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:344
msgid ""
"(<i>holding Elynia’s hand</i>) I am sure... that with Ergea’s power and "
"yours, we can do this. The bulk of their forces went north, the Triad is now "
"missing that disgusting lich... and we will be joined by those "
"reinforcements soon — I hope. And if we are meant to die here, then we’ll "
"all die fighting for a just cause."
msgstr ""
"(<i>sujetando la mano de Elynia</i>) Estoy segura... de que con el poder de "
"Ergea y el tuyo, podemos lograrlo. La mayor parte de sus fuerzas se fue al "
"norte, la Tríada ahora carece de ese repugnante liche... y pronto se nos "
"unirán esos refuerzos — espero. Y si estamos destinadas a morir aquí, "
"entonces moriremos luchando por una causa justa."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:349
msgid "... Well, yes..."
msgstr "... Bueno, sí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:354
msgid "But somehow, I feel that everything will go well!"
msgstr "¡Pero de algún modo, siento que todo saldrá bien!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. "Us" here being Anya and Irylean.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:362
msgid ""
"Elynia, what was it like talking to Ergea? She seemed quite, uh, "
"intimidating to us."
msgstr ""
"Elynia, ¿cómo fue hablar con Ergea? Ella nos pareció bastante... eh... "
"intimidante."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:367
msgid ""
"I got the impression that she’s simply been through too much in her life, "
"and it’s surely not her fault. From what I gather, Urvatha, the world we "
"usually call Inferno... is decidedly not the best place to live. Demon Lords "
"competing for succession and killing each other all the time, oppressing and "
"enslaving their subjects, and Uria coercing them into doing her bidding by "
"abusing the ancient powers she was granted by destiny... "
msgstr ""
"Tuve la impresión de que simplemente ha pasado por demasiado en su vida, y "
"ciertamente no es su culpa. Por lo que entiendo, Urvatha, el mundo que "
"solemos llamar Infierno... no es precisamente el mejor lugar para vivir. "
"Señores Demoníacos compitiendo por la sucesión y matándose entre sí todo el "
"tiempo, oprimiendo y esclavizando a sus súbditos, y Uria obligándolos a "
"cumplir sus órdenes abusando de los poderes antiguos que le concedió el "
"destino..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:372
msgid ""
"I can only say that Ergea is a much nicer person in reality if you know how "
"to approach her."
msgstr ""
"Solo puedo decir que Ergea es una persona mucho más agradable en realidad si "
"sabes cómo acercarte a ella."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:377
msgid ""
"Hm. (<i>smiling</i>) I guess you would have enjoyed talking with Elorran, "
"too."
msgstr ""
"Hm. (<i>sonriendo</i>) Supongo que también te habría gustado hablar con "
"Elorran."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:382
msgid "I guess."
msgstr "Supongo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:389
msgid "So, why did you not tell us that you were a shapeshifter?"
msgstr "Entonces, ¿por qué no nos dijiste que eras una cambiaformas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:398
msgid "(<i>surprised</i>) I... What are you talking about?"
msgstr "(<i>sorprendida</i>) Yo... ¿De qué hablas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:403
msgid ""
"I did hear your quiet remark when we were fighting those creatures in Aran-"
"Balgur. Having spent a considerable part of my life in the wild, did you "
"expect any less? I imagine your sense of hearing is just as good despite "
"your smaller ears."
msgstr ""
"Escuché tu comentario en voz baja cuando luchábamos contra esas criaturas en "
"Aran-Balgur. Habiendo pasado una parte considerable de mi vida en la "
"naturaleza, ¿esperabas menos de mí? Imagino que tu oído es igual de agudo a "
"pesar de tus orejas más pequeñas."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:408
msgid ""
"Well... I... I think I have never felt comfortable with my heritage. After "
"all... it is the very reason of my abandonment as a child..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno... yo... creo que nunca me he sentido cómoda con mi herencia. Después "
"de todo... es precisamente la razón por la que me abandonaron cuando era "
"niña..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:413
msgid ""
"I can only wonder why I wasn’t raised by my real parents. Who were they? "
"Could they still be out there, alive? But on second thought... perhaps I "
"don’t want to know."
msgstr ""
"Solo puedo preguntarme por qué no me criaron mis verdaderos padres. ¿Quiénes "
"eran? ¿Podrían estar todavía ahí afuera, vivos? Pero pensándolo mejor... "
"quizás no quiero saberlo."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:418
msgid ""
"If I had told you from the very beginning that I am a shapeshifter, you "
"would have never trusted me. How can you trust a creature who could be "
"concealing their true appearance and nature?"
msgstr ""
"Si te lo hubiera dicho desde el principio, que soy una cambiaformas, nunca "
"me habrías confiado nada. ¿Cómo puedes confiar en una criatura que podría "
"estar ocultando su verdadera apariencia y naturaleza?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:423
msgid "Are you, though?"
msgstr "¿Lo haces, acaso?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. 'We' being demonkind.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:429
msgid ""
"No! But that doesn’t change the fact that you would have distrusted me back "
"then! I mean... more than you did. You were always so distant and obsessed "
"with your duty... almost like an emotionless machine, just like you have "
"always assumed <i>we</i> were..."
msgstr ""
"¡No! Pero eso no cambia el hecho de que me habrías desconfiado en ese "
"entonces. Quiero decir... más de lo que ya lo hacías. Siempre fuiste tan "
"distante y obsesionada con tu deber... casi como una máquina sin emociones, "
"tal y como siempre asumiste que <i>nosotros</i> éramos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:434
msgid ""
"<i>(sighs)</i> I guess I still am. You could call it a coping mechanism, I "
"suppose. I originally became a druid to help others, not to take people’s "
"lives. All this bloodshed... it could have been avoided if I hadn’t made all "
"the terrible choices that led me here — the same choices that led to the "
"downfall of this world. Nobody in this era would remember, but I am in large "
"part responsible for bringing the people who ultimately doomed us all to the "
"throne of Wesnoth."
msgstr ""
"<i>(suspira)</i> Supongo que todavía lo soy. Podrías llamarlo un mecanismo "
"de defensa, supongo. Originalmente me convertí en druida para ayudar a los "
"demás, no para arrebatar vidas. Todo este derramamiento de sangre... podría "
"haberse evitado si no hubiera tomado todas las terribles decisiones que me "
"trajeron hasta aquí — las mismas decisiones que llevaron a la caída de este "
"mundo. Nadie en esta era lo recordaría, pero soy en gran parte responsable "
"de poner en el trono de Wesnoth a las personas que finalmente condenaron a "
"todos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:439
msgid ""
"When you are forced to live through the consequences of your mistakes, when "
"it’s not in your nature to kill but you have no choice... you begin to put "
"reality aside just to keep yourself in one piece. Instead of being the one "
"doing the killing, you are watching someone else do it for you. Sometimes it "
"may even seem like an enticing distraction from your own thoughts."
msgstr ""
"Cuando te ves obligada a vivir las consecuencias de tus errores, cuando no "
"está en tu naturaleza matar pero no tienes otra opción... empiezas a apartar "
"la realidad solo para mantenerte entera. En lugar de ser tú quien mata, "
"observas a alguien más hacerlo por ti. A veces incluso puede parecer una "
"distracción tentadora de tus propios pensamientos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:444
msgid ""
"Other people recall good memories to comfort themselves in times like these, "
"but each day that passes I struggle more and more to remember anything other "
"than my worst moments: the utter destruction of an era of balance and life, "
"the fall of my people, the horrors wrought by Zhangor... the blood of my "
"husband, in my own hands and drawn with my own power... and my... friends... "
"killed or destroyed in front of me... before I could do... do anything to "
"prevent it..."
msgstr ""
"Otras personas evocan buenos recuerdos para consolarse en momentos como "
"estos, pero con cada día que pasa me cuesta más y más recordar algo que no "
"sean mis peores momentos: la completa destrucción de una era de equilibrio y "
"vida, la caída de mi pueblo, los horrores causados por Zhangor... la sangre "
"de mi esposo, en mis propias manos y derramada con mi propio poder... y "
"mis... amigos... asesinados o destruidos frente a mí... antes de que pudiera "
"hacer... hacer algo para evitarlo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:453
msgid ""
"... I fear it, Anya... I fear what would happen if I allowed myself to be "
"controlled by my emotions."
msgstr ""
"... Lo temo, Anya... Temo lo que pasaría si me dejara llevar por mis "
"emociones."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:462
msgid "Elynia... I’m sorry, I did not mean to make you feel like this."
msgstr "Elynia... Lo siento, no quise hacerte sentir así."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:471
msgid ""
"... No, I am the one who should apologize. Perhaps if I shared my feelings "
"with other people more often, I— I wouldn’t be like this..."
msgstr ""
"... No, soy yo quien debería disculparse. Quizás si compartiera mis "
"sentimientos con los demás más a menudo, yo... yo no estaría así..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:476
msgid ""
"I haven’t lived for a thousand years, but I know that it is true — you would "
"feel at least a little better if you talked to someone about whatever "
"troubles you instead of blindly killing creature after creature to distract "
"yourself from the pain."
msgstr ""
"No he vivido mil años, pero sé que es verdad: te sentirías al menos un poco "
"mejor si hablaras con alguien sobre lo que te atormenta, en lugar de matar "
"criatura tras criatura a ciegas para distraerte del dolor."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:481
msgid "Perhaps... you could do that? Talk with me more often?"
msgstr "Quizás... ¿podrías hacer eso? ¿Hablar conmigo más a menudo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:490
msgid "Yes, I could... If we survive this encounter, that is."
msgstr "Sí, podría... Si sobrevivimos a este encuentro, claro."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:495
msgid "But you must promise!"
msgstr "¡Pero debes prometerlo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:504
msgid "... I... I promise."
msgstr "... Yo... lo prometo."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:509
msgid "(<i>smiling</i>)"
msgstr "(<i>sonriendo</i>)"

#. [then]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:524
msgid ""
"Go back to sleep <small>(move Elynia back to the encampment keep)</small>"
msgstr ""
"Vuelve a dormir <small>(mueve a Elynia de regreso al torreón del "
"campamento)</small>"

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:540
msgid "Ask Cron about Ergea."
msgstr "Preguntar a Cron sobre Ergea."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:543
msgid "Ask Cron about tomorrow."
msgstr "Preguntar a Cron sobre el día de mañana."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:553
msgid ""
"If I may ask, for how long have you been serving under Ergea’s banner and "
"why?"
msgstr ""
"Si se me permite preguntar, ¿desde cuándo sirves bajo el estandarte de Ergea "
"y por qué?"

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:558
msgid ""
"Cron works for the storm lady since his home in the mountains was taken by "
"the flying metal-shells. He was promised things in return for protection."
msgstr ""
"Cron trabaja para la dama de la tormenta desde que su hogar en las montañas "
"fue tomado por las carcasas metálicas voladoras. Se le prometieron cosas a "
"cambio de protección."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:563
msgid "Protection?"
msgstr "¿Protección?"

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:568
msgid ""
"The storm lady does not trust the masked men and their rusty swords. She "
"prefers help from Cron and the lizard people of the swamps. She feels safer "
"this way."
msgstr ""
"La dama de la tormenta no confía en los hombres enmascarados y sus espadas "
"oxidadas. Prefiere la ayuda de Cron y de la gente lagarto de los pantanos. "
"Se siente más segura así."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:573
msgid "What kind of things did she promise to you?"
msgstr "¿Qué clase de cosas te prometió?"

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:578
msgid ""
"The lady promised us a new home if we can help her kill the Iron Council and "
"their leader, Zhangor."
msgstr ""
"La dama nos prometió un nuevo hogar si la ayudamos a eliminar al Consejo de "
"Hierro y a su líder, Zhangor."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:583
msgid ""
"Hm, is her intention to seize Kalari for her own people and allies then?"
msgstr ""
"Hm, ¿es su intención apoderarse de Kalari para su propia gente y aliados "
"entonces?"

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:588
msgid "Cron must not discuss the storm lady’s plans with anyone else."
msgstr ""
"Cron no debe hablar de los planes de la dama de la tormenta con nadie más."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:593
msgid "... Fair enough."
msgstr "... Está bien."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:600
msgid ""
"There’s a lot of things awaiting us tomorrow, and we will need all the help "
"we can get. Do you think your people will accede?"
msgstr ""
"Hay muchas cosas que nos esperan mañana y necesitaremos toda la ayuda "
"posible. ¿Crees que tu gente aceptará?"

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:605
msgid ""
"Cron is very sure they will, but they are not many, and they cannot help as "
"much as they want."
msgstr ""
"Cron está muy seguro de que lo harán, pero no son muchos y no pueden ayudar "
"tanto como quisieran."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:610
msgid ""
"A little help is better than nothing — Ergea said we would be getting "
"reinforcements, but I don’t find that likely to happen."
msgstr ""
"Un poco de ayuda es mejor que nada; Ergea dijo que recibiríamos refuerzos, "
"pero no creo que eso vaya a ocurrir."

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:615
msgid "The storm lady always says the truth."
msgstr "La dama de la tormenta siempre dice la verdad."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:620
msgid "Yes... that’s very true... Too true, perhaps."
msgstr "Sí... eso es muy cierto... Quizás demasiado cierto."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:640
msgid "Talk to Irylean."
msgstr "Hablar con Irylean."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:643
msgid "Ask Irylean about her retirement."
msgstr "Preguntar a Irylean sobre su retiro."

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:655
msgid "Ask Irylean about the Staff of Akhlys."
msgstr "Preguntar a Irylean sobre el Bastón de Akhlys."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:674
msgid "You seem very weary, my lady. Shouldn’t you be getting some sleep?"
msgstr "Pareces muy cansada, mi señora. ¿No deberías ir a dormir?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:679
msgid ""
"Yes... But you know the situation with that. So, do you think your disciples "
"will be able to help? Can they be trusted?"
msgstr ""
"Sí... pero ya conoces la situación con eso. Entonces, ¿crees que tus "
"discípulos podrán ayudar? ¿Podemos confiar en ellos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:684
msgid ""
"They have proven to be quite reliable thus far, haven’t they? Unfortunately, "
"I can’t know whether they intend to betray us at the end like your previous "
"assistant did, my lady. If they were consorting with our enemy they’d make "
"sure we wouldn’t find out until it was too late."
msgstr ""
"Hasta ahora han demostrado ser bastante fiables, ¿no? Por desgracia, no "
"puedo saber si planean traicionarnos al final como lo hizo tu asistente "
"anterior, mi señora. Si estuvieran conspirando con nuestro enemigo, se "
"asegurarían de que no lo supiéramos hasta que fuera demasiado tarde."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:689
msgid ""
"Indeed. That’s why I am worried. If only Galas were still with us... He "
"always seemed to make the right choices."
msgstr ""
"Ciertamente. Por eso me preocupa. Si tan solo Galas siguiera con nosotros... "
"Siempre parecía tomar las decisiones correctas."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:697
msgid "Hm... perhaps."
msgstr "Hm... quizás."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:703
msgid ""
"Hm... perhaps. Then again, was it not his choice to give that ring to a cute "
"little bat? Heehee."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:708
msgid ""
"I– Malin told you about that? Oh gods, why... What even possessed Galas to "
"do that?? That ring might be gone for good now. Although... I have to admit "
"that would be a preferable fate than having it wind up in the hands of "
"another omnicidal demon one thousand years from now. Just... please don’t "
"tell anyone else what happened."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:713
msgid "Worry not, my lady. My lips are sealed!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:722
msgid "If you don’t mind the question, why did you retire before?"
msgstr "Si no te molesta la pregunta, ¿por qué te retiraste antes?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:729
msgid ""
"I guess it was a combination of circumstances... I felt Galas’ decision to "
"delegate the government of your people to those four was horribly ill-"
"advised. Then you all decided to go south and... I knew that wouldn’t end "
"well for me. From what I heard that fellow Erathan didn’t fare well in the "
"capital."
msgstr ""
"Supongo que fue una combinación de circunstancias... Sentí que la decisión "
"de Galas de delegar el gobierno de tu gente en esos cuatro fue terriblemente "
"equivocada. Luego decidieron ir al sur y... Sabía que eso no acabaría bien "
"para mí. Por lo que escuché, a ese tal Erathan no le fue bien en la capital."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:734
msgid ""
"That’s unfortunately true. And I suppose I owe you an apology for forcing "
"you to come here."
msgstr ""
"Desgraciadamente, eso es cierto. Y supongo que te debo una disculpa por "
"obligarte a venir aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:739
msgid "Bah, nobody can force me to go anywhere if I don’t want to!"
msgstr "¡Bah! Nadie puede obligarme a ir a ningún lado si no quiero."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:744
msgid "So, what were your motives?"
msgstr "Entonces, ¿cuáles fueron tus motivos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:749
msgid ""
"My lady, I am old, and I already spent enough time in the Far North to know "
"that it could never be my home. Plus, it is because of these bastards that "
"my master’s time in this world came to such an abrupt end. You know what I "
"mean with this — I have seen it in your eyes, your thirst for revenge and "
"how you quench it with the blood of your enemies..."
msgstr ""
"Mi señora, soy vieja y ya pasé suficiente tiempo en el Lejano Norte para "
"saber que nunca podría ser mi hogar. Además, fue por culpa de esos bastardos "
"que el tiempo de mi maestro en este mundo terminó de forma tan abrupta. "
"Sabes a qué me refiero con esto: lo he visto en tus ojos, tu sed de venganza "
"y cómo la sacias con la sangre de tus enemigos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:754
msgid "I do not want to talk of that now."
msgstr "No quiero hablar de eso ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:759
msgid ""
"Well... my apologies if I have offended you, my lady. It was not my "
"intention. I’ll just... go back to watching over the encampment, silently, "
"as usual."
msgstr ""
"Bueno... mis disculpas si te he ofendido, mi señora. No era mi intención. "
"Solo... volveré a vigilar el campamento, en silencio, como de costumbre."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:766
msgid "So, did you solve your little problem with that staff?"
msgstr "Entonces, ¿resolviste tu pequeño problema con ese bastón?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:771
msgid ""
"Well, yes. It’s quite interesting, actually. It turns out that with some "
"adjustments to my shielding spell, I can channel the staff’s aura and become "
"immune to poison myself!"
msgstr ""
"Bueno, sí. Es bastante interesante, en realidad. Resulta que, con algunos "
"ajustes a mi hechizo de protección, puedo canalizar el aura del bastón y "
"volverme inmune al veneno yo misma."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:776
msgid ""
"... And that would be why you asked me to heal you from the symptoms of a "
"‘cold’ at least ten times during the day, right?"
msgstr ""
"... Y esa sería la razón por la que me pediste que te curara de los síntomas "
"de un ‘resfriado’ al menos diez veces durante el día, ¿verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:781
msgid "... Right."
msgstr "... Cierto."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:786
msgid ""
"I mean, if you think it’s safe to use the artifact like that, I’m in no "
"place to stop you. My knowledge of necromancy is not exhaustive enough to "
"know exactly how that staff works or whether it might be hazardous to its "
"user. Just... be careful when using it near our people, please?"
msgstr ""
"Quiero decir, si crees que es seguro usar el artefacto así, no estoy en "
"posición de detenerte. Mi conocimiento de la nigromancia no es lo "
"suficientemente exhaustivo como para saber exactamente cómo funciona ese "
"bastón o si podría ser peligroso para quien lo usa. Solo... ten cuidado al "
"usarlo cerca de nuestra gente, ¿de acuerdo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:791
msgid "I will be, my lady, don’t worry!"
msgstr "Lo tendré, mi señora, ¡no te preocupes!"

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:808
msgid "Talk to Igor."
msgstr "Hablar con Igor."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:811
msgid "Ask Igor about his time in the northern country."
msgstr "Preguntar a Igor sobre su tiempo en el país del norte."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:814
msgid "Ask Igor about Anya."
msgstr "Preguntar a Igor sobre Anya."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:824
msgid "Everything all right, Igor?"
msgstr "¿Todo bien, Igor?"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:829
msgid ""
"Yes... I guess. It’s just that I can’t stop thinking... The elf friend died "
"in these lands."
msgstr ""
"Sí... creo. Es solo que no puedo dejar de pensar... El amigo elfo murió en "
"estas tierras."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:834
msgid "... Yes. Yes, he did. I am sorry, I couldn’t do anything—"
msgstr "... Sí. Sí, lo hizo. Lo siento, no pude hacer nada—"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:839
msgid ""
"No, there was nothing you could do. The demon lady knew what she was doing. "
"She’s a trained assassin or something, isn’t she? I have seen how my kind do "
"it. Quickly, cleanly. Their prey falls to the ground already dead. You can’t "
"heal the dead. Nobody can."
msgstr ""
"No, no había nada que pudieras hacer. La dama demonio sabía lo que hacía. Es "
"una asesina entrenada o algo así, ¿no? He visto cómo lo hace mi gente. "
"Rápido, limpio. Su presa cae al suelo ya muerta. No puedes curar a los "
"muertos. Nadie puede."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:844
msgid ""
"I just regret not coming with you... Maybe then things would’ve turned out "
"different, you know. If we had all been together?"
msgstr ""
"Solo me arrepiento de no haber ido contigo... Tal vez entonces las cosas "
"habrían sido diferentes, ¿sabes? Si hubiéramos estado todos juntos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:849
msgid ""
"Perhaps. I don’t think it would have changed much, though. If anything, you "
"would have been in danger as well and I don’t think I could have managed to "
"pull all three of us out of that accursed citadel in one piece. Mal Keshar "
"barely made it."
msgstr ""
"Quizás. Pero no creo que hubiera cambiado mucho. Es más, tú también habrías "
"estado en peligro y no creo que hubiera podido sacar a los tres de esa "
"maldita ciudadela con vida. Mal Keshar apenas lo logró."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:854
msgid ""
"I know... I’m sorry. I need to stop beating myself up about it — I’m just a "
"goblin after all, fighting things I really don’t understand in the middle of "
"something much bigger than me. Not battle goblin, just... goblin."
msgstr ""
"Lo sé... Lo siento. Necesito dejar de martirizarme por eso. Después de todo, "
"solo soy un goblin, luchando contra cosas que realmente no entiendo en medio "
"de algo mucho más grande que yo. No un goblin de batalla, solo... goblin."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:859
msgid ""
"Don’t say such things. Your time will come when you will be able to show "
"everyone that you can accomplish great things despite the labels they force "
"upon you, Igor. I am sure of it. I believe in you."
msgstr ""
"No digas esas cosas. Llegará el momento en que podrás demostrarle a todos "
"que puedes lograr grandes cosas a pesar de las etiquetas que te imponen, "
"Igor. Estoy segura de ello. Creo en ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:864
msgid ""
"That’s actually the nicest thing anyone’s ever told me... Thank you, my "
"lady. I just wish the elf friend and the scary lich were still with us. I "
"miss them a lot."
msgstr ""
"Eso es en realidad lo más bonito que alguien me ha dicho... Gracias, mi "
"señora. Solo desearía que el amigo elfo y el liche aterrador aún estuvieran "
"con nosotros. Los extraño mucho."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:869
msgid "So do I, Igor. So do I."
msgstr "Yo también, Igor. Yo también."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:876
msgid "How did your adventures in the Aragwaith country go, anyway?"
msgstr "¿Y cómo fueron tus aventuras en el país de los Aragwaith?"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:881
msgid "Oh, uh, about that..."
msgstr "Oh, eh, sobre eso..."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:890
msgid "Kinda disappointing really."
msgstr "Bastante decepcionantes, la verdad."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:895
msgid "Go on."
msgstr "Continúa."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:900
msgid ""
"Well, you see, I didn’t do any street performing for most of it. I first "
"found this gloomy old man in a tavern in a frontier town. He told me a "
"buncha vague stuff and left? After that I did errands for random people for "
"something like an eternity. I even helped save a town from a fire! And then "
"I remembered... he told me to search for a lady seer and bring her to the "
"capital... but I nearly got myself killed while searching for her all over "
"the north. I’m not even sure why I did any of that — I kept hearing the old "
"man’s words in my head like a command."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, verás, en realidad no hice ningún espectáculo callejero en la mayor "
"parte del tiempo. Primero encontré a este anciano sombrío en una taberna de "
"un pueblo fronterizo. Me dijo un montón de cosas vagas y se fue. Después "
"estuve haciendo recados para gente al azar durante lo que pareció una "
"eternidad. ¡Incluso ayudé a salvar un pueblo de un incendio! Y entonces "
"recordé... él me dijo que buscara a una vidente y la llevara a la capital... "
"pero casi me matan mientras la buscaba por todo el norte. Ni siquiera estoy "
"seguro de por qué hice todo eso: seguía escuchando las palabras del viejo en "
"mi cabeza como una orden."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:905
msgid "Old man? Who was he?"
msgstr "¿Viejo? ¿Quién era?"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:910
msgid ""
"Dunno! He never told me who he really was, but... you know that feeling like "
"you’re doing something really important and you can’t mess it up? That’s how "
"I felt about the whole thing, even though thinking back I realize... if it "
"hadn’t been me, it could’ve been anyone else, right?"
msgstr ""
"¡No sé! Nunca me dijo quién era realmente, pero... ¿sabes esa sensación de "
"que estás haciendo algo muy importante y no puedes estropearlo? Así me sentí "
"con todo eso, aunque al pensarlo bien me doy cuenta... si no hubiera sido "
"yo, podría haber sido cualquier otro, ¿no?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:915
msgid ""
"... Yes, I think I know what you mean. Somehow that sounds familiar... But "
"my head hurts if I try to remember, it must have been too long ago, before "
"the Great Fall."
msgstr ""
"... Sí, creo que sé a lo que te refieres. De algún modo eso me resulta "
"familiar... Pero me duele la cabeza si intento recordarlo; debe de haber "
"sido hace demasiado tiempo, antes de la Gran Caída."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:920
msgid ""
"I’m sorry lady Elynia, I just needed to get that outta my chest. I know it "
"doesn’t make sense but sometimes I’m afraid that maybe I did mess up in the "
"end."
msgstr ""
"Lo siento, señora Elynia, solo necesitaba sacármelo del pecho. Sé que no "
"tiene sentido, pero a veces temo que tal vez sí la arruiné al final."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:925
msgid ""
"It sounds like our paths almost crossed at the capital back then, though. I "
"wonder why I never found you there."
msgstr ""
"Parece que nuestros caminos casi se cruzaron en la capital en aquel "
"entonces. Me pregunto por qué nunca te encontré allí."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#. Yes, apparently Igor doesn't realize that what he calls 'water longbirds'
#. are actually swans.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:932
msgid ""
"Welllll, you see, sometime after taking the seer lady there, the city guard "
"kicked me out on orders from the heavy swords guy because of something to do "
"with the “local swan population”? Dunno what that was all about, Willow only "
"eats water longbirds anyway."
msgstr ""
"Pues verás, después de llevar a la vidente a la ciudad, la guardia me echó "
"por órdenes del tipo de las espadas pesadas por algo relacionado con la "
"“población local de cisnes”. No sé de qué iba todo eso; de todos modos, "
"Willow solo come aves largas de agua."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:937
msgid "... Really, now?"
msgstr "... ¿En serio?"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:942
msgid "Mhm!"
msgstr "Mhm!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:949
msgid "You seem to be getting along well with Anya."
msgstr "Parece que te llevas bien con Anya."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:954
msgid ""
"Yes! And the purple lady likes Willow a lot. I’m so used to everyone being "
"afraid of her for no reason even though she’s just a big puppy. The archer "
"guy, for example — he’d constantly avoid her. I don’t understand why."
msgstr ""
"¡Sí! Y a la dama púrpura le gusta mucho Willow. Estoy tan acostumbrado a que "
"todos le tengan miedo sin razón, aunque solo es un cachorro grande. El tipo "
"arquero, por ejemplo, siempre la evitaba. No entiendo por qué."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:959
msgid ""
"I don’t think he and the other people from the Heart Forest are fond of "
"wolves in general. They have their reasons."
msgstr ""
"No creo que él y la otra gente del Bosque del Corazón sientan aprecio por "
"los lobos en general. Tienen sus razones."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:964
msgid ""
"If you say so... But let me ask you, how come you don’t mind the demons all "
"of a sudden?"
msgstr ""
"Si tú lo dices... Pero déjame preguntarte, ¿cómo es que de repente no te "
"molestan los demonios?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:969
msgid ""
"It’s complicated. It is not so much that I don’t mind them, but rather that "
"I have seen that reality isn’t as black and white as we thought. Ergea and "
"her people... they have their own conflict with Uria going on. It turns out "
"there is no shortage of Demon Lords who tried to wage war against her in the "
"past to escape oppression. But all those attemtps were doomed to fail, until "
"now."
msgstr ""
"Es complicado. No es tanto que no me molesten, sino que he visto que la "
"realidad no es tan blanca y negra como pensábamos. Ergea y su gente... "
"tienen su propio conflicto con Uria. Resulta que no faltan Señores "
"Demoníacos que intentaron librar una guerra contra ella en el pasado para "
"escapar de la opresión. Pero todos esos intentos estaban condenados al "
"fracaso, hasta ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:974
msgid ""
"It is now up to me... to <b>us</b>, to make a difference. Tomorrow we shall "
"fight for the fate of Irdya, and if we succeed, then Inferno will follow."
msgstr ""
"Ahora depende de mí... de <b>nosotros</b>, hacer la diferencia. Mañana "
"lucharemos por el destino de Irdya, y si tenemos éxito, entonces Infierno "
"seguirá."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:979
msgid ""
"That sounds great and all but I don’t like the way she looks at me "
"scrunching up her nose every time she passes me by..."
msgstr ""
"Todo eso suena genial, pero no me gusta cómo me mira arrugando la nariz cada "
"vez que pasa por mi lado..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:984
msgid ""
"Oh, uh... that... that might just be that she has difficulty breathing the "
"air of Irdya. I think."
msgstr ""
"Oh, eh... eso... puede que solo sea que le cuesta respirar el aire de Irdya. "
"Creo."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:989
msgid "Oh, I see. Nothing to worry about then!"
msgstr "Oh, entiendo. ¡Entonces no hay de qué preocuparse!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1044
msgid "Anya..."
msgstr "Anya..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1080
msgid "Good night."
msgstr "Buenas noches."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1085
msgid "Sleep well!"
msgstr "¡Que duermas bien!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1182
msgid ""
"elynia^You purposefully enter your tent for the last time before the "
"inevitable confrontation with your enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Fully aware of the odds, you decide to grab a few things you know you will "
"need — except for your journal, that is. You also opt to leave Argan’s and "
"Galas’ journals behind, along with a note."
msgstr ""
"Entras deliberadamente en tu tienda por última vez antes de la inevitable "
"confrontación con tus enemigos.\n"
"\n"
"Totalmente consciente de las probabilidades, decides tomar algunas cosas que "
"sabes que necesitarás, excepto tu diario, claro está. También optas por "
"dejar atrás los diarios de Argan y Galas, junto con una nota."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1190
msgid ""
"elynia^When done, you give your enticing makeshift bed a final glance. Anya "
"is right — you have not gotten any proper sleep in what seems to you like "
"ages, and this could be your last opportunity to rest in your entire life.\n"
"\n"
"But you have different plans for tonight."
msgstr ""
"Cuando terminas, le das una última mirada a tu atractiva cama improvisada. "
"Anya tiene razón: no has tenido un descanso adecuado en lo que te parece una "
"eternidad, y esta podría ser tu última oportunidad de descansar en toda tu "
"vida.\n"
"\n"
"Pero tienes otros planes para esta noche."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1209
msgid "Talk to Cron"
msgstr "Hablar con Cron"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1231
msgid ""
"elynia^You silently approach Anya. Just as you expected, she is still wide "
"awake and completely attentive to her surroundings. But she obviously was "
"not counting on your stealth spell. You shudder to think what would happen "
"if Uria’s underlings decided to use similar magic to dispose of you and your "
"friends in the middle of the night."
msgstr ""
"Te acercas sigilosamente a Anya. Tal como esperabas, ella sigue "
"completamente despierta y atenta a su alrededor. Pero, obviamente, no "
"contaba con tu hechizo de sigilo. Se te hiela la sangre al pensar en lo que "
"sucedería si los esbirros de Uria decidieran usar una magia similar para "
"deshacerse de ti y tus amigos en medio de la noche."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1237
msgid ""
"elynia^You feel terrible for having to resort to such a tactic yourself. "
"Hopefully she will understand in time."
msgstr ""
"Te sientes terrible por haber tenido que recurrir tú misma a tal táctica. "
"Con suerte, ella lo entenderá a su debido tiempo."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1250
msgid "Tell Cron you are leaving now."
msgstr "Decirle a Cron que te vas ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1260
msgid "It’s time, Cron. Please take care of Anya in my absence."
msgstr "Es hora, Cron. Por favor cuida de Anya en mi ausencia."

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1265
msgid ""
"Cron will do his best to make sure nothing bad happens to the storm lady’s "
"friends."
msgstr ""
"Cron hará lo mejor que pueda para asegurarse de que nada malo le ocurra a "
"los amigos de la dama de la tormenta."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1293
msgid "Leave the encampment"
msgstr "Abandona el campamento"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1354
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1024
msgid "Hm."
msgstr "Hm."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1365
msgid "Elynia, are you there?"
msgstr "Elynia, ¿estás ahí?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1412
msgid ""
"N: Pass of Sorrows\n"
"S: Kalari Peninsula\n"
"SE: Kalari Central"
msgstr ""
"N: Paso de las Penas\n"
"S: Península de Kalari\n"
"SE: Kalari Central"

