msgid "Argan"
msgstr "Argan"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2830
msgid ""
"It is him, the tortured man to whom you owe your life, even though you did "
"not ask for it.\n"
"\n"
"The scene feels familiar to you, but you are not completely sure yet how "
"long ago it happened."
msgstr ""
"Es él, el hombre torturado a quien le debes la vida, aunque no la hayas "
"pedido.\n"
"\n"
"La escena te resulta familiar, pero no estás completamente segura de hace "
"cuánto ocurrió."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2839
msgid "<i>You have not visited me in a long time.</i>"
msgstr "<i>No me has visitado en mucho tiempo.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2856
msgid ""
"Do I really need a reason? Uria is busy unearthing some ruins on Urvatha — "
"she will not notice my absence. I just wanted to see you."
msgstr ""
"¿Realmente necesito una razón? Uria está ocupada desenterrando unas ruinas "
"en Urvatha — no notará mi ausencia. Solo quería verte."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2874
msgid "I have to admit that I expected a warmer reception."
msgstr "Debo admitir que esperaba una recepción más cálida."

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2879
msgid ""
"I suppose... it’s hard to be enthusiastic about a visit from someone who has "
"only spoken to me through crystal projections for over a century. It almost "
"feels as though we are strangers... meeting for the first time..."
msgstr ""
"Supongo... es difícil entusiasmarse con la visita de alguien que solo me ha "
"hablado a través de proyecciones de cristal por más de un siglo. Casi parece "
"que somos extraños... encontrándonos por primera vez..."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2884
msgid "Does it now?"
msgstr "¿De verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2907
msgid "I missed you... I really, really did."
msgstr "Te extrañé... de verdad, mucho."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2938
msgid "How have things been around here? Any progress?"
msgstr "¿Cómo han estado las cosas por aquí? ¿Algún progreso?"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2945
msgid ""
"With Nar-hamoth around I haven’t been able to continue with my search. But I "
"went to Ghoram-Dul the other day and asked the Seer about her and—"
msgstr ""
"Con Nar-hamoth rondando no he podido continuar con mi búsqueda. Pero fui a "
"Ghoram-Dul el otro día y le pregunté a la Vidente sobre ella y—"

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2950
msgid ""
"Not the faerie. The hive in the Grenmar region. I believe its construction "
"should be nearly finished by now?"
msgstr ""
"No la feérica. La colmena en la región de Grenmar. ¿Creo que su construcción "
"ya debería estar casi terminada?"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2959
msgid ""
"Did you come here just to ask me about such banal matters, or because you "
"wanted to see me?"
msgstr ""
"¿Viniste aquí solo para preguntarme sobre asuntos tan banales o porque "
"querías verme?"

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2964
msgid ""
"Do I have to choose between those two options? I did not expect you to be so "
"demanding from your superiors, girl."
msgstr ""
"¿Tengo que elegir entre esas dos opciones? No esperaba que fueras tan "
"exigente con tus superiores, chica."

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2969
msgid "<i>Superiors</i>, you say?"
msgstr "<i>¿Superiores?</i> ¿Dices?"

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2974
msgid ""
"I do not have all the time in the world for your empty questions. Will you "
"answer, or—"
msgstr ""
"No tengo todo el tiempo del mundo para tus preguntas vacías. ¿Responderás, o"
"—?"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2979
msgid ""
"Uria sent you, didn’t she? She sent you to keep track of my activities, as "
"if I needed another Shadow of hers around here."
msgstr ""
"Uria te envió, ¿verdad? Te envió para vigilar mis actividades, como si "
"necesitara otra Sombra suya aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2988
msgid ""
"Oh, but of course. ‘Shadow’ really suits you better than it does that "
"brainless brute, except most of the scum in this place prefers to add "
"‘Master’ to it for some stupid reason."
msgstr ""
"Oh, por supuesto. ‘Sombra’ realmente te queda mejor a ti que a ese bruto "
"descerebrado, excepto que la mayoría de la escoria en este lugar prefiere "
"añadirle ‘Maestro’ por alguna estúpida razón."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2995
msgid "You seem agitated—"
msgstr "Pareces alterada—"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#. 'Monster' here refers to Uria.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3001
msgid ""
"Dealing with your personality issues was exasperating enough back then; I "
"will <b>not</b> bear talking to you now that you have become a puppet of "
"that abusive monster. Get out."
msgstr ""
"Tratar con tus problemas de personalidad ya era bastante exasperante en "
"aquel entonces; **no** soportaré hablar contigo ahora que te has convertido "
"en un títere de ese monstruo abusivo. Lárgate."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3006
msgid "El— Elyssa—"
msgstr "El— Elyssa—"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3011
msgid "GET OUT!"
msgstr "¡LÁRGATE!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3032
msgid ""
"For long you have tried to purge your memories revolving around Argan’s "
"descent into insanity and the eventual fulfillment of his end of the bargain "
"with Uria. Alas, Norsulan technology around the time you were resurrected "
"was not advanced enough to do that kind of thing, and you are sort of stuck "
"in the past in that regard.\n"
"\n"
"Maybe some day you will learn to do the advanced mind tricks Merthiaal "
"could, and use that power to alter or clear your own memory. Surely if you "
"manage to do that, you could attain absolute control of every single "
"creature on Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Durante mucho tiempo has intentado purgar tus recuerdos sobre la caída de "
"Argan en la locura y el eventual cumplimiento de su parte del trato con "
"Uria. Lamentablemente, la tecnología norsulana en la época en que fuiste "
"resucitada no era lo bastante avanzada para hacer algo así, y en ese aspecto "
"estás atrapada en el pasado.\n"
"\n"
"Quizás algún día aprendas a realizar los avanzados trucos mentales que podía "
"hacer Merthiaal y uses ese poder para alterar o borrar tu propia memoria. "
"Sin duda, si logras hacerlo, podrías alcanzar el control absoluto de cada "
"criatura en Irdya."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3040
msgid ""
"You decide to proceed further into the ruined laboratory and try to "
"reminisce on better times."
msgstr ""
"Decides avanzar más adentro en el laboratorio en ruinas e intentar rememorar "
"tiempos mejores."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3048
msgid ""
"Proceed further into the ruined laboratory and try to reminisce on better "
"times"
msgstr ""
"Avanzar más adentro en el laboratorio en ruinas e intentar rememorar tiempos "
"mejores"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3070
msgid "Operating Room"
msgstr "Sala de Operaciones"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3071
msgid ""
"FACILITY CONDEMNED\n"
"\n"
"NO ENTRY WITHOUT LEVEL 4 PERMISSION FROM THE IRON COUNCIL"
msgstr ""
"INSTALACIÓN CLAUSURADA\n"
"\n"
"NO ENTRAR SIN PERMISO DE NIVEL 4 DEL CONSEJO DE HIERRO"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3102
msgid ""
"Some of the hive creatures have adopted these ruins as their home. You do "
"not really mind them since they are completely harmless around those whom "
"they recognize as their own kind by virtue of their identification signal "
"mechanism.\n"
"\n"
"You are absolutely certain that, unlike the Gatekeeper you just destroyed, "
"these artificial constructs have no souls of their own. Whether they have "
"minds or not is a completely different matter, though."
msgstr ""
"Algunas de las criaturas de la colmena han adoptado estas ruinas como su "
"hogar. Realmente no te molestan, ya que son completamente inofensivas con "
"aquellos a quienes reconocen como de su misma especie gracias a su mecanismo "
"de señal de identificación.\n"
"\n"
"Estás absolutamente segura de que, a diferencia del Guardián que acabas de "
"destruir, estas construcciones artificiales no poseen almas propias. Sin "
"embargo, si tienen mente o no es un asunto completamente diferente."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3125
msgid "Elyssa... There is something I need to know."
msgstr "Elyssa... Hay algo que necesito saber."

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3134
msgid ""
"I thought I told you to go away. I am not interested in helping you anymore."
msgstr "Creí haberte dicho que te fueras. Ya no estoy interesada en ayudarte."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3139
msgid ""
"I <i>need</i> your help. Please... You are the only one I could ever trust "
"who can use the powers of Darkness to block the Seer’s vision. I <i>need</i> "
"to find my wife—"
msgstr ""
"<i>Necesito</i> tu ayuda. Por favor... Eres la única en quien podría confiar "
"para usar los poderes de la Oscuridad y bloquear la visión de la Vidente. "
"<i>Necesito</i> encontrar a mi esposa—"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3144
msgid ""
"Why did you not try to find her before surrendering your free will to Uria? "
"If you truly loved the Lady of Light, the first thing you should have done "
"was—"
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué no intentaste encontrarla antes de entregar tu libre albedrío a "
"Uria? Si realmente amabas a la Dama de la Luz, lo primero que deberías haber "
"hecho era—"

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3149
msgid ""
"I already told you... I did not choose to be stranded on Urvatha for so "
"long. Uria does not want me to find Elynia yet. I am worried that her plans "
"could jeopardize your own safety. You must do something for me..."
msgstr ""
"Ya te lo dije... No elegí quedarme varado en Urvatha tanto tiempo. Uria no "
"quiere que encuentre a Elynia todavía. Me preocupa que sus planes puedan "
"poner en peligro tu propia seguridad. Debes hacer algo por mí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3154
msgid "If you find Elynia, you must kill her."
msgstr "Si encuentras a Elynia, debes matarla."

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3171
msgid "... Why?"
msgstr "... ¿Por qué?"

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#. The 'voice' Argan refers to is a female voice.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3177
msgid ""
"Because it is something you must do. That is what I was told by the voice..."
msgstr "Porque es algo que debes hacer. Eso fue lo que me dijo la voz..."

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3182
msgid ""
"You... You are in even worse shape than I thought. I simply cannot fathom "
"what is going through Uria’s mind as of late. Why would she trust <i>you</i> "
"with the command of the Empire like this?"
msgstr ""
"Tú... Estás en un estado aún peor del que imaginaba. Simplemente no puedo "
"comprender lo que pasa por la mente de Uria últimamente. ¿Por qué confiaría "
"en <i>ti</i> para el mando del Imperio de esta manera?"

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3187
msgid ""
"No. Listen. You can consult with the Seer later — I am sure she knows of the "
"voice as well, but she has always refused to speak with me. I have a "
"suspicion about that voice..."
msgstr ""
"No. Escucha. Puedes consultar con la Vidente más tarde; estoy seguro de que "
"ella también sabe sobre la voz, pero siempre se ha negado a hablar conmigo. "
"Tengo una sospecha sobre esa voz..."

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3192
msgid "Does Uria need to know?"
msgstr "¿Debe saberlo Uria?"

#. [message]: speaker=memory!Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3202
msgid ""
"Very well, then. I hope the Seer will not inform her about this, though."
msgstr ""
"Muy bien, entonces. Espero que la Vidente no le informe sobre esto, sin "
"embargo."

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3207
msgid ""
"I do not think she has found out about your search yet, has she? You know "
"the Seer is as much your ally as she is Uria’s — she does not take sides. "
"She will not betray you, but not specifically because of your affiliation "
"with Darkness. If that were all it took to communicate with her, I would not "
"need your help for that."
msgstr ""
"No creo que ella haya descubierto tu búsqueda todavía, ¿verdad? Sabes que la "
"Vidente es tanto tu aliada como lo es de Uria; ella no toma partido. No te "
"traicionará, pero no precisamente por tu afinidad con la Oscuridad. Si eso "
"fuera todo lo necesario para comunicarte con ella, no necesitaría tu ayuda "
"para ello."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3219
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Many years later, Argan’s orders would take a turn for the worse, and you "
"would happily comply with every single one. You do not really regret it in "
"the least. Killing lesser creatures is quite cathartic after all you have "
"been through. If only you could do that with your own underlings more often. "
"Wait, you mean Zhangor’s underlings now. You are quite sure he would not "
"actually mind.\n"
"\n"
"On the other hand, you were allowed to do as you pleased with your torturers "
"back in the day. If only you had the control you now have over your "
"artificially enhanced body, and Merthiaal’s heart. If only you could ravage "
"people’s minds like the true Eater of Souls could. If only..."
msgstr ""
"Años más tarde, las órdenes de Argan se volverían cada vez peores, y tú las "
"cumplirías gustosamente una por una. En realidad no te arrepientes en lo más "
"mínimo. Matar a criaturas inferiores resulta increíblemente reconfortante "
"después de todo lo que has pasado. Ojalá pudieras hacer lo mismo con tus "
"propios subordinados más a menudo. Bueno, ahora te refieres a los "
"subordinados de Zhangor. Estás bastante segura de que a él no le "
"importaría.\n"
"\n"
"Por otro lado, en su momento se te permitió hacer lo que quisieras con tus "
"torturadores. Ojalá entonces hubieras tenido el control que ahora posees "
"sobre tu cuerpo artificialmente mejorado y sobre el corazón de Merthiaal. "
"Ojalá pudieras devastar las mentes de las personas como lo hacía la "
"verdadera Devoradora de Almas. Ojalá..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3252
msgid "Proceed into the ruined room"
msgstr "Avanza hacia la habitación en ruinas"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3277
msgid ""
"This is where Argan brought you back to life — or what remains of the place, "
"in any case. You really threw a tantrum that night, blinded by the great "
"pain caused by the energy seeping through your veins, and that unfathomable "
"presence within Merthiaal’s heart reaching into your soul.\n"
"\n"
"You are not entirely sure whether the pain ceased or you just became "
"accustomed to it over the years, but you can still feel the presence on "
"occasion — namely, whenever you feel tempted to fully unleash your "
"frustration and anger."
msgstr ""
"Aquí fue donde Argan te devolvió a la vida… o al menos lo que queda del "
"lugar. Aquella noche realmente hiciste un berrinche, cegada por el gran "
"dolor que causaba la energía filtrándose por tus venas, y esa presencia "
"insondable dentro del corazón de Merthiaal alcanzando tu alma.\n"
"\n"
"No estás del todo segura de si el dolor cesó o simplemente te acostumbraste "
"con los años, pero aún puedes sentir esa presencia en ocasiones… sobre todo "
"cuando te sientes tentada a liberar por completo tu frustración y tu ira."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3285
msgid ""
"The costs and risks of being a predestined guardian have not been properly "
"documented, but everyone agrees that it was the temptation of power that "
"finally got the best of the goddess whose legacy Argan and Uria bestowed "
"upon you. But your case is an unprecedented one, and you have had to cope "
"with other difficulties along the way. The technology that binds your body "
"and soul with Merthiaal’s heart was considered highly experimental on its "
"world of origin, and every test subject was destroyed without exception.\n"
"\n"
"Maybe it was because the heart they chose for their testing was that of an "
"unborn goddess as opposed to a deceased one. Maybe it was because the Aspect "
"of Fire itself did not choose them. Or maybe those individuals simply lacked "
"the resolve, and the initial excruciating pain was too much for their feeble "
"psyches.\n"
"\n"
"Whichever the case, you are certain that even though cheating the system "
"devised by Yarae was a straining and arduous task, the Aspect of Darkness is "
"now yours to control."
msgstr ""
"Los costos y riesgos de ser una guardiana predestinada no han sido "
"documentados adecuadamente, pero todos coinciden en que fue la tentación del "
"poder lo que finalmente venció a la diosa cuyo legado Argan y Uria te "
"otorgaron. Pero tu caso es único y sin precedentes, y has tenido que "
"enfrentarte a otras dificultades en el camino. La tecnología que une tu "
"cuerpo y alma con el corazón de Merthiaal era considerada altamente "
"experimental en su mundo de origen, y cada sujeto de prueba fue destruido "
"sin excepción.\n"
"\n"
"Quizá se debió a que el corazón elegido para sus pruebas era el de una diosa "
"no nacida, en lugar de una ya fallecida. Quizá fue porque el Aspecto del "
"Fuego no las eligió. O quizá esos individuos simplemente carecían de la "
"determinación necesaria, y el dolor inicial era demasiado para sus frágiles "
"mentes.\n"
"\n"
"Sea cual sea el caso, estás segura de que, aunque burlar el sistema ideado "
"por Yarae fue una tarea ardua y agotadora, el Aspecto de la Oscuridad ahora "
"es tuyo para controlar."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3295
msgid ""
"If the once Lady of Light had not killed him, Argan would be proud to see "
"you execute his plans like clockwork.\n"
"\n"
"Proud. Nothing more than that, really.\n"
"\n"
"If you were to use Golden Age literature as reference, you would say he "
"always regarded you as a daughter. His increasing lack of empathy did not "
"allow him to see that you had feelings of a different kind for him. While "
"that truly bothered you in the beginning, you would soon learn of another "
"cost of being a guardian. To put it into perspective, of all the guardians "
"that have lived so far, only the second incarnation of the Guardian of Fire "
"found true love — and then she died under mysterious circumstances.\n"
"\n"
"Those unrequited feelings of yours vanished long ago, but that does not "
"change the fact that you owe your life to Argan and that you will do "
"everything within your power for him, even now that he is gone for good."
msgstr ""
"Si la que alguna vez fue la Dama de la Luz no lo hubiera matado, Argan "
"estaría orgulloso de verte ejecutar sus planes como un reloj.\n"
"\n"
"Orgulloso. Nada más que eso, en realidad.\n"
"\n"
"Si tomaras la literatura de la Edad Dorada como referencia, dirías que "
"siempre te consideró como una hija. Su creciente falta de empatía no le "
"permitió ver que tus sentimientos por él eran de otro tipo. Aunque eso te "
"molestó profundamente al principio, pronto aprenderías otro costo de ser "
"guardiana. En perspectiva, de todos los guardianes que han existido hasta "
"ahora, solo la segunda encarnación de la Guardiana del Fuego encontró el "
"amor verdadero… y luego murió en circunstancias misteriosas.\n"
"\n"
"Aquellos sentimientos no correspondidos desaparecieron hace mucho, pero eso "
"no cambia el hecho de que le debes la vida a Argan y que harás todo lo que "
"esté a tu alcance por él, incluso ahora que se ha ido para siempre."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. This is a bit of meta-commentary on the fact that AtS E3's final segment
#. (Divergence onwards) was in development for several months with no new scenarios
#. being released in the meantime until the entire thing was completed.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3339
msgid ""
"It feels as though you have been wasting your time with this pointless "
"introspective for months, even though it has obviously been just an hour. "
"Damn the Gatekeeper and the Seer. Things would be much easier if you could "
"just focus on commanding troops and killing opponents with complete "
"disregard for ancient riddles and the absurd notion of fate."
msgstr ""
"Se siente como si hubieras estado perdiendo el tiempo con esta introspección "
"inútil durante meses, aunque obviamente solo ha sido una hora. Maldita sea "
"la Guardiana y el Vidente. Las cosas serían mucho más fáciles si pudieras "
"concentrarte en comandar tropas y eliminar oponentes sin prestar atención a "
"acertijos antiguos ni a la absurda noción del destino."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3345
msgid "Proceed into Elyssa’s cell"
msgstr "Avanza hacia la celda de Elyssa"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3367
msgid ""
"SUBJECT 00-44A CONTAINMENT CHAMBER\n"
"\n"
"NO ENTRY WITHOUT LEVEL 6 PERMISSION FROM MAL ZAGARN"
msgstr ""
"CÁMARA DE CONTENCIÓN SUJETO 00-44A\n"
"\n"
"NO ENTRAR SIN PERMISO DE NIVEL 6 DE MAL ZAGARN"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3386
msgid ""
"The chest is empty. It has been decades since the last time anyone used it "
"to deliver parcels to you."
msgstr ""
"El cofre está vacío. Han pasado décadas desde la última vez que alguien lo "
"usó para entregarte paquetes."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3406
msgid ""
"Kendyare is still here as you left her.\n"
"\n"
"The faerie destroyed her body near the entrance to the abandoned Iron "
"Council chamber. If you were to give the necromancer a new chance you would "
"have to give her a new body as well. She was rather entertaining to have "
"around, but not particularly bright, and Nar-hamoth was abusing that to keep "
"you under constant surveillance. You simply had to act before Zhangor had a "
"chance to take advantage of her as well."
msgstr ""
"Kendyare sigue aquí tal como la dejaste.\n"
"\n"
"El hada destruyó su cuerpo cerca de la entrada a la abandonada cámara del "
"Consejo de Hierro. Si quisieras darle otra oportunidad a la nigromante, "
"también tendrías que darle un nuevo cuerpo. Era bastante entretenida de "
"tener cerca, pero no especialmente brillante, y Nar-hamoth se aprovechaba de "
"ello para mantenerte bajo constante vigilancia. Simplemente tuviste que "
"actuar antes de que Zhangor tuviera la oportunidad de aprovecharse de ella "
"también."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3414
msgid ""
"You have not really spent as much time in this cell as you would if you were "
"an ordinary creature. Thankfully, your body allows you to spend an "
"indefinite amount of time without rest. You have tried sleeping on occasion, "
"but ever since you were captured by the human scum in the capital you have "
"only had variations of the same recurring nightmares. You hoped your new "
"life would allow you to have normal dreams again, but it has only been worse "
"since then."
msgstr ""
"No has pasado tanto tiempo en esta celda como lo haría una criatura "
"ordinaria. Por suerte, tu cuerpo te permite permanecer un tiempo indefinido "
"sin descanso. Has intentado dormir en ocasiones, pero desde que fuiste "
"capturada por la escoria humana en la capital solo has tenido variaciones de "
"las mismas pesadillas recurrentes. Esperabas que tu nueva vida te permitiera "
"volver a tener sueños normales, pero desde entonces solo ha sido peor."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3426
msgid ""
"You think it is finally time to go and put those plans in motion. You glance "
"at your cell a last time to make sure you are not forgetting anything before "
"leaving. Surely none of that trash on the floor is of any use to you."
msgstr ""
"Crees que por fin ha llegado la hora de poner en marcha esos planes. Miras "
"tu celda por última vez para asegurarte de no olvidar nada antes de "
"marcharte. Seguramente ninguna de esas porquerías en el suelo te será de "
"utilidad."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3436
msgid "Find the touchplate leading to the final room"
msgstr "Busca la placa oculta que conduce a la sala final"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3458
msgid ""
"Kendyare's ward against necromantic spells. Very useful against mundane "
"enemy necromancers, absolutely useless against magic on lease from a "
"Guardian of Life. Such a shame."
msgstr ""
"La barrera de Kendyare contra los conjuros nigrománticos. Muy útil contra "
"nigromantes enemigos mundanos, absolutamente inútil contra magia prestada "
"por un Guardián de la Vida. Qué vergüenza."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3475
msgid ""
"This broken slab of rock used to be your bed. Last time you slept on it you "
"had a little accident due to your nightmares. It did not make for the most "
"comfortable sleeping surface in the first place, but now you are pretty sure "
"it would be greatly unadvisable for you to spend any significant amount of "
"time lying on it. Not that your back would resent it enough to suffer any "
"kind of permanent injury, anyway — your ability to regenerate biological "
"parts is pretty intentionally limited compared to a naturally-born guardian, "
"but you are still far sturdier than your pitiful victim here thanks to the "
"various enhancements they made to your body. You suppose there are <i>some</"
"i> advantages to having been disemboweled and implanted with an unnatural "
"power source after all."
msgstr ""
"Esta losa de roca rota solía ser tu cama. La última vez que dormiste en ella "
"tuviste un pequeño accidente debido a las pesadillas. No era precisamente la "
"superficie de descanso más cómoda para empezar, pero ahora estás bastante "
"segura de que sería muy poco recomendable pasar tiempo sobre ella. No es que "
"tu espalda lo resentiría como para sufrir alguna lesión permanente — tu "
"capacidad de regenerar partes biológicas es bastante limitada a propósito en "
"comparación con un guardián nacido de forma natural, pero sigues siendo "
"mucho más resistente que tu patética víctima aquí gracias a las diversas "
"mejoras que hicieron a tu cuerpo. Supongo que después de todo hay "
"<i>algunas</i> ventajas en haber sido destripada e implantada con una fuente "
"de poder antinatural."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3492
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3545
msgid "Your makeshift bed table. There is nothing remarkable about it."
msgstr "Tu improvisada mesita de noche. No hay nada destacable en ella."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3509
msgid ""
"Just trash that has been lying around for ages. You are not going to touch "
"it — who knows what kind of creatures have decided to make it their home."
msgstr ""
"Solo basura que lleva ahí siglos. No vas a tocarla — quién sabe qué clase de "
"criaturas han decidido hacer de eso su hogar."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3526
msgid ""
"Kendyare seems much brighter now than she did in life.\n"
"\n"
"You would take the poor woman with you, but it is probably safer here. "
"Presumably nobody will ever find her and you will never have to worry about "
"her deciding to wreak revenge on you for sweeping her out of the way like "
"that. She is just going to spend an eternity here being even more useless "
"than usual, assuming the place does not collapse first. That is not a "
"troubling notion in the least, you tell yourself."
msgstr ""
"Kendyare parece mucho más lúcida ahora que en vida.\n"
"\n"
"Te llevarías a la pobre mujer contigo, pero probablemente esté más segura "
"aquí. Presumiblemente nadie la encontrará jamás y nunca tendrás que "
"preocuparte de que decida vengarse de ti por apartarla de esa manera. Va a "
"pasar una eternidad aquí siendo incluso más inútil de lo habitual, asumiendo "
"que el lugar no se derrumbe primero. Eso no es en absoluto una idea "
"inquietante, te dices a ti misma."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3560
msgid ""
"This is an old poetry book you found amongst some ruins unearthed in the "
"Silver Lands. You used to dedicate your life to collecting every single "
"piece of history you could salvage from the many remains of Golden Age "
"civilizations, but after becoming a hybrid being your interests changed "
"drastically. Things like poetry became pointless as they do not contribute "
"to your plans in any way whatsoever, and yet... this book is still here."
msgstr ""
"Este es un viejo libro de poesía que encontraste entre unas ruinas "
"desenterradas en las Tierras Plateadas. Solías dedicar tu vida a recopilar "
"cada pedazo de historia que podías rescatar de los muchos restos de las "
"civilizaciones de la Edad Dorada, pero tras convertirte en un ser híbrido "
"tus intereses cambiaron drásticamente. Cosas como la poesía se volvieron "
"inútiles, ya que no contribuyen a tus planes de ninguna manera… y sin "
"embargo… este libro sigue aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3578
msgid "Do you want to pick the book up?"
msgstr "¿Quieres recoger el libro?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3591
msgid ""
"You take the book. A few loose pages slide onto the floor, and you pick them "
"up."
msgstr ""
"Tomas el libro. Unas cuantas páginas sueltas caen al suelo, y las recoges."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3601
msgid ""
"Of course. These are the pages you took from Argan’s journal some time after "
"he became irreversibly incoherent."
msgstr ""
"Por supuesto. Estas son las páginas que tomaste del diario de Argan algún "
"tiempo después de que se volviera irreversiblemente incoherente."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3631
msgid ""
"Once you enter that room, there will be no going back.\n"
"\n"
"Are you sure you want to proceed now?"
msgstr ""
"Una vez que entres en esa sala, no habrá marcha atrás.\n"
"\n"
"¿Estás segura de que quieres continuar ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3683
msgid "This is all your fault, Argan."
msgstr "Todo esto es tu culpa, Argan."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3692
msgid "I shouldn’t be the one to deal with this..."
msgstr "No debería ser yo quien se encargue de esto..."

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:391
msgid "Destiny — Part 1"
msgstr "Destino — Parte 1"

#. [scenario]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:56
msgid "Feerelim’s Garden"
msgstr "El Jardín de Feerelim"

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:101
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:62
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:78
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:94
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:110
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:140
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:64
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:66
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:108
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:137
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:161
msgid "team_name^Zhangor"
msgstr "Zhangor"

#. [side]: type=Chaos Lorekeeper, id=Mal Therygos
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:155
msgid "Mal Therygos"
msgstr "Mal Therygos"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:289
msgid "Defeat all enemy leaders to seize the keep"
msgstr "Derrota a todos los líderes enemigos para tomar el bastión"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:346
msgid "I’m not sure this is a good idea."
msgstr "No estoy seguro de que esto sea una buena idea."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:351
msgid ""
"This fortress is key to the defense of the Kalari region and guards an "
"entrance to the underground complex. If we intend to assist Elynia..."
msgstr ""
"Esta fortaleza es clave para la defensa de la región de Kalari y guarda una "
"entrada al complejo subterráneo. Si queremos ayudar a Elynia…"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:356
msgid ""
"I know, I know. It just seems such a contrived plan. Do we have any idea who "
"controls it at this particular time?"
msgstr ""
"Lo sé, lo sé. Solo parece un plan muy forzado. ¿Tenemos idea de quién la "
"controla en este momento?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:366
msgid ""
"Durvan is meeting with us again soon. Let us not waste any more of his time."
msgstr ""
"Durvan se reunirá con nosotros de nuevo pronto. No perdamos más de su tiempo."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:380
msgid ""
"I am concerned that sooner or later we are going to have to face against the "
"Storm Sisters. We are rather ill-prepared for such a confrontation, but "
"there is no helping it."
msgstr ""
"Me preocupa que tarde o temprano tengamos que enfrentarnos a las Hermanas de "
"la Tormenta. No estamos muy bien preparados para una confrontación así, pero "
"no hay forma de evitarlo."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:385
msgid "Who are they?"
msgstr "¿Quiénes son?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:390
msgid ""
"Zhangor’s loyal enforcers. Regrettably, they are from my own clan. We had... "
"different ideas as to how to handle Zhangor’s rise to power. They opted to "
"side with him, pledging their assassin skills to his service in order to "
"ensure that my fellow stormkind and others do not step out of line. Shortly "
"before battle I received reports indicating that they are roaming the skies "
"of Kalari Central hunting down anyone suspected of rebellious conduct."
msgstr ""
"Las fieles ejecutoras de Zhangor. Lamentablemente, son de mi propio clan. "
"Teníamos… ideas diferentes sobre cómo manejar el ascenso de Zhangor al "
"poder. Ellas optaron por aliarse con él, poniendo sus habilidades de "
"asesinas a su servicio para asegurarse de que mi gente y otros no se salgan "
"de la línea. Poco antes de la batalla recibí informes de que están rondando "
"los cielos del Kalari Central cazando a cualquiera sospechoso de conducta "
"rebelde."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:395
msgid "I imagine your head is quite highly priced right now."
msgstr "Imagino que tu cabeza tiene un precio bastante alto ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:400
msgid "Yes, it is. I am expecting them to be awaiting us in the fortress keep."
msgstr ""
"Sí, lo tiene. Espero que nos estén aguardando en el bastión de la fortaleza."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:405
msgid "Bah, we will make short work of them, for sure!"
msgstr "¡Bah, las derrotaremos en un abrir y cerrar de ojos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:437
msgid "That thing... are those... human... bodies... protruding from it?"
msgstr "Esa cosa… ¿son… cuerpos humanos… sobresaliendo de ella?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#. Fist: male (Zhangor)
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:443
msgid ""
"Uria is feared for the habit of decorating her various temples and "
"fortresses on Inferno with those who have foolishly dared to stand up "
"against her. Long ago, she realized that torturing and killing rebels was "
"not enough to make an example, so she began to use her Life powers in "
"more... creative ways. She revels in inflicting unending pain to others, and "
"so does her Fist."
msgstr ""
"Uria es temida por su costumbre de decorar sus templos y fortalezas en "
"Inferno con aquellos que osaron enfrentarse a ella. Hace mucho comprendió "
"que torturar y matar rebeldes no bastaba para dar ejemplo, así que comenzó a "
"usar sus poderes de Vida de formas más… creativas. Se deleita en infligir un "
"dolor interminable a los demás, y lo mismo hace su Puño."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#. Voice: male (Argan), Fire: female (Elyssa)
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:449
msgid ""
"The Voice used his words to control the forces of Chaos, and the Fire used "
"subtlety. While torture and bloodshed have been a common instrument for all "
"three emissaries, Zhangor has opted for the unrestrained brutality that had "
"previously marked his reign over the declining shapeshifters on Urvatha... "
"and the children of Xia’el on Irdya."
msgstr ""
"La Voz usó sus palabras para controlar las fuerzas del Caos, y el Fuego "
"recurrió a la sutileza. Aunque la tortura y la masacre han sido instrumentos "
"comunes a los tres emisarios, Zhangor optó por la brutalidad desatada que ya "
"había marcado su reinado sobre los cambiantes en decadencia en Urvatha… y "
"los hijos de Xia’el en Irdya."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:454
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Since he lacks the special connection with the Tree that Uria does have, he "
"is limited to the possibilities offered by the technology Chaos had already "
"appropriated for imitating her perverse creations. Unfortunately for his "
"innocent victims, their fate is not any less horrifying or irreversible. "
"Even if we could pry them off these biomechanical structures, they would die "
"in an instant."
msgstr ""
"Como carece de la conexión especial con el Árbol que Uria sí posee, está "
"limitado a las posibilidades que ofrece la tecnología que el Caos ya había "
"apropiado para imitar sus perversas creaciones. Por desgracia para sus "
"inocentes víctimas, su destino no es menos horrible ni reversible."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:470
#, fuzzy
msgid "The most we can do is put them out of their misery."
msgstr "Lo máximo que podemos hacer es acabar con su miseria."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. She's addressing the nameless victims turned into
#. Shaxthal turrets
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:478
msgid "I’m so sorry... I really am..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:493
msgid ""
"You know, Anya... I think I’m finally getting used to the wolves. Granted, "
"I’m still not keen on their awful breath."
msgstr ""
"Sabes, Anya… creo que por fin me estoy acostumbrando a los lobos. Claro que "
"aún no me agrada su aliento horrible."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:498
msgid "See? It’s not all that bad once you get to know them."
msgstr "¿Ves? No es tan malo una vez que los conoces."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:503
msgid ""
"Yes, sure. I still wish Willow would stop stalking me, especially since half "
"of the time that goblin follows. He’s in desperate need of a bath, that guy."
msgstr ""
"Sí, claro. Igual desearía que Willow dejara de acecharme, sobre todo porque "
"la mitad del tiempo ese goblin lo sigue. Ese tipo necesita un baño con "
"urgencia."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:508
msgid ""
"To be fair, I haven’t bathed in a while either and you don’t seem to mind."
msgstr ""
"Para ser justa, yo tampoco me he bañado en un tiempo y no pareces quejarte."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:513
msgid ""
"I— That’s... I mean, that’s not the same! Be— besides, you are surely going "
"to do it as soon as you get the chance. Unlike <i>him</i>."
msgstr ""
"Y— Eso… quiero decir, ¡no es lo mismo! Ad— además, seguro que tú lo harás en "
"cuanto tengas la oportunidad. A diferencia de <i>él</i>."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:518
msgid "You are saying that only because he’s a goblin, aren’t you?"
msgstr "Estás diciendo eso solo porque es un goblin, ¿verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=General Ramzal
#. 'Wose-born wench' referring to Elynia.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:542
msgid ""
"Ha ha ha, it is the Lady of Light’s apprentice, and the stormkind renegade! "
"Oh well, seeing as how the Fist has his own plans for the wose-born wench, I "
"may as well content myself with the corpses of these two as my trophies."
msgstr ""
"Ja, ja, ja, ¡es la aprendiz de la Dama de la Luz y la renegada de los hijos "
"de la tormenta! Bueno, dado que el Puño tiene sus propios planes para la "
"mocosa nacida de los woses, me contentaré con los cadáveres de estas dos "
"como trofeos."

#. [message]: speaker=General Ramzal
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:574
msgid ""
"Come and face me, wind witch! I’ve always been curious to see whether your "
"kind has the guts to rise against their more powerful masters."
msgstr ""
"¡Ven y enfréntame, bruja del viento! Siempre he tenido curiosidad por saber "
"si los de tu clase tienen el valor de alzarse contra sus amos más poderosos."

#. [message]: speaker=General Ramzal
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:598
msgid ""
"You are messing with the wrong crowd, little faerie. You should consider "
"returning to whatever putrid bog you came from, before you get hurt!"
msgstr ""
"Te estás metiendo con la gente equivocada, pequeña hada. Deberías pensar en "
"regresar a la ciénaga pútrida de la que saliste, ¡antes de salir herida!"

#. [message]: speaker=General Ramzal
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:619
msgid "Disgusting double-crossing hag—"
msgstr "Asquerosa bruja traicionera—"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:634
msgid ""
"You should have returned to whatever filthy cavern you crawled out from!"
msgstr ""
"¡Debiste regresar a la asquerosa caverna de la que saliste arrastrándote!"

#. [message]: speaker=General Ramzal
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:639
msgid "Damn you, miserable faerie-born creature—"
msgstr "Maldita seas, miserable criatura nacida de las hadas—"

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:657
msgid "Cron doesn’t like the foul-mouthed human and his annoying blast stick."
msgstr ""
"A Cron no le gusta el humano malhablado ni su molesto palo que explota."

#. [message]: speaker=General Ramzal
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:662
msgid "Just what do you think you are doing with that ridiculous hammer?"
msgstr "¿Qué crees que haces con ese ridículo martillo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:677
msgid ""
"That disgusting human filth could not possibly be in command of this "
"fortress alone. We ought to enter the keep and locate their true leader."
msgstr ""
"Esa asquerosa escoria humana no puede estar al mando de esta fortaleza por "
"sí sola. Debemos entrar en la torre y localizar a su verdadero líder."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:682
msgid "As you say, then, but we should make this quick. I’ll lead the way."
msgstr "Como digas, pero deberíamos darnos prisa. Yo iré al frente."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:688
msgid "Find the castellan"
msgstr "Encontrar al castellano"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1007
msgid ""
"This place is so unbearably bright even though the longest night isn’t over "
"yet. Where does all this light come from?"
msgstr ""
"Este lugar es insoportablemente brillante aunque la noche más larga aún no "
"ha terminado. ¿De dónde viene toda esta luz?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1029
msgid ""
"Perhaps it’s some kind of beacon built into the ceiling structure whose "
"light is directed at us using mirrors. I have heard of some temples in the "
"North using that kind of trick, expensive as it may be."
msgstr ""
"Quizás sea una especie de baliza incorporada en la estructura del techo cuya "
"luz se dirige hacia nosotros usando espejos. He oído que algunos templos en "
"el Norte usan ese tipo de truco, por caro que sea."

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1034
msgid "Don’t all these creatures worship darkness, though?"
msgstr "¿No adoran todas estas criaturas a la oscuridad, sin embargo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1043
msgid ""
"That is incorrect. While Uria’s minions on Irdya were mostly Merthiaal "
"worshipers for historical reasons, recently she has—"
msgstr ""
"Eso es incorrecto. Aunque los secuaces de Uria en Irdya eran mayormente "
"adoradores de Merthiaal por razones históricas, recientemente ella ha—"

#. [unit]: type=Lumeril Glyph Mistress, id=Hemérilyel
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1087
msgid "Hemérilyel"
msgstr "Hemérilyel"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1177
msgid "Uria be damned... Why did it have to be you?"
msgstr "Maldita Uria... ¿Por qué tenías que ser tú?"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1209
#, fuzzy
msgid "Demon Lord Hemérilyel"
msgstr "Derrotar a la Señora Demonio Hemérilyel"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1209
msgid "Ascetic Harbinger of Inferno’s Light"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1214
msgid "Vanquish Demon Lord Hemérilyel"
msgstr "Derrotar a la Señora Demonio Hemérilyel"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1241
msgid "Wait... Where did Daeira go?"
msgstr "Espera... ¿Dónde se fue Daeira?"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1246
msgid "Who?"
msgstr "¿Quién?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1251
msgid "The water faerie! She was with us just a few moments ago!"
msgstr "¡La hada del agua! ¡Estaba con nosotros hace solo un momento!"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1256
msgid "Water faerie?"
msgstr "¿Hada del agua?"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1261
msgid "Uh... Did I miss something? I don’t know who you’re talking about."
msgstr "Eh... ¿Me perdí de algo? No sé de quién hablas."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1266
msgid "Argh, never mind! I’ll explain later."
msgstr "¡Argh, no importa! Lo explicaré después."

#. [unstore_unit]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1403
msgid "absorbed damage"
msgstr "daño absorbido"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1416
msgid ""
"Hemérilyel is physically frail, but her magic is too strong. We must destroy "
"her protection glyphs, but that may prove impossible without the assistance "
"of someone who is as versed in the ways of Darkness as she is in the path of "
"Light."
msgstr ""
"Hemérilyel es físicamente frágil, pero su magia es demasiado poderosa. "
"Debemos destruir sus glifos de protección, pero eso puede resultar imposible "
"sin la ayuda de alguien tan versado en los caminos de la Oscuridad como ella "
"en la senda de la Luz."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1427
msgid "Er, why are you looking at me? Perhaps Anya should try instead?"
msgstr ""
"Eh, ¿por qué me miras a mí? ¿Quizás Anya debería intentarlo en su lugar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1529
msgid "It’s working! Anya!"
msgstr "¡Está funcionando! ¡Anya!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1534
msgid "Excellent."
msgstr "Excelente."

#. [message]: speaker=Hemérilyel
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1595
msgid ""
"Is this the game you are playing now, Ergea? Allying yourself with this "
"Irdyan scum so they can die for you?"
msgstr ""
"¿Es este el juego que estás jugando ahora, Ergea? ¿Aliarte con esta escoria "
"irdyana para que mueran por ti?"

#. [message]: speaker=Hemérilyel
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1610
msgid "No... not the darkness... no... please!"
msgstr "No... no a la oscuridad... no... ¡por favor!"

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1765
msgid "Look, it’s another garden!"
msgstr "Mira, ¡es otro jardín!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1771
#, fuzzy
msgid "Huh..."
msgstr "Ungh..."

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1778
msgid ""
"There must be a way to open these walls again— Anya, where are you going?"
msgstr ""
"Debe haber una forma de abrir estas paredes otra vez— Anya, ¿a dónde vas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1807
msgid "I— All right. Durvan, can you help—"
msgstr "Y— Está bien. Durvan, ¿puedes ayudar—"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1819
msgid "Oh, very well, then. I suppose Cron and Igor can help me—"
msgstr "Oh, muy bien entonces. Supongo que Cron e Igor pueden ayudarme—"

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1825
msgid "Oh, very well, then. I suppose Cron can help me—"
msgstr "Oh, muy bien entonces. Supongo que Cron puede ayudarme—"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1888
msgid ""
"This garden cannot physically be here — I fear that it might be an illusion "
"cast by Zhangor."
msgstr ""
"Este jardín no puede estar físicamente aquí — temo que pueda ser una ilusión "
"creada por Zhangor."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. Again, the Fire of Uria is Elyssa.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1894
msgid "Didn’t you say he would be in the citadel fighting the Fire of Uria?"
msgstr ""
"¿No dijiste que estaría en la ciudadela luchando contra el Fuego de Uria?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1899
msgid "More specifically, our Seer said—"
msgstr "Más específicamente, nuestro Vidente dijo—"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1908
msgid "No... That cannot be right."
msgstr "No... Eso no puede ser correcto."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [unit]: id=Zhangor, type=Angel of Blood
#. [hidden_unit]: id=Zhangor, type=Angel of Blood
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1930
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1498
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1859
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2457
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3201
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3564
msgid "Zhangor"
msgstr "Zhangor"

#. [event]: id=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1936
msgid "Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha..."
msgstr "Ja, ja, ja, ja, ja, ja..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1948
msgid "Who is there?!"
msgstr "¿Quién está ahí?!"

#. [event]: id=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1955
msgid "Did you truly think I would not find out about your plans, Ergea?"
msgstr "¿De verdad pensaste que no descubriría tus planes, Ergea?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1963
msgid "Zhangor."
msgstr "Zhangor."

#. [event]: id=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1966
msgid ""
"Did you not know that I have my own informants everywhere throughout "
"Urvatha? Of course I would make sure to subvert the Seer’s prophecy in "
"advance."
msgstr ""
"¿No sabías que tengo mis propios informantes por todo Urvatha? Por supuesto "
"que me aseguraría de subvertir la profecía del Vidente con anticipación."

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1984
msgid "Anya, teleport us away from this place at once."
msgstr "Anya, teletransportanos de este lugar de inmediato."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. "... something blocking my [teleport] power."
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1990
msgid "I can’t! I am trying but there seems to be something—"
msgstr "¡No puedo! Lo estoy intentando, pero parece haber algo—"

#. [event]: id=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1993
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Is it not appalling that the Lady of Light left a poor mixed-blood girl in "
"charge of assisting a disgraced Demon Lord with a death wish? You would "
"expect more common sense from a creature who has lived for so long and seen "
"so much. Then again, she came here seeking her own death."
msgstr ""
"¿No es espantoso que la Dama de la Luz dejara a una pobre niña mestiza a "
"cargo de asistir a un Señor Demonio caído con deseo de muerte? Esperarías "
"más sentido común de una criatura que ha vivido tanto y ha visto tanto. Pero "
"bueno, ella vino aquí buscando su propia muerte."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1997
msgid "... Elynia..."
msgstr "... Elynia..."

#. [event]: id=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:2000
msgid ""
"You want her, don’t you? But her time has already expired, and the dark fire "
"that took her will be extinguished next. I will deal with you all later... "
"assuming anything remains by then."
msgstr ""
"La quieres, ¿verdad? Pero su tiempo ya expiró, y el fuego oscuro que la tomó "
"será extinguido a continuación. Me ocuparé de todos ustedes más tarde... "
"suponiendo que quede algo para entonces."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:2058
msgid "Are those...?"
msgstr "¿Esos son...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:2063
msgid ""
"The same abominations he sent after Elorran. We could not be more unprepared "
"for this encounter."
msgstr ""
"Las mismas abominaciones que envió tras Elorran. No podríamos estar más "
"desprevenidos para este encuentro."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:2068
msgid "(<i>muttering to herself</i>) Elynia, why couldn’t you be here, now..."
msgstr ""
"(<i>murmurando para sí misma</i>) Elynia, ¿por qué no puedes estar aquí, "
"ahora...?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:2116
msgid "<i>... I never thought it would come to this...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... Nunca pensé que esto llegaría a pasar...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:2241
msgid "<i>... Why couldn’t we be together to face the end?</i>"
msgstr "<i>... ¿Por qué no pudimos estar juntos para enfrentar el final?</i>"

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:400
msgid "Breakdown"
msgstr "Colapso"

#. [unit]: type=Armageddon Imp, id=Jeru'unog
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:339
msgid "Jeru’unog"
msgstr "Jeru’unog"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:377
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2168
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2285
msgid "Locate the entrance to the lowest level"
msgstr "Localiza la entrada al nivel más profundo"

#. [event]
#. [event]: id=engineer_backstabbing_hint_handler # wmllint: ignore
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:379
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2170
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2236
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2287
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:400
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1550
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1511
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1852
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2845
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:424
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1144
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1648
msgid "Death of Elyssa"
msgstr "Muerte de Elyssa"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:468
msgid "<i>... The darkness...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... La oscuridad...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:478
msgid "<i>... The silence...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... El silencio...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:488
msgid "<i>... And then...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... Y entonces...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:498
#, fuzzy
msgid "<i>... Pain...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... El dolor...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:508
msgid "<i>... A pain so strong...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... Un dolor tan intenso...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:610
msgid "<big>Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaahhh!</big>"
msgstr "<big>¡Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaahhh!</big>"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:619
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The pain was excruciating. It was absolutely unlike any other pain I had "
"ever felt. My very soul was coming apart at the seams.\n"
"\n"
"I closed my eyes and tried to wake up from what I wished were just a "
"horrible nightmare..."
msgstr ""
"El dolor era insoportable. Era completamente diferente a cualquier otro que "
"hubiera sentido. No era solo un dolor emocional. Mi alma misma se estaba "
"desmoronando.\n"
"\n"
"Cerré los ojos e intenté despertar de lo que deseaba que fuera solo una "
"horrible pesadilla..."

#. [event]
#. 'Glare' is used here in the sense of a powerful light, not some creature's stare.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:648
msgid ""
"... to no avail. Where darkness used to be, there was a powerful eye-"
"piercing glare.\n"
"\n"
"The pain would not go away, no matter what I did. Instead, it was seeping "
"through my veins and growing greater every passing instant. With my mind "
"clouded by the horror, I could only think of one possible form of relief..."
msgstr ""
"... en vano. Donde antes había oscuridad, ahora había un resplandor tan "
"fuerte que hería la vista.\n"
"\n"
"El dolor no se iba, hiciera lo que hiciera. En cambio, se filtraba por mis "
"venas y aumentaba con cada instante que pasaba. Con la mente nublada por el "
"horror, solo podía pensar en una posible forma de alivio..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:664
msgid "Destruction."
msgstr "Destrucción."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:692
msgid ""
"I felt compelled to give in to those dark urges. Perhaps if I released "
"enough energy from my body, the pain would entirely vanish... or the dream "
"world that held me captive would crumble away and I would be released back "
"to reality..."
msgstr ""
"Sentí la necesidad de ceder a esos oscuros impulsos. Quizás, si liberaba "
"suficiente energía de mi cuerpo, el dolor desaparecería por completo... o el "
"mundo onírico que me tenía cautiva se derrumbaría y yo volvería a la "
"realidad..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:734
msgid ""
"My chest continued to burn with that energy. For a moment I considered "
"jumping into the nearby abyss in an attempt to wake up. But that moment was "
"cut short by a familiar presence."
msgstr ""
"Mi pecho seguía ardiendo con esa energía. Por un momento pensé en saltar al "
"abismo cercano para intentar despertar. Pero ese momento se interrumpió con "
"una presencia familiar."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:748
msgid "Could it be?"
msgstr "¿Podría ser?"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:802
msgid "She was there, watching me from a distance, silent, smirking."
msgstr ""
"Ella estaba allí, observándome desde la distancia, en silencio, sonriendo "
"con suficiencia."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:816
msgid ""
"The next thing I knew, I was standing in front of her, about to blast her "
"face like I did to that cave."
msgstr ""
"Lo siguiente que supe fue que estaba frente a ella, a punto de volarle la "
"cara como hice con aquella cueva."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:870
msgid ""
"Your recovery took longer than I expected. Save your energy for later, dear."
msgstr ""
"Tu recuperación tomó más tiempo del que esperaba. Guarda tu energía para "
"después, querida."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:902
msgid "What have you done..."
msgstr "¿Qué has hecho...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:911
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I would greatly prefer that you learned some self-restraint and resisted the "
"temptation to blast everything in sight. Trust me, I have been there — I "
"know what it feels like..."
msgstr ""
"Preferiría mucho que aprendieras un poco de autocontrol y resistieras la "
"tentación de destruir todo lo que ves. Créeme, yo he estado en esa "
"situación… sé cómo se siente..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:924
msgid ""
"... but I will not tolerate such displays of weakness from the predestined "
"Guardian of Earth, and I will not hesitate to rip your heart out of your "
"chest if you fail to show some respect for yourself."
msgstr ""
"... pero no toleraré semejantes muestras de debilidad de la Guardiana de la "
"Tierra predestinada, y no dudaré en arrancarte el corazón del pecho si no "
"demuestras un mínimo de respeto por ti misma."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:933
msgid "... Guardian... of Earth..."
msgstr "... Guardiana... de la Tierra..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:938
msgid ""
"Ah yes, I almost forgot — you are still a stupid and ignorant elf. I still "
"don’t understand how you lived for longer than any of us and yet your "
"awakening has only just taken place. Then again, you were blessed by "
"Iluvia..."
msgstr ""
"Ah, sí, casi lo olvido: sigues siendo una elfa estúpida e ignorante. Aún no "
"comprendo cómo lograste vivir más que cualquiera de nosotros y, sin embargo, "
"tu despertar recién ha ocurrido. Aunque claro, fuiste bendecida por Iluvia..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:951
msgid ""
"Yes, that must be it. The powers conferred by the Union atrophied your heart."
msgstr ""
"Sí, debe ser eso. Los poderes conferidos por la Unión atrofiaron tu corazón."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:960
msgid "... What... am I?"
msgstr "... ¿Qué... soy yo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:965
msgid ""
"An abomination. A creature that violates the laws of nature for the purpose "
"of protecting it in some way. That’s the farce set up by the First Gods. "
"Your energy heart draws from an unlimited power source and provides you with "
"vast potential according to the aspect that Irdya’s seed itself assigned to "
"you: some degree of control over earth, absolute command of the arcane flame "
"and all the creatures whose life force is based on it, and immortality at an "
"inconvenient cost."
msgstr ""
"Una abominación. Una criatura que viola las leyes de la naturaleza con el "
"propósito de protegerla de algún modo. Esa es la farsa creada por los "
"Primeros Dioses. Tu corazón de energía se alimenta de una fuente de poder "
"ilimitada y te concede un potencial vasto según el aspecto que la semilla de "
"Irdya misma te asignó: cierto control sobre la tierra, dominio absoluto "
"sobre la llama arcana y todas las criaturas cuya fuerza vital depende de "
"ella, e inmortalidad a un costo inconveniente."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:974
msgid ""
"Didn’t you ever wonder why no other elves had your unprecedented affinity "
"with the faerie realm? Why your abnormally long life has been an endless "
"strife? Why you could never conceive children? Why every single person you "
"ever loved died?"
msgstr ""
"¿Nunca te preguntaste por qué ningún otro elfo tenía tu afinidad sin "
"precedentes con el reino feérico? ¿Por qué tu vida anormalmente larga ha "
"sido una lucha interminable? ¿Por qué nunca pudiste concebir hijos? ¿Por qué "
"cada una de las personas que alguna vez amaste murió?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:979
msgid "... The necromancer... The necromancer I vanquished..."
msgstr "... El nigromante... El nigromante al que vencí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:984
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Argan told me about that. Just another conceited sorcerer with his mouth "
"full of air in the end. People tend to overestimate the dying words of those "
"skilled in the forbidden arts, mostly out of fear. No, my dear, you were "
"always cursed before even meeting that insignificant necromancer. You could "
"even say Irdya herself cursed you."
msgstr ""
"Argan me habló de eso. Solo otro hechicero engreído con la boca llena de "
"aire, al final. La gente tiende a sobrestimar las palabras de quienes "
"practican las artes prohibidas en su lecho de muerte, en su mayoría por "
"miedo. No, querida mía, siempre estuviste maldita incluso antes de "
"encontrarte con ese nigromante insignificante. Podrías incluso decir que la "
"propia Irdya te maldijo, y no sería del todo inexacto."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:989
msgid ""
"Every guardian that has existed shares your curse. Even I do, in spite of my "
"condition as an unwilling usurper."
msgstr ""
"Cada guardián que ha existido comparte tu maldición. Incluso yo, a pesar de "
"mi condición de usurpadora involuntaria."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:994
msgid "Why did you not kill me?"
msgstr "¿Por qué no me mataste?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:999
msgid ""
"Because that would be a terrible waste of potential. Trust me, I could not "
"wish harder for the day your soul is permanently destroyed, but this is not "
"the most appropriate moment for that."
msgstr ""
"Porque sería un terrible desperdicio de potencial. Créeme, no podría desear "
"con más fuerza el día en que tu alma sea destruida permanentemente, pero "
"este no es el momento más apropiado para eso."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1004
msgid ""
"Ah yes, I forgot to mention that clause... Naturally-born guardians like you "
"awaken once their soul fully merges with their energy heart, and the only "
"way to kill a guardian is through their heart, so... (<i>smirking</i>)"
msgstr ""
"Ah, sí, olvidé mencionar esa cláusula... Los guardianes nacidos de forma "
"natural como tú despiertan una vez que su alma se fusiona por completo con "
"su corazón de energía, y la única forma de matar a un guardián es a través "
"de su corazón, así que... (<i>sonríe con suficiencia</i>)"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1009
msgid "I should destroy you right now. You are the abomination, not me."
msgstr "Debería destruirte ahora mismo. Tú eres la abominación, no yo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1014
msgid ""
"And then who would help you fight our common enemy? Do you even know what "
"turned him into the monster you fought in Wesmere?"
msgstr ""
"¿Y entonces quién te ayudaría a luchar contra nuestro enemigo común? ¿Acaso "
"sabes qué lo convirtió en el monstruo al que enfrentaste en Wesmere?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1019
msgid ""
"Zhangor? Ergea said he is a shapeshifter. Isn’t that the true form of a "
"shapeshifter?"
msgstr ""
"¿Zhangor? Ergea dijo que es un cambiaformas. ¿No es esa la verdadera forma "
"de un cambiaformas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1024
msgid ""
"Ha, ha, your ignorance is as limitless as the powers you will eventually "
"master and use against me. No, shapeshifters do not have a true form beyond "
"that which they individually choose for themselves; granted, they are nearly "
"indistinguishable from humans or elves during childhood."
msgstr ""
"Ja, ja, tu ignorancia es tan ilimitada como los poderes que eventualmente "
"dominarás y usarás contra mí. No, los cambiaformas no tienen una forma "
"verdadera más allá de la que eligen individualmente para sí mismos; claro, "
"durante la infancia son casi indistinguibles de los humanos o los elfos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1029
msgid ""
"Zhangor chose a form that is as hideous as his soul. He might have taken "
"some inspiration from the Gatekeeper he slew in Urvatha — the Gatekeeper "
"whose heart he consumed and absorbed into his body."
msgstr ""
"Zhangor eligió una forma tan horrenda como su alma. Puede que se inspirara "
"en el Guardián de la Puerta al que mató en Urvatha… el Guardián cuyo corazón "
"consumió y absorbió en su cuerpo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1235
msgid ""
"True shapeshifters were never meant to become guardians. Every creature was "
"created in such way they could be eliminated should they represent a peril "
"to the balance of nature, but the oldest shapeshifters defy that rule, as "
"you undoubtedly realized after dealing with Zhangor. Combined with the heart "
"of a guardian, they may also defy the soul clause by turning the entirety of "
"their nigh indestructible bodies into their hearts."
msgstr ""
"Los verdaderos cambiaformas nunca fueron concebidos para convertirse en "
"guardianes. Cada criatura fue creada de tal forma que pudiera ser eliminada "
"si representaba un peligro para el equilibrio de la naturaleza, pero los "
"cambiaformas más antiguos desafían esa regla, como sin duda te diste cuenta "
"después de enfrentarte a Zhangor. Combinados con el corazón de un guardián, "
"también pueden desafiar la cláusula del alma convirtiendo la totalidad de "
"sus casi indestructibles cuerpos en sus corazones."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1251
msgid ""
"We should be thankful that the girl you took under your wing does not have "
"the same grandiose aspirations as our delightful Demon Lord."
msgstr ""
"Deberíamos estar agradecidos de que la niña que tomaste bajo tu protección "
"no tenga las mismas grandiosas aspiraciones que nuestro encantador Señor "
"Demonio."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1263
msgid "Wh— Anya... What is she?"
msgstr "¿Q-Qué… Anya… Qué es ella?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1285
msgid "She is a thing we mistakenly assumed would never exist."
msgstr "Es algo que asumimos por error que nunca podría existir."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1309
msgid "She is the true Guardian of Darkness of the Second Cycle."
msgstr "Es la verdadera Guardiana de la Oscuridad del Segundo Ciclo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1459
msgid ""
"I do not know how she came into existence, seeing as how the seed on Yrathid "
"was said to have been absorbed by Merthiaal. Then again, it is just as "
"troubling that the Uria we all know exists, as well as your counterpart on "
"Silida. Who really knows what was going through the heads of the three "
"goddesses who ended and restarted it all."
msgstr ""
"No sé cómo llegó a existir, considerando que se decía que la semilla en "
"Yrathid había sido absorbida por Merthiaal. Aunque, de igual forma, resulta "
"inquietante que Uria exista, al igual que tu homóloga en Silida. ¿Quién sabe "
"realmente qué pasaba por la cabeza de las tres diosas que terminaron y "
"reiniciaron todo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1562
msgid "There is another Guardian of Earth like me?"
msgstr "¿Hay otra Guardiana de la Tierra como yo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1569
msgid ""
"I would hardly call her such. Her pact with Uria requires her to sit idle in "
"her stupid faerie land being generally useless. Granted, she did secretly "
"guide Argan so we would find you, and so I would ‘kill’ you."
msgstr ""
"Yo no la llamaría así. Su pacto con Uria la obliga a quedarse sentada en su "
"estúpido reino feérico siendo, en general, inútil. Eso sí, ella guio en "
"secreto a Argan para que te encontráramos… y para que yo te ‘matara’."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1574
msgid ""
"It is rather disappointing, really. I am fairly certain she would be a more "
"competent aid than you."
msgstr ""
"Es bastante decepcionante, en realidad. Estoy casi segura de que ella sería "
"una ayuda más competente que tú."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1579
msgid "What do you want me to do?"
msgstr "¿Qué quieres que haga?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1584
msgid ""
"First, we must destroy Zhangor, together. Then, we can decide who gets to "
"inherit Irdya through an old-fashioned duel between just the two of us."
msgstr ""
"Primero, debemos destruir a Zhangor, juntas. Después, podremos decidir quién "
"heredará Irdya con un duelo a la antigua, solo entre nosotras dos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1589
msgid "What... do you intend to do with Anya?"
msgstr "¿Qué… piensas hacer con Anya?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1594
msgid ""
"She can be my apprentice if she wishes. Otherwise, she can live as long as "
"she doesn’t try to interfere with my own plans. "
msgstr ""
"Puede ser mi aprendiz si así lo desea. De lo contrario, podrá vivir mientras "
"no intente interferir con mis propios planes."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1599
msgid ""
"It is said that Uria wants to invade that world, Ethea; that she might find "
"a way to harness the Union, and you intend to sit here and do nothing other "
"than solving your irrelevant quarrel with Zhangor?"
msgstr ""
"Se dice que Uria quiere invadir ese mundo, Ethea; que podría encontrar la "
"forma de aprovechar la Unión, ¿y tú piensas quedarte aquí sin hacer nada más "
"que resolver tu disputa irrelevante con Zhangor?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1604
msgid ""
"It is not as irrelevant as you think. Anyway, Uria has various options to "
"choose from on Ethea, and I suspect she will opt for all of them: the body "
"of the Union, for starters; then there is the Seed of Life, and whoever the "
"goddesses designated as the rightful heiress of the Aspect of Life, if "
"anyone at all. But Uria will not be alone in her quest, for the new Guardian "
"of Water on Norsula also plans business with Ethea. In fact, he is already "
"there."
msgstr ""
"No es tan irrelevante como crees. De todos modos, Uria tiene varias opciones "
"para elegir en Ethea, y sospecho que optará por todas ellas: el cuerpo de la "
"Unión, para empezar; luego está la Semilla de la Vida y, si es que existe, "
"quienquiera que las diosas hayan designado como la legítima heredera del "
"Aspecto de la Vida. Pero Uria no estará sola en su búsqueda, porque el nuevo "
"Guardián del Agua en Norsula también tiene asuntos pendientes con Ethea. De "
"hecho, ya está allí."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1609
msgid ""
"In the worst case, one will win and reshape our reality at their whim. In "
"the best case, they will only manage to destroy themselves along with Ethea. "
"It is pretty pointless to intervene either way. Uria promised to me I would "
"inherit this world before she decided to exhume the present you left for "
"her, and now that she will be too busy confronting the Norsulan and his "
"forces..."
msgstr ""
"En el peor de los casos, uno de ellos ganará y remodelará nuestra realidad a "
"su antojo. En el mejor de los casos, solo conseguirán destruirse a sí mismos "
"junto con Ethea. Es bastante inútil intervenir de cualquier forma. Uria me "
"prometió que heredaría este mundo antes de decidir desenterrar el regalo que "
"le dejaste, y ahora que estará demasiado ocupada enfrentando al norsulano y "
"sus fuerzas…"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1614
msgid ""
"You may call me ignorant and stupid, but I don’t fail to notice you refer to "
"Uria with disdain. What is stopping you from taking her on directly? Have "
"you been on her side all this time merely because you fear her?"
msgstr ""
"Puedes llamarme ignorante y estúpida, pero no dejo de notar que hablas de "
"Uria con desdén. ¿Qué te impide enfrentarte a ella directamente? ¿Has estado "
"de su lado todo este tiempo solo porque le temes?"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1621
msgid ""
"She stood still for a moment, pondering my words. Her reaction was delayed "
"and mechanical; she pushed me with her strange weapon, and both my chest and "
"the weapon’s core glowed with the color of blood. A familiar feeling of void "
"followed. While the pain in my body diminished, I felt weaker and barely "
"able to stand. Still, I could recognize the energy expelled by the artifact."
msgstr ""
"Ella se quedó quieta por un momento, reflexionando sobre mis palabras. Su "
"reacción fue tardía y mecánica; me empujó con su extraña arma, y tanto mi "
"pecho como el núcleo del arma brillaron con el color de la sangre. Siguió "
"una sensación familiar de vacío. Aunque el dolor en mi cuerpo disminuyó, me "
"sentía más débil y apenas podía mantenerme en pie. Aun así, pude reconocer "
"la energía expulsada por el artefacto."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1625
msgid ""
"Do not forget who is in charge, my dear. I can end your life in an instant "
"if you decide to be uncooperative. We are doing this on <i>my</i> terms."
msgstr ""
"No olvides quién manda aquí, querida. Puedo acabar con tu vida en un "
"instante si decides no cooperar. Esto lo haremos en <i>mis</i> términos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1630
msgid "(<i>gasping for air</i>) ... I..."
msgstr "(<i>jadeando</i>) … Yo…"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1635
msgid ""
"And from now on, you shall remain completely silent unless I require you to "
"speak. Do you understand?"
msgstr ""
"Y de ahora en adelante, permanecerás completamente en silencio salvo que yo "
"te pida hablar. ¿Entiendes?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1644
msgid "Of course you do."
msgstr "Por supuesto que sí."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1676
msgid "bind"
msgstr "atar"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1685
msgid "Ugh—"
msgstr "Ugh—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1694
msgid ""
"I forgot to mention that you are also bound to follow me wherever I go, all "
"thanks to a very simple spell. If you attempt to escape you’ll just feel "
"even <i>more</i> pain. And you surely do not want that, do you?"
msgstr ""
"Olvidé mencionar que también estás atada a seguirme a dondequiera que vaya, "
"gracias a un hechizo muy simple. Si intentas escapar, solo sentirás aún "
"<i>más</i> dolor. Y estoy segura de que no quieres eso, ¿verdad?"

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1714
msgid "Potion of Dreadful Taste"
msgstr "Poción de Sabor Horrendo"

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1717
msgid "Yuck!"
msgstr "¡Puaj!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1767
msgid "Why are you attacking me?"
msgstr "¿Por qué me atacas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1782
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Yet another of Zhangor’s tricks. I commend his attention to detail, but "
"turning every single one of my allies against me will not suffice to stop me."
msgstr ""
"Otra de las tretas de Zhangor. Realmente presta atención a los detalles, "
"pero volver a todos mis aliados contra mí no bastará para detenerme."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1791
msgid "The Union was not enough to destroy that demon."
msgstr "La Unión no fue suficiente para destruir a ese demonio."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1796
msgid "I thought I commanded you to remain silent."
msgstr "Creí haber ordenado que permanecieras en silencio."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1805
msgid ""
"If you truly wanted to kill me you would have done so already. You want my "
"help against Zhangor, but there is nothing I can offer that you do not "
"already have. You even have the Ruby of Fire!"
msgstr ""
"Si realmente quisieras matarme, ya lo habrías hecho. Quieres mi ayuda contra "
"Zhangor, pero no hay nada que yo pueda ofrecerte que no tengas ya. ¡Incluso "
"tienes el Rubí de Fuego!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1810
msgid ""
"A weapon. A catalyst of destruction that is much safer to use for our kind "
"than our own inner power. I intend to tear Zhangor apart with it, but the "
"fact that he is a creature of both light and darkness puts me at a "
"disadvantage. To counteract his power I need the assistance of someone well "
"versed in the path of Light, and he knows that; hence he secured the support "
"of Demon Lord Hemérilyel and her subordinates and brought them with him."
msgstr ""
"Un arma. Un catalizador de destrucción mucho más seguro para los de nuestra "
"clase que nuestro propio poder interno. Pienso destrozar a Zhangor con él, "
"pero el hecho de que sea una criatura de luz y oscuridad me pone en "
"desventaja. Para contrarrestar su poder necesito la ayuda de alguien versado "
"en el camino de la Luz, y él lo sabe; por eso aseguró el apoyo de la Señora "
"Demonio Hemérilyel y de sus subordinados, y los trajo con él."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1815
msgid ""
"As the Lady of Light you used to be, you understand the powers of light "
"better than I do, and you control an aspect that is also affiliated with it."
msgstr ""
"Como la Dama de la Luz que fuiste, entiendes los poderes de la luz mejor que "
"yo, y controlas un aspecto que también está afiliado a ella."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1824
msgid ""
"Ergea said I would find a power beneath Kalari that would allow us to turn "
"the tide of war in our favor and purge Uria’s influence from Irdya. Was "
"she... lying?"
msgstr ""
"Ergea dijo que encontraría un poder bajo Kalari que nos permitiría cambiar "
"el curso de la guerra a nuestro favor y purgar la influencia de Uria en "
"Irdya. ¿Estaba… mintiendo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1829
msgid ""
"That demoness asked our Seer many things and failed to understand nearly all "
"of them. About the particular thing you ask, she was... right, in a way."
msgstr ""
"Esa demonio preguntó muchas cosas a nuestra Vidente y no entendió casi "
"ninguna. En cuanto a lo que preguntas, estaba… en lo cierto, de alguna forma."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1834
msgid ""
"The power to end this was always within you, dear. Who knows how things "
"would have turned out if you had healed Argan instead of killing him! The "
"Lady of Light and the Master of Darkness, wielding the Union <i>and</i> the "
"Aspect of Earth against Uria! But since you did not follow that road, you "
"might as well say I am the power you sought."
msgstr ""
"El poder para terminar con esto siempre estuvo dentro de ti, querida. ¡Quién "
"sabe cómo habrían resultado las cosas si hubieras sanado a Argan en vez de "
"matarlo! La Dama de la Luz y el Maestro de la Oscuridad, empuñando la Unión "
"<i>y</i> el Aspecto de la Tierra contra Uria. Pero como no seguiste ese "
"camino, bien puedes decir que yo soy el poder que buscabas."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1843
msgid "You sound decidedly bitter whenever you mention Argan. What is..."
msgstr ""
"Suena como si te llenaras de amargura cada vez que mencionas a Argan. ¿Qué…"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1848
msgid "None of your business. Keep your mouth shut."
msgstr "No es asunto tuyo. Cierra la boca."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1857
msgid "Why do you want Irdya so much?"
msgstr "¿Por qué deseas tanto Irdya?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:1862
msgid "Will you ever stop asking questions?"
msgstr "¿Vas a dejar de hacer preguntas algún día?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2017
msgid ""
"The underground portion of this citadel is larger than you may have "
"suspected, and it can take a whole day to cover it entirely. Teleporting "
"around here is an impossibility since your last intrusion, so we’ll need to "
"create some shortcuts ourselves."
msgstr ""
"La parte subterránea de esta ciudadela es más grande de lo que podrías haber "
"sospechado, y puede tomar un día entero recorrerla por completo. "
"Teletransportarse aquí es imposible desde tu última intrusión, así que "
"tendremos que crear algunos atajos nosotros mismos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2027
msgid "I haven’t done this in a while."
msgstr "Hace tiempo que no hago esto."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2040
msgid ""
"If the demoness’ unsettling grin is any indication, destroying things is as "
"stimulating for her as it is for me. I suppose that is the curse of our "
"kind. What were the First Gods’ intentions when entrusting their precious "
"creation to such flawed stewards?"
msgstr ""
"Si la inquietante sonrisa de la demonio es un indicio, destruir cosas la "
"estimula tanto como a mí. Supongo que esa es la maldición de los de nuestra "
"especie. ¿Cuáles fueron las intenciones de los Primeros Dioses al confiar su "
"preciosa creación a unos guardianes tan defectuosos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2049
msgid "Destroy that wall."
msgstr "Destruye esa pared."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2059
msgid ""
"Excellent. You will eventually learn to focus your energy for more "
"productive purposes."
msgstr ""
"Excelente. Con el tiempo aprenderás a enfocar tu energía para propósitos más "
"productivos."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2065
msgid ""
"That is a vain hope, of course. You really do not believe the elf will ever "
"attain a greater degree of control over her aspect; she is just too "
"incompetent for the burden. You can only wonder why events conspired to make "
"her the heiress of Irdya instead of someone more mentally and emotionally "
"fit."
msgstr ""
"Es una esperanza vana, por supuesto. En realidad no crees que la elfa logre "
"jamás alcanzar un mayor control sobre su aspecto; simplemente es demasiado "
"incompetente para soportar esa carga. Solo puedes preguntarte por qué los "
"acontecimientos conspiraron para hacerla la heredera de Irdya en vez de a "
"alguien más capacitado mental y emocionalmente."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2107
msgid ""
"That crack was not there before. But it matters little — we can continue "
"descending by our own means. There is another corridor right below this area "
"if I’m not mistaken..."
msgstr ""
"Esa grieta no estaba ahí antes. Pero importa poco: podemos seguir "
"descendiendo por nuestros propios medios. Hay otro pasillo justo debajo de "
"esta zona, si no me equivoco..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2122
msgid ""
"That should do just fine. There is an underground river just adjacent to the "
"corridor that we can follow."
msgstr ""
"Eso servirá perfectamente. Hay un río subterráneo junto al pasillo que "
"podemos seguir."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2152
msgid ""
"This passage leads to another corridor where we will surely find more "
"opposition. It might be a good idea to summon some help to clear the path "
"ahead."
msgstr ""
"Este pasaje conduce a otro corredor donde seguramente encontraremos más "
"oposición. Podría ser buena idea invocar ayuda para despejar el camino."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2164
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Elyssa can now summon <b>Fire Wraiths</b> on any unoccupied tiles adjacent "
"to her."
msgstr ""
"Elyssa ahora puede invocar Espíritus de Fuego junto a Elynia sin importar la "
"distancia entre ambas."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeru'unog
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2209
msgid "Cowards! The Fire must be extinguished for her betrayal! Go, find her!"
msgstr ""
"¡Cobardes! ¡El Fuego debe extinguirse por su traición! ¡Vamos, encuéntrenla!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2214
msgid ""
"That must be yet another of those minor Demon Lords. I wonder what kind of "
"story Zhangor made up for them."
msgstr ""
"Debe ser otro de esos Señores Demonio menores. Me pregunto qué clase de "
"historia les habrá inventado Zhangor."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2219
msgid "You <i>are</i> betraying Uria by plotting against Zhangor."
msgstr "<i>Estás</i> traicionando a Uria al conspirar contra Zhangor."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2224
msgid ""
"Only if she wants to put it in that light. Ergea explained to you how the "
"succession system works on Urvatha; did you forget?"
msgstr ""
"Sólo si ella quiere verlo de esa manera. Ergea te explicó cómo funciona el "
"sistema de sucesión en Urvatha; ¿lo has olvidado?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2229
msgid ""
"Not really. But I would appreciate it if you stopped reading my thoughts and "
"memories at every opportunity."
msgstr ""
"No, en realidad. Pero agradecería que dejaras de leer mis pensamientos y "
"recuerdos a cada oportunidad."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2234
msgid "Vanquish Demon Lord Jeru’unog"
msgstr "Derrota al Señor Demonio Jeru’unog"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeru'unog
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2256
msgid "Defeated by a faerie and a human! How can this be?"
msgstr "¡Derrotado por un hada y un humano! ¿Cómo puede ser?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2268
msgid "I am <b>not</b> human."
msgstr "<b>No</b> soy humana."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2336
msgid ""
"... So, you obtain the power of a god and still manage to drag your feet all "
"over the place for an eternity? Seriously? You don’t even walk!"
msgstr ""
"... Así que obtienes el poder de un dios y aun así logras arrastrar los pies "
"por todas partes durante una eternidad. ¿En serio? ¡Ni siquiera caminas!"

