msgstr "noctum"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:968
msgid ""
"Xia’el, the Guardian of Earth. Her First Cycle self, to be precise. Don’t "
"feel too intimidated by her stature, though — I very much doubt this is to "
"scale."
msgstr ""
"Xia’el, la Guardiana de la Tierra. Su yo del Primer Ciclo, para ser "
"precisos. Pero no te intimides demasiado por su tamaño — dudo mucho que esté "
"a escala."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:973
msgid "She is... she was a faerie? I am not sure what I was expecting."
msgstr "¿Ella es... era una hada? No estoy segura de qué esperaba."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:978
msgid ""
"Big shoes to fill? Then again, it looks like neither of you have ever worn "
"shoes for reasons that are surely beyond my ability to comprehend. And "
"again, most likely not to scale."
msgstr ""
"¿Zapatos grandes que llenar? Aunque parece que ninguna de ustedes ha usado "
"zapatos nunca, por razones que seguramente escapan a mi comprensión. Y, de "
"nuevo, probablemente no esté a escala."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:983
msgid ""
"No, I mean... She looks so beautiful and dignified... but at the same time, "
"she is... so..."
msgstr ""
"No, quiero decir... se ve tan hermosa y digna... pero al mismo tiempo, es... "
"tan..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:988
msgid ""
"Mundane? By now you should know gods come in all shapes and sizes. Although "
"anyone can play god to a sufficiently ignorant crowd."
msgstr ""
"¿Común? A estas alturas deberías saber que los dioses vienen en todas las "
"formas y tamaños. Aunque cualquiera puede hacerse pasar por dios ante una "
"multitud suficientemente ignorante."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:993
msgid "I suppose you would know about that kind of thing."
msgstr "Supongo que sabes de ese tipo de cosas."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:998
msgid ""
"You don’t need miracles, prophecies or mind control to rule over uncivilized "
"brutes. You just need to establish clear boundaries and show your subjects "
"the consequences for stepping out of line. Sooner or later someone will test "
"your power regardless, so there is little point to claiming godhood unless "
"you want to paint an even larger target on your back."
msgstr ""
"No necesitas milagros, profecías o control mental para gobernar sobre brutos "
"incivilizados. Solo debes establecer límites claros y mostrar a tus súbditos "
"las consecuencias de cruzarlos. Tarde o temprano alguien pondrá a prueba tu "
"poder de todos modos, así que no tiene mucho sentido proclamarse dios a "
"menos que quieras pintar un blanco aún más grande en tu espalda."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1003
msgid ""
"Ignoring the entire Uria situation for a moment, what this world needs right "
"now is not another false god. It just needs someone able to purge all the "
"scum and build a new order from the ground up. If that someone happens to "
"have god-like powers, then the job should be certainly much easier. But it "
"does not have to be like that."
msgstr ""
"Ignorando toda la situación de Uria por un momento, lo que este mundo "
"necesita ahora mismo no es otro dios falso. Solo necesita a alguien capaz de "
"purgar toda la escoria y construir un nuevo orden desde cero. Si esa persona "
"tiene poderes divinos, el trabajo seguramente será mucho más fácil. Pero no "
"tiene que ser así."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1011
msgid ""
"You don’t need to play the role of the Guardian of Earth if that’s not what "
"you want."
msgstr ""
"No necesitas desempeñar el papel de Guardiana de la Tierra si no es lo que "
"quieres."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1021
msgid "I can feel the question lingering in the back of your head."
msgstr "Puedo sentir la pregunta que te ronda en la cabeza."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1030
msgid ""
"When my mentor realized the true nature of the Sceptre of Fire, she asked me "
"to wield it against the enemies of Irdya... with her dying breath."
msgstr ""
"Cuando mi mentora comprendió la verdadera naturaleza del Cetro de Fuego, me "
"pidió que lo empuñara contra los enemigos de Irdya... con su último aliento."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1035
msgid ""
"This cursed artifact is bad for your health. You must not use it ever again."
msgstr ""
"Este artefacto maldito es malo para tu salud. No debes usarlo nunca más."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1040
msgid "I just said—"
msgstr "Acabo de decir—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1045
msgid ""
"You can say anything you want, but it does nothing to change the fact that "
"you are a creature of Light trying to wield a power that is harmful to your "
"mind and soul."
msgstr ""
"Puedes decir lo que quieras, pero eso no cambia el hecho de que eres una "
"criatura de la Luz intentando manejar un poder que es dañino para tu mente y "
"alma."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1050
msgid "Niryone’s staff rightfully belongs to me—"
msgstr "El bastón de Niryone me pertenece legítimamente—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1055
msgid ""
"I assure you, the <i>thing</i> lurking beneath the Ruby’s lustrous surface "
"does not care for any sentimental attachment you may have to it. Your "
"mentor’s intentions may have been noble, but if you want to save Irdya you "
"are going to have to learn to let go of the past and not waste your "
"potential living an eternal life of regret."
msgstr ""
"Te aseguro que la <i>cosa</i> que acecha bajo la lustrosa superficie del "
"Rubí no se preocupa por ningún apego sentimental que tengas hacia él. Las "
"intenciones de tu mentora pudieron ser nobles, pero si quieres salvar Irdya "
"tendrás que aprender a dejar el pasado atrás y no desperdiciar tu potencial "
"viviendo una vida eterna de arrepentimiento."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1060
msgid ""
"If you truly want to honor her memory... if you want to make your friends’ "
"sacrifices worth it, then it is time for you to become the Guardian of Earth "
"we need instead of the Lady of Light who lost to her own Darkness. But if "
"you don’t feel up to the task then you are free to stay behind, drowning in "
"an endless ocean of sorrow for what little is left of eternity."
msgstr ""
"Si realmente quieres honrar su memoria... si quieres que los sacrificios de "
"tus amigos valgan la pena, entonces es hora de que te conviertas en la "
"Guardiana de la Tierra que necesitamos en vez de la Dama de la Luz que "
"perdió contra su propia Oscuridad. Pero si no te sientes capaz, eres libre "
"de quedarte atrás, ahogándote en un océano interminable de tristeza por lo "
"poco que queda de la eternidad."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1132
msgid ""
"Hm. He is not here like I expected. I suppose his intention is to make some "
"kind of dramatic entrance later."
msgstr ""
"Hm. No está aquí como esperaba. Supongo que su intención es hacer algún tipo "
"de entrada dramática más tarde."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1137
msgid "Elynia, there is something here you should see."
msgstr "Elynia, hay algo aquí que deberías ver."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1142
msgid ""
"Move Elynia and Elyssa to (28, 20) and the immediately adjacent locations"
msgstr "Mueve a Elynia y Elyssa a (28, 20) y a las ubicaciones adyacentes."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1294
msgid "What is that in the middle of the blood lake?"
msgstr "¿Qué es eso en el medio del lago de sangre?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1308
msgid ""
"The Seed of Earth, the place from which all life on Irdya originally sprang."
msgstr ""
"La Semilla de la Tierra, el lugar del que brotó originalmente toda la vida "
"en Irdya."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1314
msgid ""
"It is currently sealed in its chamber. There is not much that can be done "
"with it by anyone other than the Guardian of Earth. Generally speaking, "
"nobody is supposed to see or tamper with the thing that lays within; not "
"even the controlling Guardian herself. That is to say, not even you."
msgstr ""
"Actualmente está sellada en su cámara. No hay mucho que pueda hacerse con "
"ella salvo por la Guardiana de la Tierra. En términos generales, nadie "
"debería ver ni alterar lo que yace dentro; ni siquiera la propia Guardiana "
"que la controla. Es decir, ni siquiera tú."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1320
msgid ""
"... Unless, of course, you wanted to reset life on Irdya back to the "
"beginning. That is how the Second Cycle was started. But if you did that, "
"then every living or non-living creature currently standing on this world "
"would be erased from existence — even you."
msgstr ""
"... A menos, claro, que quisieras reiniciar la vida en Irdya desde el "
"principio. Así fue como comenzó el Segundo Ciclo. Pero si hicieras eso, "
"entonces toda criatura viva o no viva que existe actualmente en este mundo "
"sería borrada de la existencia — incluso tú."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1325
msgid ""
"Doing that would destroy Zhangor for sure, but Uria is not on Irdya, and the "
"loss would be little more than a minor inconvenience to her in the long "
"term. But if you feel particularly selfish about your pitiful existence, "
"this is an option for you to consider."
msgstr ""
"Hacer eso destruiría a Zhangor con seguridad, pero Uria no está en Irdya, y "
"la pérdida no sería más que una leve molestia para ella a largo plazo. Pero "
"si te sientes particularmente egoísta con respecto a tu patética existencia, "
"esta es una opción a considerar."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1334
msgid "That would be a coward’s choice, don’t you think?"
msgstr "Sería una elección cobarde, ¿no lo crees?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1339
msgid ""
"Possibly. But if the guardian in question feared the absolute end of their "
"own existence, then one could say that making the choice would take some "
"degree of courage."
msgstr ""
"Posiblemente. Pero si la guardiana en cuestión temiera el fin absoluto de su "
"propia existencia, entonces se podría decir que tomar esa decisión "
"requeriría cierto grado de valentía."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1348
msgid "What is your choice?"
msgstr "¿Cuál es tu elección?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1357
msgid "Do not worry, it is not a binding decision, yet."
msgstr "No te preocupes, aún no es una decisión definitiva."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1362
msgid ""
"Is that the only possible use for the power stored in this place? To destroy "
"all life in our world so it can start anew?"
msgstr ""
"¿Es ese el único uso posible para el poder almacenado en este lugar? "
"¿Destruir toda la vida en nuestro mundo para que pueda comenzar de nuevo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1367
msgid ""
"If Merthiaal’s cautionary story is any indication, yes. But Uria believes "
"otherwise. She believes that the seeds can be used for other things if the "
"aspect you control is either Life or Existence, based on the efforts of her "
"predecessor — or the very unreliable information we have about them, anyway. "
"But her attempts to find the seed on Urvatha have proven fruitless so far, "
"and her patience is wearing thin. As ludicrous as it sounds, she no longer "
"wants to find <i>just</i> the Body of the Union on Ethea."
msgstr ""
"Si la historia de advertencia de Merthiaal sirve de indicación, sí. Pero "
"Uria cree lo contrario. Cree que las semillas pueden usarse para otras cosas "
"si el aspecto que controlas es Vida o Existencia, según los esfuerzos de su "
"predecesor —o la información poco fiable que tenemos sobre ellos, en todo "
"caso. Pero sus intentos de encontrar la semilla en Urvatha han sido "
"infructuosos hasta ahora, y su paciencia se está agotando. Por absurdo que "
"parezca, ya no quiere encontrar <i>solo</i> el Cuerpo de la Unión en Ethea."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1372
msgid "I see. Then, there is no point in doing anything with ours."
msgstr "Ya veo. Entonces, no tiene sentido hacer nada con la nuestra."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1377
msgid ""
"I suppose. There is so much we still don’t know about our own creation..."
msgstr "Supongo. Hay tanto que aún no sabemos sobre nuestra propia creación..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1382
msgid ""
"Come to think of it, we should be thankful that Delethia’s actions ensured "
"we would not get a proper Guardian of Existence for this cycle who could "
"turn out to be an even more powerful deranged psychopath than Uria. Well, "
"probably. That girl, Anya... her sole existence raises many questions we "
"thought we had already answered."
msgstr ""
"Ahora que lo pienso, deberíamos agradecer que las acciones de Delethia "
"garantizaran que no tuviéramos una verdadera Guardiana de la Existencia en "
"este ciclo, que podría resultar ser una psicópata aún más poderosa y demente "
"que Uria. Bueno, probablemente. Esa chica, Anya... su mera existencia "
"plantea muchas preguntas que creíamos ya resueltas."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1410
msgid ""
"... But of course. The bastard’s plans aren’t as aligned with Uria’s own as "
"I originally thought."
msgstr ""
"... Pero por supuesto. Los planes de ese bastardo no están tan alineados con "
"los de Uria como pensaba originalmente."

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1523
msgid ""
"What a glorious day for Irdya! So, at long last, Argan’s little girl solved "
"the puzzle!"
msgstr ""
"¡Qué día tan glorioso para Irdya! Así que, al fin, la pequeña de Argan "
"resolvió el acertijo."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1552
msgid "You are a disgusting liar and a traitor, Zhangor."
msgstr "Eres un mentiroso repugnante y un traidor, Zhangor."

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1581
msgid ""
"Excellent. That makes us equals in the eyes of the Lady of Light. Or should "
"I now call her the Guardian of Earth on Irdya?"
msgstr ""
"Excelente. Eso nos hace iguales a los ojos de la Dama de la Luz. ¿O debería "
"llamarla ahora la Guardiana de la Tierra en Irdya?"

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1590
msgid ""
"Ah yes, Elynia... I have not forgotten what you and Argan did to me. Do you "
"have any idea what it feels like to live for hundreds of years in agonizing "
"pain with your limbs scattered across the land and buried deep in the "
"ground? Do you?"
msgstr ""
"Ah, sí, Elynia... No he olvidado lo que tú y Argan me hicieron. ¿Tienes idea "
"de lo que se siente vivir durante cientos de años en un dolor agonizante, "
"con tus miembros esparcidos por la tierra y enterrados profundamente en el "
"suelo? ¿La tienes?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1595
msgid ""
"You’ve got nothing to fear; this time I shall make sure <i>nothing</i> "
"remains of your wretched body for Uria to bring back."
msgstr ""
"No tienes nada que temer; esta vez me aseguraré de que <i>nada</i> quede de "
"tu miserable cuerpo para que Uria lo devuelva."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1600
msgid "And I shall make sure your soul is destroyed forever as well."
msgstr "Y yo me aseguraré de que tu alma también sea destruida para siempre."

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1605
msgid "Without the Union? Go ahead, try your best!"
msgstr "¿Sin la Unión? Adelante, ¡haz tu mejor intento!"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1643
#, fuzzy
msgid "Demon Lord Zhangor"
msgstr "Derrota al Señor Demonio Zhangor"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1643
#, fuzzy
msgid "Angel of Blood, Scourge of Irdya"
msgstr "Ángel de Sangre"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1646
msgid "Vanquish Demon Lord Zhangor"
msgstr "Derrota al Señor Demonio Zhangor"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1653
msgid ""
"Zhangor’s Gatekeeper powers allow him to debilitate and destroy the Energy "
"Heart of a Guardian"
msgstr ""
"Los poderes de Guardián de Zhangor le permiten debilitar y destruir el "
"Corazón de Energía de un Guardián."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1966
msgid "What are you trying to do now?"
msgstr "¿Qué intentas hacer ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1983
msgid ""
"His body is affixed to the ground, just avoid getting hit by his lightning!"
msgstr ""
"Su cuerpo está fijado al suelo, ¡simplemente evita ser alcanzado por sus "
"rayos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2267
msgid ""
"Oh, is that what we are doing now, Zhangor? I expected you to be more "
"creative than this in a real fight."
msgstr ""
"Ah, ¿eso es lo que vamos a hacer ahora, Zhangor? Esperaba que fueras más "
"creativo que esto en un combate real."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2375
msgid "Destroying these things is increasing my power somehow..."
msgstr "Destruir estas cosas está aumentando mi poder de alguna forma..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2380
msgid ""
"There is something about the energy released by these cores, although I have "
"a feeling Zhangor benefits from it as well."
msgstr ""
"Hay algo en la energía liberada por estos núcleos, aunque tengo la sensación "
"de que Zhangor también se beneficia de ello."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2490
msgid "Oh dear gods, will this ever stop?"
msgstr "Oh, dioses, ¿acaso esto no terminará nunca?"

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2499
msgid ""
"What is the matter, Guardians? Do you fear killing those of your own kin "
"now? Have you not become accustomed to it over the course of your pathetic "
"lives?"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué sucede, guardianas? ¿Ahora temen matar a los de su propia especie? "
"¿Acaso no se han acostumbrado a ello a lo largo de sus patéticas vidas?"

#. [case]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2594
#: After_the_Storm/macros/character-defines.cfg:8
msgid "Galas"
msgstr "Galas"

#. [case]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2614
msgid "Delanith-Isáwen"
msgstr "Delanith-Isáwen"

#. [case]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2620
msgid "Reghara"
msgstr "Reghara"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. This sentence could be interpreted in two different ways; either Elyssa
#. is stating that she wouldn't want to kill the real Anya, or that she
#. does not necessarily consider the real Anya to be the real Guardian of
#. Darkness, and hence she might not hesitate in killing her. This
#. ambiguity is intentional.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2749
msgid ""
"I would hate to have to kill you... if you were the real Guardian of "
"Darkness."
msgstr ""
"Odiaría tener que matarte... si fueras la verdadera Guardiana de la "
"Oscuridad."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2756
msgid "You abandoned me..."
msgstr "Me abandonaste..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. ‘Demon’ here refers to Zhangor.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2764
msgid "Posing as my dearest friend will not save you from my wrath, demon!"
msgstr ""
"Hacerse pasar por mi amiga más querida no te salvará de mi ira, demonio."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2775
msgid "You left me to die..."
msgstr "Me dejaste morir..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2782
msgid "Your imitation of Argan is once again absolutely pathetic."
msgstr "Tu imitación de Argan es una vez más absolutamente patética."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2789
msgid "You betrayed me..."
msgstr "Me traicionaste..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2796
msgid "This cheap trick will not break me down this time."
msgstr "Este truco barato no me derrumbará esta vez."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2807
msgid "You killed me..."
msgstr "Me mataste..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2814
msgid ""
"I could slaughter a whole host of these stupid elves a thousand times, "
"Zhangor. Is this all you’ve got?"
msgstr ""
"Podría masacrar a todo un ejército de estos estúpidos elfos mil veces, "
"Zhangor. ¿Es esto todo lo que tienes?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2821
msgid "You failed to protect me..."
msgstr "No lograste protegerme..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2828
msgid "I no longer care for any of this, Zhangor. I no longer care."
msgstr "Ya no me importa nada de esto, Zhangor. Ya no me importa."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2839
msgid ""
"You are no small part of the cause of my departure from this world, you know."
msgstr ""
"No eres una parte menor de la causa de mi partida de este mundo, ¿lo sabías?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2846
msgid "I could not care less about a walking joke like you."
msgstr "No podría importarme menos un chiste andante como tú."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2853
msgid "You could have prevented my death, Elynia. You could have—"
msgstr "Podrías haber evitado mi muerte, Elynia. Podrías haber—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2860
msgid "No... there was nothing I could do. Stop this!"
msgstr "No... no había nada que pudiera hacer. ¡Detén esto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. 'Her' refers to Elynia.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2875
msgid "I assume you are important to her in some way?"
msgstr "Supongo que eres importante para ella de algún modo."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2882
msgid ""
"... You were too late to save me, Elynia. If only you had not allowed him "
"into your heart—"
msgstr ""
"... Llegaste demasiado tarde para salvarme, Elynia. Si tan solo no le "
"hubieras permitido entrar en tu corazón—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2889
msgid "NO! I don’t want to remember this! I’LL KILL YOU!"
msgstr "¡NO! ¡No quiero recordar esto! ¡VOY A MATARTE!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2900
msgid ""
"With your power you surely could have banished those foul creatures to "
"whence they came. Useless child."
msgstr ""
"Con tu poder, seguramente podrías haber desterrado a esas viles criaturas al "
"lugar de donde vinieron. Niña inútil."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2907
msgid "... You peered into places you shouldn’t have, Zhangor."
msgstr "... Husmeaste en lugares donde no debiste, Zhangor."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2914
msgid "I wonder what became of my kind under your command..."
msgstr "Me pregunto qué fue de los míos bajo tu mando..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2932
msgid "HA! I hope you enjoyed your stay with us, sweetheart."
msgstr "¡JA! Espero que hayas disfrutado tu estancia con nosotros, querida."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2939
msgid "I’LL KILL YOU!"
msgstr "¡VOY A MATARTE!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. Use your imagination here. See also E3S7A.2's intro text.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2947
msgid ""
"You must feel proud of yourself, allying with a mass-murderer like this c—"
msgstr ""
"Debes sentirte orgullosa de ti misma, aliándote con un asesino en masa como "
"este h—"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2954
msgid "That couldn’t possibly be my own memory... I don’t think..."
msgstr "Eso no podría ser un recuerdo mío... o al menos eso creo..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2965
msgid ""
"For someone who wants so much to stop Uria, you are hardly any different "
"from her kind."
msgstr ""
"Para alguien que tanto desea detener a Uria, no eres muy diferente a los de "
"su clase."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2972
msgid "... You are not wrong."
msgstr "... No te equivocas."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2979
msgid ""
"Taking advantage of my protégé’s heart so soon after my death... You truly "
"are a shameless creature."
msgstr ""
"Aprovechándote del corazón de mi protegida tan pronto después de mi "
"muerte... Realmente eres una criatura sin vergüenza."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2986
msgid "I’ve had enough. You will not break me again."
msgstr "Ya tuve suficiente. No volverás a romperme."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3000
msgid "... Is this..."
msgstr "... ¿Es esto...?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3007
msgid "Child..."
msgstr "Hija..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3014
msgid "M— mother...? No... NO! STOP!"
msgstr "M— ¿madre...? No... ¡NO! ¡DETENTE!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3034
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3040
msgid ""
"They are manifestations of Zhangor’s will — not even real shapeshifters!"
msgstr ""
"Son manifestaciones de la voluntad de Zhangor… ¡ni siquiera son cambiaformas "
"reales!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3175
msgid "Brace yourself!"
msgstr "¡Prepárate!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3249
msgid "Wh— what is... happening to him..."
msgstr "Q-q-qué... le está pasando..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3254
msgid "This is getting out of hand. We need to defeat him here and now!"
msgstr "Esto se está saliendo de control. ¡Debemos derrotarlo aquí y ahora!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3259
msgid "... to his body..."
msgstr "... a su cuerpo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3270
msgid "Elyssa? Are you still with me?"
msgstr "¿Elyssa? ¿Sigues conmigo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3279
msgid ""
"Is this... Is this the fate of our kind should we allow emotions to "
"overpower our minds?"
msgstr ""
"¿Es esto... el destino de nuestra especie si permitimos que las emociones "
"dominen nuestras mentes?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3289
msgid ""
"No... Zhangor devoured the heart of a Gatekeeper. He became like this of his "
"own volition. Focus, Elyssa."
msgstr ""
"No... Zhangor devoró el corazón de un Guardián. Se volvió así por su propia "
"voluntad. Concéntrate, Elyssa."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3300
msgid "FOCUS!"
msgstr "¡CONCÉNTRATE!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3398
msgid "He’s preparing to unleash a devastating attack, watch out!"
msgstr "¡Se está preparando para desatar un ataque devastador, cuidado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3538
msgid "... You... CANNOT..."
msgstr "... Tú... NO PUEDES..."

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3585
msgid "... destroy ME..."
msgstr "... destruirme a MÍ..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3612
msgid "Do you think we can do it? He should not be able to focus us anymore!"
msgstr ""
"¿Crees que podemos lograrlo? ¡Ya no debería poder concentrarse en nosotros!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3617
msgid "No... I’m not ready yet! Just keep striking at him with all you have!"
msgstr ""
"No... ¡Aún no estoy lista! ¡Solo sigue atacándolo con todo lo que tengas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3622
msgid "(<i>feminine voice</i>) ... I am... the Angel of Blood..."
msgstr "(<i>voz femenina</i>) ... Soy... el Ángel de la Sangre..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3742
msgid ""
"You are nothing but a sad memory of who you once were. It seems Uria did not "
"do such a good job in bringing you back from your grave."
msgstr ""
"No eres más que un triste recuerdo de lo que alguna vez fuiste. Parece que "
"Uria no hizo tan buen trabajo al traerte de tu tumba."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:3749
msgid ""
"Perhaps she was aware that you would eventually betray her. Or perhaps she "
"did not have the same infatuation she had with Argan."
msgstr ""
"Quizás ella sabía que eventualmente la traicionarías. O quizás no tenía la "
"misma fascinación que tuvo con Argan."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4006
msgid "What I do know for sure..."
msgstr "Lo que sé con certeza..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4039
msgid "... is that you are done. Elynia!"
msgstr "... es que ya terminaste. ¡Elynia!"

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#. 'He' is intended to be used in the sense of a deity here.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4076
msgid "(<i>feminine voice</i>) ... He will come for you... at the end..."
msgstr "(<i>voz femenina</i>) ... Él vendrá por ti... al final..."

#. [message]: speaker=Zhangor
#. 'Him' also as a deity here.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4093
msgid "(<i>feminine voice</i>) ... the Four will not suffice to defeat Him..."
msgstr ""
"(<i>voz femenina</i>) ... Los Cuatro no serán suficientes para derrotarlo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4102
msgid "Pierce into the heart of stone..."
msgstr "Penetra en el corazón de la piedra..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4132
msgid "... release the soul back to the void..."
msgstr "... libera el alma de regreso al vacío..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4147
msgid "... break the curse of Yarae..."
msgstr "... rompe la maldición de Yarae..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4170
msgid "... dispel the spirit from this world."
msgstr "... disipa el espíritu de este mundo."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [side]: type=Guardian of Earth Aradellys, id=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4275
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:221
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:60
msgid "Aradellys"
msgstr "Aradellys"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:4277
msgid "<i>It is all well, children of Irdya. You may rest now.</i>"
msgstr "<i>Todo está bien, hijos de Irdya. Ahora pueden descansar.</i>"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:334
msgid "Rise up, Elynia-Thanadria, Guardian of Earth."
msgstr "Levántate, Elynia-Thanadria, Guardiana de la Tierra."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:369
msgid ""
"You and the heiress of the First Guardian of Darkness have much work left to "
"do."
msgstr ""
"Tú y la heredera de la Primera Guardiana de la Oscuridad aún tienen mucho "
"trabajo por delante."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:388
msgid "I am here."
msgstr "Estoy aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:397
msgid "Have I mentioned yet how much I despise you?"
msgstr "¿Ya te he dicho cuánto te detesto?"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:420
msgid ""
"Dear Anya,\n"
"\n"
"I am sure that by the time you find the glyph containing this encoded "
"message you will have won the battle on the surface and proven yourself "
"worthy of your title as the Lost Guardian of Darkness on Irdya. I am also "
"certain that Ergea will have finally revealed to you the destiny that was "
"laid for me by the will of our creators.\n"
"\n"
"You will surely know by then as well what Uria’s plan entails for all of us. "
"As Elorran said, Irdya is not the only world at peril.\n"
"\n"
"There are many other worlds like ours which will be similarly wiped from "
"existence if Uria gets hold of the Body of the Union and the Seed of Life on "
"Ethea."
msgstr ""
"Querida Anya:\n"
"\n"
"Estoy segura de que, para cuando encuentres el glifo que contiene este "
"mensaje codificado, habrás ganado la batalla en la superficie y demostrado "
"ser digna de tu título como la Guardiana Perdida de la Oscuridad en Irdya. "
"También estoy convencida de que Ergea finalmente te habrá revelado el "
"destino que me fue impuesto por la voluntad de nuestros creadores.\n"
"\n"
"Para entonces, seguramente también sabrás lo que implica el plan de Uria "
"para todos nosotros. Como dijo Elorran, Irdya no es el único mundo en "
"peligro.\n"
"\n"
"Hay muchos otros mundos como el nuestro que serán borrados de la existencia "
"si Uria consigue el Cuerpo de la Unión y la Semilla de la Vida en Ethea."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:472
msgid ""
"Our mission is to stop Uria at all costs.\n"
"\n"
"We know that not all of the worlds seeded to have a Guardian have reached "
"maturity yet. We know that Ethea might not have its own Guardian of Life "
"yet. But it is our hope that we might be able to find her before Uria "
"herself does, and ensure that we have a chance to stop her somehow. We know "
"that the Guardian of Water from Norsula has arrived there, and may have "
"already seized its seed. Our main concern for the moment is finding the real "
"heiress of Uria on Ethea, and the Body of the Union. Unfortunately for us, "
"we do not know much about Ethea or where to begin our search."
msgstr ""
"Nuestra misión es detener a Uria a toda costa.\n"
"\n"
"Sabemos que no todos los mundos sembrados para tener un Guardián han "
"alcanzado aún su madurez. Sabemos que Ethea quizá no tenga todavía su propia "
"Guardiana de la Vida. Pero esperamos poder encontrarla antes que Uria misma, "
"y asegurar así que tengamos una oportunidad de detenerla de algún modo. "
"Sabemos que la Guardiana del Agua de Norsula ha llegado allí, y puede que ya "
"haya tomado su semilla. Por el momento, nuestra principal preocupación es "
"encontrar a la verdadera heredera de Uria en Ethea y el Cuerpo de la Unión. "
"Por desgracia para nosotros, sabemos poco sobre Ethea o por dónde comenzar "
"nuestra búsqueda."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:485
msgid ""
"Sitting idly here on Irdya would not accomplish anything for the continuance "
"of our existence. According to Elyssa, and the Guardian of Earth on Silida, "
"my work here is complete. Irdya has slowly come back to life over the last "
"few centuries, a feat which would have been impossible without my presence.\n"
"\n"
"I have seen both life and destruction take place since I was woken up from "
"my slumber. Darkness has been an opposing force for very long, but as Mal "
"Keshar, Anlindë, and Elyssa herself proved to me, it can also be "
"revitalizing for a world that needs the means to protect itself from two "
"scorching suns and the malignant forces that broke the previous balance."
msgstr ""
"Quedarme ociosa aquí en Irdya no lograría nada para la continuidad de "
"nuestra existencia. Según Elyssa y la Guardiana de la Tierra en Silida, mi "
"labor aquí ha concluido. Irdya ha ido recuperando lentamente la vida durante "
"los últimos siglos, una hazaña que habría sido imposible sin mi presencia.\n"
"\n"
"He visto tanto la vida como la destrucción desplegarse desde que desperté de "
"mi letargo. La oscuridad ha sido una fuerza opuesta durante muy largo "
"tiempo, pero como Mal Keshar, Anlindë y la propia Elyssa me demostraron, "
"también puede ser revitalizante para un mundo que necesita medios para "
"protegerse de dos soles abrasadores y de las fuerzas malignas que rompieron "
"el equilibrio anterior."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:593
msgid ""
"The impenetrable darkness currently shrouding Irdya protects it from the "
"gaze of the Seer of Uria, but if it lasts for too long, all life on Irdya "
"will end as well.\n"
"\n"
"While Elyssa was previously responsible for this barrier within the "
"frontiers of the Chaos Empire, the power that recently extended it far and "
"beyond is not hers. It is yours.\n"
"\n"
"I never got the chance to speak to you about these matters because of how "
"distant I became ever since I had to kill Argan. I thought that opening up "
"and letting others into my life could only cause more harm to them.\n"
"\n"
"But I finally realized that this did not solve anything. By isolating myself "
"from the world I only made things worse for everyone, something which even "
"Elyssa could see. Perhaps she understood this better than I because of our "
"shared curse, or maybe it was something she learned while under Argan’s "
"protection."
msgstr ""
"La oscuridad impenetrable que actualmente envuelve Irdya la protege de la "
"mirada de la Vidente de Uria, pero si perdura demasiado tiempo, toda la vida "
"en Irdya también llegará a su fin.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque Elyssa era anteriormente responsable de esta barrera dentro de las "
"fronteras del Imperio del Caos, el poder que recientemente la extendió mucho "
"más allá no es suyo. Es tuyo.\n"
"\n"
"Nunca tuve la oportunidad de hablarte de estos asuntos porque me volví "
"distante desde que tuve que matar a Argan. Pensaba que abrirme y dejar "
"entrar a otros en mi vida solo podría causarles más daño.\n"
"\n"
"Pero finalmente comprendí que eso no resolvía nada. Al aislarme del mundo "
"solo empeoré las cosas para todos, algo que incluso Elyssa pudo ver. Tal vez "
"ella entendió esto mejor que yo por nuestra maldición compartida, o quizás "
"fue algo que aprendió mientras estaba bajo la protección de Argan."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:609
msgid ""
"Then again, it also appears to be natural for Guardians of Darkness to see "
"through that invisible veil that conceals people’s fragile minds. And you "
"are a Guardian of Darkness too — the power to peer into my feelings is a "
"part of your self, and you were unconsciously making use of it all along.\n"
"\n"
"All this time, you tried to reach into me, and I would not let you in. But "
"now it is all clear."
msgstr ""
"Por otro lado, también parece natural que los Guardianes de la Oscuridad "
"puedan ver a través de ese velo invisible que oculta las frágiles mentes de "
"las personas. Y tú eres una Guardiana de la Oscuridad también: el poder de "
"asomarte a mis sentimientos es parte de ti, y lo has estado usando "
"inconscientemente todo este tiempo.\n"
"\n"
"Todo este tiempo intentaste llegar a mí, y yo no te dejé entrar. Pero ahora "
"todo está claro."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:649
msgid ""
"I am sorry, Anya.\n"
"\n"
"I am sorry for not realizing any of this before. I should have let you reach "
"into my heart. We should have done this together like you wanted.\n"
"\n"
"Even though things did not turn out as either of us hoped, you were a good "
"friend."
msgstr ""
"Lo siento, Anya.\n"
"\n"
"Lamento no haberme dado cuenta de nada de esto antes. Debería haberte dejado "
"entrar en mi corazón. Deberíamos haber hecho esto juntas, como tú querías.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque las cosas no salieron como ninguna de las dos esperaba, fuiste una "
"buena amiga."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:665
msgid "A better friend than I deserved, perhaps."
msgstr "Quizás una mejor amiga de la que yo merecía."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:671
msgid "There are so many things you do not know yet, Anya..."
msgstr "Hay tantas cosas que aún no sabes, Anya..."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:858
msgid ""
"I am no-one to decide your fate for you, Anya, but the first thing you must "
"do is to come at peace with your feelings and end the night.\n"
"\n"
"And once you have made a decision, you must ensure that the breach remains "
"well guarded and protected. We do not know how to seal it yet, but if we can "
"defeat Uria, we will surely find a way to undo the damage she has caused on "
"Irdya and Urvatha over the years.\n"
"\n"
"And then, I will return and keep the promise I made to you."
msgstr ""
"No soy nadie para decidir tu destino, Anya, pero lo primero que debes hacer "
"es reconciliarte con tus sentimientos y poner fin a la noche.\n"
"\n"
"Y una vez que hayas tomado una decisión, debes asegurarte de que la brecha "
"permanezca bien custodiada y protegida. Aún no sabemos cómo sellarla, pero "
"si logramos derrotar a Uria, seguramente encontraremos la forma de deshacer "
"el daño que ha causado en Irdya y Urvatha a lo largo de los años.\n"
"\n"
"Y entonces, volveré y cumpliré la promesa que te hice."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:868
msgid "Goodbye, my friend."
msgstr "Adiós, mi amiga."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:885
msgid "Trust your heart."
msgstr "Confía en tu corazón."

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:445
msgid "Destiny — Part 3"
msgstr "Destino — Parte 3"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. The narrator refers to Anya in second person throughout
#. this scenario, and interacts directly with her at the end.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:261
msgid ""
"You are now the Guardian of Darkness.\n"
"\n"
"On Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Ahora eres la Guardiana de la Oscuridad.\n"
"\n"
"En Irdya."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:273
msgid ""
"No...\n"
"\n"
"Actually, you do not consider the title befitting of your actual role. Ever "
"since you recovered from the gruesome attack of Zhangor’s beasts, Ergea has "
"used you as an instrument to liberate both her people and Irdya from Uria’s "
"influence. They call you the “Dark Lady”, “Yechnagoth revived”, the “Goddess "
"of Darkness”, and a myriad other titles you do not actually deserve or care "
"for.\n"
"\n"
"You feel like a pawn in someone’s game. But you are not quite sure anymore "
"for which side you play.\n"
"\n"
"Things were far easier when Elynia was around. You admired her stalwart "
"sense of righteousness. You admired her courage in confronting the most "
"fearsome enemies faced by Irdya in this era; enemies once thought "
"invincible, now fallen and destroyed forever."
msgstr ""
"No…\n"
"\n"
"En realidad, no consideras que el título se ajuste a tu verdadero papel. "
"Desde que te recuperaste del atroz ataque de las bestias de Zhangor, Ergea "
"te ha usado como instrumento para liberar tanto a su pueblo como a Irdya de "
"la influencia de Uria. Te llaman la “Dama Oscura”, “Yechnagoth revivida”, la "
"“Diosa de la Oscuridad” y una infinidad de otros títulos que en realidad no "
"mereces ni te importan.\n"
"\n"
"Te sientes como un peón en el juego de alguien. Pero ya no estás del todo "
"segura de para qué bando juegas.\n"
"\n"
"Las cosas eran mucho más sencillas cuando Elynia estaba cerca. Admirabas su "
"firme sentido de la justicia. Admirabas su valor para enfrentarse a los "
"enemigos más temibles que ha conocido Irdya en esta era; enemigos que antes "
"se creían invencibles y que ahora han caído y han sido destruidos para "
"siempre."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:285
msgid ""
"However, after reading the journals of Galas, Elynia, and Argan, you cannot "
"help but feel profoundly disheartened.\n"
"\n"
"You grew up hearing of Elynia’s feats from Elorran and Tara. Now that you "
"know more about her and are nearly her equal in power, it all suddenly feels "
"vain and pointless. So many things could have been avoided if Uria and her "
"people did not monopolize access to knowledge about your destiny...\n"
"\n"
"A sentiment of uselessness suddenly overwhelms you. You are a fraud. You "
"have not even been able to control the darkness that keeps Naia and Sela’s "
"light from reaching Irdya’s surface. For how long does Ergea intend you to "
"play your act for the Chaos rebels?"
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, tras leer los diarios de Galas, Elynia y Argan, no puedes "
"evitar sentirte profundamente desanimada.\n"
"\n"
"Creciste escuchando las hazañas de Elynia de boca de Elorran y Tara. Ahora "
"que sabes más sobre ella y eres casi su igual en poder, todo de repente te "
"parece vano e inútil. Tantas cosas podrían haberse evitado si Uria y su "
"gente no hubieran monopolizado el acceso al conocimiento sobre tu destino…\n"
"\n"
"Un sentimiento de inutilidad te invade de golpe. Eres un fraude. Ni siquiera "
"has podido controlar la oscuridad que impide que la luz de Naia y Sela "
"llegue a la superficie de Irdya. ¿Por cuánto tiempo más piensa Ergea que "
"sigas interpretando tu papel para los rebeldes del Caos?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:295
msgid ""
"If only you could consult with Elynia about the matter. If only the other "
"Guardian of Darkness, Elyssa, had stayed on Irdya instead of taking your "
"friend to that alien world.\n"
"\n"
"“If only”...\n"
"\n"
"Elynia told you to trust your heart, but you are not quite sure you can do "
"that anymore. After all, it was your heart that deceived you in the first "
"place; it blinded you to Elynia’s actual plan, and it fooled you into "
"thinking that perhaps she would ever consider you as anything more than a "
"‘friend’."
msgstr ""
"Si tan solo pudieras consultar con Elynia sobre el asunto. Si tan solo la "
"otra Guardiana de la Oscuridad, Elyssa, se hubiera quedado en Irdya en lugar "
"de llevarse a tu amiga a ese mundo extraño.\n"
"\n"
"“Si tan solo”...\n"
"\n"
"Elynia te dijo que confiaras en tu corazón, pero ya no estás segura de poder "
"hacerlo. Después de todo, fue tu corazón el que te engañó desde un "
"principio; te cegó ante el verdadero plan de Elynia y te hizo creer que "
"quizás alguna vez podría considerarte como algo más que una ‘amiga’."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:305
msgid ""
"But enough of that emotional nonsense. Your role as a Guardian of Darkness "
"is to make decisions with your mind, not your heart. You have gathered all "
"the knowledge you need for making a decision now.\n"
"\n"
"What does your mind tell you?"
msgstr ""
"Pero basta de esas tonterías emocionales. Tu papel como Guardiana de la "
"Oscuridad es tomar decisiones con la mente, no con el corazón. Has reunido "
"todo el conocimiento necesario para decidir ahora.\n"
"\n"
"¿Qué te dice tu mente?"

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:317
msgid "Find the teleport glyph leading to the breach site"
msgstr "Encontrar el glifo de teletransporte que lleva al sitio de la brecha"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:340
msgid ""
"There is absolutely nothing else of value encoded into this crystal glyph. "
"Time to move on."
msgstr ""
"No hay absolutamente nada más de valor codificado en este glifo de cristal. "
"Es hora de seguir adelante."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:480
msgid ""
"That was not the right glyph.\n"
"\n"
"The crude maps you found of these underground levels show a plethora of "
"teleport glyphs without any indication as to their respective destinations. "
"It is ridiculous. Whoever built this stronghold did not know the first thing "
"about proper organization!\n"
"\n"
"Well, there is no going back now."
msgstr ""
"Ese no era el glifo correcto.\n"
"\n"
"Los mapas burdos que encontraste de estos niveles subterráneos muestran una "
"plétora de glifos de teletransporte sin ninguna indicación sobre sus "
"respectivos destinos. Es ridículo. Quienquiera que haya construido esta "
"fortaleza no tenía la menor idea de lo que es una organización adecuada.\n"
"\n"
"Bueno, ya no hay vuelta atrás."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:520
msgid "Oh. It is you again. I thought you disappeared for good this time."
msgstr ""
"Oh. Eres tú otra vez. Pensé que esta vez habías desaparecido para siempre."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:537
msgid "It has been a while."
msgstr "Ha pasado un tiempo."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:551
msgid "Did you find the cake you wanted?"
msgstr "¿Encontraste el pastel que querías?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:556
msgid ""
"No... I did not. I have hardly eaten anything in weeks. My mind has just "
"been... sort of wandering off constantly. I feel like I shouldn’t be here."
msgstr ""
"No… No lo hice. Apenas he comido nada en semanas. Mi mente simplemente ha "
"estado… divagando constantemente. Siento que no debería estar aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:566
msgid "You seem even more despondent than before."
msgstr "Pareces aún más abatida que antes."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:571
msgid ""
"... This whole situation is just too overwhelming. I feel lost. Ergea is not "
"helpful — she wants me to play a role that wasn’t meant for me."
msgstr ""
"... Toda esta situación es simplemente demasiado abrumadora. Me siento "
"perdida. Ergea no ayuda: quiere que desempeñe un papel que no estaba "
"destinado para mí."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:576
msgid "This is about Elynia, am I correct?"
msgstr "Esto es sobre Elynia, ¿verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:581
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:845
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr "¿Qué quieres decir?"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:586
msgid "You feel lost without her."
msgstr "Te sientes perdida sin ella."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. This line is repeated later in the scenario.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:592
msgid "... I do. I really do."
msgstr "... Sí. Realmente sí."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:602
msgid ""
"I have been thinking about what you said about destiny... You know, after "
"becoming this... thing... I became, I somehow feel even less in control of "
"my life than I was before."
msgstr ""
"He estado pensando en lo que dijiste sobre el destino... Sabes, después de "
"convertirme en esta... cosa... en la que me he convertido, de algún modo "
"siento que tengo incluso menos control sobre mi vida que antes."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:607
msgid "How so, exactly?"
msgstr "¿Cómo es eso exactamente?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. This is indeed meant to be reminiscent of Elyssa's thoughts in E3S8A.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:613
msgid ""
"My actions have constantly been dictated by someone else. Elorran, Elynia, "
"Ergea... I have never truly been free, have I? Just constantly following "
"orders like a machine, unquestioning. But all of a sudden I feel compelled "
"to question everything, if that makes sense? And the worst part is that I "
"can’t tell if it’s because of my connection to Darkness, or because I became "
"a Guardian and now I feel this constant pain within my heart..."
msgstr ""
"Mis acciones han estado dictadas constantemente por alguien más. Elorran, "
"Elynia, Ergea... Nunca he sido verdaderamente libre, ¿verdad? Siempre "
"siguiendo órdenes como una máquina, sin cuestionar. Pero de repente me "
"siento obligada a cuestionarlo todo, ¿tiene sentido? Y lo peor es que no "
"puedo decir si es por mi conexión con la Oscuridad o porque me convertí en "
"una Guardiana y ahora siento este dolor constante en mi corazón..."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:618
msgid ""
"Would that be your actual heart, or the divine instrument demonkind calls "
"the Energy Heart?"
msgstr ""
"¿Sería tu corazón real, o el instrumento divino que la raza demoníaca llama "
"el Corazón de Energía?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:623
msgid "I can’t even tell the difference anymore."
msgstr "Ya ni siquiera puedo notar la diferencia."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:628
msgid ""
"I can only speculate about the nature and extent of your powers, but I would "
"expect Guardians of Darkness to be better in touch with the notion of agency "
"seeing as how their domain revolves around the matters of mind. If the gift "
"you now possess comes with greater self-awareness, then it is up to you to "
"make use of it in a way that can advance your own existence towards a "
"positive outcome."
msgstr ""
"Solo puedo especular sobre la naturaleza y el alcance de tus poderes, pero "
"esperaría que los Guardianes de la Oscuridad tuvieran un mejor vínculo con "
"la noción de voluntad, ya que su dominio gira en torno a los asuntos de la "
"mente. Si el don que ahora posees viene con una mayor autoconciencia, "
"entonces depende de ti usarlo de una manera que pueda conducir tu existencia "
"hacia un resultado positivo."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:633
msgid "But what if the only path forward I see involves leaving people behind?"
msgstr ""
"¿Pero qué pasa si el único camino hacia adelante que veo implica dejar gente "
"atrás?"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:638
msgid ""
"The future is constantly clouded in darkness, but you need not be afraid of "
"the core substance of your being, do you? We are not always given a choice, "
"but when we are, it is up to us to make the right one — and a Guardian’s "
"choices carry more weight upon our reality than anyone else’s."
msgstr ""
"El futuro está constantemente nublado por la oscuridad, pero no necesitas "
"temer a la sustancia central de tu ser, ¿verdad? No siempre se nos da una "
"elección, pero cuando la tenemos, depende de nosotros tomar la correcta, y "
"las decisiones de un Guardián tienen más peso sobre nuestra realidad que las "
"de cualquier otra persona."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:644
msgid "Have you pondered the matter of destiny yet?"
msgstr "¿Has reflexionado ya sobre el asunto del destino?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:649
msgid "I... uh... What do you mean?"
msgstr "Yo... eh... ¿Qué quieres decir?"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:654
msgid ""
"I must not have talked to you about it. My apologies. You need not worry "
"about it for now."
msgstr ""
"No debo haberte hablado de eso. Mis disculpas. No necesitas preocuparte por "
"ello por ahora."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:659
msgid "I have so many questions..."
msgstr "Tengo tantas preguntas..."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:664
msgid "Xia’el does not have answers for you anymore, sadly."
msgstr "Xia’el ya no tiene respuestas para ti, lamentablemente."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:674
msgid ""
"Am I ever going to find out what happened to my parents after I was born?"
msgstr ""
"¿Alguna vez voy a descubrir qué pasó con mis padres después de que nací?"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:679
msgid ""
"As a matter of fact, yes. I opted not to tell you the entire story out of "
"concern for your emotional state in battle, but I can finish it now if you "
"would like."
msgstr ""
"De hecho, sí. Opté por no contarte toda la historia por preocupación por tu "
"estado emocional en batalla, pero puedo terminarla ahora si lo deseas."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:684
msgid ""
"What?! You knew the rest of the story but didn’t tell it to me?! I thought "
"you said you were just a medium and you didn’t have it!"
msgstr ""
"¡¿Qué?! ¿Sabías el resto de la historia y no me lo contaste?! ¡Pensé que "
"dijiste que solo eras un medio y que no la tenías!"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:689
msgid ""
"I said your question was already answered, and it was. I never specified "
"whether I was able to intentionally postpone delivering a non-essential part "
"of the answer or not. I apologize, but it had to be done."
msgstr ""
"Dije que tu pregunta ya estaba respondida, y lo estaba. Nunca especifiqué si "
"podía o no posponer intencionadamente la entrega de una parte no esencial de "
"la respuesta. Lo siento, pero debía hacerse."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:694
msgid "(<i>sighs</i>) I understand. And... I’m sorry for my outburst."
msgstr "(<i>Suspira</i>) Entiendo. Y... lo siento por mi arrebato."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:699
msgid "So, let us pick up from where we left last time..."
msgstr "Entonces, retomemos desde donde lo dejamos la última vez..."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:704
msgid ""
"The hearts of Mintha and the Nameless One were overflowing with newfound "
"happiness and purpose after conceiving a child that they could call their "
"own. The offspring would be a new free creature born of faerie and "
"demonkind, a unique combination completely unheard of before. The future of "
"the two lovers seemed bright for once."
msgstr ""
"Los corazones de Mintha y el Sin Nombre rebosaban de nueva felicidad y "
"propósito tras concebir a un hijo que podían llamar suyo. La descendencia "
"sería una nueva criatura libre nacida de hada y demonio, una combinación "
"única y completamente desconocida hasta entonces. El futuro de los dos "
"amantes parecía brillante por una vez."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:709
msgid ""
"It was not rare for travelers to get lost in the forests of Glamdrol, and "
"Mintha and the Nameless One routinely guided them out of the forest without "
"overtly revealing themselves. However, one fateful night, a mysterious "
"interloper found them first. The couple did not know what to make of the "
"situation. How did he manage to enter their home entirely unnannounced?\n"
"\n"
"The Wanderer came to them to impart his knowledge of events past, and events "
"that had not yet come to pass. He told them of the looming threat of the "
"Chaos Empire, Merthiaal’s legacy, the War Against the Unknown, and the "
"return of the Lady of Light. And he told them of one possible fate that "
"awaited the unborn child and its parents — for the Nameless One had not "
"fully escaped Uria’s grasp, and the keen-nosed Demon Lord Nar-hamoth "
"personally sought to make the shapeshifter pay a hefty price for their "
"transgressions."
msgstr ""
"No era raro que los viajeros se perdieran en los bosques de Glamdrol, y "
"Mintha y el Sin Nombre los guiaban fuera del bosque sin revelarse "
"abiertamente. Sin embargo, una fatídica noche, un misterioso intruso los "
"encontró primero. La pareja no sabía qué pensar de la situación. ¿Cómo logró "
"entrar en su hogar sin anunciarse en absoluto?\n"
"\n"
"El Errante vino a ellos para impartirles su conocimiento de acontecimientos "
"pasados y de eventos que aún no habían ocurrido. Les habló de la amenaza "
"inminente del Imperio del Caos, el legado de Merthiaal, la Guerra contra lo "
"Desconocido y el retorno de la Dama de la Luz. Y les habló de un posible "
"destino que aguardaba al niño no nacido y a sus padres: pues el Sin Nombre "
"no había escapado completamente de las garras de Uria, y el astuto Señor "
"Demonio Nar-hamoth buscaba personalmente hacer que el cambiante pagara un "
"alto precio por sus transgresiones."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#. Reminder that Nar-Hamoth is the Shadow of Uria.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:717
msgid ""
"The couple were uncertain as to whether to believe the Wanderer’s words or "
"not. How could their child just so happen to be the one destined to become "
"the New Guardian of Darkness? If their offspring would indeed be found along "
"with them by Uria’s forces before coming of age, then it would all have been "
"for naught, and the world would be plunged into an eternal darkness — one "
"much deeper and more pervasive than even that of the Endless Night, a "
"darkness that would cause even the Seed of Earth to wither and die, and then "
"all life would simply cease to be.\n"
"\n"
"Before departing, the Wanderer offered them an alternative: Mintha could "
"give birth and hold the child in her bosom for one month, but afterwards she "
"would have to leave it in the care of a human family — more specifically, "
"one already fraught with loss. Finally, if the Nameless One hoped to escape "
"the Shadow of Uria for good, they would have to either die, or relinquish "
"their physical form for good.\n"
"\n"
"Upon saying that, the man left as silently as he came, fading into the dark "
"of the night. They considered going after him to ask more questions, but "
"somehow he did not even leave a trail for them to follow."
msgstr ""
"La pareja no estaba segura de si creer o no las palabras del Errante. ¿Cómo "
"podía ser que su hijo fuera precisamente el destinado a convertirse en el "
"Nuevo Guardián de la Oscuridad? Si su descendencia fuera encontrada junto a "
"ellos por las fuerzas de Uria antes de llegar a la madurez, todo habría sido "
"en vano, y el mundo quedaría sumido en una oscuridad eterna, una mucho más "
"profunda y abrumadora que incluso la de la Noche Interminable; una oscuridad "
"que haría que incluso la Semilla de la Tierra se marchitara y muriera, y "
"entonces toda la vida simplemente dejaría de existir.\n"
"\n"
"Antes de partir, el Errante les ofreció una alternativa: Mintha podría dar a "
"luz y tener al niño en su regazo durante un mes, pero después tendría que "
"dejarlo al cuidado de una familia humana, más específicamente una ya marcada "
"por la pérdida. Finalmente, si el Sin Nombre esperaba escapar de la Sombra "
"de Uria para siempre, tendría que morir o renunciar para siempre a su forma "
"física.\n"
"\n"
"Al decir eso, el hombre se marchó tan silenciosamente como llegó, "
"desvaneciéndose en la oscuridad de la noche. Consideraron ir tras él para "
"hacer más preguntas, pero de algún modo ni siquiera dejó un rastro para que "
"lo siguieran."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:726
msgid ""
"Nine months they spent pondering the Wanderer’s words. Nine months they "
"spent hoping that what they heard was naught but the ravings of a senile "
"man. But rumors of Chaos Empire incursions began to spread around the "
"marches, and the Nameless Shapeshifter caught wind of them as well. Their "
"rendezvous with the vengeful Demon Lord was imminent.\n"
"\n"
"Neither of them ever imagined they would be faced with a decision that would "
"concern not only the fruit of their love, but also the fate of an entire "
"world. Could they really risk dooming their child to certain death when they "
"had the option to give it some semblance of a proper life with humans until "
"the day of its awakening?"
msgstr ""
"Pasaron nueve meses reflexionando sobre las palabras del Errante. Nueve "
"meses esperando que lo que escucharon no fuera más que los desvaríos de un "
"anciano senil. Pero los rumores de incursiones del Imperio del Caos "
"comenzaron a extenderse por las fronteras, y el Cambiante Sin Nombre también "
"los escuchó. Su encuentro con el vengativo Señor Demonio era inminente.\n"
"\n"
"Ninguno de ellos imaginó jamás que se enfrentarían a una decisión que "
"concerniera no solo al fruto de su amor, sino también al destino de todo un "
"mundo. ¿Podían realmente arriesgarse a condenar a su hijo a una muerte "
"segura cuando tenían la opción de darle algún atisbo de una vida adecuada "
"con los humanos hasta el día de su despertar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:733
msgid ""
"And so it came to pass that the child was born. Their offspring "
"subconsciously took on some of Mintha’s features due to her being the very "
"first thing it saw in the world. The Nameless One and Mintha cared for it "
"for a month, regarding it as the most precious thing in their lives.\n"
"\n"
"Stricken with grief, Mintha traveled into the northern country and left the "
"creature in the care of a farmer couple. She thought the exchange would be "
"fair for them, as they had just lost their own newborn to a deadly plague. "
"The humans never thought to question the nature of the unfamiliar child left "
"by their front door in the night. They decided to give her the name of their "
"late daughter and raise her as their own."
msgstr ""
"Y así ocurrió que el niño nació. Su descendencia adoptó inconscientemente "
"algunos rasgos de Mintha debido a que ella fue la primera cosa que vio en el "
"mundo. El Sin Nombre y Mintha cuidaron de ella durante un mes, "
"considerándola la cosa más preciosa en sus vidas.\n"
"\n"
"Afligida por la pena, Mintha viajó al país del norte y dejó a la criatura al "
"cuidado de una pareja de granjeros. Pensó que el intercambio sería justo "
"para ellos, pues acababan de perder a su propio recién nacido por una plaga "
"mortal. Los humanos nunca se cuestionaron la naturaleza del niño desconocido "
"dejado en la puerta de su casa durante la noche. Decidieron darle el nombre "
"de su difunta hija y criarla como propia."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:740
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Faerie of Resurrection finally returned to Glamdrol, and shared a last "
"passionate kiss with the Nameless Shapeshifter. Together they cast a spell "
"that unbound the soul of the demon from their mortal body. The lovers had "
"agreed to spend the rest of eternity together no matter if they were unable "
"to embrace one another again.\n"
"\n"
"And it was so that the soul of the Nameless One went to an eucalyptus tree, "
"and Mintha went back to her original form to keep them company, right where "
"she first found them."
msgstr ""
"El Hada de la Resurrección finalmente regresó a Glamdrol y compartió un "
"último beso apasionado con el Cambiante Sin Nombre. Juntos lanzaron un "
"hechizo que liberó el alma del demonio de su cuerpo mortal. Los amantes "
"habían acordado pasar el resto de la eternidad juntos, aunque no pudieran "
"volver a abrazarse.\n"
"\n"
"Y así fue que el alma del Sin Nombre se trasladó a un eucalipto, y Mintha "
"volvió a su forma original para hacerle compañía, justo donde lo encontró "
"por primera vez."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:749
msgid ""
"When the Demon Lord Nar-hamoth found the corpse of his former slave he could "
"only growl and trample the forest in frustration for being denied his "
"revenge."
msgstr ""
"Cuando el Señor Demonio Nar-hamoth encontró el cadáver de su antiguo "
"esclavo, solo pudo gruñir y pisotear el bosque en frustración por haberle "
"sido negada su venganza."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:758
msgid ""
"I don’t know what I was expecting... I— I think I know exactly which forest "
"that was. I had been there before... I... I..."
msgstr ""
"No sé qué estaba esperando... Yo... Creo que sé exactamente qué bosque era. "
"He estado allí antes... Yo... Yo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:763
msgid "They would not have been able to tell you."
msgstr "No habrían podido decírtelo."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:768
msgid ""
"That entire forest... it doesn’t exist anymore... the entire place... Oh "
"gods..."
msgstr "Todo ese bosque... ya no existe... todo el lugar... Oh, dioses..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:783
msgid "I could’ve killed him. I could’ve killed Nar-hamoth..."
msgstr "Podría haberlo matado. Podría haber matado a Nar-hamoth..."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:788
msgid "You did not know."
msgstr "No lo sabías."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:795
msgid "Heh, but it wouldn’t have changed anything, would it..."
msgstr "Je, pero no habría cambiado nada, ¿verdad...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:806
msgid ""
"They could have both taken me with them deep into the country and we would "
"have all survived together..."
msgstr ""
"Podrían haberme llevado con ellos al interior del país y todos habríamos "
"sobrevivido juntos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:811
msgid "It was a risk they chose not to take."
msgstr "Fue un riesgo que eligieron no asumir."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:816
msgid ""
"Choices, huh... it’s all down to choices... Do they even matter in the end?"
msgstr ""
"Elecciones, ¿eh...? Todo se reduce a las elecciones... ¿Realmente importan "
"al final?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:833
msgid "What am I supposed to do now?"
msgstr "¿Qué se supone que debo hacer ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:838
msgid ""
"I think you already know what you are going to do. It is not even going to "
"be a choice, is it?"
msgstr ""
"Creo que ya sabes lo que vas a hacer. Ni siquiera será una elección, ¿verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:850
msgid ""
"What you do next is a constant. No matter how you get here, you always do "
"what you want to do, as well as what is expected of you. They do not "
"<i>have</i> to be mutually exclusive concepts, after all."
msgstr ""
"Lo que hagas a continuación es una constante. No importa cómo llegues aquí, "
"siempre haces lo que quieres hacer, además de lo que se espera de ti. "
"Después de todo, no <i>tienen</i> por qué ser conceptos mutuamente "
"excluyentes."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:857
msgid "I suppose so..."
msgstr "Supongo que sí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:928
msgid "How long have I spent staring into this pond?"
msgstr "¿Cuánto tiempo he pasado mirando fijamente este estanque?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:962
msgid "Access denied."
msgstr "Acceso denegado."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:972
msgid ""
"All right. That was unexpected.\n"
"\n"
"Perhaps this is the teleport glyph you have been looking for all along, and "
"it was locked on purpose?\n"
"\n"
"Maybe Elynia and Elyssa did not want you to follow them after all."
msgstr ""
"Está bien. Eso fue inesperado.\n"
"\n"
"¿Quizás este sea el glifo de teletransporte que has estado buscando todo "
"este tiempo, y estaba bloqueado a propósito?\n"
"\n"
"Tal vez Elynia y Elyssa no querían que las siguieras después de todo."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:994
msgid "A wall moves."
msgstr "Un muro se mueve."

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1029
msgid "Find another access way to the breach site"
msgstr "Encuentra otra vía de acceso al sitio de la brecha"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1039
msgid "Crystal Glyph (Argan)"
msgstr "Glifo de Cristal (Argan)"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1048
msgid "Crystal Glyph (Elyssa)"
msgstr "Glifo de Cristal (Elyssa)"

#. [event]
#. This line is Argan speaking about Uria.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1063
msgid ""
"Her mission as the Guardian of Life of our cycle was subverted by her own "
"will through a series of unfortunate circumstances, but not stopped. Whereas "
"a normal Guardian of Life should ensure that life can prosper and thrive in "
"their world, Uria has destroyed the lives of countless people on Urvatha and "
"Irdya. However, she has also <i>created</i> life by stealing and embracing "
"technology created on Norsula, as well as ancient Irdya. The scriptures say "
"that a Guardian of Life should not be able to <i>create</i> life!"
msgstr ""
"Su misión como Guardiana de la Vida de nuestro ciclo fue subvertida por su "
"propia voluntad a través de una serie de desafortunadas circunstancias, pero "
"no detenida. Mientras que un Guardián de la Vida normal debería asegurar que "
"la vida prospere y florezca en su mundo, Uria ha destruido las vidas de "
"incontables personas en Urvatha e Irdya. Sin embargo, también ha <i>creado</"
"i> vida al robar y adoptar tecnología creada en Norsula, así como en la "
"antigua Irdya. ¡Las escrituras dicen que un Guardián de la Vida no debería "
"ser capaz de <i>crear</i> vida!"

#. [event]
#. This line is still Argan speaking.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1076
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The fact that the Norsulans have access to unprecedented knowledge of the "
"guardians’ biology has been useful to Uria so far, but she fears the day "
"that was foretold by the Seer, in which “the new Guardian of Water will "
"arise and attempt to rob the Guardian of Life’s rightful prize”. Although "
"Uria has agents on Norsula trying to find this man — or beast — before his "
"awakening can take place, such a task is doomed to failure."
msgstr ""
"El hecho de que los Norsulanos tengan acceso a un conocimiento sin "
"precedentes sobre el aspecto biológico de los guardianes ha sido útil para "
"Uria hasta ahora, pero ella teme el día que fue predicho por el Vidente, en "
"el que “el nuevo Guardián del Agua surgirá e intentará arrebatarle al "
"Guardián de la Vida el premio que le corresponde”. Aunque Uria tiene agentes "
"en Norsula tratando de encontrar a este hombre —o bestia— antes de que pueda "
"despertar, tal tarea está condenada al fracaso."

#. [event]
#. This line is still Argan speaking.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1089
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Norsula is a large world, even larger than Ethea or Irdya. Around the time I "
"first arrived on Irdya, Norsulans were still a largely ignorant bunch, "
"lacking the boon of magic that the Irdyans embraced early on in their "
"world’s history. But at some point, their technological development rate "
"greatly surpassed that of Irdya or even Ethea. Some say that an external "
"influence contributed to their accelerated evolution as a world."
msgstr ""
"Norsula es un mundo grande, incluso más grande que Ethea o Irdya. Cuando "
"llegué por primera vez a Irdya, los Norsulanos seguían siendo en gran parte "
"un grupo ignorante, carentes del don de la magia que los Irdyanos abrazaron "
"temprano en la historia de su mundo. Pero en algún momento, su ritmo de "
"desarrollo tecnológico superó repentinamente al de Irdya e incluso al de "
"Ethea. Algunos dicen que una influencia externa contribuyó a su evolución "
"acelerada como mundo."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1113
msgid ""
"The glyph’s contents seem to be in a language you have never read nor heard "
"before."
msgstr ""
"El contenido del glifo parece estar en un idioma que nunca has leído ni "
"escuchado antes."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1127
msgid ""
"This glyph seems different from the rest. It seems to encode some kind of "
"spell instead of a message.\n"
"\n"
"You wonder what would happen if you try it out."
msgstr ""
"Este glifo parece diferente a los demás. Parece codificar algún tipo de "
"hechizo en lugar de un mensaje.\n"
"\n"
"Te preguntas qué pasaría si lo intentas."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1143
msgid ""
"Nothing.\n"
"\n"
"This is absolutely pointless."
msgstr ""
"Nada.\n"
"\n"
"Esto es absolutamente inútil."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1169
msgid ""
"Wait a moment.\n"
"\n"
"This glyph’s message seemed unintelligible to you before, but now it is not."
msgstr ""
"Espera un momento.\n"
"\n"
"El mensaje de este glifo te parecía ininteligible antes, pero ahora no lo es."

#. [event]
#. Elyssa speaking.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1188
msgid ""
"Just as Norsula’s technological advancements were the consequence of "
"external influence, much of Ethea’s technological and cultural advancements "
"have been the consequence of secret exchanges with Norsula and lesser worlds "
"over centuries. In fact, only very recently has Norsula’s existence been "
"revealed to Ethean commoners, sparking all kinds of conflicts between the "
"many ruling countries."
msgstr ""
"Así como los avances tecnológicos de Norsula fueron consecuencia de una "
"influencia externa, gran parte de los avances tecnológicos y culturales de "
"Ethea han sido el resultado de intercambios secretos con Norsula y mundos "
"menores a lo largo de los siglos. De hecho, solo muy recientemente la "
"existencia de Norsula ha sido revelada a los plebeyos etheanos, desatando "
"todo tipo de conflictos entre los muchos países gobernantes."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1206
msgid ""
"The contents of this glyph seem to have been encoded quite a while ago, "
"given what you already know from Elynia."
msgstr ""
"El contenido de este glifo parece haber sido codificado hace bastante "
"tiempo, dado lo que ya sabes por Elynia."

#. [event]
#. Elyssa speaking.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1210
msgid ""
"Ethean technology is said to not be very advanced, but the persistent "
"meddling of Valdir’s successor and his people have slowly yet steadily "
"changed the status quo. Uria’s agents have traveled from the unprotected "
"Norsula and infiltrated Ethea to arrange the scenario for her eventual "
"arrival, but everything seems to indicate that the Guardian of Water also "
"has an agenda of his own involving the seed on that world.\n"
"\n"
"The Seer’s ramblings on the matter are hazy and confusing, mentioning more "
"and more nonsensical titles that cannot be accurately attributed to any "
"known key individuals. The only thing that we know for sure is that the Seer "
"will eventually be slain, thus making it impossible for us to know what "
"happens past that point in time."
msgstr ""
"Se dice que la tecnología etheana no es muy avanzada, pero la persistente "
"intromisión del sucesor de Valdir y su gente ha cambiado lenta pero "
"firmemente el statu quo. Los agentes de Uria han viajado desde la "
"desprotegida Norsula e infiltrado Ethea para preparar el escenario para su "
"eventual llegada, pero todo parece indicar que el Guardián del Agua también "
"tiene su propia agenda relacionada con la semilla de ese mundo.\n"
"\n"
"Las divagaciones del Vidente sobre el asunto son confusas y nebulosas, "
"mencionando cada vez más títulos sin sentido que no pueden atribuirse con "
"precisión a ningún individuo clave conocido. Lo único que sabemos con "
"certeza es que el Vidente será finalmente asesinado, lo que hará imposible "
"para nosotros saber qué ocurre más allá de ese punto en el tiempo."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1269
msgid ""
"This seems to be the teleport glyph you were searching for. But... do you "
"really want to proceed with this plan?\n"
"\n"
"Are you absolutely sure that it is worth it?"
msgstr ""
"Este parece ser el glifo de teletransporte que estabas buscando. Pero... "
"¿realmente quieres continuar con este plan?\n"
"\n"
"¿Estás absolutamente segura de que vale la pena?"

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1274
msgid ""
"female^Yes, I am absolutely sure. I need to see Elynia again. I need her."
msgstr ""
"femenino^Sí, estoy absolutamente segura. Necesito ver a Elynia otra vez. La "
"necesito."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1285
msgid ""
"female^No. Perhaps I will explore around a little more and try to make up my "
"mind about this."
msgstr "No. Quizás explore un poco más e intente decidirme sobre esto."

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1291
msgid "female^No."
msgstr "No."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1319
msgid ""
"No matter how much I want, Irdya will never be my true home. I’ve always "
"been an outcast. I don’t belong with either species. And I don’t want to "
"take part in Ergea’s plans anymore."
msgstr ""
"Por mucho que lo desee, Irdya nunca será mi verdadero hogar. Siempre he sido "
"una paria. No pertenezco a ninguna de las dos especies. Y ya no quiero "
"formar parte de los planes de Ergea."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1324
msgid ""
"At least on Ethea I might be able to find Elynia... and tell her... that I "
"want to be with her..."
msgstr ""
"Al menos en Ethea podría encontrar a Elynia... y decirle... que quiero estar "
"con ella..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1330
msgid "Do you?"
msgstr "¿De verdad lo deseas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1335
msgid "Yes, I do. I really do."
msgstr "Sí, lo deseo. De verdad lo deseo."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1341
msgid "Is this your heart speaking, or your mind?"
msgstr "¿Es tu corazón quien habla, o tu mente?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1346
msgid "... I guess it’s both."
msgstr "... Supongo que ambos."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1351
msgid "Oh dear gods... Am I really speaking to myself now?"
msgstr "Oh, dioses... ¿Realmente estoy hablando conmigo misma ahora?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1356
msgid "... Forgive me, Durvan, Ergea, Irylean..."
msgstr "... Perdónenme, Durvan, Ergea, Irylean..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1532
msgid "Why do you still hesitate, girl? You are almost there."
msgstr "¿Por qué sigues dudando, chica? Ya casi has llegado."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1537
msgid ""
"... What if Elynia rejects me? What if I am not actually supposed to do this?"
msgstr "... ¿Y si Elynia me rechaza? ¿Y si en realidad no debería hacer esto?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1543
msgid "<i>Trust your heart.</i> Those were Elynia’s own words."
msgstr ""
"<i>Confía en tu corazón.</i> Esas fueron las propias palabras de Elynia."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1548
msgid "That is correct. I..."
msgstr "Es cierto. Yo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1565
msgid "I will do this."
msgstr "Lo haré."

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1576
msgid "I am sorry, Elynia. But... I need you..."
msgstr "Lo siento, Elynia. Pero... te necesito..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1595
msgid "<i>... I need you...</i>"
msgstr "<i>... Te necesito...</i>"

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1632
msgid ""
"You feel as though a certain other Guardian of Darkness may have missed "
"something..."
msgstr ""
"Tienes la sensación de que cierto otro Guardián de la Oscuridad pudo haber "
"pasado algo por alto..."

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:511
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr "Epílogo"

#. [side]: type=Guardian of Earth Aradellys, id=Aradellys
#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:50
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:100
msgid "team_name^Aradellys"
msgstr "Aradellys"

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:482
msgid ""
"Ha ha ha ha ha! It has been hundreds of years since my last visit to Silida, "
"and yet, nothing has changed. I am so delighted to see your subjects here, "
"Xia’el — it is such a warm welcome. Did you miss me?"
msgstr ""
"¡Ja ja ja ja ja! Han pasado cientos de años desde mi última visita a Silida, "
"y sin embargo, nada ha cambiado. Me complace tanto ver a tus súbditos aquí, "
"Xia’el; es una bienvenida tan cálida. ¿Me extrañaste?"

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:492
msgid ""
"We had a pact of neutrality and mutual respect, Xia’el. You would not "
"interfere with my plans, and I would let you govern your precious people "
"here in peace. But it has come to my attention that there has been a breach "
"of terms on <i>your</i> part. My Seer just revealed some... <i>troubling</i> "
"things to me."
msgstr ""
"Teníamos un pacto de neutralidad y respeto mutuo, Xia’el. Tú no "
"interferirías en mis planes, y yo permitiría que gobernaras a tu preciada "
"gente aquí en paz. Pero he sabido que ha habido un incumplimiento de "
"términos por <i>tu</i> parte. Mi Vidente acaba de revelarme algunas cosas... "
"<i>preocupantes</i>."

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:502
msgid ""
"You have been meddling with my personal playground in the main branch of our "
"universe; corrupting and manipulating he who used to serve as my Voice on "
"Irdya, as well as his treacherous protégé. What did you expect to accomplish "
"with this? To circumvent our pact by utilizing the Guardian of Earth on "
"Irdya as your piece for your next move? Did you truly believe I would never "
"find out?"
msgstr ""
"Has estado entrometiéndote en mi patio de juegos personal en la rama "
"principal de nuestro universo; corrompiendo y manipulando a quien solía ser "
"mi Voz en Irdya, así como a su traicionero protegido. ¿Qué esperabas lograr "
"con esto? ¿Eludir nuestro pacto usando al Guardián de la Tierra en Irdya "
"como tu pieza para tu siguiente jugada? ¿De verdad creíste que nunca me "
"enteraría?"

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:507
msgid ""
"My only intention was to fulfill my duty as the Guardian of Earth and point "
"my children on Irdya in the correct direction. That is to say, as far away "
"from your grasp as possible so they may stage your ultimate downfall."
msgstr ""
"Mi única intención era cumplir mi deber como Guardiana de la Tierra y guiar "
"a mis hijos en Irdya en la dirección correcta. Es decir, tan lejos de tu "
"alcance como sea posible, para que puedan preparar tu caída definitiva."

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:513
msgid ""
"On Ethea? Hm, hm, well, it just so happens that my forces are already on "
"their way there, and this time I will <i>personally</i> take care of any "
"opposition we find."
msgstr ""
"¿En Ethea? Hm, hm, pues resulta que mis fuerzas ya están en camino allí, y "
"esta vez me encargaré <i>personalmente</i> de cualquier oposición que "
"encontremos."

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:518
msgid ""
"Even the new Guardian of Water? I received word that he is already there."
msgstr ""
"¿Incluso el nuevo Guardián del Agua? Recibí noticias de que ya está allí."

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:529
msgid ""
"You fear him, don’t you? Of course, he poses as much danger to our existence "
"as you do, but he at least manages to keep his destructive tendencies under "
"control. You, on the other hand... you are a corrupted goddess, Lyphanea — "
"if I may not stop you, then someone else has to take up that mission for me."
msgstr ""
"Le temes, ¿verdad? Por supuesto, él representa tanto peligro para nuestra "
"existencia como tú, pero al menos logra mantener sus tendencias destructivas "
"bajo control. Tú, en cambio... eres una diosa corrompida, Lyphanea; si yo no "
"puedo detenerte, entonces alguien más tendrá que asumir esa misión por mí."

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:544
msgid ""
"(<i>enraged</i>) I see how it is, then! But tell me, Aradellys, did you "
"forget the Rule of One?"
msgstr ""
"(<i>furiosa</i>) ¡Veo cómo son las cosas, entonces! Pero dime, Aradellys, "
"¿olvidaste la Regla del Uno?"

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:550
msgid "I did not."
msgstr "No la olvidé."

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:555
msgid ""
"Your insolence cannot go unpunished. Even though I knew from the very "
"beginning that things would come to this... I cannot allow you to interfere "
"with my plans any further. You are a poor excuse for a Guardian of Earth, "
"and this is not even your rightful domain. The true Guardian of Earth is "
"awake, so your purpose in this universe has been fulfilled."
msgstr ""
"Tu insolencia no puede quedar sin castigo. Aunque sabía desde el principio "
"que las cosas llegarían a esto... no puedo permitir que sigas interfiriendo "
"en mis planes. Eres una pobre excusa de Guardiana de la Tierra, y este ni "
"siquiera es tu dominio legítimo. El verdadero Guardián de la Tierra está "
"despierto, así que tu propósito en este universo ya se ha cumplido."

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:560
msgid ""
"Now that you have helpfully advanced <i>my</i> pieces to the world on which "
"I needed them in the first place, the game is over for you. After all, "
"<i>there can only be one</i>."
msgstr ""
"Ahora que has movido tan amablemente <i>mis</i> piezas al mundo en el que "
"las necesitaba desde un principio, el juego se terminó para ti. Después de "
"todo, <i>solo puede haber uno</i>."

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:565
msgid ""
"I am willing to face oblivion at your hand for my transgressions. But you "
"shall spare my people."
msgstr ""
"Estoy dispuesta a enfrentar el olvido a manos tuyas por mis transgresiones. "
"Pero deberás perdonar a mi gente."

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:570
msgid "Hm, hm, what makes you think that I have to keep my word anymore?"
msgstr "Hm, hm, ¿qué te hace pensar que aún debo mantener mi palabra?"

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:583
msgid ""
"Please, if there is anything left of the kind Lyphanea in your heart, you "
"shall spare my people as we agreed—"
msgstr ""
"Por favor, si queda algo de la bondadosa Lyphanea en tu corazón, deberás "
"perdonar a mi gente como acordamos—"

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:589
msgid "<i>Lyphanea is no more.</i>"
msgstr "<i>Lyphanea ya no existe.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:631
msgid ""
"If it helps, your subjects will be able to enjoy whatever afterlife is in "
"store for them. But you... <b>will not.</b> Farewell, Xia’el. Your reign on "
"Silida is over."
msgstr ""
"Si te sirve de consuelo, tus súbditos podrán disfrutar del más allá que les "
"aguarde. Pero tú... <b>no lo harás.</b> Adiós, Xia’el. Tu reinado en Silida "
"ha terminado."

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:758
msgid ""
"Soon there will be a reckoning, Elynia-Thanadria — mark my words. Do not "
"forget who made the resurrection of your new ally possible in the first "
"place..."
msgstr ""
"Pronto llegará el ajuste de cuentas, Elynia-Thanadria; grábate bien mis "
"palabras. No olvides quién hizo posible la resurrección de tu nuevo aliado "
"en primer lugar..."

#. [part]
#. The lines consisting of a single em dash represent a long pause.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:23
msgid ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"—\n"
"\n"
"Darkness... I begin to get used to it, again."
msgstr ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"—\n"
"\n"
"Oscuridad... Empiezo a acostumbrarme de nuevo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:30
msgid ""
"I spent eons in the darkness beneath the earth, not feeling, not seeing... "
"not thinking. I long to return to that state and let myself fall into the "
"void; unfeeling, uncaring, detached from it all.\n"
"\n"
"Even endless sleep would be preferable to what I am left here to face: a "
"reality I cannot amend. Irdya is now in jeopardy due to the machinations of "
"terrible forces I cannot possibly control or confront. Not anymore.\n"
"\n"
"I thought I could save Irdya from impending doom this time, but I failed. I "
"failed utterly, just like I did before, and again. All I have accomplished "
"with my recklessness so far has been accelerating the process of our "
"destruction. Perhaps my curse was more than the pompous last words of a "
"necromancer after all; I lost my friends, my people, my home... and my love."
msgstr ""
"Pasé eones en la oscuridad bajo la tierra, sin sentir, sin ver... sin "
"pensar. Anhelo regresar a ese estado y dejarme caer en el vacío; sin sentir, "
"sin preocuparme, desconectada de todo.\n"
"\n"
"Incluso un sueño eterno sería preferible a lo que me queda aquí por "
"enfrentar: una realidad que no puedo enmendar. Irdya está ahora en peligro "
"debido a las maquinaciones de fuerzas terribles que no puedo controlar ni "
"confrontar. No más.\n"
"\n"
"Creí que podía salvar a Irdya de la inminente perdición esta vez, pero "
"fallé. Fallé por completo, como ya lo había hecho antes, y otra vez. Todo lo "
"que he logrado con mi imprudencia hasta ahora ha sido acelerar el proceso de "
"nuestra destrucción. Quizás mi maldición fue algo más que las pomposas "
"últimas palabras de un nigromante después de todo; perdí a mis amigos, mi "
"gente, mi hogar... y mi amor."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:37
msgid ""
"“One of us shall fall; the other shall live forever”, he said before our "
"second and last battle.\n"
"\n"
"Of course... my memory has grown rusty after so long. But I think I never "
"fully realized the implications of his words.\n"
"\n"
"“You shall witness the eventual decay and death of everything you have or "
"shall come to love. You shall regret your actions. And you shall either be "
"forced to end your own life, or live in perpetual suffering. That is the "
"price for my defeat.”\n"
"\n"
"Somehow the choice seems trivial now... And if the fate of Irdya states so, "
"someone more competent will take my place and bring them to victory. And "
"then... I’ll be remembered as a coward. A coward who deserted her friends "
"because she could not bear causing them more harm."
msgstr ""
"“Uno de nosotros caerá; el otro vivirá para siempre”, dijo antes de nuestro "
"segundo y último combate.\n"
"\n"
"Por supuesto... mi memoria se ha vuelto oxidada tras tanto tiempo. Pero creo "
"que nunca comprendí del todo las implicaciones de sus palabras.\n"
"\n"
"“Serás testigo de la decadencia y muerte eventual de todo lo que tienes o "
"llegarás a amar. Lamentarás tus acciones. Y se te obligará a acabar con tu "
"propia vida o a vivir en un sufrimiento perpetuo. Ese es el precio por mi "
"derrota.”\n"
"\n"
"De algún modo, ahora la elección parece trivial... Y si el destino de Irdya "
"así lo dicta, alguien más competente tomará mi lugar y los llevará a la "
"victoria. Y entonces... seré recordada como una cobarde. Una cobarde que "
"abandonó a sus amigos porque no soportaba causarles más daño."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:46
msgid ""
"“<i>It is not too late.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"No. It’s pointless."
msgstr ""
"“<i>No es demasiado tarde.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"No. Es inútil."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:51
msgid ""
"“<i>Your journey has just begun. Your destiny is afoot; you cannot give up "
"now.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"But we have already lost... It’s over..."
msgstr ""
"“<i>Tu viaje acaba de comenzar. Tu destino está en marcha; no puedes "
"rendirte ahora.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"Pero ya hemos perdido... Se acabó..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:56
msgid ""
"“<i>As long as you live, you can learn from your mistakes, help your "
"friends, and most importantly, help Irdya.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"How?"
msgstr ""
"“<i>Mientras sigas con vida, puedes aprender de tus errores, ayudar a tus "
"amigos y, lo más importante, ayudar a Irdya.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"¿Cómo?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:61
msgid "“<i>Uria is the most powerful Guardian, but not the only one.</i>”"
msgstr "“<i>Uria es la Guardiana más poderosa, pero no la única.</i>”"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:70
msgid "... Who are you?"
msgstr "... ¿Quién eres?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:76
msgid "<big>WHO ARE YOU?!</big>"
msgstr "<big>¡¿QUIÉN ERES?!</big>"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:79
msgid "(<i>Anya’s voice</i>) “... Elynia?”"
msgstr "(<i>La voz de Anya</i>) “... ¿Elynia?”"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:85
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Two days had passed since our bittersweet victory in the Valley. Mal Hekuba "
"and his creations were gone, and the blast was mostly absorbed into the "
"collapsing portal. For a moment I had hoped none of what followed was more "
"than just a bad dream, a nightmare.\n"
"\n"
"It could not have been more real."
msgstr ""
"Habían pasado dos días desde nuestra agridulce victoria en el Valle. Mal "
"Hekuba y sus creaciones habían desaparecido, y la explosión fue absorbida en "
"su mayor parte por el portal en colapso. Por un momento, había esperado que "
"nada de lo sucedido fuera más que una pesadilla.\n"
"\n"
"No podría haber sido más real."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:90
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Anya and Durvan found me after an entire day of searching the nearby hills. "
"I had been badly injured by the fight with the lich, and my staff was gone.\n"
"\n"
"Elorran was right in his assessment of the situation. We should have "
"destroyed the Ruby before embarking upon this pointless quest. This has all "
"been my fault. Even before Uria centered her attention on Irdya... I had the "
"opportunity to avoid all this."
msgstr ""
"Anya y Durvan me encontraron tras un día entero de búsqueda en las colinas "
"cercanas. Había resultado gravemente herida en la lucha con el liche, y mi "
"bastón se había perdido. La aparición de Elyssa después de mi estrecha "
"escapatoria no fue, ciertamente, un sueño.\n"
"\n"
"Elorran tenía razón en su evaluación de la situación. Deberíamos haber "
"destruido el Rubí antes de embarcarnos en esta búsqueda inútil. Todo esto ha "
"sido mi culpa. Incluso antes de que Uria centrara su atención en Irdya... "
"tuve la oportunidad de evitar todo esto."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:96
msgid ""
"Many of our men simply did not survive our underground struggle. Anya "
"exhausted herself teleporting as many of them back to a safe location as she "
"could within that minuscule window of time; naturally, that wasn’t enough to "
"save them all.\n"
"\n"
"The girl remains as optimistic as usual, in spite of the grim circumstances. "
"I don’t think I can understand how she manages to do this after all we’ve "
"been through together."
msgstr ""
"Muchos de nuestros hombres simplemente no sobrevivieron a nuestra lucha "
"subterránea. Anya se agotó teletransportando a tantos de ellos como pudo a "
"un lugar seguro en esa pequeña ventana de tiempo; naturalmente, eso no fue "
"suficiente para salvarlos a todos.\n"
"\n"
"La chica sigue tan optimista como siempre, a pesar de las lúgubres "
"circunstancias. No creo poder entender cómo consigue hacerlo después de todo "
"lo que hemos pasado juntas."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:101
msgid ""
"She suggested that we return north to rejoin Elorran and decide our next "
"move.\n"
"\n"
"I know I need to recover Argan’s journal more than anything; the information "
"contained within it is most likely vital. Valen has not spoken a word about "
"it yet, however, so at best we can hope that Elorran’s many informants—"
"throughout Uria’s domain, and even Irdya—have gathered enough intelligence "
"on Uria and Elyssa’s plans by now."
msgstr ""
"Ella sugirió que regresáramos al norte para reunirnos con Elorran y decidir "
"nuestro próximo movimiento.\n"
"\n"
"Sé que necesito recuperar el diario de Argan más que nada; la información "
"que contiene es probablemente vital. Sin embargo, Valen no ha dicho una "
"palabra al respecto aún, así que, en el mejor de los casos, podemos esperar "
"que los numerosos informantes de Elorran —a lo largo del dominio de Uria, e "
"incluso en Irdya— hayan reunido suficiente información sobre los planes de "
"Uria y Elyssa para ahora."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:107
msgid ""
"Anya can easily determine Elorran and Tara’s current location with her "
"necklace. When she last communicated with them, they were seeking a place to "
"hide in the Falrore region, not too far northeast from Raelthyn. That’s most "
"likely where we are going now."
msgstr ""
"Anya puede determinar fácilmente la ubicación actual de Elorran y Tara con "
"su collar. La última vez que se comunicó con ellos, estaban buscando un "
"lugar para esconderse en la región de Falrore, no muy lejos al noreste de "
"Raelthyn. Es muy probable que ahí sea a donde nos dirigimos ahora."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:116
msgid ""
"The perpetrators of these hideous crimes against life were evidently "
"commanded to not take any prisoners or claim lands for their leaders.\n"
"\n"
"It took us an entire day and then some more to arrive to Raelthyn, but the "
"landscape along the road was hardly different to what we found in Falrore. "
"Tortured corpses everywhere, ruined buildings, entire towns and forests "
"burned down... It was clear that their victims never stood a chance. All "
"capable warriors had been sent to the front lines in the southern regions "
"and the borders of the Chaos Empire on purpose.\n"
"\n"
"Our enemies were aware of this. That’s why they were awaiting the "
"opportunity to invade the unprotected country, distracting the Grand Council "
"with pointless skirmishes. But they couldn’t smuggle their forces in and "
"pass unnoticed... Clearly, they had found a way to teleport their massive "
"armies anywhere, perhaps by using that damned artifact."
msgstr ""
"Los perpetradores de estos horrendos crímenes contra la vida fueron "
"claramente ordenados a no tomar prisioneros ni reclamar tierras para sus "
"líderes.\n"
"\n"
"Nos tomó un día entero y algo más llegar a Raelthyn, pero el paisaje a lo "
"largo del camino apenas era diferente de lo que encontramos en Falrore. "
"Cadáveres torturados por todas partes, edificios en ruinas, pueblos y "
"bosques enteros quemados... Estaba claro que sus víctimas nunca tuvieron "
"oportunidad. Todos los guerreros capaces habían sido enviados a las líneas "
"del frente en las regiones del sur y las fronteras del Imperio del Caos a "
"propósito.\n"
"\n"
"Nuestros enemigos eran conscientes de esto. Por eso esperaban la oportunidad "
"de invadir el país desprotegido, distrayendo al Gran Consejo con escaramuzas "
"inútiles. Pero no podían infiltrar sus fuerzas y pasar desapercibidos... "
"Claramente, habían encontrado una forma de teletransportar sus enormes "
"ejércitos a cualquier lugar, tal vez usando ese maldito artefacto."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:123
msgid "In effect, I caused this."
msgstr "En efecto, yo causé esto."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:127
msgid ""
"But once we made it to the capital region, we found out that not all was "
"lost. Or perhaps more precisely, we arrived in the nick of time."
msgstr ""
"Pero una vez que llegamos a la región de la capital, descubrimos que no todo "
"estaba perdido. O quizás, más precisamente, llegamos justo a tiempo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:136
msgid ""
"I could barely sleep on our way to Fort Astar. Perhaps it was because of "
"this that I couldn’t hear that voice again — that otherworldly, intriguing "
"voice.\n"
"\n"
"But this voice was not the one that attacked me in Kalari before. That voice "
"was just as beautiful, but terrifying rather than calming, and when she "
"taunted me again in Wesmere I assumed it was Uria. Who spoke to me before "
"Anya woke me up? Who could be interested in our success? Could it be the "
"fabled Guardian of the Arcane Flame herself? Could it be I’m losing my mind "
"because of everything that has happened since Galas and Mal Keshar woke me "
"up?\n"
"\n"
"I have always been rather skeptical about these matters, but the little "
"information we have gathered so far suggests that the Guardian—often "
"referred to as Eloh—is as real as Uria is, or at the very least, she used to "
"be. But if she truly lives, why hasn’t she helped us? It’s evident we have "
"not been graced by her divine powers for as long as we have existed. The "
"elves of the Great Continent have had to deal with much misfortune "
"throughout history, all on their own."
msgstr ""
"Apenas pude dormir en nuestro camino al Fuerte Astar. Quizás fue por esto "
"que no pude escuchar esa voz de nuevo — esa voz intrigante y de otro mundo.\n"
"\n"
"Pero esta voz no era la que me atacó en Kalari antes. Esa voz era igual de "
"hermosa, pero aterradora en lugar de tranquilizadora, y cuando me provocó de "
"nuevo en Wesmere, asumí que era Uria. ¿Quién me habló antes de que Anya me "
"despertara? ¿Quién podría estar interesado en nuestro éxito? ¿Podría ser la "
"legendaria Guardiana de la Llama Arcana en persona? ¿O será que estoy "
"perdiendo la cabeza por todo lo que ha pasado desde que Galas y Mal Keshar "
"me despertaron?\n"
"\n"
"Siempre he sido bastante escéptica respecto a estos asuntos, pero la poca "
"información que hemos reunido hasta ahora sugiere que la Guardiana —a menudo "
"referida como Eloh— es tan real como lo es Uria, o al menos lo fue. Pero si "
"realmente está viva, ¿por qué no nos ha ayudado? Es evidente que no hemos "
"sido agraciados con sus poderes divinos durante todo el tiempo que hemos "
"existido. Los elfos del Gran Continente han tenido que enfrentar muchas "
"desgracias a lo largo de la historia, completamente solos."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:143
msgid ""
"But I digress. What really matters now is not whether I’m slowly turning "
"into a deranged old hag—hopefully not—but rather what our current situation "
"is.\n"
"\n"
"We traveled westward as swiftly as we could with what little we had in terms "
"of supplies and human support. On the other hand, it never seems too "
"difficult for Durvan to convince his fellow men that the Grand Council has "
"fallen along with all proper military order and that the fate of their "
"country now lies in the hands of a few people led by a legendary elf, a "
"mixed-blood faerie, and a necromancer. The lowliest of individuals of any "
"given species tend to be gullible like that — and that is obviously "
"something Uria and her minions knew.\n"
"\n"
"Oh, Argan, how I wish your charisma wasn’t put to use by an evil goddess "
"from another world."
msgstr ""
"Pero me desvío. Lo que realmente importa ahora no es si estoy convirtiéndome "
"lentamente en una vieja loca —espero que no— sino cuál es nuestra situación "
"actual.\n"
"\n"
"Viajamos hacia el oeste tan rápido como pudimos con los pocos suministros y "
"apoyo humano que teníamos. Por otro lado, nunca parece ser demasiado difícil "
"para Durvan convencer a sus compañeros de que el Gran Consejo ha caído junto "
"con todo el orden militar y que el destino de su país ahora está en manos de "
"unas pocas personas lideradas por una elfa legendaria, una hada de sangre "
"mixta y un nigromante. Los individuos más humildes de cualquier especie "
"tienden a ser crédulos de esa manera —y eso es obviamente algo que Uria y "
"sus secuaces sabían.\n"
"\n"
"Oh, Argan, cómo desearía que tu carisma no hubiera sido utilizado por una "
"diosa maligna de otro mundo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:150
msgid "A Path to Follow"
msgstr "Un camino a seguir"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:151
msgid ""
"Leaving Huldnyir Hills and all the destruction in the border towns behind, "
"we promptly found a half-abandoned guard post beside the large flooded "
"region carved out by the great explosion in Glamdrol a little more than half "
"a year ago. They informed us of recent skirmishes, an advancing platoon, and "
"two refugees on a mission.\n"
"\n"
"Just as Valen previously assured us, they were still alive and in one piece, "
"at Fort Astar, and they had the journal.\n"
"\n"
"Mal Keshar did an excellent job of instructing Kyara to not allow anyone "
"else to access the contents of the journal, whatever his reasons were."
msgstr ""
"Dejando atrás las colinas de Huldnyir y toda la destrucción en los pueblos "
"fronterizos, encontramos rápidamente un puesto de guardia medio abandonado "
"junto a la gran región inundada creada por la gran explosión en Glamdrol "
"hace poco más de medio año. Nos informaron sobre recientes escaramuzas, un "
"pelotón que avanzaba y dos refugiados en una misión.\n"
"\n"
"Tal como Valen nos había asegurado anteriormente, todavía estaban vivos y en "
"una pieza, en el Fuerte Astar, y tenían el diario.\n"
"\n"
"Mal Keshar hizo un excelente trabajo al instruir a Kyara para que no "
"permitiera que nadie más accediera al contenido del diario, cualesquiera que "
"fueran sus razones."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:164
msgid ""
"“<i>I still remember when Uria first woke me up; her smile, her kindness. "
"She reminded me so much of Elynia...\n"
"\n"
"But all that has faded away with time. So much time has passed since she "
"brought me back to life...\n"
"\n"
"She still assures me she will bring new life to Irdya when the time comes, "
"as her role as the Guardian of Life demands — she is supposed to keep our "
"worlds on track to facilitate our progress.</i>”"
msgstr ""
"“<i>Todavía recuerdo cuando Uria me despertó por primera vez; su sonrisa, su "
"amabilidad. Me recordaba tanto a Elynia...\n"
"\n"
"Pero todo eso se ha desvanecido con el tiempo. Ha pasado tanto tiempo desde "
"que me devolvió a la vida...\n"
"\n"
"Aún me asegura que traerá nueva vida a Irdya cuando llegue el momento, como "
"lo exige su papel como Guardiana de la Vida: se supone que debe mantener "
"nuestros mundos en curso para facilitar nuestro progreso.</i>”"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:171
msgid ""
"Many pages are missing or seriously damaged. Argan’s writing often becomes "
"incoherent and meaningless as well, and some passages are not written in the "
"common script. Trying to make sense of this journal will be exceptionally "
"difficult."
msgstr ""
"Faltan muchas páginas o están seriamente dañadas. La escritura de Argan a "
"menudo se vuelve incoherente e incomprensible, y algunos pasajes no están "
"escritos en la escritura común. Intentar comprender este diario será "
"excepcionalmente difícil."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:174
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"“<i>I sorely miss the light of my soul, the elf to whom I devoted my life on "
"Irdya. I tried to find her and failed, and the Seer will not respond to my "
"inquiries. In fact, the Seer does not respond to anyone but Uria herself. "
"But Uria has different plans for me...\n"
"\n"
"She says locating Elynia is not important right now, and that I must deal "
"with the barbarians in the Great Desert first, to begin the process. What "
"process, I ask? What is the point of building a civilization from the scum "
"left after the Fall? Uria could enter Irdya with ease if she so desired. She "
"could then find the Seed of Earth, initiate a new cycle, and wait countless "
"eons.\n"
"\n"
"She says she knows an alternative. But first, she requires my support.</i>”"
msgstr ""
"“<i>Extraño profundamente la luz de mi alma, la elfa a quien dediqué mi vida "
"en Irdya. Traté de encontrarla y fracasé, y la Vidente no responde a mis "
"consultas. De hecho, la Vidente no responde a nadie excepto a Uria misma. "
"Pero Uria tiene planes diferentes para mí...\n"
"\n"
"Dice que localizar a Elynia no es importante ahora, y que primero debo "
"ocuparme de los bárbaros en el Gran Desierto, para iniciar el proceso. ¿Qué "
"proceso?, pregunto. ¿Cuál es el sentido de construir una civilización a "
"partir de la escoria que quedó después de la Caída? Uria podría entrar en "
"Irdya con facilidad si así lo deseara. Podría entonces encontrar la Semilla "
"de la Tierra, iniciar un nuevo ciclo y esperar incontables eones.\n"
"\n"
"Dice que conoce una alternativa. Pero primero, requiere mi apoyo.</i>”"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:181
msgid ""
"It’s hard to make sense of his ramblings. In some passages, he describes "
"Uria as a beautiful creature; in others, as a hideous monster whose cause he "
"laments serving.\n"
"\n"
"Was it the pain caused by his new body that numbed his reason, or the damage "
"Uria inflicted on his soul by using him as her Voice?"
msgstr ""
"Es difícil entender sus divagaciones. En algunos pasajes, describe a Uria "
"como una criatura hermosa; en otros, como un monstruo horrendo cuya causa "
"lamenta servir.\n"
"\n"
"¿Fue el dolor causado por su nuevo cuerpo lo que entumeció su razón, o el "
"daño que Uria infligió a su alma al usarlo como su Voz?"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:187
msgid ""
"“<i>The Voice, the Seer, and the Shadow. And as soon as we find Elynia, "
"there will be four, and four will spread our message of Life to the other "
"worlds.</i>”"
msgstr ""
"“<i>La Voz, la Vidente y la Sombra. Y tan pronto como encontremos a Elynia, "
"serán cuatro, y los cuatro difundirán nuestro mensaje de Vida a los otros "
"mundos.</i>”"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:228
msgid ""
"Uria has gathered much knowledge through her most devout followers, sent to "
"the outer worlds seeking any information she may require. Most of what we "
"have learned comes from the ruins in Karash, which appear to have existed "
"for longer than life as we know it. And of course, the Seer is always "
"willing to help once provided with the right questions by her.\n"
"\n"
"It is all so convoluted, I can barely begin to understand. I remember we "
"once believed in the Gods of Light and Darkness and such, but now..."
msgstr ""
"Uria ha reunido mucho conocimiento gracias a sus seguidores más devotos, "
"enviados a los mundos exteriores en busca de cualquier información que pueda "
"necesitar. La mayor parte de lo que hemos aprendido proviene de las ruinas "
"de Karash, que parecen haber existido por más tiempo que la vida tal como la "
"conocemos. Y, por supuesto, la Vidente siempre está dispuesta a ayudar, una "
"vez que ella le proporciona las preguntas adecuadas.\n"
"\n"
"Todo es tan enrevesado que apenas puedo comenzar a comprenderlo. Recuerdo "
"que una vez creíamos en los Dioses de la Luz y la Oscuridad y cosas así, "
"pero ahora..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:233
msgid ""
"Their kind, that of the First Gods; they ruled over everything that existed "
"and would exist for an eternity. Peaceful as they were, they lacked the "
"means to deal with what would end that eternity. The First Struggle took "
"place.\n"
"\n"
"It is said that most of them perished. A war amongst their kind; a more "
"powerful entity feeding upon them; none of our sources provide us with "
"factual information about the First Struggle, only speculations.\n"
"\n"
"Amongst the few survivors there were beings of light, and beings of "
"darkness, but only one master of the balance between both. He stepped forth "
"at the end of the Struggle to unite the others and create their legacy; a "
"construct none but him could access directly."
msgstr ""
"Los de su clase, los Primeros Dioses; gobernaron sobre todo lo que existía y "
"existiría por una eternidad. Pacíficos como eran, carecían de los medios "
"para enfrentar lo que pondría fin a esa eternidad. Tuvo lugar la Primera "
"Lucha.\n"
"\n"
"Se dice que la mayoría de ellos pereció. Una guerra entre los de su propia "
"clase; una entidad más poderosa que se alimentaba de ellos; ninguna de "
"nuestras fuentes nos brinda información fáctica sobre la Primera Lucha, solo "
"especulaciones.\n"
"\n"
"Entre los pocos supervivientes había seres de luz y seres de oscuridad, pero "
"solo uno era maestro del equilibrio entre ambos. Él dio un paso al frente al "
"final de la Lucha para unir a los demás y crear su legado; un constructo al "
"que ninguno salvo él podía acceder directamente."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:240
msgid ""
"Yarae, the Protector of the Tree of Life that gave us birth; the Tree that "
"represented the Ten aspects of his people, and from which Ten gods would "
"come into existence to function as the protectors and ideals of all their "
"descendants. Ten demons who would serve as the testament of the existence of "
"the First Gods and their universe."
msgstr ""
"Yarae, el Protector del Árbol de la Vida que nos dio nacimiento; el Árbol "
"que representaba los Diez aspectos de su pueblo, y del cual nacerían Diez "
"dioses para funcionar como protectores e ideales de todos sus descendientes. "
"Diez demonios que servirían como testimonio de la existencia de los Primeros "
"Dioses y su universo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:268
msgid "Ten demon gods to rule over our universe."
msgstr "Diez dioses demoníacos para gobernar nuestro universo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:278
msgid ""
"Life, Water, Thunder, Earth, Fire, Darkness, Light, Air, Ice, Existence; the "
"forces governing our reality, all sprung from the Tree along with the seeds "
"of their guardians, and their respective worlds. In time, life would spread "
"farther beyond throughout our universe, while ten worlds would enjoy the "
"rule of their assigned protectors.\n"
"\n"
"But things did not go exactly as planned."
msgstr ""
"Vida, Agua, Trueno, Tierra, Fuego, Oscuridad, Luz, Aire, Hielo, Existencia; "
"las fuerzas que gobiernan nuestra realidad, todas brotaron del Árbol junto "
"con las semillas de sus guardianes y sus respectivos mundos. Con el tiempo, "
"la vida se expandiría aún más a lo largo de nuestro universo, mientras diez "
"mundos gozarían del gobierno de sus protectores asignados.\n"
"\n"
"Pero las cosas no salieron exactamente como estaba previsto."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:284
msgid ""
"Even in the beginning, the world of the Guardian of Fire fell apart, "
"creating the blazing moon that would in time be known as Karash. The seed of "
"Fire crashed into Norsula, paving the way for perpetual chaos on a dark "
"world that was destined to belong to the bellicose beast that was the "
"Guardian of Water, not the fair woman whose songs told of a peaceful "
"existence on a bright land that would never be. The fate of their shared "
"domain hung by the delicate thread of their strange mutual love-hate "
"relationship; in time, that thread would be severed by the Guardian of Water "
"himself by piercing through her heart with his maw.\n"
"\n"
"Around the same time, a remarkably immature Guardian of Darkness would grow "
"inexplicably jealous over Yarae’s favoritism towards her sisters of Earth "
"and Life; for both the wielder of the Arcane Flame and the mistress of the "
"Void had powers and physical attributes she did not. She would rebel against "
"her creator and attempt to harness the full extent of her power, only to "
"fail and cause the utter destruction of all life in her domain, including "
"herself.\n"
"\n"
"Meanwhile, something happened to the Tree..."
msgstr ""
"Incluso al principio, el mundo de la Guardiana del Fuego se desmoronó, "
"creando la luna ardiente que con el tiempo sería conocida como Karash. La "
"semilla de Fuego se estrelló en Norsula, allanando el camino para un caos "
"perpetuo en un mundo oscuro que estaba destinado a pertenecer a la belicosa "
"bestia que era el Guardián del Agua, y no a la hermosa mujer cuyos cantos "
"hablaban de una existencia pacífica en una tierra brillante que nunca sería. "
"El destino de su dominio compartido pendía del delicado hilo de su extraña "
"relación de amor-odio; con el tiempo, ese hilo sería cortado por el propio "
"Guardián del Agua al atravesarle el corazón con sus fauces.\n"
"\n"
"Casi al mismo tiempo, una Guardiana de la Oscuridad notablemente inmadura "
"comenzaría a sentir celos inexplicables del favoritismo de Yarae hacia sus "
"hermanas de Tierra y Vida; pues tanto la portadora de la Llama Arcana como "
"la señora del Vacío tenían poderes y atributos físicos que ella no poseía. "
"Se rebelaría contra su creador e intentaría aprovechar todo el alcance de su "
"poder, solo para fracasar y causar la destrucción total de toda la vida en "
"su dominio, incluida ella misma.\n"
"\n"
"Mientras tanto, algo le ocurrió al Árbol..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:291
msgid ""
"It is said a powerful force beyond imagination possessed it and its "
"Protector. Yarae turned against the First Gods, and fled into our universe "
"to summon the powers of his remaining demons against his own brethren. Only "
"three of our guardians refused the call, aware that disobeying him "
"constituted an unforgivable sin, and that they could not stand a chance "
"against his ire.\n"
"\n"
"The remaining First Gods saw no option but to sacrifice themselves to create "
"a new entity that could rival the traitor and his corrupted creations: "
"Iluvia, the Avatar of the Union of Light and Darkness. She would obtain the "
"support of the three guardians who remained loyal to the First Gods and "
"their purpose: Uria, of Life, her sister of Earth and the Arcane Flame, and "
"her sister of Existence and Secrets.\n"
"\n"
"With their combined forces, they defeated Yarae and incarcerated him within "
"the Great Void. Alas, the cost was too great: all the other guardians were "
"destroyed, and so were the mortals who joined his cause—willingly or not—as "
"well as those unfortunate witnesses of the lengthy battle between gods."
msgstr ""
"Se dice que una fuerza poderosa más allá de la imaginación poseyó al Árbol y "
"a su Protector. Yarae se volvió contra los Primeros Dioses y huyó a nuestro "
"universo para invocar los poderes de sus demonios restantes contra sus "
"propios hermanos. Solo tres de nuestros guardianes rehusaron la llamada, "
"conscientes de que desobedecerlo constituía un pecado imperdonable y de que "
"no tendrían ninguna posibilidad frente a su ira.\n"
"\n"
"Los Primeros Dioses restantes no vieron otra opción que sacrificarse para "
"crear una nueva entidad que pudiera rivalizar con el traidor y sus "
"creaciones corruptas: Iluvia, el Avatar de la Unión de la Luz y la "
"Oscuridad. Ella obtendría el apoyo de los tres guardianes que permanecieron "
"leales a los Primeros Dioses y a su propósito: Uria, de la Vida; su hermana "
"de la Tierra y la Llama Arcana; y su hermana de la Existencia y los "
"Secretos.\n"
"\n"
"Con sus fuerzas combinadas, derrotaron a Yarae y lo encarcelaron en el Gran "
"Vacío. Pero el costo fue demasiado grande: todos los demás guardianes fueron "
"destruidos, al igual que los mortales que se unieron a su causa —de buena "
"gana o no—, así como aquellos desafortunados testigos de la prolongada "
"batalla entre dioses."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:300
msgid ""
"Our three goddesses did not have the power to repair the great damage "
"caused. And most importantly, it was never within their abilities to "
"resurrect the fallen.\n"
"\n"
"With her last forces, Iluvia instructed them to take the bulk of the "
"survivors to the remote worlds of Urvatha and Silida so they could continue "
"to progress on their own in a reality set apart from the rest, created by "
"the Guardian of Existence, and guarded by the Gatekeepers born from her many "
"hearts.\n"
"\n"
"Uria and her sister of Earth sacrificed their lives to restart the process "
"that brought them into existence, wiping out any remaining lives along with "
"their own, thus putting an end to the First Cycle."
msgstr ""
"Nuestras tres diosas no tenían el poder para reparar el gran daño causado. Y "
"lo más importante, nunca estuvo dentro de sus habilidades resucitar a los "
"caídos.\n"
"\n"
"Con sus últimas fuerzas, Iluvia les instruyó llevar a la mayoría de los "
"supervivientes a los mundos remotos de Urvatha y Silida, para que pudieran "
"seguir progresando por su cuenta en una realidad apartada del resto, creada "
"por la Guardiana de la Existencia y custodiada por los Guardianes del Portal "
"nacidos de sus muchos corazones.\n"
"\n"
"Uria y su hermana de la Tierra sacrificaron sus vidas para reiniciar el "
"proceso que las trajo a la existencia, aniquilando cualquier vida restante "
"junto con la suya propia, poniendo así fin al Primer Ciclo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:309
msgid ""
"Life flourished anew, with the hope of a new beginning.\n"
"\n"
"But the goddesses knew that it would not be the same."
msgstr ""
"La vida floreció de nuevo, con la esperanza de un nuevo comienzo.\n"
"\n"
"Pero las diosas sabían que no sería lo mismo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:314
msgid ""
"The Tree is tainted with imperfection, and so is our universe: strife and "
"chaos, death and misery.\n"
"\n"
"Near the end, the goddesses saw what was coming for us; and although no-one "
"had the chance to document it in detail before the process began, they did "
"leave some clues.\n"
"\n"
"And to ensure we would have the necessary resources to forge our own "
"destiny, Iluvia provided us with the legacy of the First Gods: two orbs, "
"each one holding the essences of Light and Darkness; and her own sacred "
"body. Their locations remained unknown until relatively recently: Irdya, "
"wherein the seed of Earth was planted, no longer tied to its guardian; "
"Norsula, wherein the new Guardians of Water and Fire would finally find "
"peace; and Ethea, wherein the seed of Life would prosper in solitude until "
"the new Guardian would return to claim it."
msgstr ""
"El Árbol está manchado de imperfección, y lo mismo ocurre con nuestro "
"universo: conflictos y caos, muerte y miseria.\n"
"\n"
"Cerca del final, las diosas vieron lo que se avecinaba; y aunque nadie tuvo "
"la oportunidad de documentarlo con detalle antes de que comenzara el "
"proceso, sí dejaron algunas pistas.\n"
"\n"
"Y para asegurarse de que tendríamos los recursos necesarios para forjar "
"nuestro propio destino, Iluvia nos proporcionó el legado de los Primeros "
"Dioses: dos orbes, cada uno conteniendo las esencias de Luz y Oscuridad; y "
"su propio cuerpo sagrado. Sus ubicaciones permanecieron desconocidas hasta "
"hace relativamente poco: Irdya, donde se plantó la semilla de la Tierra, ya "
"no ligada a su guardián; Norsula, donde los nuevos Guardianes de Agua y "
"Fuego finalmente encontrarían la paz; y Ethea, donde la semilla de la Vida "
"prosperaría en soledad hasta que la nueva Guardiana regresara para "
"reclamarla."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:321
msgid "Gathering Storm"
msgstr "Tormenta en formación"

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:322
msgid ""
"And it is with Iluvia’s legacy that our new Guardian of Life intends to put "
"an end to the fruitless existence to which we were doomed."
msgstr ""
"Y es con el legado de Iluvia que nuestra nueva Guardiana de la Vida pretende "
"poner fin a la existencia infructuosa a la que estábamos condenados."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:332
msgid ""
"My conviction falters. Everything since I returned to Irdya has been a "
"nightmare, and I begin to suspect I am becoming part of it myself. The mere "
"act of thought demands more effort than it used to, as if my very mind was "
"falling apart. Recent events have only increased this feeling of detachment "
"from reality.\n"
"\n"
"It was only a few days ago, in the Heart. While I was inspecting Reghara’s "
"prisoners, he mockingly alluded to his men and their toy. “What toy?”, I "
"asked. He somehow assumed I am concerned enough with their leisure "
"‘activities’ to have heard of this depravity beyond description; these "
"Irdyans should be thankful that Uria will not let me give them what they all "
"deserve at once."
msgstr ""
"Mi convicción flaquea. Todo desde que regresé a Irdya ha sido una pesadilla, "
"y empiezo a sospechar que yo misma estoy convirtiéndome en parte de ella. El "
"simple acto de pensar requiere más esfuerzo que antes, como si mi propia "
"mente se estuviera desmoronando. Los eventos recientes solo han aumentado "
"esta sensación de desconexión de la realidad.\n"
"\n"
"Fue hace solo unos días, en el Corazón. Mientras inspeccionaba a los "
"prisioneros de Reghara, él aludió burlonamente a sus hombres y su juguete. "
"“¿Qué juguete?”, pregunté. De alguna manera asumió que estoy lo "
"suficientemente preocupada por sus ‘actividades’ de ocio como para haber "
"oído de esta depravación indescriptible; estos irdyanos deberían estar "
"agradecidos de que Uria no me permita darles lo que todos merecen de una vez."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:344
msgid ""
"They had tortured the poor creature for weeks, keeping her alive with the "
"powers we taught them, and forcing her to feed upon the flesh of past "
"prisoners. But nothing is enough to hold a person who has already lost the "
"will to live.\n"
"\n"
"Despite the mud and wounds, her face and her hair were strangely familiar. "
"Had I met anyone like her before my own fall, or was I somehow responsible "
"for her fate? I put those questions and the pain they caused me aside, and "
"resolved to give her another chance.\n"
"\n"
"I would take full responsibility of her life... hoping our recently acquired "
"Norsulan technology would be enough to make the difference."
msgstr ""
"Habían torturado a la pobre criatura durante semanas, manteniéndola viva con "
"los poderes que les enseñamos, y obligándola a alimentarse de la carne de "
"prisioneros anteriores. Pero nada es suficiente para retener a una persona "
"que ya ha perdido la voluntad de vivir.\n"
"\n"
"A pesar del barro y las heridas, su rostro y su cabello eran extrañamente "
"familiares. ¿Había conocido a alguien como ella antes de mi propia caída, o "
"era yo de alguna manera responsable de su destino? Dejé de lado esas "
"preguntas y el dolor que me causaban, y resolví darle otra oportunidad.\n"
"\n"
"Asumiría toda la responsabilidad de su vida... esperando que la tecnología "
"norsulana recientemente adquirida fuera suficiente para marcar la diferencia."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:356
msgid ""
"Her subsequent awakening reminded me of my own, except that I did not have "
"the power to tap into her mind and comfort her, unlike Uria.\n"
"\n"
"I did not ask the girl what seemed to cause her more pain than before. Was "
"it the many modifications we had to perform on her devastated body to enable "
"her to live once again, or the separation of her body and her soul? Or "
"perhaps... the presence of the Source within her.\n"
"\n"
"Her name..."
msgstr ""
"Su posterior despertar me recordó al mío, excepto que no tenía el poder de "
"conectarme con su mente y consolarla, a diferencia de Uria.\n"
"\n"
"No le pregunté a la chica qué parecía causarle más dolor que antes. ¿Fueron "
"las numerosas modificaciones que tuvimos que realizar en su cuerpo devastado "
"para permitirle vivir de nuevo, o la separación de su cuerpo y su alma? O "
"tal vez... la presencia de la Fuente dentro de ella.\n"
"\n"
"Su nombre..."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:454
msgid ""
"This is not the same Uria I first met in the darkness. The kind and loving "
"girl who kept my broken body alive does not exist anymore."
msgstr ""
"Esta no es la misma Uria que conocí en la oscuridad. La muchacha amable y "
"amorosa que mantuvo con vida mi cuerpo roto ya no existe."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:457
msgid ""
"Her name was Lyphanea. Her people saw her as some kind of messiah meant to "
"do great things for the denizens of Urvatha, who longed for the end of the "
"Era of Great Strife and the beginning of the fabled Era of Unity. They all "
"knew she had been chosen by destiny to become the new Guardian of Life, "
"successor of one of the goddesses who sacrificed their very existence to "
"give the universe a new opportunity to live.\n"
"\n"
"But things changed after that fateful day."
msgstr ""
"Su nombre era Lyphanea. Su gente la veía como una especie de mesías "
"destinada a hacer grandes cosas por los habitantes de Urvatha, quienes "
"anhelaban el fin de la Era de las Grandes Disputas y el inicio de la "
"legendaria Era de la Unidad. Todos sabían que había sido elegida por el "
"destino para convertirse en la nueva Guardiana de la Vida, sucesora de una "
"de las diosas que sacrificaron su propia existencia para darle al universo "
"una nueva oportunidad de vivir.\n"
"\n"
"Pero las cosas cambiaron después de aquel fatídico día."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:462
msgid ""
"That day, we were exploring ancient ruins in our endless quest for knowledge "
"of our destinies. Lyphanea thought the ruins could guard the secret of the "
"creation of life, but all we found there were more vague scriptures and "
"grandiose descriptions of the feats performed by the previous Guardian of "
"Life.\n"
"\n"
"Upon our return to the village, we saw the aftermath of the carnage.\n"
"\n"
"Her people were not conquered and enslaved as is the norm with other demon "
"lords. No... the malefactor behind the bloodshed had a very specific goal in "
"mind: ensuring that the foretold Era of Unity would never come to pass. "
"Dorvoth of the Valdemons knew nothing specific about the girl who was to "
"become the new Guardian of Life, only her species, so the logical step for "
"him was methodical genocide."
msgstr ""
"Aquel día, explorábamos ruinas antiguas en nuestra interminable búsqueda de "
"conocimiento sobre nuestros destinos. Lyphanea pensaba que las ruinas podían "
"guardar el secreto de la creación de la vida, pero todo lo que encontramos "
"allí fueron escrituras vagas y grandiosas descripciones de las hazañas "
"realizadas por la anterior Guardiana de la Vida.\n"
"\n"
"Al regresar a la aldea, vimos las secuelas de la carnicería.\n"
"\n"
"Su gente no fue conquistada ni esclavizada como suele ser la norma con otros "
"señores demoníacos. No… el malhechor detrás de la masacre tenía un objetivo "
"muy específico en mente: asegurarse de que la profetizada Era de la Unidad "
"nunca llegara a suceder. Dorvoth de los Valdemonios no sabía nada concreto "
"sobre la muchacha que se convertiría en la nueva Guardiana de la Vida, solo "
"conocía su especie, por lo que el paso lógico para él fue un genocidio "
"metódico."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:469
msgid ""
"Of course, what little he knew about Lyphanea’s destiny was information he "
"obtained from the Seer herself: a being who betrays no-one, and takes no "
"side in any conflict.\n"
"\n"
"This Demon Lord Dorvoth simply failed to ask her the correct question."
msgstr ""
"Por supuesto, lo poco que sabía sobre el destino de Lyphanea era información "
"que obtuvo de la propia Vidente: un ser que no traiciona a nadie y que no "
"toma partido en ningún conflicto.\n"
"\n"
"Este Señor Demonio, Dorvoth, simplemente no supo formularle la pregunta "
"correcta."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:474
msgid ""
"After that day, Lyphanea changed. She focused all her time and energy "
"probing the mysteries of the Aspect of Life. But it was all in vain.\n"
"\n"
"Decades later, Dorvoth did not simply meet the girl always predestined to "
"end him, but an enraged goddess bent on his destruction. A goddess who had "
"just learned that creating or restoring life was not amongst the powers "
"naturally conferred to her by the Tree.\n"
"\n"
"He never stood a chance against she who went on to adopt the name of her "
"predecessor as her own."
msgstr ""
"Después de aquel día, Lyphanea cambió. Centró todo su tiempo y energía en "
"sondear los misterios del Aspecto de la Vida. Pero todo fue en vano.\n"
"\n"
"Décadas después, Dorvoth no se encontró simplemente con la muchacha "
"destinada desde siempre a acabar con él, sino con una diosa enfurecida "
"decidida a su destrucción. Una diosa que acababa de descubrir que crear o "
"restaurar vida no estaba entre los poderes naturalmente conferidos a ella "
"por el Árbol.\n"
"\n"
"Nunca tuvo oportunidad alguna frente a aquella que adoptaría el nombre de su "
"predecesora como propio."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:481
msgid ""
"Uria kept telling herself it would only be a matter of time, that she would "
"help both her world and the one I adopted as my own, but as time passed by, "
"her efforts proved fruitless... until she met the Seer herself.\n"
"\n"
"The Seer told her that Yarae consciously chose to prevent us from reaching "
"his tier of power, placing various restrictions in the design of our "
"universe. Restrictions that could be overcome or exploited given sufficient "
"time and research. Restrictions that Delethia herself may have managed to "
"break in order to create the Gatekeepers and her other rumored progeny. "
"Restrictions that could be abolished with the various instruments left "
"behind by the First Gods.\n"
"\n"
"Uria began to see our universe not as a system which she was meant to heal "
"and protect, but rather as an inherently flawed creation that needed to be "
"replaced."
msgstr ""
"Uria seguía diciéndose a sí misma que solo sería cuestión de tiempo, que "
"ayudaría tanto a su mundo como al que yo adopté como propio, pero con el "
"paso del tiempo, sus esfuerzos resultaron infructuosos… hasta que conoció a "
"la propia Vidente.\n"
"\n"
"La Vidente le dijo que Yarae eligió conscientemente impedir que nosotros "
"alcanzáramos su nivel de poder, imponiendo varias restricciones en el diseño "
"de nuestro universo. Restricciones que podrían superarse o aprovecharse dado "
"suficiente tiempo e investigación. Restricciones que la propia Delethia tal "
"vez logró romper para crear a los Guardianes del Portal y a su otra supuesta "
"descendencia. Restricciones que podrían ser abolidas con los diversos "
"instrumentos que dejaron los Primeros Dioses.\n"
"\n"
"Uria comenzó a ver nuestro universo no como un sistema que debía sanar y "
"proteger, sino como una creación inherentemente defectuosa que necesitaba "
"ser reemplazada."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:488
msgid ""
"Unbeknownst to Dorvoth, he was indirectly responsible for fulfilling the "
"prophecy of the Era of Unity; at least in its most literal form.\n"
"\n"
"Over time, Uria conquered every last Demon Lord who stood in her way and "
"forced them to either join her cause or be annihilated... along with their "
"subjects. She established a new power hierarchy with herself at the top and "
"the belligerent Demon Lords forced to serve her for as long as they lived. "
"It did not take her much time to crush all those who dared to defy the new "
"order.\n"
"\n"
"From every conquered race, Uria would learn something new, for the peoples "
"of Urvatha are all descended from survivors of the First Cycle, and a few of "
"them managed to preserve some ancient knowledge to this day."
msgstr ""
"Sin saberlo, Dorvoth fue indirectamente responsable de cumplir la profecía "
"de la Era de la Unidad; al menos en su forma más literal.\n"
"\n"
"Con el tiempo, Uria conquistó a cada último Señor Demonio que se interponía "
"en su camino y los obligó a unirse a su causa o ser aniquilados… junto con "
"sus súbditos. Estableció una nueva jerarquía de poder con ella misma en la "
"cima y los beligerantes Señores Demonio forzados a servirle mientras "
"vivieran. No le llevó mucho tiempo aplastar a todos aquellos que osaron "
"desafiar el nuevo orden.\n"
"\n"
"De cada raza conquistada, Uria aprendería algo nuevo, pues los pueblos de "
"Urvatha son todos descendientes de los supervivientes del Primer Ciclo, y "
"algunos lograron preservar hasta hoy un conocimiento antiguo."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:495
msgid ""
"She would eventually gain access to Silida, a sibling world that existed "
"under the same starless sky as Urvatha. And of course, she would find a way "
"to subdue the Guardian of Earth born there to ensure she would not interfere."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente obtendría acceso a Silida, un mundo hermano que existía bajo el "
"mismo cielo sin estrellas que Urvatha. Y, por supuesto, encontraría la "
"manera de someter a la Guardiana de la Tierra nacida allí para asegurarse de "
"que no interfiriera."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:498
msgid ""
"In time, Uria would come up with a contrived series of theories and plans to "
"ascend to the level of the First Gods without committing Merthiaal’s "
"mistakes. The goal: creating a new, perfect universe in which life would be "
"completely controlled by her will; a universe without death; a universe "
"without Yarae’s creations; and most importantly, a universe where she would "
"be the only ruling goddess.\n"
"\n"
"But to achieve that goal, she would have to cope with the power growing "
"inside her; the power of the guardians, drawn from the Source amidst the "
"endless void beyond our universe; unlimited power.\n"
"\n"
"It is clear now that she failed to escape from the nefarious tendrils of "
"that corrupting force."
msgstr ""
"Con el tiempo, Uria idearía una enrevesada serie de teorías y planes para "
"ascender al nivel de los Primeros Dioses sin cometer los errores de "
"Merthiaal. El objetivo: crear un nuevo y perfecto universo en el que la vida "
"estaría completamente controlada por su voluntad; un universo sin muerte; un "
"universo sin las creaciones de Yarae; y lo más importante, un universo donde "
"ella sería la única diosa gobernante.\n"
"\n"
"Pero para alcanzar ese objetivo, tendría que lidiar con el poder que crecía "
"dentro de ella; el poder de los guardianes, extraído de la Fuente en medio "
"del interminable vacío más allá de nuestro universo; un poder ilimitado.\n"
"\n"
"Ahora está claro que no logró escapar de los nefastos tentáculos de esa "
"fuerza corruptora."

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:506
msgid ""
"I am writing this now as I prepare for the inevitable. My arrangement with "
"Uria requires me to forfeit free will in order to allow Elyssa to live. "
"Sooner or later, this will lead to my own demise, but I am somehow not "
"troubled by this notion. It is said that great things will come afterwards.\n"
"\n"
"If anyone finds this journal, they will learn the truth. But I also want "
"them to ensure that Elynia does as well. And then, when the time comes, she "
"will know what must be done. And she will know that she need not mourn my "
"death.\n"
"\n"
"Because, sometimes, your loved ones must be willing to sacrifice their lives "
"for a greater cause."
msgstr ""
"Escribo esto ahora mientras me preparo para lo inevitable. Mi acuerdo con "
"Uria requiere que renuncie a mi libre albedrío para permitir que Elyssa "
"viva. Tarde o temprano, esto conducirá a mi propia desaparición, pero de "
"algún modo no me preocupa esta idea. Se dice que grandes cosas vendrán "
"después.\n"
"\n"
"Si alguien encuentra este diario, aprenderá la verdad. Pero también quiero "
"que se aseguren de que Elynia lo haga. Y entonces, cuando llegue el momento, "
"sabrá lo que debe hacer. Y sabrá que no necesita llorar mi muerte.\n"
"\n"
"Porque, a veces, tus seres queridos deben estar dispuestos a sacrificar sus "
"vidas por una causa mayor."

#. [character_profile]: id=Durvan, race=human, gender=male
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:10
msgid "Suthwood"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Durvan, race=human, gender=male
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:15
msgid ""
"<b>Durvan</b> is a young huntsman from the small border village of Suthwood, "
"in the southern outskirts of the Heart Forest.\n"
"\n"
"For most remote settlements on the edges of the deep forest, hunting is not "
"only the backbone of their economy but also the core of their self-defense "
"strategy. The steep terrain combined with the impenetrable nature of the "
"woods might provide a natural barrier against foreign invaders, but this "
"does little to deter those better acquainted with the local geography, such "
"as bandits and necromancers — major threats which have seen a resurgence in "
"the past three years, an unfortunate consequence of the Grand Council’s "
"focus on waging war against the Chaos Empire.\n"
"\n"
"It follows that huntsmen like Durvan are highly respected members of society "
"in the forested borderlands, no matter how little their field experience "
"might be. Sadly, this sentiment is seldom shared by the more affluent "
"Aragwaith of the inner country, who more often than not regard them as "
"illiterate barbarians with no understanding of tactics or craftsmanship."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Anya, race=faerie, gender=female
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:30
#, fuzzy
msgid "Demon Lord Elorran"
msgstr "Señor Demonio Alavys"

#. [character_profile]: id=Anya, race=faerie, gender=female
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Originally introduced to Elynia’s group in the guise of a helpless human "
"girl, <b>Anya</b> is in truth a faerie of the deep forest strongly attuned "
"to the power of Darkness. For a long time she has journeyed the Far North in "
"the company of her adopted family: the <b>Demon Lord Elorran</b> and the "
"dryad <b>Tara</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Having heard and admired Elynia’s exploits for a long time, Anya was chosen "
"as the perfect candidate to bring the Lady of Light to Elorran’s side, with "
"the intention of destroying the Ruby of Fire before Uria could get her hands "
"on it. Unfortunately, Elynia refused to accede to Elorran’s terms and "
"instead decided to take the Ruby with her on a last mission. In order to "
"ensure that the Ruby remains safe and that Elynia and Elorran have a way to "
"communicate should any unexpected developments arise, the latter dispatched "
"Anya to accompany her for the remainder of her mission."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:42
msgid ""
"Following the demise of Elorran and Tara, Anya revealed to Elynia and Durvan "
"that she was abandoned by her parents as a child due to their intense hatred "
"of faeriekind creatures, an all too common trait amongst the humans of the "
"Far North. Tara found the girl shortly after, and brought her to Elorran, "
"who then took pity on her and decided to raise her with Tara’s help despite "
"the dangers of his life as a rebel leader.\n"
"\n"
"Having nowhere else left to go, Anya decided to follow Elynia until the end."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:49
#, fuzzy
msgid "Anya, the Guardian of Darkness"
msgstr "Guardiana de la Oscuridad"

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:50
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Dark Lady"
msgstr "¡A las armas! ¡Por la Dama Oscura!"

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:51
msgid "The Ten Guardians, Demon Lord Ergea"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:52
msgid ""
"While attempting to secure a strategical keep in Kalari Central, Anya’s "
"group ran into a trap set up by the <b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b>, where a "
"number of advanced Shaxthal creatures known as the <b>Deathbringers</b> "
"cornered them in a sealed-off room. In an attempt to give Durvan and Ergea a "
"chance to escape, Anya used up all her strength to fight the creatures to no "
"avail, only to be mortally wounded in battle herself and reduced to the same "
"viscuous form as all other fallen shapeshifters.\n"
"\n"
"Just as the human and the demon lord were about to give into hopelessness, "
"Anya’s remains suddenly lit up with the intensity of a small sun, throwing "
"the twisted creatures into disarray as her body began taking shape again, "
"lifted upwards by an unseen force. Immediately after, a powerful energy "
"emanated from her, maiming and hurting her enemies while leaving her friends "
"untouched. As the abominations desperately fled the broken keep, Anya’s body "
"finished congealing into its usual form, her consciousness barely recovered "
"from the motionless haze she had been submerged into following her fatal "
"injuries.\n"
"\n"
"With her companions’ assistance, Anya made it out of the keep and understood "
"that her new life as the <b>Guardian of Darkness</b> had just begun."
msgstr ""

#. [story_recap]: id=IftU
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:5
msgid "Invasion from the Unknown"
msgstr ""

#. [story_recap]: id=IftU
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:6
msgid ""
"Long after the <b>Great Fall</b>, the last forest elves of Irdya living in "
"the Valley of Elynia face a new threat hailing from unknown lands to the "
"south. <b>Galas</b> and his patrol group successfully repel the outsiders, "
"only for a larger host to arrive three days later and completely overpower "
"the valley’s defenses. Much to the elves’ horror, the soldiers from the so-"
"called <b>Chaos Empire</b> prove nigh unstoppable this time around, counting "
"powerful otherwordly creatures amongst their ranks, an insatiable thirst for "
"blood, and an unstoppable zeal for their wicked gods: <b>Uria</b> and "
"<b>Yechnagoth</b>."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:9
msgid "I. Exodus"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:11
msgid ""
"What won your victory was nothing else than the power of the Union, at hands "
"of the Master of Darkness <i>and</i> the Lady of Light — a human and an "
"elven lady."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:14
msgid ""
"Following a bloody battle at Telchior’s Hold, <b>Lord Lédinor</b>, Galas, "
"and the elf enchantress <b>Anlindë</b> convene to figure out a way forward. "
"Having run out of options that would not result in complete extinction of "
"elvenkind at the hands of the Chaos Empire, Lord Lédinor chooses to stay "
"behind and rally part of the remaining defense forces to mount a "
"distraction; meanwhile, Galas is taked with leading a complete evacuation of "
"the valley towards the northern desert.\n"
"\n"
"In the middle of the evacuation, Galas and his forces run into a powerful "
"lich from the times before the Fall by the name of <b>Mal Keshar</b>. The "
"elves manage to subdue the necromancer, and while interrogating him Galas "
"finds out more about the nature of the Chaos Empire’s forces, as well as "
"certain events from the times of the Fall — in particular, about elvenkind’s "
"previous victory against <b>demons</b> from <b>Inferno</b>. Mal Keshar "
"recounts the story of the <b>Lady of Light</b> and the <b>Master of "
"Darkness</b>, their triumph against the <b>Demon Lord</b>, and their long "
"slumber in the depths of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Ignoring his subordinates’ protests and Anlindë’s reluctance, Galas decides "
"to trust the lich’s words and accept his promises of guiding the elves to "
"the depths of the <b>Heart Mountains</b>, where the two legendary heroes lie "
"dormant."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:22
msgid "II. Seeking the Light"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Your sacrifice won’t be forgotten, and I swear that I will not rest until "
"the last of our enemies is reduced to cinders on the ground."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:27
msgid ""
"After a long and perilous journey across the desert — including a brief "
"encounter with the forces of Chaos — the forest elves reach the mountain "
"range and proceeded underground, where they find out that the forces of the "
"<b>Chaos Warlord</b> have already arrived in search for the Lady of Light. "
"Through sheer coincidence, Galas’s expedition force runs into the dwarves of "
"<b>Herthgar</b> and forge an impromptu alliance to repel the invaders.\n"
"\n"
"Upon meeting with <b>King Asthorgar</b> and the Runemaster <b>Althurin</b> "
"at the dwarven capital, the group learn of the heroic deeds of <b>Kalehssar</"
"b> of the <b>Quenoth</b> elves centuries before the Chaos invasion, "
"including his travels across the sands in search for a new home for his "
"people, his alliance with the dwarves of <b>Gnalvarden</b>, his voyage far "
"into the Vast Sea and towards Zocthanol Isle, and his slaying of "
"<b>Yechnagoth, the Eater of Souls</b>.\n"
"\n"
"King Asthorgar warns Galas that although his people may find refuge in the "
"surface lands of the Far North, he has no doubt that the Chaos Empire will "
"eventually march towards them as well. Aware of the major risks they are "
"about to face in their search for the two heroes, Galas opts to send the "
"elves’ main host north under the leadership of <b>Lord Inodien</b>, while he "
"and his companions proceed deeper underground with Althurin’s help.\n"
"\n"
"In the deepest reaches of Irdya, Galas’s band finally find the resting place "
"of the heroes. Inside, however, they only find and awaken one of them: "
"<b>Elynia, the Lady of Light</b>. Following some initial confusion, the "
"faerie explains that her lover <b>Argan, the Master of Darkness</b> died. "
"After recounting the full story of the Fall and the <b>War of Wesmere</b> "
"from her point of view, she reveals that Anlindë was in truth the sole "
"surviving apostate from amongst the cultists who once served the <b>Demon "
"Lord Zhangor</b> in Wesmere.\n"
"\n"
"On the way back to the underground capital, the group run into the Chaos "
"Warlord’s vanguard in the middle of their relentless siege. Aided by "
"Elynia’s powers of Light and Mal Keshar’s undead soldiers, Galas’s group "
"finally manage to break through and reach the king’s palace. With "
"devastating losses on the dwarves’ side, King Asthorgar resolves to lead his "
"people out of the infested caves. Fully aware that an emergency evacuation "
"like this would likely result in the complete annihilation of Herthgar "
"otherwise, and despite Galas’s attempts to change her mind, Anlindë assumes "
"the last defense of the dwarven kingdom, hoping to stall for time while "
"everyone else escapes to the Far North.\n"
"\n"
"While King Asthorgar and Galas exit the caves, Anlindë finally comes face to "
"face with the <b>biomechanical creature</b> known as the Chaos Warlord. "
"Despite the elf even resorting to using Zhangor’s forbidden magic, the Chaos "
"Warlord crushes her with ease. In a last-ditch attempt to defeat the "
"creature, Anlindë brings the entire central section of the caves down, "
"resulting in her own death; however, despite suffering various injuries, the "
"Chaos Warlord survives and retreats back to the lands of the Empire in the "
"south."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:40
msgid "III. Armageddon"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:42
msgid ""
"Uria is a forgiving god, but there is little that can be done to remedy "
"things when fools like you actively refuse to listen to her Voice."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:43
msgid "The Chaos Emperor"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:45
msgid ""
"In the Far North, Galas, Elynia, and Mal Keshar makes their way through the "
"<b>Aragwaith country</b> and into their capital, <b>Raelthyn</b>, where they "
"participate in the <b>Grand Council of the Northern Peoples</b> alongside "
"Lord Inodien and Lady Unarye. In exchange for the elves being granted lands "
"to settle in the country, Galas pledges his people’s allegiance to the Grand "
"Council, including a formal declaration of war from the elves against the "
"Chaos Empire, and their assistance in the war effort. As an additional "
"condition imposed by the Council, the Lady of Light, Mal Keshar, and all "
"necromancers under the latter’s tutelage are required to pledge "
"unconditional allegiance to it while also renouncing the elves’ own "
"leadership.\n"
"\n"
"While on a diplomatic mission to secure an alliance with the orcish tribes "
"before the Chaos Empire can do so themselves, Galas’s band runs into the "
"lich <b>Mal Hekuba</b> from the <b>Iron Triad</b>, who attempts to "
"manipulate Elynia into seeking the Emperor’s counsel regarding Argan’s fate. "
"After repelling the lich’s forces, Elynia and Mal Keshar come to terms with "
"Galas’s pact with the Grand Council and agree with his secret plan to "
"infiltrate the Chaos Empire and take its leader down. Galas then delegates "
"leadership of the elves of the Valley to Lord Inodien and Lady Unarye.\n"
"\n"
"While leaving the northlands, Galas begins hearing an ominous voice in his "
"head trying to instill doubt and fear into him. Shortly after, the group "
"runs into Mal Hekuba a second time, who unsuccessfully attempts to bar their "
"path before fleeing the battlefield again.\n"
"\n"
"At the plains of Wesmere, the group explore the desolate ruins of the realm "
"that were once Zhangor’s domain on Irdya. While the demon’s residual taint "
"causes hallucinations and infighting amongst Galas’s group, the voice in the "
"elf’s head grows louder and more forceful, revealing itself to be the Chaos "
"Emperor trying to take control of his body in order to murder the Lady of "
"Light. Galas manages to resist just long enough for Elynia to purge the "
"darkness out of his body."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:54
msgid "IV. The Union"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:56
msgid ""
"This is only the beginning, Lady of Light. The beginning of your downfall. "
"Everything and everyone you hold dear shall perish in time."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:59
msgid ""
"Thanks to a chance encounter with a dwarven task force under Althurin’s "
"command, Galas, Elynia, and Mal Keshar manage to mount an all-out offensive "
"on the capital of the Chaos Empire, the Heart fortress. In the dungeon, they "
"find an imprisoned and tortured <b>Lédinor</b>; after helping him back on "
"his feet, Elynia privately reveals to Galas that the old elf might be "
"infected with something that could allow the Emperor to control him like he "
"attempted to do with Galas.\n"
"\n"
"In the lower levels, they finally meet <b>Elyssa, the Chaos Warlord</b> — "
"the <b>Fire of Uria</b> — who proceeds to subdue the trio and force them to "
"flee deeper into a hive of biomechanical abominations deep under the "
"fortress. Before encountering demoness a second time, Elynia convinces Mal "
"Keshar to channel a great darkness coming from deep below to help her summon "
"the <b>Union of Light and Darkness</b> — the same legendary power she and "
"Argan once wielded against Zhangor. With the legendary power now on their "
"side, the duo defeat Elyssa; however, Elynia has an unexpected change of "
"heart before dealing the killing blow, and spares the creature’s life.\n"
"\n"
"After crossing the gateway from Irdya into the frozen wastes of Inferno, the "
"group fight their way into the Chaos Emperor’s lair, where they finally "
"learn the truth that Elynia had suspected and concealed from them for a long "
"time: the Chaos Emperor is none other than <b>Argan, the Master of Darkness</"
"b> — the <b>Voice of Uria</b>. Despite her immense emotional turmoil upon "
"seeing him turned into a biomechanical monster in service of evil, Elynia "
"resolves to put an end to Argan’s dominion over Irdya and kill him, to which "
"he responds in kind.\n"
"\n"
"Although Elynia and Mal Keshar initially gain the upper hand against Argan’s "
"minions by utilizing the power of the Union, the dark sorcerer levels the "
"field by puppeteering the latter’s body, thus forcing Elynia to take him "
"down and rendering her incapable of channeling the Union without approaching "
"Argan up close. Despite Argan’s augmented body, Galas and Elynia manage to "
"prevail over him. An enraged <b>Uria</b> resolves to take action, "
"transforming Argan into a large misshapen beast, and assuming partial "
"control of his body. Mal Keshar rejoins the fight in the nick of time, "
"allowing the trio to fatally wound Argan; this results in the power of the "
"Union splitting apart and abandoning both Argan’s and Elynia’s bodies.\n"
"\n"
"While on his death throes, Argan apologizes to Elynia for somehow “allowing” "
"Uria to become who she is now and for allowing her to control him. Powerless "
"to do anything to bring her beloved back, the heartbroken faerie accepts "
"Lédinor’s suggestion to take Argan’s journal right as the lair and its "
"connection to Irdya begin to collapse. On their way out, Uria decides to "
"strike yet again by using the infection in Lédinor’s body to transform him "
"into another monster, who then Galas is forced to take down.\n"
"\n"
"Some time after escaping the destruction of the Heart fortress, the trio "
"decide to head back to the Far North to pay the forest elves a visit, with "
"the intention of sailing towards Zocthanol Isle in search of answers "
"regarding Uria and Yechnagoth."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_verlissh
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:16
msgid "On the Verlissh"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_verlissh
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:19
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The <b>Verlissh</b> are a primitive Rythenian lifeform brought to Irdya by "
"the <b>Argazar</b>. Under certain conditions, these creatures can combine to "
"form larger and more complex units, and even integrate themselves into "
"foreign organisms, adapting to their bodies and augmenting them. The "
"symbiotic relationship they develop with their host comes at a price for "
"both, however — the host and the Verlissh become reliant on each other’s "
"functions to survive."
msgstr ""
"Los <b>Verlissh</b> son una forma de vida Rytheniana primitiva traída a "
"Irdya por los <b>Argazar</b>. Bajo ciertas condiciones, estas criaturas "
"pueden combinarse para formar unidades más grandes y complejas, e incluso "
"integrarse en organismos ajenos, adaptándose a sus cuerpos y aumentándolos. "
"Sin embargo, la relación simbiótica que desarrollan con su huésped tiene un "
"precio para ambos: el huésped y los Verlissh se vuelven dependientes de las "
"funciones del otro para sobrevivir."

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_verlissh
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:21
msgid ""
"<b>Uria</b> has learned that the Argazar civilization used the Verlissh to "
"enhance the abilities and strength of their <b>‘biomechanical’</b> warriors. "
"There are ruins scattered across Irdya from which we could obtain samples "
"to, in time, raise a whole army to put an end to the current Dark Age."
msgstr ""
"<b>Uria</b> ha descubierto que la civilización Argazar utilizaba a los "
"Verlissh para mejorar las habilidades y la fuerza de sus guerreros "
"<b>‘biomecánicos’</b>. Hay ruinas esparcidas por Irdya de las que podríamos "
"obtener muestras para, con el tiempo, levantar un ejército completo y poner "
"fin a la actual Edad Oscura."

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:26
msgid "On Norsula"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The advanced <b>Norsulan</b> technology stolen by Uria’s agents from those "
"working for the one who is rumored to be the reincarnation of <b>Valdir</b> "
"has been very helpful for our ends; understanding the most interesting "
"creations of the Argazar people would have proved nearly impossible without "
"a better-documented modern reference."
msgstr ""
"La avanzada tecnología <b>Norsulana</b> robada por los agentes de Uria a "
"quienes trabajaban para aquel que se rumorea es la reencarnación de "
"<b>Valdir</b> ha sido de gran ayuda para nuestros fines; comprender las "
"creaciones más interesantes del pueblo Argazar habría resultado casi "
"imposible sin una referencia moderna mejor documentada."

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#. The hexadecimal numbers represent the following ASCII sequence:
#. RUBYOFFIRE
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:33
msgid ""
"I do find it amusing that one of the biggest breakthroughs in the Norsulan "
"pursuit of godhood happens to be based on <i>my</i> own research which ████ "
"and I wrote down on our grimoire back there. How <i>delightful</i> it is to "
"find out that so many generations later, the rulers of Norsula’s "
"technological empire would indulge in the same sort of blasphemy that got me "
"banished here in the first place! ██\n"
"\n"
"I do█find their use of the Missing Number for this purpose an absolute "
"mockery of the dark arts; alas, I infer that necromancy never became as "
"widespread over there as it did on Irdya. Quite curious, that; is Norsula "
"special for having such a strong barrier between itself and Arvadelidrya, or "
"is Ird█a special for the opposite phenomenon? If the latter, could it be "
"because of the Wesfolk tampering with π§█ € +¢ Á ███ 52 55 42 59 4F 46 46 49 "
"52 45"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#. The hexadecimal numbers represent the following ASCII sequences:
#. EL / IAMSORRY
#. When Argan says "for her sake", it is unclear who she's referring to
#. (it could be Uria or another unspecified female person).
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:41
msgid ""
"%¶█Ä¡° █Ü 45 4C suppose Uria is content with continuing experimentation on "
"Subject 00-44A for the time being.█\n"
"\n"
"ª ß§§█C§ &amp;██P surprisingly resistant to contamination, unlike ¶C¨ ø█ "
"W-39 © É/ 5ƒ suppose it is the same quality that makes Irdyan humans more "
"resistant to essences from beyond the physical realm. ██©█ evolutionary "
"advantage, perhaps?\n"
"\n"
"49 41 4D 53 4F 52 52 59 sentimentality is the enemy of progress. █ must "
"carry out Uria’s plan for her sake."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_merthiaal
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:50
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Eater of Souls"
msgstr "El Frente Oriental"

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_merthiaal
#. Redacted: Xia'el, Yrathid
#. Note: Urvatha = Inferno. Uria is considered the mother of Inferno
#. in a strictly figurative sense.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:56
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"According to some ancient legends of disputable origin, the <b>First</b> "
"sculpted a <b>beautiful maiden</b> out of fine dust, ██████, and bestowed "
"her control over the awesome power that flows through the veins of every one "
"of her <b>faerie</b> descendants, including the elves of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Those legends also tell of one of her siblings: <b>Merthiaal the Ashen One</"
"b>, who owing to her bold actions would come to be known as the <b>Eater of "
"Souls</b>. Even after a cycle has passed, the oldest races of Irdya and "
"other worlds continue to remember her, and avoid mentioning her true name in "
"conversation. If they must, they will speak of her as <b>‘Yechnagoth’</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Now, Merthiaal fervently desired the First’s favor. Alas, no matter how hard "
"she tried, someone with such an aching heart could not possibly manage to "
"tame the <b>Aspect of Darkness</b>. She could never accept that the First "
"only had eyes for the <b>wielder of the Arcane Flame</b>, and <b>Uria</b>, "
"the Guardian who would come to be regarded as the <b>mother of Urvatha</b>.\n"
"\n"
"As time went on, envy rooted deep within Merthiaal’s mind. In an attempt to "
"prove her worth, she committed an <b>unspeakable sin</b> against the order "
"of the Universe. Her control over Darkness was lost as a result. Her own "
"world, ███████, was destroyed, along with <b>every soul</b> on it. Any "
"further damage was only narrowly averted thanks to Uria’s timely "
"intervention.\n"
"\n"
"Merthiaal’s heart, soul, and memories were preserved through eons, but her "
"body was not.\n"
"\n"
"Now we have the means to build a new body that may allow her power to flow "
"unimpeded once again. If she can be convinced to accept Uria’s offer, then "
"she shall have a new opportunity to destroy the descendants of her rival and "
"allow us to reign over this decadent world."
msgstr ""
"Según algunas leyendas antiguas de origen discutible, la <b>Primera</b> "
"esculpió a una <b>hermosa doncella</b> a partir de fino polvo y le otorgó el "
"control sobre el asombroso poder que fluye por las venas de cada uno de sus "
"descendientes <b>feéricos</b>, incluidos los elfos de Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Esas leyendas también hablan de uno de sus hermanos: <b>Merthiaal, la "
"Cenicienta</b>, quien debido a sus acciones audaces llegaría a ser conocida "
"como la <b>Devoradora de Almas</b>. Incluso después de un ciclo, las razas "
"más antiguas de Irdya y otros mundos continúan recordándola y evitan "
"mencionar su verdadero nombre en conversación. Si deben hacerlo, la llaman "
"<b>‘Yechnagoth’</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Ahora, Merthiaal deseaba fervientemente el favor de la Primera. Sin embargo, "
"por mucho que lo intentó, alguien con un corazón tan doliente no podía "
"dominar el <b>Aspecto de la Oscuridad</b>. Nunca pudo aceptar que la Primera "
"solo tuviera ojos para la <b>portadora de la Llama Arcana</b> y <b>Uria</b>, "
"la Guardiana que llegaría a ser considerada la <b>madre de Urvatha</b>."

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_puzzle_gate_key
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:71
msgid "Worn Parchment"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_puzzle_gate_key
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:74
msgid ""
"(Most of the parchment is worn to the point of being completely illegible, "
"save for the following bits circled in what could either be red ink or "
"blood)\n"
"\n"
"[...] Beta Power Plant [...] E4 [...]\n"
"\n"
"[...] 97 [...] Detritus Processing [...]\n"
"\n"
"[...] Delta Power Substation [...] 2F [...]"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_memo_9153
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:88
msgid ""
"Per the Fire of Uria’s command, work on the Ivyel program at the Wesmere "
"Abaddon 3 Facility shall be transferred to Kalari Central, Level E5, "
"effective immediately. All assets are to be relocated within 70 days. "
"Coastal transfer route West-1 has been assigned for this task.\n"
"\n"
"Signed off by: Mal Kendria, Iron Council"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_memo_9149
#. The notes for this entry are written by Mal Si'ah, who uses they/them or gender-neutral pronouns to refer to themselves.
#. This is only relevant in languages with more than one first-person pronoun.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:100
msgid ""
"Per the Fire of Uria’s command, work on the Thornfire program shall be "
"discontinued permanently, and all related assets — including the "
"experimental housing unit — must be destroyed within 10 days.\n"
"\n"
"Signed off by: Mal Kendria, Iron Council\n"
"\n"
"⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯\n"
"Note #1 (Mal Si’ah)\n"
"\n"
"Truly, it is a pity that Argan’s untimely demise set us back so much, in so "
"many unexpected ways. For two whole centuries Mal Abaddon and I had been "
"looking forward to the completion of this project. To add insult to injury, "
"the cancelation has turned his preaching even more insufferable than it "
"already was.\n"
"\n"
"Alas, the Fire’s word is law now — if she sees no use in Thornfire then she "
"must have her reasons. Besides, like Argan would constantly say to us back "
"in the day, “we must put our personal ambitions aside for the sake of the "
"ultimate reward”.\n"
"\n"
"At the end of the day, I am but a humble servant bound by oath to work in "
"benefit of her Empire.\n"
"\n"
"⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯\n"
"Note #2 (Mal Si’ah)\n"
"\n"
"Even when it comes to disposing of aborted experiments, these absolute "
"buffoons have no work ethic at all — leaving me to do over half of the job "
"entirely by myself! Would that they had learned a thing or two from their "
"precious Emperor! Sigh.\n"
"\n"
"I miss that poor maniac. May he rest in peace."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_note_443
#. This entry is written by Mal Si'ah, who uses they/them or gender-neutral pronouns to refer to themselves.
#. This is only relevant in languages with more than one first-person pronoun.
#. Redacted text:
#. "Argan managed to achieve such unparalleled success with Subject 00-44A. Some say it was a blessing from Uria — others say it was his power as the Master of Darkness."
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:130
msgid ""
"If Yechnagoth’s original soul was able to fully utilize the power of her "
"<b>energy heart</b> after being transplanted to a new body, why could "
"another soul not do the same? Why, <b>contamination</b>, of course! That "
"pesky obstacle is the main thing that stands between us and the ability to "
"create a god. Even now, I fail to comprehend how █████ ███████ to achieve "
"████ unparalleled ███████ ████ ███████ 00-44A█ Some say ██ ███ █ ████████ "
"████ ████ — others say it was ███ █████ ██ ███ ██████ ██ ████████. Yet, my "
"analysis never revealed any lingering influence from either of them.\n"
"\n"
"As much as I hate to admit it, last night that arrogant cretin Mal Hekuba "
"suggested a most splendid idea. Contamination is, in essence, the rejection "
"of godhood by lifeforms whose souls were never destined for it. But, what if "
"instead of installing the core unit into a creature that naturally has a "
"soul, we used a non-sentient host alongside an <i>inert</i> donor soul? The "
"energy heart might only need to perceive the <i>presence</i> of a soul, not "
"its <i>agency</i>.\n"
"\n"
"In the past, scholars often argued that things without a soul cannot be "
"considered <i>living</i> creatures, for they have no inherent force to push "
"them towards a certain destiny. Indeed, fully artificial lifeforms like pure "
"Shaxthals do not and <i>cannot</i> fathom their own pitiful existence devoid "
"of purpose other than feeding, breeding, and obeying the <b>will of the "
"hive</b>. Only a decadent civilization like the Argazars could have "
"intentionally come up with such an obscene mockery of life.\n"
"\n"
"In our universe there is no rule forbidding things lacking a soul from being "
"<i>granted</i> one by an external influence. Necromancers throughout the "
"millennia have used this to their advantage, denying themselves passage to "
"Arvadelidrya in exchange for greater power. Whether it be their own rotting "
"bodies, or flashy trinkets pilfered from opulent tyrants, they have proven "
"beyond a doubt that you can graft a soul on pretty much anything that has "
"physical form.\n"
"\n"
"Despite her initial disgust upon finding out who contributed to my proposal, "
"the <b>Fire</b> expressed interest in finding out how we could use this as a "
"basis for the development of a new class of weaponry. I am disappointed to "
"see Argan’s protégée indulge in this primitive way of thinking, but if it is "
"what it takes to give the Thornfire program a new lease on life, then so be "
"it.\n"
"\n"
"I am sorry, Argan, but neither you nor I were ever the kind to turn our "
"backs on inspiration whenever it struck. Plus, would it not be the greatest "
"irony of all if an innately <b>soulless</b> creature were to attain "
"apotheosis?"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_prophecy1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:149
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Day of the Longest Night"
msgstr "La Dama de la Luz."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_prophecy1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:152
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"On the day of the Longest Night, the New Guardian of Darkness shall rise "
"from beyond to claim her rightful place amongst the Guardians of the Second "
"Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"On that day, the New Guardian of Life shall rise again, more powerful than "
"before.\n"
"\n"
"That is the day we have lived for.\n"
"\n"
"The day that shall bring upon our doomed existence the promise of a new "
"beginning."
msgstr ""
"En el día de la Noche Más Larga, la Nueva Guardiana de la Oscuridad surgirá "
"desde más allá para reclamar su lugar legítimo entre las Guardianas del "
"Segundo Ciclo."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_urvatha
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:163
#, fuzzy
msgid "Urvatha"
msgstr "Karathas"

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_urvatha
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:166
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Originally a peaceful world not predestined to harbor civilization, Urvatha "
"was chosen by Iluvia as one of the destinations for the survivors of the "
"First Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"Over time, the lack of a guardian who could guide them resulted in "
"devastating and long-lasting wars over increasingly scarce resources — thus "
"earning it a new name for outsiders and natives alike: <b>‘Inferno’</b>.\n"
"\n"
"While Urvatha continues to be largely heterogeneous, its most inhospitable "
"regions are much better known in Irdyan lore than the rest.\n"
"\n"
"Despite originally lacking a guardian and a seed, Urvatha has become the "
"domain of the New Guardian of Life."
msgstr ""
"<b>Urvatha</b>\n"
"\n"
"Originalmente un mundo pacífico no destinado a albergar civilización, "
"Urvatha fue elegido por Iluvia como uno de los destinos para los "
"sobrevivientes del Primer Ciclo.\n"
"\n"
"Con el tiempo, la falta de un guardián que pudiera guiarlos resultó en "
"guerras devastadoras y prolongadas por recursos cada vez más escasos, "
"ganándose así un nuevo nombre entre forasteros y nativos por igual: "
"«Inferno».\n"
"\n"
"Aunque Urvatha sigue siendo en gran medida heterogéneo, sus regiones más "
"inhóspitas son mucho más conocidas en la tradición irdyana que el resto.\n"
"\n"
"A pesar de carecer originalmente de un guardián y una semilla, Urvatha se ha "
"convertido en el dominio del Nuevo Guardián de la Vida."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_silida
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:177
msgid "Silida"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_silida
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:180
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Originally a barren world not predestined to sustain life, Silida was chosen "
"by Iluvia as one of the destinations for the survivors of the First Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"It is said that before being erased from existence, the Guardians of Life "
"and Existence adapted this lifeless world as a new home for their peoples. "
"However, their task was left unfinished, and the new inhabitants of the "
"world died out after a few generations. Only many eons later would Silida be "
"populated again by faerie creatures.\n"
"\n"
"Despite originally lacking a guardian and a seed, Silida has become the "
"domain of the New Guardian of Earth."
msgstr ""
"<b>Silida</b>\n"
"\n"
"Originalmente un mundo árido no destinado a albergar civilización, Silida "
"fue elegido por Iluvia como uno de los destinos para los sobrevivientes del "
"Primer Ciclo.\n"
"\n"
"Se dice que antes de ser borrados de la existencia, los Guardianes de la "
"Vida y la Existencia adaptaron este mundo sin vida como un nuevo hogar para "
"sus pueblos. Sin embargo, su tarea quedó inconclusa, y los nuevos habitantes "
"del mundo se extinguieron tras unas pocas generaciones. Solo muchos eones "
"más tarde Silida volvería a ser poblado por criaturas feéricas.\n"
"\n"
"A pesar de carecer originalmente de un guardián y una semilla, Silida se ha "
"convertido en el dominio del Nuevo Guardián de la Tierra."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:189
#, fuzzy
msgid "On Corruption"
msgstr "¿Una pregunta?"

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:192
msgid ""
"The First Gods created us and the reality we live in with the intent that "
"our own Original Ten would protect and rule over their creation, and "
"eventually replace their forefathers entirely. Little did they know of the "
"many trials they would face during the First Cycle, and the betrayal that "
"would result in the abrupt end of their own existence."
msgstr ""
"Los Primeros Dioses nos crearon a nosotros y a la realidad en la que vivimos "
"con la intención de que nuestros propios Diez Originales protegieran y "
"gobernaran su creación, y eventualmente reemplazaran a sus predecesores por "
"completo. Poco sabían de las muchas pruebas que enfrentarían durante el "
"Primer Ciclo, y de la traición que resultaría en el abrupto fin de su propia "
"existencia."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:194
msgid ""
"Little did they know that the same corruptive force that ravaged their "
"universe would manipulate the order of events to ensure an entryway through "
"the Tree of Life itself."
msgstr ""
"Poco sabían que la misma fuerza corruptora que asoló su universo manipularía "
"el orden de los acontecimientos para asegurar una entrada a través del "
"propio Árbol de la Vida."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:196
msgid ""
"It would ensure that the souls of our ten demon gods would be connected "
"directly to the Tree through their very hearts. And then it would corrupt "
"the Tree, and its Protector."
msgstr ""
"Se aseguraría de que las almas de nuestros diez dioses demoníacos estuvieran "
"conectadas directamente al Árbol a través de sus propios corazones. Y "
"entonces corrompería el Árbol, y a su Protector."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:201
#, fuzzy
msgid "On Existence"
msgstr "Existencia"

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:204
msgid ""
"The First Gods no longer exist, and now the Tree is completely unguarded. "
"Our universe and our guardians will fail to accomplish their intended "
"mission. Not even Delethia could see this until the First Cycle was over. "
"The songs of our own Ten will never be uttered within the boundaries of our "
"existence, and the wound on the Tree will never be healed."
msgstr ""
"Los Primeros Dioses ya no existen, y ahora el Árbol está completamente "
"desprotegido. Nuestro universo y nuestros guardianes fracasarán en cumplir "
"su misión prevista. Ni siquiera Delethia pudo ver esto hasta que terminó el "
"Primer Ciclo. Los cantos de nuestros propios Diez nunca se pronunciarán "
"dentro de los límites de nuestra existencia, y la herida en el Árbol nunca "
"sanará."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:206
msgid ""
"Even at the last moment, Delethia could not fully control the final outcome; "
"however, her greatly increased foresight and power after defeating Yarae did "
"allow her to alter it to a limited extent."
msgstr ""
"Incluso en el último momento, Delethia no pudo controlar por completo el "
"resultado final; sin embargo, su previsión y poder enormemente aumentados "
"tras derrotar a Yarae le permitieron alterarlo en cierta medida."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Our lives were carefully arranged before she sacrificed her own to create "
"the Gatekeepers. She entrusted Uria and Xia’el with the devices necessary to "
"put her secret plan into motion. The Second Cycle began."
msgstr ""
"Nuestras vidas fueron cuidadosamente ordenadas antes de que ella sacrificara "
"la suya propia para crear a los Guardianes del Portal. Confió a Uria y "
"Xia’el los artefactos necesarios para poner en marcha su plan secreto. Así "
"comenzó el Segundo Ciclo."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:210
msgid "At the end, only Four will prevail."
msgstr "Al final, solo Cuatro prevalecerán."

#. [world_entry]: id=the_ten_guardians
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:225
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Ten Guardians"
msgstr "La Tríada"

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_life
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:277
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aspects: Life"
msgstr "aspecto de la vida"

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_life
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:280
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The aspect of <b>Life</b> deals primarily with the creation and sustainment "
"of life, as well as the very essence of being in all of its manifestations.\n"
"\n"
"All non-faerie human and human-like creatures were created in the image of "
"the first <b>Guardian of Life</b>, who governed over <b>Ethea</b> during the "
"First Cycle. This incarnation of <b>Uria</b> would prove essential for "
"defeating the corrupted <b>Yarae</b> by using her great might to vanqiush "
"his allies one by one, at the cost of countless innocent lives.\n"
"\n"
"Her next incarnation came into existence on a world other than Ethea due to "
"unknown reasons."
msgstr ""
"El aspecto de la Vida se ocupa principalmente de la creación y el "
"sostenimiento de la vida, así como de la esencia misma del ser en todas sus "
"manifestaciones.\n"
"\n"
"Todas las criaturas humanas y humanoides no faéricas fueron creadas a imagen "
"de la primera Guardiana de la Vida, que gobernó Ethea durante el Primer "
"Ciclo. Esta encarnación de Uria resultó esencial para derrotar al Protector "
"corrupto del Árbol al orquestar la caída de los aliados de Yarae, a costa de "
"innumerables vidas inocentes en todas partes.\n"
"\n"
"Su siguiente encarnación surgió en un mundo distinto a Ethea por razones "
"desconocidas."

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_earth
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:289
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aspects: Earth"
msgstr "aspecto de la tierra"

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_earth
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:292
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The aspect of <b>Earth</b> is one of four aspects which directly support "
"Life, paving the way for creation.\n"
"\n"
"All faeriekind creatures were created in the image of the first <b>Guardian "
"of Earth</b>, who was tasked with ruling over <b>Irdya</b> during the First "
"Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"Some myths claim that faeriekind beings were fully incorporeal until after "
"the ascension of the first incarnation of <b>Xia’el</b>, a woman said to "
"have been created out of golden dust by <b>Yarae</b> himself. The god fell "
"in love with his own creation, and desperately wanted her affection; the "
"goddess, however, did not reciprocate, spending the days instead lamenting "
"her subjects’ inability to fully bask in the wonders of the physical realm. "
"As a favor, Yarae granted them physical bodies made from the same fine "
"dust.\n"
"\n"
"Her next incarnation came into existence on a world other than Irdya due to "
"unknown reasons."
msgstr ""
"El aspecto de la Tierra es uno de los cuatro aspectos directamente "
"conectados a la Vida en un rol de apoyo, allanando el camino para la "
"creación.\n"
"\n"
"Todas las criaturas faéricas fueron creadas a imagen de la primera Guardiana "
"de la Tierra, quien fue encargada de gobernar Irdya durante el Primer "
"Ciclo.\n"
"\n"
"Algunas fuentes afirman que los seres faéricos eran originalmente "
"incorpóreos y extremadamente raros hasta la ascensión de la primera "
"encarnación de Xia’el, una mujer que se dice fue creada a partir de polvo "
"dorado por el mismo Yarae, el Protector del Árbol. Su influencia podría "
"haber concedido a su especie el don de una existencia más física en mayor "
"número, aunque perdiendo la inmortalidad en el proceso. Existen varias "
"versiones del mito, algunas afirman que la forma de Xia’el fue un favor "
"concedido por Yarae después de enamorarse de la criatura.\n"
"\n"
"Su siguiente encarnación surgió en un mundo distinto a Irdya por razones "
"desconocidas."

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:303
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aspects: Darkness"
msgstr "aspecto de la oscuridad"

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:307
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Unlike the majority of the aspects constituting reality, Darkness and Light "
"are derived from the nature of the First Gods themselves, stemming from "
"Existence, and connected to Life in a structural role.\n"
"\n"
"Just like Darkness precedes and succeeds Light from a physical standpoint, "
"it also deals with matters of the mind, whereas Light deals with the soul of "
"every being born under the Tree of Life. However, just as both aspects "
"complement each other, they may also exchange places according to the "
"circumstances.\n"
"\n"
"Merthiaal, the Guardian of Darkness on Yrathid, was the last guardian to be "
"born during the First Cycle, and at the same time, she was the first "
"guardian to perish. Although Yarae’s conflict had not yet begun, he did have "
"an indirect role in causing Merthiaal’s downfall. The young guardian’s "
"emotions clouded her reason; jealousy consumed her heart from inside as she "
"watched her creator’s predilection for her sisters Uria and Xia’el.\n"
"\n"
"In a desperate attempt to prove her worth to Yarae and even surpass his own "
"power, the girl subverted her world’s seed and tried to absorb its energy "
"for herself. Alas, even though their blood was always one and the same, the "
"guardian and the Seed of Darkness were never meant to become one.\n"
"\n"
"Not having learned her own song beforehand, Merthiaal could not assume full "
"control of her new powers. Instead of becoming the true goddess she desired "
"to be, the very aspect she controlled was destroyed — her mind succumbed to "
"insanity as her horrifying new body absorbed the souls of each and every one "
"of her fellow Yrathidians.\n"
"\n"
"Uria put an end to Merthiaal’s rampage by ripping her heart out, destroying "
"her body, and sealing her self in the hope that Yarae could do something to "
"remedy the situation. However, Yarae was offended by the proposition; he "
"refused to help with the resurrection and healing, choosing instead to "
"preserve the lifeless world intact as a testament to his child’s hubris.\n"
"\n"
"That incarnation of Uria would never be able to bring Merthiaal back to "
"life, and the Guardian of Darkness would come to be known as the Eater of "
"Souls, the antithesis of the Guardian of Light. Now lacking a distinct seed, "
"Yrathid would not be restored at the end of the First Cycle, remaining "
"instead a graveyard world per Yarae’s wishes."
msgstr ""
"A diferencia de la mayoría de los aspectos que constituyen la realidad, la "
"Oscuridad y la Luz derivan de la naturaleza misma de los Primeros Dioses, "
"procedentes de la Existencia y conectados a la Vida en un rol estructural.\n"
"\n"
"Así como la Oscuridad precede y sucede a la Luz desde un punto de vista "
"físico, también trata asuntos de la mente, mientras que la Luz se ocupa del "
"alma de cada ser nacido bajo el Árbol de la Vida. Sin embargo, al igual que "
"ambos aspectos se complementan, pueden también intercambiar lugares según "
"las circunstancias.\n"
"\n"
"Merthiaal, la Guardiana de la Oscuridad en Yrathid, fue la última guardiana "
"en nacer durante el Primer Ciclo, y al mismo tiempo, fue la primera "
"guardiana en perecer. Aunque el conflicto de Yarae aún no había comenzado, "
"él tuvo un rol indirecto en causar la caída de Merthiaal. Las emociones de "
"la joven guardiana nublaron su razón; los celos consumieron su corazón desde "
"adentro mientras observaba la predilección de su creador por sus hermanas "
"Uria y Xia’el.\n"
"\n"
"En un intento desesperado por probar su valía ante Yarae e incluso superar "
"su propio poder, la joven subvirtió la semilla de su mundo e intentó "
"absorber su energía para sí misma. Sin embargo, aunque su sangre siempre fue "
"una y la misma, la guardiana y la Semilla de la Oscuridad nunca estuvieron "
"destinadas a convertirse en una sola."

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S8B_prophecy1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:324
msgid "Lost Prophecy"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S8B_prophecy1
#. Line 1: the ‘Four’ are individuals of indeterminate genders.
#. Line 2: except for the ‘Four’, these names refer to inanimate objects.
#. Line 3: these names also refer to inanimate objects.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:330
msgid ""
"The Infertile Mother shall give birth to Four.\n"
"\n"
"These Four shall seek shelter in the Second. The First shall be consumed, "
"the Tree shall be infected.\n"
"\n"
"The missing Fifth shall provide knowledge. The Eleventh and the Twelfth "
"shall provide hope."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness_and_light
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:339
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aspects: Darkness and Light"
msgstr "Vuelo de la Oscuridad"

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness_and_light
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:342
msgid ""
"The Aspects of Darkness and Light are both interwoven in the very fabric of "
"our reality. Although the powers they confer are often underestimated on "
"their own, the combination of either aspect with any other can have "
"formidable effects. It is generally agreed that the combination of Darkness "
"and Light in particular serves as a connection to the power of the Union — a "
"power most intimately related to Creation itself."
msgstr ""
"Los Aspectos de la Oscuridad y la Luz están entrelazados en el mismo tejido "
"de nuestra realidad. Aunque los poderes que confieren suelen subestimarse "
"por separado, la combinación de cualquiera de ellos con otro puede tener "
"efectos formidables. Se acepta generalmente que la combinación de Oscuridad "
"y Luz en particular sirve como vínculo con el poder de la Unión, un poder "
"íntimamente relacionado con la Creación misma."

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_pairs
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:347
msgid "Aspects: Pairs"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_pairs
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:350
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Life draws from Light and Darknesss, Existence draws from Darkness and "
"Light. Fire and Water oppose each other just as Creation and Destruction do. "
"Thunder and Ice are opposites in the same sense as Earth and Air complement "
"each other.\n"
"\n"
"All the aspects that govern our universe are closely related and equally "
"important to the continuance of reality. Their roles are as flexible as "
"necessary to accomplish the ultimate goal of preserving the First Gods’ "
"legacy, no matter the cost."
msgstr ""
"Todos los aspectos que gobiernan nuestro universo están estrechamente "
"relacionados y son igualmente importantes para la continuidad de la "
"realidad. Sus roles son tan flexibles como sea necesario para cumplir el "
"objetivo supremo de preservar el legado de los Primeros Dioses, sin importar "
"el costo."

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_knowledge
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:357
msgid "Aspects: Knowledge"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_knowledge
#. “To brook” below is used in an obsolete sense; namely
#. “to use/enjoy/have the full employment of” (from wiktionary).
#. It also serves as a pun.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:363
msgid ""
"Fire forges knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Light wards knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Darkness craves knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Water brooks knowledge."
msgstr ""
"El Fuego forja el conocimiento.\n"
"\n"
"La Luz protege el conocimiento.\n"
"\n"
"La Oscuridad ansía el conocimiento.\n"
"\n"
"El Agua alberga el conocimiento."

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_energy_heart
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:374
msgid "On the Energy Heart"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_energy_heart
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:377
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Guardian-class beings are distinguished by the existence of a special organ "
"in their bodies called the Energy Heart. The organ acts as a virtuallly "
"unlimited source of energy and sustenance for the creature, able to keep it "
"alive under circumstances that would otherwise result in permanent damage or "
"even death. In fact, the host body can suffer any kind of injuries and they "
"will be gradually healed by the Energy Heart, the healing rate depending on "
"the severity of the damage as well as the host’s contamination level.\n"
"\n"
"The organ goes through its own growth and maturation process independent "
"from the host body. Norsulan studies conducted on the Seed of Fire during "
"the Second Cycle have shown that it is possible to artificially grow the "
"organ in the bodies of non-Guardians, albeit with disastrous effects. An "
"alternative approach was used to build the first prototype of an artificial "
"Guardian, keeping the Energy Heart in a separate insulated container with a "
"direct pathway to the host’s nervous system, and an electronic control "
"unit.\n"
"\n"
"The research subjects were all deceased Norsulans, and none of them managed "
"to establish a stable connection with their Energy Hearts. It is suspected "
"that there is a less evident connection between the body, Energy Heart, and "
"spirit of a real Guardian that allows them to fully control their three "
"constituent parts — a connection to the seed that gave them birth, and the "
"Greater Design laid out first by Yarae, and then by Delethia."
msgstr ""
"Los seres de clase Guardián se distinguen por la existencia de un órgano "
"especial en sus cuerpos llamado Corazón de Energía. Este órgano actúa como "
"una fuente prácticamente ilimitada de energía y sustento para la criatura, "
"capaz de mantenerla con vida en circunstancias que de otro modo provocarían "
"daños permanentes o incluso la muerte. De hecho, el cuerpo huésped puede "
"sufrir cualquier tipo de heridas y estas serán sanadas gradualmente por el "
"Corazón de Energía, a una velocidad que depende de la gravedad del daño y "
"del nivel de contaminación del huésped.\n"
"\n"
"El órgano atraviesa su propio proceso de crecimiento y maduración "
"independiente del cuerpo huésped. Los estudios norsulanos realizados sobre "
"la Semilla de Fuego durante el Segundo Ciclo demostraron que es posible "
"hacer crecer artificialmente el órgano en cuerpos no guardianes, aunque con "
"efectos desastrosos. Se utilizó un enfoque alternativo para construir el "
"primer prototipo de un Guardián artificial, manteniendo el Corazón de "
"Energía en un contenedor aislado con un conducto directo al sistema nervioso "
"del huésped y una unidad de control electrónico."

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_union
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:386
msgid "On the Union"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_union
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:389
msgid ""
"The Orbs of Light and Darkness do not just allow those blessed by Iluvia to "
"summon the Union itself. Given every aspect’s individual affiliation with "
"either path, it may be possible to use the Orbs as instruments to tap into "
"the powers of the other aspects.\n"
"\n"
"As the first Avatar of the Union herself, Iluvia made use of this mechanism "
"to aid Uria and Xia’el in destroying every other corrupted guardian before "
"banishing Yarae from our universe."
msgstr ""
"Los Orbes de Luz y Oscuridad no solo permiten a quienes son bendecidos por "
"Iluvia invocar a la propia Unión. Dada la afiliación individual de cada "
"aspecto con uno u otro camino, puede ser posible usar los Orbes como "
"instrumentos para acceder a los poderes de los otros aspectos.\n"
"\n"
"Como primera Avatar de la Unión, Iluvia hizo uso de este mecanismo para "
"ayudar a Uria y Xia’el a destruir a todos los demás guardianes corrompidos "
"antes de desterrar a Yarae de nuestro universo."

